Name: 1770 House
Comments: Took out Saturday night - missed the ambiance of the dining room but the food quality, service, portions and presentation were excellent. Taking out again midweek!

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Everything about this restaurant is exquisite from the welcoming fireplace upon entering to the warmed milk served with tea and coffee. Attention to detail is unparalleled.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: My first time and really enjoyed it.  Excellent meal and service.  Great atmosphere - perfect Friday night spot after a long week. We will b back

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Lovely inn & restaurant, excellent service, very good food

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Great food, excellent service, and amazing atmosphere.  I will be returning

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Great meal and service!

Name: 1770 House
Comments: 1770 house consistently has the best food in East Hampton.  The ambiance is wonderful - quiet.  Some may say it's "stuffy" but I disagree. I always have a nice night out eating at 1770 House.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: We need to dine there more often   Worth the drive from Southampton

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Always excellent food and service.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Fantastic chef and cozy warm space.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: The 1770 House is the jewel box of east hampton .the tavern is chic and decorated beautifully comfortable with banquet seating and its  interesting looking at the historic foundation and fireplace.The menu is yummy and the music played  is also a bit of mellow rock and roll history   The lovely tranquil main dining room is quiet with tables spaced well to provide personal space.   Both the food and service in both is first rate. I've been many times and whether it's a regular night.  restaurant week or $17.70 night in the tavern, it's always a special night when we go to The 1770 House.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Every single thing on the menu was AMAZING! Pricey but highly recommended!

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Excellent food and great service! The restaurant never disappointed us whenever we went there for dinner. We highly recommend to all white have not tried this restaurant yet. Whatever you order, you will not be disappointed.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Always great food, service is excellent. Great cocktails. Love sitting downstairs in the tavern, very cozy.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: My wife and I love this place and make it an ANNUAL MUST during the winter time in the hamptons. We always end up having a drink by the fireplace and before/or/after a fantastic meal. Highly recommend this place for special occasions.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: The service was absolutely fantastic. The food was amazing as well.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Mid-winter overnight stay was spectacular! Inn and restaurant were outstanding and the staff couldn't have been more charming.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: The hostess wouldnt seat us at a corner , private table because she said they were committed (room remained 90% empty for the hour we were there). Not her fault but she seated a loud, obnoxious party next to us. Not pleasant.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: No other restaurant in the Hamptons comes close to the atmosphere and food quality of the 1770 house.   There might be places that are 'hot" for a year or two or where you might see more famous people , but this who want fine food in a refined atmosphere go to the 1770 House.   Pricey on Friday and Sat night but the Sunday thru Thursday Prix Fixe is a terrific value.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: As usual, food was delicious, device was excellent, atmosphere was great and all personnel were warm, welcoming and professional.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: We loved our experience at 1770 house. The food was absolutely incredible, the decor was beautiful, and the wait staff were attentive and helpful. Highly recommend! We look forward to coming back again!

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Perfection, love this place!

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Food was great!

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Always an exceptional dinner here.  And this is one of the very few restaurants where you can have a conversation over dinner.  It's quiet enough to hear your friends.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: 1770 is one of my favorite restaurants on Long Island. We decided to stay at the inn the last minute and I am so happy we did. Great service and very clean. I highly really recommend it both the inn and restaurant. We will definitely be back.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: It was lively. Perfect 20th anniversary meal.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: The service was sporadic with one waiter & busboy for the dining room. My cocktail was a watered down run&tonic. The food was delicious.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: The Tavern menu and cooking is excellent, and in a delightful and cozy "old inn tavern" below-ground space from the Revolutionary War era.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Organic chicken, Brussels sprout salad and date cake: the best. The service is consistently impeccable.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Everything was perfect! Will visit again!

Name: 1770 House
Comments: A perfect restaurant, in terms of ambience, service drink, and food.Our servers were very knowledgeable and skilled  about the menu and gracious hospitality.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Always good . one of the best in the Hamptons you can even hear everyone at the table which is rare these days.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: We would go every few months but instead go every few years simply to see if things have changed with the food preparation. They have not.  The menu always tempts but the food is always under-flavored, (not just under-seasoned, which some dishes are), and yet the salad is always too salty.   Frustrating because we are strongly drawn to this elegant room, comforting yet sophisticated inn ambience, superb service, good wine choices, well-made drinks, lovely venue.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Absolutely loved the ambiance and charm of 1770. Waiter was very knowledgeable of food and wine recommendations. The food was amazing we will definitely return !

Name: 1770 House
Comments: I love the chicken cooked to perfection on its bed of delicate mushed potatoes the sticky dates cales is out of this world.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Our meal and service were both excellent

Name: 1770 House
Comments: 1770 House continues to be East Hamptons best restaurant....Creative menu, great service and a sensational value during restaurant week.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Best place in East Hampton. They are consistently lovely. The food was delicious a wonderful dinning experience. Recommend highly.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: Such a cozy place and wonderful staff! The food is delicious! They just need to have a heavier pour with wine. Thats my only suggestion.

Name: 1770 House
Comments: 1770 House was fabulous, as usual. Going there for Restaurant Week made it a tremendous bargain. I still would highly recommend it even when it is not Restaurant Week.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Ambience, food , staff.. terrific

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: The food was spectacular and the patio seating was perfect in a summer night

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Most amazing meal and service. Have been looking forward to eating here and it didn't disappoint.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: we went to dinner on an evening that kept predicting thunderstorms off and on .  mostly off.  we went after it seemed like the weather would cooperate.  It did for the most part, but the servers got caught in downpours and were drenched but didn't' miss a beat.  I commend them and the delicious food that they brought out while holding a napkin above it so it wouldn't get wet.  We had a delightful time  thank you!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Celebrated 15th anniversary on the patio. Food and ambience was great and looking forward to trying the ice cream pints we brought home from the parlor next door.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Great food. Excellent service

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Arethusa is always exceptional in every way, food, service, ambiance. Our absolute favorite place to dine.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Never disappoints!   Food and service were excellent.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: One of the best meals weve had! The service was outstanding. We wanted to catch a glimpse of the Neowise comet and when we told the hostess, she wrote us a list of viewing spots in the area to try. Amazing food and drinks, amazing people.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Simply put, Al Tavalo is our favorite place to eat. Wonderful service, great waiters and servers, ambiance and food that are second to none.  We eat there at least once a month.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: A s always, A Wonderful Anniversary Dinner!!!!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Best restaurant in CT by far. Such a special place.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Wonderful, as always. Such a treat. Though we were closer to the road because they have added outdoor seating, it was such a wonderful meal.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Excellent, as always! Id love to see bigger olives in the martinis, with a blue cheese stuffed option :). Servers are impeccably trained, and were amazing.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Unforgettable! Everything was splendid. We cant wait for our next chance to return.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: The best food in the Litchfield Hills -- as good as the best restaurants in NYC and other large/gourmet cities. The staff is friendly and accommodating. A little pricey, but the experience is worth every penny. Keep up the excellent work!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: We had an amazing experience . Service was perfect. Food exquisite We made another reservation to come back in a few weeks. Very impressed all around

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: This is my favorite restaurant anywhere! The inventive farm-to-table cuisine is second to none and never disappoints. The menu changes frequently featuring seasonal and fresh ingredients. And the ice cream is to die for!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Great dining experience...food choices and preparation you just don't find elsewhere.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Thank you. A beautiful and indispensable restaurant. I can dive in you halibut any time. We will be back soon. What. Treat.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Fabulous food served in outdoor patio dining all with appropriate distancing and masks.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Always a huge fan. The staff are terrific and attentive; consummate professionals.Was a bit disappointed with the squash blossoms as the stuffing was bland, and they were soggy.  The rest of the meal was excellent. Also a bit bummed about the corkage fee after sharing a glass with the wait staff and the chef. (I always tip based on the bottle brought, and I know restaurants rely on wine sales etc.)Will gladly recommend and go back!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Food was delicious, every course was tasty and satisfying, while bringing unique flavors perfectly cooked. Yes it was expensive but great value, who wants to pay less and not receive unique and tasty dining. And, the service was truly excellent, amazing to see the numbers of wait staff, and all so enthusiastic!  The only improvement suggested Is to have more outdoor seating, hard to do while social distancing but necessary.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Words cannot describe the incredible dining experience we had at Arethusa al Tavolo. We were impressed from start to finish with service and food and will definitely go back for another fine dinner.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Food was AMAZING! I would 100% recommend it! The service was great also!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Exceptional experience!  A must experience for any foodie out there and for anyone who appreciates quality, locally produced food.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: My wife and I went out for our 26th Wedding Anniversary.  Everything was wonderful and we look forward to coming back.  They treat you like family.  We love this restaurant!Peter Cordeau

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Food was unique and beautifully presented BUT the restaurant was so dark that we had to use our cellphone flashlights to see the menu and although the food looked like pieces of art  the room was too dark to really appreciate it.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: This is our go to fine dining experience in Connecticut.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: This was our second time eating at Arethusa al Tavolo and it didnt disappoint. Prices are average for fine dining but the food and service are outstanding which makes it completely worth it. Cant wait to go back again!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Outstanding from beginning to end. Our favorite restaurant hands down! From the food to the service!!! Just absolutely incredible. Love our date nights at Arethusa Al Tavolo!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Wow! Usually the veggies play 2nd fiddle in the entree, not here, they were just as much a star of the meal as the rest of the dish. I know they grow their own vegetables on the their farm, but the preparation was fantastic. We are definitely going back.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Lovely destination restaurant...people travel from miles for good reason.  Suggest making your reservations well in advance.  Be sure to check out the Bakery across the street to bring a bit back home (and because you may not have room for dessert) also the Ice Creamery and Cheese shop next door...

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Always a great experience! Drinks, food, atmosphere are all top notch. Highly recommended!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Overall I would give a good rating. the service was excellent with there attention to detail . The menu was pretentious  and difficult to understand, too many things in each dish. Less is more would be my recommendation. The ambience is not great with the tables to close together and no evidence of sound abatement. It was noisy and difficult to carry on a conversation. How ever I did enjoy the dinner and would recommend to anyone who does not mind the negatives.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Superb as always

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Honestly, this has been the first dining experience I've had in a while where every single step of the meal was noteworthy. We sat down and both my father and husband (who were celebrating their birthdays) were presented with hand written birthday cards from the owner. The wine selection was perfect, the gluten free bread was dynamite. And every part of the meal was amazing. Nothing was wasted.  The dynamics of all of the flavors were flawless. Seriously. Incredible meal. Thank you.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: The food was really very good and we enjoyed it. Thanks also for the thoughtfulness as we celebrated our anniversary - the card and ice cream were unexpected so thanks again. Overall we had  great experience and will recommend this to friends too.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Always consistently excellent food and service! Thank you for a wonderful dining experience!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: This is such a FABULOUS restaurant and the food is delicious. We just picked the wrong night and got seated in the bar area. There were people standing next to our table pretty much the whole night. It was hard for the waitress to serve us it was so crowded. They did try and ask people to move they just kept coming back. I would definitely go back it is my favorite restaurant. I would just ask for a different table OR not go by a holiday ( Valentine's day).

Name: Atera
Comments: Excellent food, vibe, and ambiance!

Name: Atera
Comments: Perfection.

Name: Atera
Comments: A culinary temple. Each and every dish was a work of art. I loved the way each dish was explained. I look forward to returning. The only thing I would change is the music, it didnt go with the experience.

Name: Atera
Comments: Food is good, not great. In my opinion the price is not justified.

Name: Atera
Comments: The whole experience was outstanding

Name: Atera
Comments: If someone asks us where to go for fine dining with New York vibe, this is the place. There is no similar restaurant anywhere in the world. Try their reserve pairing to make the experience even better.

Name: Atera
Comments: Wonderful in every way! Amazing food and great service.

Name: Atera
Comments: Absolutely amazing food and service in an intimate setting. I am vegetarian and they made me an entire special menu to accommodate my dietary restriction. A must go to!

Name: Atera
Comments: Always the best meal of our lives. Services is SPECTACULAR. chef and kitchen are truly phenomenal creating a menu that is nothing short of course after course of taste treat (especially given dietary restrictions). Staff is attentive but not bothersome. We look forward to dining at Atera every year. Special. Memorable and delicious.

Name: Atera
Comments: Great experience. Certainly recommend.

Name: Atera
Comments: OK. I'm not one for superlatives, but I have to say that my dinner at  Atera was the best dining experience one could ever hope for. From the minute you are greeted, until your departure 9 close to three hours later), you are pampered and fed like never before. It was our 25th anniversary, and every staff member knew about it, congratulated us (by name), and made our night feel so extra special. Once one of the amazing staff, David, found out that I was Grateful Dead fan, the music (which was played at the perfect volume) featured a wonderful set of Dead tunes. Now the food: in a word-- beyond. Seventeen courses. Not too stingy, not too much. Actually had to make room for the last two savory courses. (There's always room for dessert-- courses 16 and 17). I did the temperance drink pairing-- crazy inventive and fun (not a must, but if you have a few $ you don't mind spending, it adds a nice comic dimension to an otherwise very serious and very delicious tasting menu. Chef Ronny is on hand (and is very hands on) overseeing every detail.  He is 35, looks like he is 25, and cooks like he's been doing this forever. This is one restaurant experience you cannot miss. As an aside: We stayed over at 11Howard- a beautiful boutique hotel nearby. Had the 6pm Atera seating. Went to AIRE ancient baths after dinner (9-10:30pm)-- around the block-- for an amazing post-dinner spa experience. If you want to be a hero, treat your special someone to a night like this-- it won't be soon forgotten!Extra shout out to David at Atera-- thank you for a very special evening.

Name: Atera
Comments: exceptional meal .  All dishes were superbly presented and perfectly balanced.  I enjoyed all the savory dishes but the last few sweet ones were disappointing.

Name: Atera
Comments: Small seat restaurant. Two seatings a night. Good wine pairings. Nice food presentation.

Name: Atera
Comments: My husband and I were in NYC from Atlanta to celebrate his 50th birthday, and I surprised him with reservations at Atera.  The atmosphere is fantastic and the seating allowed for conversation with others if desired.  The tasting menu was absolutely sublime and the chefs and staff were engaging.  highly recommend getting the wine pairings as well.

Name: Atera
Comments: A memorable and just a great culinary experience.

Name: Atera
Comments: The food was incredible and the service was wonderful. My friend and I had a fantastic time.

Name: Atera
Comments: One of my favorite restaurants in the world

Name: Atera
Comments: As good a meal as Ive eaten in New York.  Anywhere, in fact.  Wine accompaniment was superb.  Loved the soundtrack too (Metallica, Fine Young Cannibals, INXS, the Stones... ).

Name: Atera
Comments: Exceptional experience. The chef is an artist and you can feel his inspiration in his cuisine, which is quite rare.

Name: Atera
Comments: Phenomenal, artistic and joyful. Its evident that every staff member loves what they do.

Name: Atera
Comments: Best restaurant in NYC

Name: Atera
Comments: Chef Ronny and his team have really brought Atera back to the spotlight in NYC.  Highly recommended for those that enjoy a wonderful evening with great hosts and even better food.

Name: Atera
Comments: Nice place for dinning

Name: Atera
Comments: While the food was spectacular, one of the waiters (older gentleman with a ponytail) verbally threatened me for dropping my napkin. If you drop this napkin again me and you will have a problem and will need to resolve this outside.  As you can imagine this completely ruined my night and I would never imagine that the service staff would speak to their patrons in that manner.  Despite the food, I will recommend to all my family and friends to stay away for the restaurant given my experience.

Name: Atera
Comments: Divine. The food was beautiful and the service was thoughtful and attentive. It was a true pleasure to watch the care, precision and mastery that went in to each tasting.

Name: Atera
Comments: Last time I had this fantastic of a gastronomical experience was at Noma, Copenhagen . Chef Emborg meticulously crafted each dish with attention to detail for taste, texture and presentation. Every course was a culinary delight.Hats off to the service crew & staff, bravo! Cheers to Chef, for a brilliant execution and the best evening of 2020, yet. Thank you

Name: Atera
Comments: I was rather disappointed with Atera.  The food was fine; it is Michelin star grade.  But the atmosphere was too uptight, the chef looked angry and unhappy and one of the Scot servers was rude.  I am not able to enjoy food in a tense ambiance and for the price I paid I expected the entire staff, starting with the chef, to have minimum charm.  Some dishes were rather heavy:  I wished I had seen more creativity rather than the usual suspects: caviar, uni, foie gras and truffle oil.  I enjoyed the opening cocktail, the dumpling and the passion fruit mochi.  I am a bit concerned by the level of cholesterol that comes as part of the entire tasting menu.  Sadly I will not be coming back, nor will I recommend Atera to others.  Good luck.

Name: Atera
Comments: It is truly a top restaurant and deserve three Michelin stars. Very creative delicious elegant artsy and pleasing menue.

Name: Atera
Comments: Always a joy! Exciting dishes, 5 star service, hard to beat this!

Name: Atera
Comments: Amazing meal with 16 courses that ranged from very good to amazing.  Service is perfect.  Love sitting at counter and watching the chefs prepare the courses.  Also enjoyed the music selections that play and keep the atmosphere pretty casual.

Name: Atera
Comments: They charged us 1,000 for a meal for two. We are not going back to this restaurant.

Name: Atera
Comments: Very unassuming location but lovely relaxed dining room with guests dressed from relaxed to smart casual. Special mention must go to Messrs Abbick and Manka at front of house who genuinely provided some of the best service Ive ever experienced at any restaurant - the entire team is incredibly friendly and personable.The food was of a very high standard as youd expect and immaculately presented. The team were happy to explain more about each dish and their passion for their work was evident. If you have the funds to go (it isnt cheap, we saved months for it), enjoy food and youre looking for a fine dining experience in NY, Id happily recommend this place.

Name: Atera
Comments: this was an extraordinary experience. the entire time we were there was incredible. from the food, to the service even down to the music selection....it was all great. the chef is creative, the staff is attentive, the restaurant is intimate and comfortable. with only 14-18 dining at a time you are wanting for nothing. you do pay a price for all of this but it was all worth while!!!!

Name: Atera
Comments: Everyone made a birthday memorable and delicious

Name: Atera
Comments: Second visit to Atera. Still my favorite fine-dining restaurant in NYC. Just perfect!

Name: Atera
Comments: Atera was a highlight of my recent trip to New York. The food and ambience was amazing. Jordan who took care of us was a superstar. I was lucky enough to score 2 seats over the new year holidays at this super intimate place and the overall experience was definitely deserving of its 2 Michelin stars. Just go and be dazzled and oh, get at least one member of your dining party opt for the temperance pairing. Just do it! Xoxo

Name: Atera
Comments: PerfectEach course was impressive

Name: Atera
Comments: As a foodie and a 30-year hospitality professional, this experience was absolutely fascinating!  It felt a little "Eyes Wide Shut" when I first arrived; a very small, intimate dining area (there were only 17 guests for my seating), and the staff was completely silent in front of us to begin.  Service was flawless, and the team moved effortlessly among each other for 15 courses.  A great ballet, and amazing to watch.  The cuisine was creative and flavorful (think Kaluga caviar paired with a quenelle of pistachio gelato and IPA), but I can't honestly think of a single course that I would request again.  This show was all about the ceremony of the service and plate presentation.  I opted for the coursing paired with wine, and I enjoyed several varietals I'd never tried before; Bosco (blended with Vermentino) from Cinque Terre in Northern Italy, Mencia from Ribeira Sacra, Spain.

Name: Atera
Comments: One of the best fine dinning restaurants in NY, had an amazing night there.

Name: Atera
Comments: Atera is exceptional.   The food (about 17 courses!) was amazing.  Very creative, with combinations of food one might never consider yet they all blended beautifully.  The U-shaped table facing the chefs turned out to be a wonderful addition.  All the staff was very attentive, friendly and as interactive as you wanted them to be (or not!).   The service was noteworthy.  Everything you would expect from a Michelin 2 star...and more.   I have never been to a restaurant where so much attention was given to your personal comfort and interests, in addition to proper and timely serving and removal of food and drink.  I would highly, highly recommend Atera.  True, it is expensive, but given the amount and type of food, it was truly worth the money spent, as no expense was spared by the restaurant in the selection, preparation and delivery of the meal.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Outdoor seating was great. Service was great.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Tbh, service really made it bad. I understand, our reservation was pretty late (9:15) but the service felt as if they didnt want to be there or be bothered.  I tend to visit nice establishments often and of such a high recommended place it didnt feel equivalent to other places Ive been. Not pouring the water for us stating your being coovid safe when ya touching the vase is just adding to the germs. We should only have to touch our utensils especially when were spending $300+ In one sitting. When we were done with our appetizer plates and bread instead of taking them away they were moved to the edge of an already crowded and small table. We waited 15 minutes for the bill and OUR server (Ed) wasnt even the one who got it. Another gentleman named Drew stepped in since he seen the look on our faces. I try not to sound spoiled but thats what you spend your money for sometimes. To indulge and be served properly and I dont believe we were. Im sure it was just a one-off but one persons off day is one customers first impression. Does not really make one want to come back. Oh and the girl especially didnt like it so that didnt really help me for the rest of the date night

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Doing a great job with outdoor dining -  but why on earth are servers in long sleeves plus ties and managers wearing jackets??  Get these folks some short sleeve shirts!!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: I do not normally leave reviews but I was disappointed overall in the experience. While our server was great, both in my party had to send back the steaks because they were overcooked-all gray color in a Med Rare steak. As we finished the recooked meal, it appeared we were being rushed and ultimately while trying to order another round of drinks were told by a nervous waiter that we had to leave because of the time limit on the table. Mind you it was 9 and they closed at 10 (no one really seen waiting) and we were still drinking and contemplating dessert, and again, had earlier had to wait 20+ minutes for new steaks and sides. The waiter again apologized but said it was a management rule and claimed they were booked later as he presented us with our check. Nothing removed for the food issue and a check of $450 to which we noted once more would be more and were dumbfounded that a restaurant would not continue to serve two people spending this amount, to which he nodded and appeared embarrassed. I know this is the era of COVID where we are told we should just be thankful for the restaurant to be open but this was not a positive experience, especially for the price.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Simply amazing

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The outdoor seating isnt super comfortable, but still nice to eat great food again!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Really great food and service

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Cheesesteak was bomb and worth $130. Would buy again

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: My experience was great. Wife had a great time for her birthday.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Outstanding experience staff and food excellent.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Food and service fantastic as always!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Delicious food, outstanding service, and charming atmosphere. Looking forward to going back soon.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Food was amazing! Good service

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: We had an important high level business meeting with out of town guests. Barclay prime turned out to be the perfect location. Elegant and impressive with great food, but not too noisy. Impeccable service throughout the night.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Have to say....Not Good.  I have dined at top steakhouses across the US. This was suppose to be one of them according to reviews ,but unfortunately for me it wasn't even in my top 20.   Place was WAAAYY to dark number 1..never before have I had to use my phone flashlight to see the menu.  Waiter was not friendly...seemed he couldn't be bothered.  Saw him once throughout the night.  Took forever to take our order..had a helper who was a bit nicer, but not a super friendly personality.  Food was OK.  Nothing spectacular.  From carpaccio, tuna tartare, and lobster bisque soup....ehhh 5 out of 10. Had a Prime ribeye, was OK....not really seasoned that much.  Dining partner had a Prime Strip...Not Good.  Dessert was Ok having had the banana creme brle and coffee...Overall, not worth the $300.  Would not return or recommend.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The food was amazing! Our server did a great job as well. No complaints and cant wait to go back.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Best steakhouse in Philly period. Their Wagyu cuts are insane quality. Fully recommend the American Wagyu Ribeye paired with either a Filet or preferably the Bone-in strip.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Awesome place. Great food!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The best meal I've ever had. Words can not describe the cheesesteak! I can not stop thinking about that indescribable sandwich. We also shared the seafood tower. Extremely fresh and so delicious.  Dover sole to die for and steak done to perfection. Wish I could eat here every day. Service and decor simply wonderful!.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Great as usual, cant go wrong with anything to be honest. This was a classic Wagyu RibEye, Bone-In NY, Truffle Mac and Creamed Spinach for my wifes bday! Doesnt get better

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The wait staff was outstanding in their service.  The fillet was delicious but the ribeye steak was tough and had quite a bit of grizzle or tendons

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The filet and lamb were amazing!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Waited 3 years for this sandwich omg . Worth the wait #phillycheesesteak #barclayprime #excellent

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: An overpriced restaurant with few redeeming features.  The waitress was about as snotty as one can be:  I order my meat well- done.  "You mean like a hockey puck."  While the salads were ok, the crab cakes were mediocre and overpriced.  The filet was equally mediocre, but to add a further insult, there was a $4 charge for A1 sauce.  Even though the charge was removed, the Gaul to  place this on the bill shows an utter disregard for the customer.  The baked potato and the martini were ok.Not worth another visit.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Everything was good, but having dined here several times over recent years, something seemed to be lacking to live up to the pomp and circumstance.  Service was off-pace (e.g. appetizers served before the earlier ordered cocktails arrived-which were rather average).  Steaks were good, but not off the chart good-not even the Waygu filet.  The sides were excellent-tater tots and truffle mac and cheese were as good as ever.  Deep dish cookie dessert was uninspired.  Id return based on previous experiences, but not in a rush after this visit.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The food was really good. Pleasant surprise with the carrots. The customer service was outstanding. The waiter was extremely personable. The waiter really made the evening special for my birthday.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Great food and service

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Amazing dinner ! Will def be back ! Everything from service time food was exceptional !!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Perfect meal, ambiance, service; no better restaurant in Philadelphia or beyond, in my opinion.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Amazing food and service.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The food was delicious. Service was excellent, the staff were very friendly and helpful. We had a great dinner, will definitely visit again.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: It was fine but not for the price definitely not worth it.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: My partner loves the ribeye at the Palm and Knife and Fork (in AC). But he says the ribeye he had at BP is best he ever had. Says it was perfectly marbled and tender and flavorful. Charred on outside perfect juicy medium rare doneness on inside. We also enjoyed hamachi crudo and foie  gras starters. Cocktails good but not stellar and expensive. Didnt love brussel sprouts. not done enough but he liked them. loved banana creme brulee for dessert. Two glasses bordeaux good value

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: We had great food and the service was exceptional.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Everything was done at the highest level. From arrival to departure, everything and everyone was top notch. I highly recommend this as a special occasion restaurant.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Amazing food you get what You pay for. Drinks are a little pricy but overall awesome experience

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: A special birthday treat for dad.  Started off with cocktails and apps in the bar.  Service was a bit slow during happy hour, but it was friendly.  Our server Erin was helpful and friendly in the dining room.  Thank you for making a kid-friendly pasta dish for my 9-year-old.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Service was terrific. Everything prepared to perfection, from hot buttered brioche to dessert. We enjoyed NY strip, mushrooms, baked potato, lobster bisque - all of it outstanding. We were there for a date, but the rest of the dining room on a busy Thursday evening seemed to be exclusively business meetings (which makes sense since the prices will make you look twice if you are not expensing it!) Our server Jeff was knowledgeable about everything from whiskey to the restaurants history. Classic steakhouse with great seafood options as well!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The caviar with a glass of champagne  was delicious!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Unbelievable place! Every single dish we had was top quality, the service was outstanding and the ambience perfect! Make sure to order the beet pasta! Can wait to come back

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Amazing as always

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Loved this restaurant.  Shocked that I was able to find something so amazing without anyone recommending it.  I took a chance on Open Table and the hit was a great one.Chef is from Sicily.  Restaurant located in a former home in Venice, and is absolutely charming. The wait staff and all were very attentive and the food could not have been more delicious.  Not inexpensive, but worth every dollar.  Delish!  I will go back again and again.Oh, and they had the social distancing down pat, having put up trellises in a variety of places with ivy and flowers on them.  Really charming place.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Authentic Italian food. Best pasta in town. Great outdoor seatimg. Fabulous wine selection!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Everything was delicious!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Ive been here multiple times, the meal is amazing, staff is extremely educated when it comes to wine selection, and the food I just top notch. Price point is in the higher end, but the value is great, $100 or so per person for an amazing dining experience  even outside in the new COVID world

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Barrique is my absolute favorite restaurant in Venice. The food is out of this world, the staff is the best, the wine list is awesome and reasonably priced, and the ambience is perfection. It's a hidden gem!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: A great neighborhood restaurant that is predictably amazing!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Wonderful place for Covid 19........so safe.   The patio was so lovely and cozy........feel like in NYC!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Food, service, ambience were all fantastic! Great alfresco dining experience. Service was incredible. Food and wine were out of this world delicious.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: The food was great and the service was fantastic. A lovely candlelit place, great for a date or with a small group.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Amazing food. Definitely will be back

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Such a lovely restaurant. Service is fantastic and food is DELICIOUS! The pasta is amazing!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: My waiter Michael was extremely helpful and gave several possibilities since it was my first time in this establishment. I had the scallops for the appetizer, which were amazing and the freshly made ink linguine with lobster with wild mushroom sauce which was complimented by a fine glass of white wine recommended by Michael. He actually brought me options, which I think helped to complete my meal.  It was a wonderful experience!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: My daughter has been raving about Barrique for a long time, my first time was amazing!  The food was incredible, the Scallops and Ragu are a must!Friendly staff, great atmosphere, can't wait to go back!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: This place redefines Italian Cuisine. Every time I come to LA is one of the places on my list. As a born and raised Italian living in the US for the last 40 years, It takes a ton. to impressed me, but this place, no matter what you are eating, is a notch above the rest.Consistency is another. key to their success. When you come to a place 10 times and it is always great. that says a lot.One not to miss!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Amazing experience.  Great dishes.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: amazing food! Our waiter was informative and attentive.  We highly recommend this lovely, little, taste of Italy!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Fantastic as always!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Barrique was wonderful! It was a quaint, upscale, romantic dinner for two. Service was excellent across every staff member we encountered. The food was delicious and thoughtfully prepared. My favorite dish was the scallop starter. I felt everything was well priced for the quality and experience :]

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: AMAZING wow What a treat this place is the best! Truly!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: What a beautiful experience to be out after being home for months. The food was amazing, the waiter super friendly and the ambiance romantic and wonderful. Highly recommended!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: This was the most enjoyable evening!The service was excellent, the food fantastic!We cannot wait to go back and are fortunate to live only 15 min. away!!!!Birte

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Our first time dining out since the Pandemic and it was heaven! Everything was delicious and wonderful! We were very comfortable with the health and safety standards they had implemented. Most of the tables in this restaurant are outside but we set inside with some other diners (since outside was full) and felt very safe.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: A great spot for a delicious meal! the service was great, made us feel like they knew us. will definitely be back.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Always a great meal! We go regularly, and have never been disappointed.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Great food. Great service. Very romantic! I definitely recommend it.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: This meal was beyond amazing!! One of my top five meals in the last five years!! Cant wait to go back!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: First dining out in months...  Barrique never disappoints and tonight was not exception.  Happy to see them open and several other couples enjoying the evening.Staff wore masks & gloves and the spacing of tables was appropriate and safe.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Excellent quality, service and ambiance.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Great experience

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: I would put Barrique up there with any Italian in LA, they also have some specialty dishes that are very unique and can't find anywhere else.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: The people were very friendly and very pleasant. I liked the pasta in Al dente very deliciously.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Fillet mignon was on the dry, side.sea-bass was so-so.Nice servers.A bit overpriced.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Excellent service, delicious food, romantic ambiance. Took my boyfriend for his birthday dinner who is a major Italian foodie and he said its his favorite meal/restaurant in LA. Brought our own bottle of wine, for which our waiter researched and then suggested dishes that would pair well with our wine. Will return for any special event.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: We loved the food and ambiance.  The restaurant is charming and homey.  Excellent pastas.  Attentive service.  We will return.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: My boyfriend and I come here for both of our birthdays every year and we are never disappointed! From the mouth watering food to our favorite server Michael who is so sweet and always provides the best wine recommendations Barrique is easily our favorite restaurant in Santa Monica.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Delightful place-food and service were amazing!  Fantastic wine list!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Best scallops and best filet ever.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Barrique is a hidden gem on main street Venice. The the ambiance is romantic and the food is great. It was very noisy however and the seating is quite close.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Order the bone in ribeye, it's the reason you came, it's amazing.Also, oysters are great and you cannot lose with the sides

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Bavettes is by far my favorite restaurant.  We split oysters and shrimp which was very good.  Smoked salmon Caesar salad which was fabulous. Oh....-and the warm bread with amazing crust was divine.  Salmon dish slightly spiced was delicious. Loaded baked potato with diced bacon very tasty. Son in law had a steak that was very good and my daughter had chicken.  Everything was delicious.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Food lived up to the hype!!! But the plate that stole the show was the Brussel Sprouts!!! Never in my wildest dreams did I expect them to be this good! Highly recommend them!!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Amazing steakhouse in Chicago! Great for a date night or birthday dinner! Service was excellent and food was outstanding!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: I had been looking forward to my reservations for months.  It was a late night reservation due to availability.  We ordered an appetizer that was forgotten about until we reminded our server.  It was brought out moments before our entre.  This put a damper on a highly anticipated date night for my husband's birthday.  The appetizer was later comped and service was good up until we had to flag down our server to get our dessert wrapped up to go.  Food was good but the service will not have me returning.  There are far better restaurants with top notch service for the price.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Best restaurant in the city consistently top notch

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Everything was great, service, food, ambiance. We had to book our reservation well in advance, but it lived up to the wait. Would recommend, and would go again.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Ambiance and food  were outstanding. Possibly the best steak dinner my wife and I have ever had.  We both had the filet . Cooked to perfection and melted in your mouth. We were celebrating my wife's birthday and I called ahead for reservations and table on the main floor. Great table but our server never mentioned the occasion to my wife. Would highly recommend for outstanding food,  terrific surroundings and memorable night.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Slow service and did not honor reservation time

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Best steakhouse in the city. And the seafood is amazing as well.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: The filet mignon was cooked to perfection .  The service from Klause was excellent. We highly recommend this romantic and fantastic place.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Best steak in Chicago.  Would definitely recommend to anyone!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: We were sat at a table towards the door last night. Very drafty when the door opened. Disappointing they did not do more to keep the doors from being open at same time.Food was very good. I thought the service was just average. Was expecting exceptional experience, was just pretty good

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Our waiter Ben was great, we didnt feel rushed. We sat downstairs in a booth and the music and atmosphere was nice . The bottle of wine we had paired beautifully with our steak .

Name: Bavette's
Comments: The best!!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Very enjoyable place to visit, the burger is a must!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: One of the best steaks in Chicago! Try bone marrow and ribeye, they are the must.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Steak had to be sent back twice and on the third time it was overcooked and tasted terrible. Huge disappointment but the waiter was very good and they were nice enough to remove my steak from the bill. Sides and apps were delicious. Very very dark restaurant.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: I try and get to Bavettes as often as possible - amazing place.  Had difficulty with my prior visit as I had an 8:00 PM reservation (Downstairs - Parlor) and they seated me at 9:20 PM so I was very upset.  This reservation would be my last if that happened again but they were perfect in everyway on this visit.  We sat downstairs (preferred space), waiter was awesome and the food is always the star here.  Bavette's has the best atmosphere in the city - we will be back!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Went to celebrate my daughters birthday- the hostess acknowledged that and then no one after that mentioned her birthday. Somewhat of a bummer as several tables near us were served desserts with sparklers.  We were lucky that Erik finally made it back to our table to get a dessert order let alone send sparklers. Laid back is one thing but Erik takes it to an art form. Food was wonderful, back staff was on the ball, Erik seemed not to care

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Very good food, but not exceptional within this price range.  Terrific, friendly and timely service.  Good wine selection at reasonable prices.  Background music is too loud and interferes with conversation.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Waiting for a reservation without knowing how long the table is going to be, being told that it's 2mins which turns into 10mins is frustrating. Multiple times they got the order wrong and I've cooked better $70 Ribeyes at home

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Waited 40 minutes to be sat, and then were sat in the basement

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Food was good and service was very friendly but timing of food delivery was uneven. We ordered three steaks, all medium...one came out medium, another medium-well and a third well-done. All top quality beef but not as ordered. Sides large and good. We had a booth, which was great.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: The food was great and we enjoyed the atmosphere and music!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Food was excellent service and waiting time was right on schedule . Staff did a great job

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Took me several months to get a reservation but it was worth it. My wife and I went with my brother and his wife. For appetizers we ordered the steak tartare, shrimp cocktail and half dozen oysters. All were great. For steaks the bone in ribeye and the petite fillet. They were cooked perfectly with great flavor. For sides, the sweet potatoes, crab stuffed avocado salad, truffle mac and cheese and elote style corn. For me the elote style corn was the best but all were good. As for the wine, I highly recommend the Colombo Apertura Pinot Noir. One of the best wines I have had in a long time. No dessert unfortunately but if you see the amount of food we ordered you will understand why we passed.The ambiance of the place was also very cool. The music was great and the noise level was a little high but sitting in the booth we didn't have much difficulty hearing. There is a great bar area both upstairs and down. Only complaint is the restroom situation. They are single restrooms and there was at least one to two waiting in line. Not a big deal.Overall an excellent meal and great scene. Would love to go back so I better get to work trying to secure another reservation. People did walk in without a reservation and I overheard them being told hour thirty to an hour forty-five. Not that unusual for a high-end restaurant downtown but I prefer a reservation.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Amazing food and great service.  Definitely worth a trip to Bavette if you are going through Chicago.  YUM!!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: It was fabulous !!!! We love Bavettes ...It is our most favorite restaurant ever !!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Well executed food but the service left quite a bit to be desired.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Amazing service and food was outstanding.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Went to Bavette's for a date night and the food was really good! Only disappointment was the length of time we were there. We ended up being there for 3.5 hours due to the wait time on our steaks. Also, I ordered a bone-in filet cooked medium+ and it was pretty well-done except close to the bone. Still very flavorful though!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: We were there for my boyfriends surprise 30th! The staff went above and beyond to make this special surprise perfect!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: The first time I came to Bavette's we only had appetizers and side dishes--and it was amazing. I wanted to come back and get to experience one of the best steaks in Chicago. It definitely lived up to the hype and as always, the sides (specifically the wedge salad with their famous bacon and the garlic mashed potatoes) were fantastic as well. The ambiance makes you feel like you've stepped into a classic Chicago speakeasy, especially in the basement and the service was on point. Great spot to celebrate a special occasion.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Bavettes came highly recommended. First of all, it is quite dark in the dining room. The rest rooms are old and small. The bar area has a rather nice ambiance. There is an additional dining room in the "dungeon" which provides less noise and more privacy. The food is pricey and I would suffice it to say that you do not necessarily get your money's worth. The portions are relatively small. The filet mignon and lamb chops were average. However, the crab was excellent! The service is attentive. I think there are many other superior options for steaks, chops and seafood in the area.  We will not be returning to Bavettes anytime soon.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Loved the food! Came out very fast. Service was amazing. Food was hot and seasoned just right. Will be back!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: So good! Their Mac and cheese with bacon

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Amazing! Great experience!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Wonderful anniversary dinner.  Impeccable service. Phenomenal food.  My favorite restaurant in Chicago,

Name: Bavette's
Comments: My wife and I had an excellent time.  The ambiance was amazing!  The music playing was sultry and seductive.  The food was great!!!! The service was outstanding!!!! I would recommend this restaurant to anyone!!! Perfect date night restaurant!!!

Name: Benu
Comments: Splendid, best quail I have ever had. The caviar with egg is extremely tasty.

Name: Benu
Comments: Wonderful evening of fine dining.

Name: Benu
Comments: We have been wanting to try Benu for years, so were excited to finally make a night of dining here.  The service was outstanding.  The timing of the dishes coming out was excellent and we found the servers to be professional and also very charming.  The food, though, fell a bit short of expectations for a 3-star restaurant.  Most of the starting tastes were delicious, but some of the main courses were not very good.  The xiao long bao and beef courses were excellent, but the soup was rather bland and the BBQ quail had an overwhelming smoke flavor that was unappealing.  After dining at Quince, Acquerello, and Manresa, we were disappointed in the food at Benu.  It was a good experience overall, but not really worth the price in comparison with similar class restaurants.

Name: Benu
Comments: Technicality wise it is at the highest caliber. Service was impeccable. Atmosphere is very calm and intricate. Personally, it felt amazing to see simple everyday Asian food presented in exquisite ways.Lots of praise for the Benu team

Name: Benu
Comments: Amazing from start to finish. The food, service and hospitality were unmatched.

Name: Benu
Comments: Loved every dish and service was superb

Name: Benu
Comments: Really great food. Some courses were out of this world, some courses were just really good but not worth the cost. All in all a great experience for a special occasion.

Name: Benu
Comments: One of The most amazing meals of my life. The food was perfect. And THE SERVICE: like a ballet! Also The Ambience, The Music. The beautiful Wine list! A Trip to San Francisco is only complete it if you visit Benu: The Food Cathedral!

Name: Benu
Comments: The food was exceptional

Name: Benu
Comments: The xiao long bao is an explosion of flavor - a truly amazing creation!  This alone made this a life experience.  Flawless!

Name: Benu
Comments: Food is good, no problemNeed a more comfortable chair to be honest.And need to increase the distance between tables defintely.

Name: Benu
Comments: Innovative and classic at the same time. What an experience!

Name: Benu
Comments: Absolutely excellent and attentive service of 3 Michelin star.   The food was wonderful.   Thank you

Name: Benu
Comments: it has actually improved from last time I was there, thought there was no room to move further, but I am wrong, they can do even better than better

Name: Benu
Comments: Every item of food was truly unique.  The explanation by the staff was very clear and welcome

Name: Benu
Comments: Amazing. Well be back!

Name: Benu
Comments: Im still blown away by the culinary experience and Service. That the Benu team provides. The menu was beyond delightful. Loved the Asian influence and all the delicacies. Pictures speak for itself.

Name: Benu
Comments: Anniversary dinner!

Name: Benu
Comments: We went for our anniversary. Very beautiful dishes and tasty as well. I dont like raw food so Benu is the right type of restaurant for me. Most of dishes are from China and Korea. If you like Asian food or want to try Asian food, then you will like it

Name: Benu
Comments: Worth it. It's a month of daycare/preschool for one kiddo. But I like good food/booze, so does my husband, and I appreciated the multicultural, equal gender reppin that night.

Name: Benu
Comments: Most incredible restaurant on the West Coast, worth every penny and the entire trip!

Name: Benu
Comments: Outstanding quality of food, drinks, presentation, and service.

Name: Benu
Comments: An upscale dining experience great for a date night.  The food and service were excellent, but be prepared to spend some serious money.

Name: Benu
Comments: Each dish looked like a masterpiece. The taste  of the food divine. The minimalist decor soothes the senses and awakens imagination. Excellent service.

Name: Benu
Comments: Repeat visit to this exceptional restaurant. Interesting dishes, wonderful presentation, excellent wine pairing. Overall, an extraordinary experience.

Name: Benu
Comments: A new found appreciation for ingredients I grew up with. A fascinating and well thought out twist on Korean and Chinese cuisine. One of the most perfect meals Ive had. Every bite was a dream and the portions were perfect. Benu is an institution and a must visit if youre in SF!

Name: Benu
Comments: My favourite dining experience to date. We went for our anniversary and the service was beyond impeccable. The flavours were inventive and yet still so delicious. Such a special dining experience!

Name: Benu
Comments: Each dish, brought one by one to the table at a comfortable rate, was amazing.  It felt like we were dining in our own home as there was continual interaction with the kindly, professional wait staff.  They were eager to answer questions and seemed to enjoy how much we were enjoying the experience.  I loved the presentation of each delicacy in a special bowl or on a plate made just for that offering.  The only flaw to our evening, one which was not under the control of the waitstaff was the loud talking from a nearby table of business people who could not have actually been eating, or at least not really savoring what was being brought to them.  The food itself was totally worth the price, which is admittedly not for the faint of heart.  You cannot get these dishes anywhere else and the ingredients are rare or difficult to source. The wine offerings were similarly stunning and so were the prices for wines by the glass, which added substantially to our final bill.  It was a special event for us, so we didn't mind the loud conversation nearby us nor the final bill-- we were prepared for that .  It was an epic evening.

Name: Benu
Comments: Its really an amazing restaurant which deserved 3 stars Michelin

Name: Benu
Comments: Hands down the very best service you will ever receive, and the food was euphoric.

Name: Benu
Comments: Really enjoyed the meal.   Loved the Asian influences.

Name: Benu
Comments: have good service

Name: Benu
Comments: I have twice dined at Benu!! The cuisine and the staff are quite amazing! Also, I really appreciated that the tasting menu had quite a few new additions between my 1st visit and most recent visit!

Name: Benu
Comments: Great Meal as the last time. Great food and service from start to the desserts. Every time will be back to SF will visit Benu. All best for all team great job.

Name: Benu
Comments: Sublime restaurant experience.

Name: Benu
Comments: Delicious. Innovative flavor profiles, consistent and excellent execution, thoughtful and perfectly balanced wine pairingsThe service was knowledgeable, professionally enthusiastic, and unobtrusive. Loved our main wait person and the somm was excellent!

Name: Benu
Comments: Outstanding ! Never disappointed! The food is exquisite, innovative, yet with a respect to the spirit of traditional Chinese and Asian gastronomy. The staff is A+.

Name: Benu
Comments: Creative and delicious food in a wonderfully sedate setting.

Name: Benu
Comments: Pretentious & largely tasteless food served by smug, arrogant staff.

Name: Benu
Comments: Amazing place to have one of the best nights of your life! Special Mention to the wine pairing, it was simply perfect for the tasting menu, which is an artwork from Corey. My most sincerely congratulations for him! Every course was a tremendous experience of flavors and textures in another different level. Also the service was spectacular. Every person knows what they are talking about and they make you feel really nice during the whole experience. Really really happy for being there.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Where does one begin. My God, this place was top drawer all the way. Our server Mathew was incredible,  he asked,  he explained, he was attentive,  on a Saturday night no less w all the craziness that ensues on a busy night.  The food was off the charts,  the stuffed peppers and the Saffron crepe where just intense. The cocktails were beautifully orchestrated,  overall a great time and will certainly be returning when I get back to Raleigh.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Favorite restaurant in Raleigh, hands down. Really special new things to try, along with wonderful versions of classics. Seriously, incredible flavors, amazing atmosphere and design - love.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: My second time here and was pleased to bring along three others that had not been to Bida Manda before. It was the perfect experience. From the unique cocktails, amazing apps, tasty entrees and superior service.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Food was great!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: I was thrilled to finally be able to visit Bida Manda!  Due to its deserved popularity, short notice evening reservations are hard to come by, so lunch proved to be a great option.  I thoroughly enjoyed the pork belly soup.  It is unlike anything I've ever had.  For a soup, it is incredibly rich and filling.  The portion was so large that I had more than enough for lunch the next day.  Our server Sophia was so friendly and knowledgeable.  The only downside (and a small one for me) is that the table next to us was very very close.  I look forward to going back to Bida Manda and trying some of the other great menu options!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: The food was delicious! I'll definitely be coming back!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Amazing meal. The most flavorful dishes I have had. I recommend the papaya salad with duck.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: The Green Papaya salad with Lemongrass Chicken is absolutely delightful. Highly recommended.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We attended dinner at Bida Manda for our second anniversary. The staff was very friendly and the food was very good. They start by bringing out some complimentary shrimp chips, which were really pleasant. Our waiter recommended the lettuce wraps as an appetizer and they were hands down the best dish of the night... Im not usually a lettuce wrap kind of guy either. We split the Manda Herb Salad with chicken and Tom Khem (short ribs and pork belly) and they balanced each other nicely. The short ribs were a little dry, but the gravy and fatty pork belly balanced them out well and they tasted delicious. The salad was really nicely balanced. The food is about $20 per entree, but we have enough leftovers for both of our lunches tomorrow, so the value is good for the price.After the waiter packed up our food, he brought us some complimentary macarons to celebrate our anniversary. They were the best macarons weve ever had, and Ive been to Paris. To cleanse our palates at the end of the meal, they served us each a small shot of lemon juice, lime juice, and ginger, which was a great way to wrap up the wonderful experience. Were moving soon, but if were ever in town again, well be revisiting Bida Manda for sure.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Our server Savannah was fantastic, so was the food and drink. Always a great time!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Really delicious and great service.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Food took over an hour to come out. I had ordered a thai tea and it was not ready. They said it would be ready in 5-10 minutes. 20 minutes later they brought out a tea that was nothing like how it normally is. When the food came out it came out very spread out. over 15 minutes between when my food came out and when my guests did. I was very disappointed by this since I have had good experiences in the past and wanted to share with others but was very much let down.  Food was good unsure if I would bring friends for lunch session again.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Service was super; but too noisy, otherwise great!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Great place, great foodHad a great date time with hubby

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Love this place so of course I chose it for my birthday dinner with my best friends. The service is awesome and those waitresses are the nicest people ever! The appetizers are so delicious, its hard to save room for my main course but you have to try it all! My favorite is the lettuce wraps and chicken stirfry. Thank you for the desserts So many wonderful choices and so delicious! Try the special margarita and you wont regret it

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar

We had spring rolls, papaya salad with lemongrass chicken that could have been boring in bad hands but was extremely flavorful and delicious, and a short rib/pork belly dish that was delicious.  Cant find any fault with this place.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Interesting menu and tasty preparation of both cocktails and food.  One our our favorite restaurants in Raleigh.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Exceptional food, service, and atmosphere!  Highly Recommend.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: The food was absolutely fantastic and the service was superb. Will most definitely come back.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Diana was a great server.  Very attentive and made sure our dietary needs were met and that our food was spectacular.  Our table was ready on time as per our reservation.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Fantastic as usual.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Will absolutely be back!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Beyond superb service. What makes this place good is how knowledgable the servers are on the food. All these questions they can answer so clearly and simply. The food quality is always superb. The ambiance was great.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: ALWAYS WONDERFUL! HAVE BEEN HERE MANY TIMES AND NEVER DISAPPOINTED.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We had an absolutely fabulous time. Ross was very attentive, informative and friendly, and the food was phenomenal! Bida never ceases to amaze!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: I had been looking forward to dinner at Bida Manda and I was not disappointed! Food and service were amazing and I would happily go back!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We thoroughly enjoyed Bida Manda! We started with the Lettuce cups and the Summer Rolls. Both were outstanding. I planned to have the Chicken Curry and at the last moment changed my mind and ordered the Green Papaya Salad with flat iron steak. I am so glad I did! The steak was perfectly cooked and the green papaya was crisp and refreshing. My dinning companion ordered the Basil Stir-fry with Tofu. She said it was the best she had ever had! The prices were good too.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Bida Manda became our favorite restaurant from our first visit. The staff and service are always top notch, the food never ever disappoints and the attention to detail in the entire experience is first class. We love this place so much.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We were sat early for our late reservation which was great! Our server was so sweet and very knowledgeable of each menu item. The food was amazing, each bite was better than the last!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: food was unique and delicious. Service was fantastic

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Delicious, quality food. We enjoyed the ramen, lettuce wraps, and spring roll very much. Our services was also wonderful.  Would highly recommend (make a reservation)!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Waiter was amazing and so helpful! Loved it!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Dinner was incredible! Our server was wonderful! The guests next to us were a bit loud and in a heated discussion but we still had a delicious dinner

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Always enjoy Bida Manda!  Original, special, tasty food and OUTSTANDING service!  Helps to book in advance.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Bida Manda is always a great choice for excellent food and service.  It was, of course, full at lunchtime but still got great service.  I had not been there for several years since the first year it opened.  I was a little disappointed at the lack of originality in the food  (quality was great) which seemed much like regular Vietnamese.  My memory was that the menu was more original and authentic with their mother's recipes.  Pad Tai, Pho and Spring Rolls are not what I expect from them.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Its been essentially the same menu for years, and yet the meals never disappoint.  Absolutely love the rice wraps, curry, and sea bass.  The room is a little loud but not so much that we wouldnt want to go back!  One of our favorite restaurants in the Raleigh/Cary area, and apparently we share the same feelings with a lot of other people!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: It was great! The food and atmosphere are amazing!

Name: Bones
Comments: My husband and I celebrated our anniversary this past Saturday and decided to try out Bones, a few people had recommended the place to us before we decided to come here and heard awesome things about it so we were excited to try it out. Everything from making the reservations to the customer service and the dinner was on point! Our reservation was made for 8:30 pm and early in the afternoon one of the employees called me to confirm the reservation and he wished us a happy anniversary (I requested on my reservation an anniversary dessert) I thought that was really nice and thoughtful. When we arrived at the location we were greeted by the valet parking attendant and right away he opened our doors and took our car in. When we walked in and checked in with the host he immediately acknowledged the occasion of our celebration and we were immediately seated. When seated we noticed the tabla had been decorated with anniversary confetti and our waiter offered us a complimentary glass of champagne. The champagne was delicious! we ordered the Scotch Smoked Salmon with Onion, Capers, and Dill Cream as an appetizer; for dinner my husband ordered the Mixed Grill (Filet Mignon, Lamb and Pheasant Sausage) I ordered the Bone-In Rib Eye (20 oz) and for dessert we shared the Warm Pecan Pie with Praline Sauce and French Vanilla Ice Cream. Everything was DELICIOUS! After all this goodness we expected out bill to be a bit crazy but to our surprise it was beyond reasonable for the food and service we experienced. I would definitely come back and would totally recommend this establishment to anyone who is looking for an awesome dinning experience that is worth the money.

Name: Bones
Comments: Always consistent!!!  The staff is wonderful and most have been there for years!!  Great steak house....the best in Atlanta!

Name: Bones
Comments: Food was all absolutely divine, service was stellar and every request was attended to with great care. Best dining experience in a long time.

Name: Bones
Comments: Drove from Alabama to Atlanta to celebrate an anniversary and Bones was A great choice they made it very special.

Name: Bones
Comments: Pleasant staff and atmosphere. Made us feel very welcome. The food was outstanding! Cant wait to go back!

Name: Bones
Comments: We have eaten here many times over the past years and as per usual, Bones never disappoints!!

Name: Bones
Comments: My fianc and I visited Bones recently for his birthday. The staff was polite, accommodating, and really inviting . The food was delicious, and the atmosphere was exactly what I was hoping for. The only critique would be the time it took to bring the check out, the staff may have gotten a tad bit busy. Other than that , it was a very  pleasant experience, I will be returning.

Name: Bones
Comments: We had an incredible dinner celebrating our anniversary. The thoughtfulness and quality of food surpasses our expectations every time. Thank you!

Name: Bones
Comments: Great way to celebrate our anniversary! Food was delicious and service was GREAT!

Name: Bones
Comments: Fantastic attention to detail! Superb service with outstanding food! From the host stand to dessert it was perfect.

Name: Bones
Comments: Bones went above and beyond to make sure our anniversary dinner was special!

Name: Bones
Comments: All around excellent experience. Went for my wifes birthday! We loved it. Will be back.

Name: Bones
Comments: This is our second trip to Bones since reopening and the waiters, servers, concierge are all wearing masks and socially distancing tables with an empty adjacent to you.   Always outstanding and the team is impeccable!

Name: Bones
Comments: Bones is one of my favorite restaurants in Atlanta, especially for an awesome steak. My most recent visit I was not impressed at all with my Filet as it was too bland. My partner LOVED the porterhouse as it had a lot of flavor. The lobster tails were good. Dessert always amazing. It just didn't blow me away the last visit. I'll definitely go back just disappointed with the last visit.

Name: Bones
Comments: Great to back there and take a friend from out of town that had never been

Name: Bones
Comments: The service was wonderful. Our waiter was friendly and attentive. I had the lobster, macaroni and cheese, and greens. It was divine. Margaritas were on point too.

Name: Bones
Comments: The service was impeccable. All of our steaks were cooked to perfection. The sides were delicious and well portioned. Fantastic experience all the way around.

Name: Bones
Comments: Phenomenal food and personalized service, as always! We were celebrating my husbands 50th birthday and they had a private room set up for our group. The table was decorated with confetti and the menus were personalized with his name! Very special! We enjoyed our evening very much! Because of Covid, the restaurant was skipping every other table and all staff were wearing tight fitting masks. I didnt see a single employee remove their mask even once, or pull it below their nose. At all! Felt very safe.

Name: Bones
Comments: Perfect as always

Name: Bones
Comments: Food was great, I did feel rushed though. Appreciate the complimentary champagne and dessert but would have rather looked at the menu and chose my own dessert. Would have appreciated an after dinner drink too but felt rushed to get out

Name: Bones
Comments: Great food, great service, fantastic wine list and great environment.

Name: Bones
Comments: Bones is the best! Everything is perfect from start to finish.

Name: Bones
Comments: Even though we are not regulars the staff Treated us great for our sons 21st birthday.

Name: Bones
Comments: A great place to go for a special dinner!  The steaks were cooked perfectly, and the sides were delicious!  We recommend the Bones salad, lobster bisque soup, hash browns (they were very unique), mushrooms (great compliment to the steaks), and grilled asparagus.

Name: Bones
Comments: It was my first time. It was a business dinner. I will return.

Name: Bones
Comments: Perfect steakhouse experience, nothing is better than Bones - food, service, and the ambiance!  There are lots of upscale steak places in Atlanta but Bones is the best.

Name: Bones

Name: Bones

Name: Bones

We had a wonderful waiter and everything was perfect. We said we must find more reasons to visit Bones in the future. Best steakhouse in Atlanta by far.

Name: Bones

Name: Bones
Comments: Top-notch service and excellent food. They handled every small request we had with pleasure.

Name: Bones
Comments: Was an amazing evening made special by a simple click on Open Table for birthday,  several employee took the time to Say something.  Food left nothing to be desired it was amazing,  No rush simply pleasant meal.

Name: BONDST
Comments: We were super happy with all the food (especially the tuna tarts & miso seabass) until the sushi arrived. You could feel that the fish was good but they simply did not know how to make proper sushi. There was way too much rice which was also over-cooked and the fish was not sliced thin enough. Also, the service was very bad. They walked around yawning and didn't even care to ask us how the food was.

Name: BONDST

So, maybe it was high expectations, but we came again for Valentines last weekend and it was not the same.  The food was mostly pretty good, but certainly not great.  The things i described as wanting from the last time were far off from what the waiter recommended this time.  In general, it was a very disappointing meal.  don't get me wrong, i wouldn't say the food was bad, but for this level (and price) of restaurant, it needs to be great.  Last year i'd give it 5-stars, but this year only 2-stars.

Case in point: the sundried tomato, avocado roll with garlic ponzu oil and green tea salt.....in a word, FABULOUS!!Chef Mark Spitzer is an absolute genius!  Two weeks ago, I 'discovered' the Sake 'Braised' Short Ribs with Miso Daikon, Roasted Fuji Apple and Red Shiso Sauce.I promise you that whatever you order at BondSt will bring you joy!!

Highly recommend all dishes above  wait staff were friendly, attentive and accommodating. Will absolutely be back again.

Comments: The hostess could be a little more respectful and kind. Condescending isnt the best welcome into an establishment.

Comments: As usual, a great experience in every way.  Food, service, atmosphere were all outstanding.  Its the only restaurant in the Covid era that we feel comfortable dining inside. Masks, gloves, cleanliness and social distancing procedures are all meticulously maintained.  They are an example all restaurants should follow.

Name: Buccan
Comments: It was our anniversary and Fathers Day. The receptionist read my note allowing us to come at 7 PM instead of 5:30 PM.
