My mother-in-law has dementia and it gave us more time to feed her before we had to leave our house. It was our first visit and it wont be our last. The mixed drinks, appetizers and entrees were unique and delicious. It was our pleasure to eat at your fine establishment, thanks for a wonderful evening.

Name: Buccan
Comments: This place is a gem.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Amazing food and delicious cocktails, amazing service. Hands down my favorite restaurant on palm beach island. Even have had delicious takeout during covid.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Buccan is one of the safest restaurants I have been to during this pandemic.  They are awesome!!!  You will totally safe.  Everyone is wearing gloves and masks and the tables are more than 6' apart.  Not to mention the food is always amazing!!!

Name: Buccan
Comments: We absolutely loved our experience at Buccan. Great atmosphere and service, excellent food. The agnolotti stands out as particularly delicious, and the watermelon martinis were killer.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Spectacular. Food and service

Name: Buccan
Comments: Love it. Great food and atmosphere.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Amazing food and service! This is our favorite restaurant in Palm Beach!

Name: Buccan
Comments: Fantastic is always.  One of our favorite restaurants anywhere.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Enjoyed a nice dinner. Service was outstanding.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Another fantastic experience at Buccan.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Buccan was a pleasure as always! Spacing and cleanliness have been made paramount for the new normal and the menu is, as always, amazing!

Name: Buccan
Comments: Amazing! Everything was delicious.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Always amazing

Name: Buccan
Comments: They never disappoint! A very special dining experience an always go back for the steak tartare! Best Ive ever had!!

Name: Buccan
Comments: Everything was outstanding, I have never been disappointed since I started dining here over 5 years ago.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: From service to our meal the evening was one to remember. The staff at Cafe Monarch are on a level of their own.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: It was excellent, as always.  The food is creative and amazing.  The service is outstanding.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: The best food, service, very romantic and special.  1st class all the way. Can't wait to go back.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: My current favorite restaurant. I travel for work, and this restaurant beats everything in New York, San Francisco, LA, Santa Fe, and points in between. Bold flavor combinations with perfect acidity and balance. The Chef rocks!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: One of the top restaurants in Scottsdale! Its a must go!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Very romantic atmosphere. Service was awesome. The best food we have ever had so delicious every course. The waiter was so informed on food and wine. It was our wedding anniversary and we loved out experience.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Great place to dine for a special occasion. Our waiter and the staff were fantastic

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Great food but better service! one of the best dining experiences in Phoenix

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: This was my first time and won't be my last!! We had looked to come here before and why we did not I am not sure. Our server Kyle was wonderful and very knowledgeable. We enjoyed every aspect of the meal the course selections were beautiful the presentation and flavors exceeded. I can't wait to bring my husband back.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: This place is definitely a photo shoot spot if you're looking for a romantic, warm and cozy place to start an unforgettable night date. The service was impeccable started with the wine pairing from the extensive list.  It's a 4-course dinner menu with least two options per course, but you can get  la carte if you sit at the bar. For pricing, everything is determined by the fourth course of your choosing. I chose the "Dijon Brushed New Zealand Lamb Rack" which was $120. While my mother (whom I brought for long-overdue Mother's Day dinner) ordered the "Niman Ranch USDA Prime Ribeye" which was $135. The other three courses are included in that price. We also ordered the add-on "Hudson Valley Foie Gras" which was out of this world--my mom loved it so much that she wouldn't save any for me. Dessert is extra, ours were $12 each. The dessert menu includes not only cakes but sorbets, dessert cocktails, coffee, grappa, digestifs, cordials, dessert wine and more.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Great food, great staff and the ambience was fantastic. Highly recommend.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Excellent as always!!  The entire staff was exceptional!  Food was superb...we keep coming back because Monarch truly is the best in Phoenix!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Amazing food - best service!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Fabulous food, service and atmosphere.  Thank you to John and Juan and everyone at Cafe Monarch.  We will be back.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Cafe Monarch is always an amazing experience and tonight did NOT disappoint!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: As always enjoyed it very much

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: The entire staff was outstanding. The restaurant exudes total style and class. The food far exceeded my high expectations and the Chilean Sea Bass was the best piece of fish I have ever eaten.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Beautiful and delicious restaurant.  The service was first rate and the cuisine was of the highest caliber.  Our bill was approximately $200 a person with tip.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: This was an experience, a real treat!  Great place to celebrate a special occasion or just enjoy upscale dining.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Noahs the best, but the whole place is first class. So grateful for a place like this that makes you feel so special. They will redefine how you view service.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: We always have a great experience at Cafe Monarch. Each course has a wonderful combination of flavors and is very visually appealing. I would further emphasize that when you are spending several hundred dollars for dinner/drinks you don't want to feel hurried or rushed but rather made to feel you are taking part in an event or a very enjoyable experience. We definitely feel that way every time we dine here and greatly appreciate that they incorporate this into their way of doing business with their customers. By comparison some of the high end "scene" seafood and steakhouses in Old Town have decor is that is modern/beautiful and their service is polite/attentive but we always feel hurried along. They try to do it inconspicuously but it is always noticed. For the same money we would rather return again and again for the experience we receive at every Cafe Monarch visit.Keep up the amazing job!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: We came here for our parents anniversary/Mom's bday dinner.  Older parents had never experienced the pairings available and what a treat.  They both loved it.  Only compliant was the music was a bit too loud and on a short loop. The waiter = awesome. The service = on point! The food = cheers to the chef. My mom inhaled the chilean sea bass. My brother and I didn't even get a taste :( The wine pairings = Magnifique! Deserts were a treat for the celebration and we wanted more! Strongly recommend the experience - oh and put down those cell phones to absorb it all! - The valet = excellent photographic skills my friend! and BAM with that light! You were on it! Black Manhattans - BOOM! so good. All the staff were EXCEPTIONAL!!!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: This continues to be the best restaurant in Arizona.  Flawless in every regard.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Phenomenal service and creative menu! Will be returning

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Beautiful restaurant!  Delicious food.  Great for special occasions.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Always enjoy eating at Cafe Monarch.  The ambience and decor of the inside and outside is wonderful.  The food and service is excellent.  Can't wait to return.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Magical place to have dinner. Can't wait to return!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: One of my most favorite spots!!  Wonderful service and fantastic food!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: From the very first minute we walked in the door, we felt welcomed & that they were happy we had come! The most beautiful restaurant we have ever dined in! Our hostess was lovely & so sweet. This is our 3rd visit to Cafe Monarch & we see something new each time. There is so much beauty everywhere, we just try to soak it all in. Gorgeous fresh white roses & greenery centerpiece, plus a real flame lamp. Beautiful lamp stands all over with real lighted candles on them. Chandeliers are amazing, so sparkling & spectacular! Service is perfect in every way, such attention to detail & so gracious, makes you feel like some kind of royalty! We  were blessed with Kyle as our waiter, who instantly remembered us from the month before, when we celebrated my birthday. This time we brought our daughter for her 50th birthday & she was overwhelmed. Just delightful in every way! Spectacular food, every course, every bite, phenomenal. You really just can't believe how wonderful it all is! Best food we have ever had, in any restaurant, anywhere! No exaggeration. When our daughter got up to use the restroom, a waiter refolded her napkin, so when she came back it was just like new. A nice touch! Attention to every detail imaginable! I love the detailed description of each course, by our server when they brought our food. For her birthday, they brought out the most amazing chocolate dessert, remembering that she was gluten free. It came with a lighted sparkler in it, so fun & a great picture moment! The cocktails were pretty & so delicious! Kyle was outstanding throughout! He remembered so many things about my tastes in food & made accommodations accordingly. Very impressive!! We plan to dine at Cafe Monarch as often as possible, making sure we bring all of our family, at one time or another. Our daughter is already planning to come back for their 30th wedding anniversary in December & they live in Colorado! That's how great Cafe Monarch is! We absolutely LOVE it! Thanks Kyle! So Special

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: The food was delicious and was definitely worth the price. My boyfriend and I went here for our anniversary and they really made it feel like a special occasion. I would highly recommend this place to anyone.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Great as always, every bit is delicious and the service was very professional, we will be back.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Exceptional staff. All very friendly, knowledgeable, wished us a happy anniversary. Made us feel special and like only ones there. Food was beautiful and amazing.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Coming from Europe, we are spoiled with good food.This was by far my best experience of high end food in the US.A  suggestion:  All portions were perfect. The main course was too much.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Amazing food and service was outstanding. Would definitely recommend for a romantic date night.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: We enjoy Cafe Monarch for special occasions.  It is a little pricey (we typically spend at least $500 per couple) but it always makes for a memorable evening.  Their garden is terrific with comfortable temperatures even in summer.  All dishes on their 4 course menu are first class.  The staff is second to none. Important, social distancing and face masks are enforced.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: We went for our 30th anniversary.  Everything was spectacular.  Loved to food.  The wine choices that were made for me were very good.  Strongly recommend.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: What's more to say about Cafe Monarch.  The food and service is always outstanding.  Especially impressive during the this pandemic is the extra care they are taking care to give all their guests a safe environment.  All staff are wearing masks. Even the valet was masked and wearing gloves.  They've removed approx 25% of their tables to overly comply with the social distancing guidelines.My wife and I couldn't have felt safer dining in our own home.

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: My favorite restaurant in the United States!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Not the best seating, the lamb was very fatty. Otherwise decent experience!

Name: Caf Monarch
Comments: Just not really worth $600 date night

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: The food was delicious and the service superb. There are very few fine dining restaurants left in the area and Cafe Provence doesnt disappoint. Dessert was delicious and the coffee first rate. I particularly appreciated the affordable wine list $30-50 is plenty to pay for wine. Particularly when most restaurant lists feature wine that can be purchased in the local liquor store for $15-20 and charge at least $60 for it. Ill come again and recommend it to my friends.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: The menu is seasonal so recommendations are difficult. Everything is always fresh and amazing. I always order fish dishes. The fish, no matter what kind is always very fresh and perfectly cooked.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Crab cake, veal entrees and lemon cherry almond dessert were all fabulously delicious & beautiful presentation! Conversation friendly, inviting ambience and professional engaging waitress made for a delightful lunch experience.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Wonderful menu! We loved our aperitif and meal! Our service was impeccable!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Always exceptional dining experience with such detail to seasonal flavors.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: It certainly lives up to its reputation! The food was of the highest quality we have found in Kansas City, among the top-tier restaurants. Service was top-notch and everything was better than we expected. We will definitely be back.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Wonderful as usual

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: This is a lovely place. The food was great and the ambience was relaxing. They fully decorated the empty tables with little vignettes. It was a nice touch.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Caf Provence sets the standard of excellence in KC region. The food, flavors, presentation, creativity, and attentive staff are always wonderful.. Cest magnifique!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Amazing food, service!  I want to come all the time!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: First time we tried Cafe Provence and it was very good.  Highly recommend.  We really enjoyed it and will definitely be back.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: The restaurant was the perfect setting as we celebrated our 50th wedding anniversary.  Our waiter was knowledgeable on both wine and food questions, the pace of service was very good and the meal was outstanding.  One of the best meal experiences we've had in a very long time.  Thanks to the entire staff.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: We had lunch outside which was our choice.  You might consider putting a fan or two outdoors to move some air around.Thanks.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Exquisite as always. Every single dish is delicious! Chicken with morel brandy cream sauce could be poured over shoe leather and its be divine but luckily its served with a succulent chicken breast....ate every morsel! My brother, whos fluent en francaise had the beef bourginon which he lapped up. Neither of us had eaten out much since Feb so it was a real treat!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Wonderful wait staff and menu!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Simply the best place for lunch or dinner with a french flair for food, service and style.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Always a great meal with exception customer service.  A definite favorite night out for any occasion!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Aside from the statewide mask mandate, everything was excellent. Food was fantastic as always. We finally got to try their Monday souffl, which was so worth it!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: A favorite place to eat.  Knowledgeable server.   Love the ambience.   Great food.  Love the French Market too!!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: I had lunch with friends,and we sat outside. Food and service were both fabulous!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Chicken crepes, Corvino bass special and new summer lemon cherry almond crunch dessert were all delicious and beautifully presented.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: We were here yesterday for lunch. Needless to say all main dishes, soup and salads were just perfect and so was the service!Notable was my Trout Fish dish was just delectable. As always very efficient service.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: We appreciate the consistent quality and it is a long time favorite for us.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: It was my first time and it was worth all the great things I had heard about it.  Can't wait to come back!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: As always, best food in the Midwest!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Delicious food in a Parisian- like setting. Friendly and knowledgeable waitstaff. Wonderful date spot or special occasion venue. We will definitely be back soon!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Always a fabulous artful meal with excellent customer service!  Thank you!!!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: The best restaurant in KC !   Perfect for lunch or dinner....whether for two, alone or a small group.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: food was excellent as usual.  appreciate the attention to virus safety

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Time and time again... the best dining experience in KC.   Fabulous food (try the veal), ambience as genuine as if you were sitting in a France.  Wonderful service.   A joy, every time.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Amazing french restaurant! Service and food were great. We'll go back for sure. Merci beaucoup!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Did the 4 course prix fixe tonight. Smoked salmon, potato salad - crisp potatoes with tasty salmon with a CinsaultCorn bisque, pesto - this wowed us! Sweet and savory with a sparkling white wineSkate wing, brown butter, haricot vert, tomato with a muscadet - what you would expect from one of the best French restaurants in the country! Lemon, cherry and cassis verrine with crme chantilly - excellent finish to a great dinner. Tart cherries... French press coffeeWe had staff did 1/2 glass wine pairings for us. Excellent service. Social distancing done tastefully inside. Only 7 tables and 2 bar seats available. More seating outside with distancing n mind too. All staff wore masks and never lowered them to talk. Love Cafe Provence will continue to return!!!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Great food. The staff was friendly and helpful.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: I adore this beautiful French restaurant! The food is fantastic. The service is exceptional and the ambiance is quaint and transport you to France. I come here often.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Cafe Provence is our favorite place because they always offer the full package dining experience.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: This was our 1st time back after the COVID-19 quarantines. The food was excellent as always. The service was also great

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: We celebrated a birthday and enjoyed a phenomenal meal which made the celebration fantastic!  Flowers had been ordered from a near-by florist and had been delivered for the table!Absolutely perfect!!!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Best french restaurant in kc

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: It was delicious. Outside seating and our server was wonderful.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Dining a Caf Provence is always the gustatory highlight of the day. The food is consistently superb, the wine list (though not large) has a broad variety of quality wines, and the staff are uniformly warm and accommodating.

Name: Charleston
Comments: A very elegant dining experience. Menu has the best gourmet offerings one could desire!  Worth the price!!

Name: Charleston
Comments: Eating here is an event and is sublime from start to finish.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Always a pleasure. Fine wines. Pricey, but worth it for special occasions. Portions are small (tasting) but magnificent.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Excellent as always!  Bartender was exceptionally knowledgeable, and food was fantastic

Name: Charleston
Comments: Food & service is great , worth the price.Best experience

Name: Charleston
Comments: Very good food; average to good service; a bit noisy.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Wonderful service, outstanding food. A great dining experience!!!!

Name: Charleston
Comments: Charleston is one of the top tier restaurants in the mid Atlantic region.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Outstanding food preparation. First rate wine list.Impeccable service.Elegant comfortable ambience.For special occasions.

Name: Charleston
Comments: This was the most amazing meal my wife and I ever had. Special occasions become elevated dining in a place like this. We were incredibly happy with our experience

Name: Charleston
Comments: The food is always good. The location is great and the view of the water you can't beat.

Name: Charleston
Comments: BEST FOOD, BEST SERVICE, BEST DINING EXPERIENCE EVER!!!

Name: Charleston
Comments: Excellent food! One of the best spots in Baltimore.

Name: Charleston
Comments: My favorite restaurant!  I love the way the menu is presented with no categories.

Name: Charleston
Comments: By far, the best restaurant in Baltimore.  Cindy Wolf is a creative genius.  She  also keeps the restaurant performing like a well-choreographed dance.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Outstanding menu, wine selection, and service.  An experience not to be missed.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Wonderful for a special occasion. Food, service, and ambiance are all outstanding.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Best place for a romantic night out or special occasion with amazing food, and great service.  The lobster curry bisque or the she crab soup are both delicious.  Local and fresh ingredients are used.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Outstanding food and impeccable service.  What else do you need?!! The perfect place to celebrate a special occasion and now a more casual dining opportunity in the bar.  Charleston is expensive, but worth every penny!

Name: Charleston
Comments: Formality reigns with kindness and gentleness!  Delicious dining experience.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Special occasions with wife. Always more special here at Charleston.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Memorable food experience. We went for a special birthday, and the meal lived up to the hype and the price. They pay attention to details and you feel special about being in the beautiful place eating gorgeous and delicious food.

Name: Charleston
Comments: I've been here twice for special occasions and absolutely love it.  The food is spectacular and the service is outstanding.  Completely worth it.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Cindy Wolf's oldest is still her best and food shines at Charleston

Name: Charleston
Comments: Cindy Wolf knows how to run a restaurant.  Charleston has been renovated since it's inception but there was never a time the food wasn't top notch. Innovate and delicious.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Some of the finest food and service in the area.  The best sauces and selections of foods.  Super wine list and pairings.  High quality everything.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Great restaurant wonderful food and service never had a bad meal.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Baltimore's finest restaurant. Every detail is perfect, from the drinks, food, service, and decor.  Pricy but worth a visit.

Name: Charleston
Comments: It has been several years since I ate there but it remains the best restaurant/meal/evening I have had to date.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Definitely a special occasion spot, never disappointed, exceptional food and service.

Name: Charleston
Comments: So here's the thing. The food wasn't bad. It was good. It just wasn't $500+ for two people good. My husband and I have been to exceptional Michelin star/bib gourmand restaurants in the United states, UK, and elsewhere. These places provide you with an excellent experience and fantastic food that we feel are worth the amount they charge. The bottom line for us was the service was nice, the food was good, but it was absolutely not worth how much we paid especially when compared to world class restaurants that charge nearly HALF the price for an unforgettable experience. Not for us.

Name: Charleston
Comments: The portions were very small and very rich.  I ordered a filet mignon medium and got rare,  The cheesecake for dessert was the size of an ice cube.  The service was outstanding.  Overall, it was nice; but I did not consider it a good value.

Name: Charleston
Comments: We hadn't been to the Charleston for many years.  We were not disappointed.  It was a wonderful experience.  The food was great and the service was superb.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Baltimore institution. Wine bar with most delicious food in the world.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Fantastic private dinner for 16.  I will return whenever I'm in Baltimore.

Name: Charleston
Comments: A top notch experience from start to finish!

Name: Charleston
Comments: Best Restaurant ever!! Wonderful experience all around!!! A must when visiting Baltimore.

Name: Charleston
Comments: One of my favorite restaurants! My wife and I frequent Charleston celebrating many momentous occasions and the New Year's menu is always extra special.  Charleston is one the best restaurants in the United States. Everything is perfection. I have had the pleasure of dining here many times and it always amazes. The lamb I had here recently was the best preparation I have ever eaten. The truffle soup with foie gras I had recently is something I'll be thinking about for many months. Quiet honestly you just have to eat try the diversity of the menu to experience it. No review could describe quality and taste of food or does justice to all the flavors. You just have to eat it!   A true culinary experience. The service is truly professional and friendly.  No better way to start a new year.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Imho the only destination in Baltimore for true fine dining. Opt for the pairing menu to get the most out of most food and wine.

Name: Charleston
Comments: Dinner was outstanding from start to finish. Great service and great food.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Closed. No reservation confirmation. Went to Anson instead

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Best crab cake ever!!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: We really enjoyed our dinner!  Taylor introduced himself as our server and that Steve would be assisting him, however we had at least 2 others assisting. The service was outstanding! We did the the 6 course, my husband did it with the wine pairing. They were very generous with the wine, there were a few wines that he really enjoyed and he was offered a 2nd pour. Food was very good and Taylor was very helpful in helping us choose the selections for the courses.The restaurant also had a jazz type band, they played at just the right volume so that you could enjoy the music and still have conversation.If this restaurant was located close to our home, it would become a "go to" for us!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Always a pleasure to dine at the Grill. The staff was outstanding and every morsel was delicious.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Food was great. We are vegetarian and there were enough options for me and my husband. They are very kind people and they have a fantastic service.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Great service and very good food.Wine selection was superb.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Food and service was outstanding! I am looking foward to sharing great times with friends and family here.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: We went to Charleston Grill for our anniversary. They treated us so well and the food was outstanding!  My wife felt it was one of the best dinners she had ever had!!  What a very special night for us. Every aspect of the dinner was perfect!!  Great serving and great taste!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Amazing highly recommend this dinner!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Just an amazing perfect meal!  Came for a girls weekend and this meal and our server Adam were truly a highlight of the trip.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: It was fantastic! Highly recommend and would definitely come back.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: If youre looking for superb service and delicious cuisine - look no further. Make your reservation now. Every request was accommodated with a smile, from our preferred seating to the pace of our meal. Our waiter, Jerry, was personable and knowledgeable. He went out of his way to make sure we had a perfect experience. It felt like we were the only guests in the restaurant. We are excited to return.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Great food, great service, very attentive to our 2 year old granddaughter!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Great date night location! Love music until after closing time, great drinks and a variety to choose from. Service and food was outstanding, cant wait to go back!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Absolutely fabulous dinner, from start to finish! Great wines also.... cannot wait to go back!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Have stayed at the Belmond several times.  This is our second time dining at Charleston Grill located on the property.   The service was exceptional and the food was awesome.   We had the crab cake and I must say one of the best I have had.  My husband had the oysters.  I had the flounder and it was delicious.   Next time will definitely try the tasting menu!! Cant wait to return.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Spectacular evening!  We did the tasting menu and wine pairing.  Food was delicious and wait staff impeccable!  A must if wanting a fine dining true experience!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Last night in Charleston was the best dining experience we had all week!  Amazing food, outstanding service, and quiet and romantic ambiance.  Everything we could have asked for in a dinner date!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Everything was excellent!  My husband had the steak and said it was one of the best he had and I had the linguine and enjoyed every bite.  Bread offerings were great and drinks were wonderful!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Wonderful meal, great ambiance and excellent music for the occasion

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Nice food, expensive, and where are the young clients?.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: The service and wine list were great, but we were both disappointed with the food. We ordered oysters and the 4 course tasting menu. They werent kidding about tasting, we did not get much, what we did get was not very impressive, definitely not worth it. I would not go back or recommend it.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: It was our belated Valentines dinner. We especially enjoyed the little extra touches: the treats after dinner, coffee from a french press, etc. Service and food was excellent.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Got off to a very slow start waiting for our drinks. They were not as good as weve had elsewhere. We did the chefs choice tasting  - amazing crab cake. Everything else was nice but very rich. We all had stomach issues later in the night.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: We went for my husbands birthday dinner.  The staff treated us so well & made it very special!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Amazing food and service!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Outstanding food and service. The crab cake was the best I have ever had(and I have had many)!  We will definitely be back!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Fantastic food and service - would highly recommend!!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Lovely food and service. Excellent selection of white Burgundy. Order the crab cakes!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: A great dining experience......

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Amazing food!! Great service. wonderful dessert. A bit pricey, but well worth it.I'd recommend this as one of the great restaurants anywhere.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Wonderful evening celebrating our 30th Anniversary!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Overall attention to detail and high quality of food and service

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Everything was wonderful. The Williams Duo music was fantastic!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Amazing wine list, including half a page of vintage champagne

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: We love the food! The restaurant is beautiful and the valet service wonderful, but the food is the star.I always order the caviar and am never disappointed. We also ordered the sunchoke side to share, and it was the best thing I have literally ever eaten. Amazing. In addition, the service is great and you will leave full, as the wait staff brings snacks along the way throughout your experience. Even cute little dessert bites.Definitely in my top two places to eat in Charleston.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Great food and service.  The staff was attentive and responsive to our every need.  Charleston Grill is one of our favorite dining stops in the city.

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: My wifes birthday and the meal and evening were fantastic, great food, superb service!

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Excellent in all aspects. The hydroponically grown salad leaves were delicious and great to see the current technologies being brought to the table for our enjoyment

Name: Charleston Grill
Comments: Wonderful in all ways. Crab cake was amazing!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Well-executed, French-influenced cocktails. Tasty rillettes and pt. All our entrees were excellent. Great outdoor setting.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Chez Billy Sud has done a great job mastering outdoor dining during both the Covid 19 period and very warm weather.  The service was excellent, the menu, though limited,delivered many of the restaurant's standards.  Only disappointment, no coffee or desert.Definitely worth a visit during these trying times.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Waiter was friendly and knowledgeable.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Patio dining at Chez Billy Sud is the way to go during the pandemic. Gracious and attentive service and delicious, well-prepared food make Chez Billy Sud a welcome oasis.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: It was terribly hot on the patio, but that could not be helped. Our waitresswas really wonderful and I know it was really HOT for her, because she neverstopped working! The food was excellent. Happy to have you all opened again.I will be back...but after the sun goes down! Thanks!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: We had been trying to eat at Chez Billy Suds for the past 2 years, but for different reason or another we hadnt been.  Well, we finally made it on Friday!  All the expectations were reached!  Food, ambiance and service were great!  Call out to our waiter!!!Even Mother Nature with  a little bit of a breeze on an 80+ degree evening.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Great. The service was the best.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Fantastic! Felt comfortable with their covid measures, food was wonderful, service impeccable, and best cosmo Ive had in a long time.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: What a treat to dine on the lovely patio. They really maintained safe social distancing!  Trout and gazpacho were delish; service was fantastic.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Honestly, the layout they have outside just turns their outside venue into an oven. Between the two cement walls, the sun, and lack of air flow into the area it just wasnt any fun. Simply put, the service was not great either and have add on 18% tip along a service fee for the COVID adjustments theyve had to endure. But honestly its just shy of extortion, 5% seems little but they literally did nothing other move it outside to a warm and uncomfortable venue in hopes of health and safely. Shame they feel the need to charge costumers more in a time of crises rather than relief.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: A staff so warm and caring that gave us  just the right amount of attention.  Soft shell crabs so delicious that we returned a week later for more!  And all were extremely careful about spacing and sanatizing .  We felt very secure.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: The best gin and tonic Ive ever had (Hendricks gin).

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Ice Cold Martini, Chilled Ros, Excellent Soft Shell Crabs! Wonderful Chicken Liver Mousse (would love the recipe) served with piping hot toasted baguette.  The service was performed perfectly with facemasks and little contact.  A beautiful D.C. summer evening on a romantic outdoor patio. Couldn't ask for more.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Awesome place.  I would recommend this place to a friend..

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: My friend and I arrived (both women) and were seated at a 2 top not on the patio but outside of it. We were both wearing nice dresses. A young couple directly after us was seated inside the patio at a nice 4 top. She was wearing jeans and a crop top; he was wearing shorts and a tee shirt - both had on tennis shoes. They were 20 years younger and were given a better table. They were in and out within an hour. My friend and I had a cocktail, a bottle of wine, appetizers, our main course and desert (that the waiter didnt bother to take out of the to go container.) Ive definitely had better service. The food was outstanding but the service was lacking.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Had inside table which was great due to a/c on a humid DC night!  The dining room was atmospheric and quietly elegant.  Our server Torrance was awesome, and very helpful when deciding what to order.  I had duck confit which was amazing, 2 others had the steak & frites which they said was excellent, and one other had the burger which he couldn't finish because it was so big!  But he said it was delicious.  Nice pre-dinner cocktail menu.  I had the Pimms cup which was yummy.  Nice touch was that we didn't order any desserts, but were sent home with 2 complimentary small chocolate cakes to share.  We will definitely be back!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: We returned to Chez BS after a long hiatus from any restaurant dining.  CBS had just opened the week previous and only outside on their patio.  The patio/alley is more than comfortable and real feels like vacation.  CBS has installed wonderful overhead awnings that are both handsome and practical.  We enjoyed our meal and were sent home with desert fixings - 2nd week open no desert menu yet.  We loved our father's day meal at 6:30.  No rushing - good a service and fine food.  BTW - our last meal out before the CV 19 shutdown was at Chez BS so we did a bit of a loop.  Best to all! Stay safe and we certainly felt that way last Sunday.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Delicious food and very attentive service, particularly during a very challenging time. Good to be able to dine there again!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: All tables are now seated outside and on a beautiful evening it is really special. One of the best Caesar saladsIve ever had and I recommend the trout and soft shells. Post shutdown, our server seemed especially pleased to have customers. Cant wait to go back. Tip them generously bc theyve been out of work!!!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Delicious meal and outstanding service in their patio.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Chez Billy SudMy wife and I eloped earlier in the day and came to Chez Billy Sud to celebrate our first meal together. We wanted a good outdoor dinner, given the COVID-19 environment. Somewhere new for us that would be tasty, with good decor.Our experience was excellent and memorable. The setup of the outdoor seating felt like we were in a different city, not Washington, D.C. - it was a pleasant surprise. The food was great. We had caesar salad, tomato cucumber soup, steak frites, and a chocolate dessert. The steak frites especially were wonderful.Our server Torrance really took care of us. He gave us good recommendations and he was engaging. He and the other servers took appropriate precautions in helping us and the restaurant, but they were all still friendly and attentive. We received a round of champagne on the house, plus an additional round from another family kind enough to surprise us with one.And when we left, everyone at the restaurant started clapping for us. It was a special moment that will stick with us for our lifetime.Overall 5 Star experience - no question. Well be back!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Chez Billy Sud was recommended to us as a great place for a quiet family birthday dinner, great ambiance, excellent food and for just being a perfect place for French dining. It had all that and met all expectations and more. The staff are super friendly. I wish the inside seating opened soon. It is filled with vintage things, there's an old woodburning fireplace and it just smells incredibly. Definitely looking forward to coming back.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: It was so great to get back to Chez Billy Sud a few days after they re-opened. The staff here does such a great job and it was great to see them after all this time. We sat out on the patio and the weather was perfect! The food - soft shell crabs - just outstanding!! Still the best soft shells in the city! Love this restaurant. Looking forward to coming back soon!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Always fantastic! Currently, they have a limited patio menu but it is still delicious.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Absolutely the best preparation and presentation. For me, THE go-to special occasion place.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Service was amazing. I would definitely go back with friends the scene is great! Perfect for a quick French bite or drinks with friends.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Wonderful service as they opened back up. Lovely!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Exceptional. The dining room, the ambiance, the meal, the service - bravo! Thank you, Debra and Chez Billy Sud, for a delightful evening.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: A great little intimate and delicious restaurant. Steak and mussels were wonderful, as was the Caesar salad.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Just a perfect date night spot. Cosy bistro seating. Super friendly staff. Tasty dishes, both seasonal offerings and French classics. We will be back!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Great experience. Service and food were fantastic. Great atmosphere for date night.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Chez Billy was amazing!! I cant say enough good things about our experience. The food was amazing. The ambiance is perfect, very quaint and chic. Will be back !!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Fantastic food and ambience!  We will definitely come back.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: In my opinion, it's the best overall French restaurant in DC.  Yes, better than Le Dip.  But please don't go, as I don't want it to get any harder for me to get a table here.  Service is always attentive and professional.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: The three of us had trout, tuna, and salmon, all was excellent.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Beautiful little French restaurant in Georgetown with gorgeous interior and perfect menu. Went to brunch and every detail is magnificent!  Service attentive and friendly. The Nioise salad was delicious and be sure to sample the beignets.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Chez Billy Sud is a true neighborhood restaurant that works well for either a casual night out or a more special date night. The food is always on point and the execution is true to the classics. Nothing is 're-imagined' or 'interpreted', just technically cooked extremely well. Our server (whose name I didn't catch, regretfully) was tremendous and seemed to be handling 1/2 the dining room incredibly graciously. We had drinks at 3 different restaurants during our night, and the ones at Chez billy Sud were the most consistently executed and well-balanced. Consistency is a sadly overlooked attribute when everyone wants to be 'new' but Chez Billy Sud continues to exemplify the idea that care and execution are the real drivers of success. We'll absolutely be back, especially for the patio and rose in the summer / spring.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: This is an 'casual' vibe but upscale French restaurant, elegant, charming, with impeccable service.  The food is outstanding.  Highly recommended.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Dining experience was spectacular as always. Party included a 90 year old. Service was courteous. Noise level low as we were seated in small front room having few tables, and tables wee well spaced.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: We came for lunch at 12:30 on Saturday and it was EXTREMELY noisy.  It finally quieted down later.My salad was good once they cooked the tuna a little more.  The waiter could have been more attentive.  He seemed to disappear at times.  We thought it was odd that they don't offer espresso or cappuccino.  Maybe simplicity is better for them, but we thought it was a bit inhospitable. He said there were so many coffee places nearby... Not a big problem.  Overall, it was a very nice lunch.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Those steaks were super delicious as well as salad, side of veggies and deserts :) It was in the evening a day before all LA restaurants started close and serve only take-out orders. Seemed many customers cancelled reservations, very unusual to see empty tables, dining just few customers. Top class food for sure, at same time cozy and casual atmosphere, I wish they make a little more reasonable prices. Like, 36 oz bone-in ribeye steak was $205 that perfect size to share for 2, $102.50 each person, probably $20-$30 higher than Mastros, BOA, etc.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: My experience here was amazing. Great food & impeccable service. We had many things on the menu & they were all exquisitely done. For meats, the Porcini rubbed short ribs are fantastic. If you can afford it, the 36oz Ribeye (or NY Steak) is a must for the table. It was dry aged spectacularly. Truly one of the best steaks in all of LA.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: I dont know where to start. I arrived and several of my guests preceded me. Their wine has been decanted but no water poured as they waited. After about 5 minutes the waitress appeared and I told her that we would start with champagne, foccacia and salad immediately but she responded that we had to order everything at the same time or the chef wouldnt even look at the order. So we sat and decided the entire order which I then shared with waitress. I ordered lots of food and then asked if we could order more just in case we wanted more afterwards and was told that it depended on whether or not they needed to turn the table. The sides came out first and after a few minutes we served them and them finally ate them before the meet arrived. I brought the service issue to my servers attention and she then proceeded to avoid me even though I had told her earlier that i was picking up the tab for our party of 6. Empty water glasses and plates left on the table between courses. I flagged down other servers or personnel to get service. It was a rather  unfortunate series of events that made for a less than special evening for the birthday celebration intended.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Extremely disappointed with the steak. My group and I tasted nothing but salt on a $200 bone in. I was excited and looked forward to our visit but I was extremely disappointed with the quality of the food.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Fantastic dining experience! Loved the food and wine. Excellent service. Fun vibe. Very expensive, but felt like a special night out. Would highly recommend!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Our sixth visit was unfortunately our least favorite. We LOVE Chi Spacca. Even this off night was pretty wonderful. That said, we noticed a pricing issue between what was on the menu and what we were charged for an item, and one of our meat dishes was far too rare for us to enjoy, which was especially disappointing since we had ordered the same thing three times before, and it was fantastic. Service is always terrific, and if this had been my first visit, I probably would have loved it, but since we have seen Chi Spacca at its most spectacular, this visit was a bit of a letdown.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: My wife and I celebrated our 25th anniversary, and the food, service and ambience exceeded all expectations. Although the restaurant is pricy, for a special occasion it is more than worth the money!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Always a fantastic experience.   One of the best in LA for a reason.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Most of our food was outstanding. The oil-soaked bread with burrata, the little gem salad, the plate of citrus (a wonderfully refreshing palate cleanser before the main course), the broccoli, and the lemon posset with balsamic were all delightful. The only dish that my made my partner and I look at each other and say anything other than, "Wow, this is perfect," was, surprisingly enough, the meat entree. We ordered the Porcini Rubbed Beef Short Ribs, and I have to say that the salsa verde was more enjoyable than the meat itself. They tasted overcooked and were somewhat lacking in flavor. That being said, we still cleaned the plate as the short ribs would still blow most out of the water - even if they didn't live up to the chi Spacca standard. Our service didn't meet the typical standard of a award-winning restaurant, either. Our server was not very attentive and we had empty, dirty plates stacked in front us more than once, though I suppose this is better than an over-attentive server, and it may be because we chose counter seating rather than a table. All in all, I would recommend chi Spacca with an 8/10 stars.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: We had a reservation but it wasnt honored. We waited 25 minutes in a very small outer space with no seating and the door to the actual restaurant was kept closed so we couldnt look inside.The look and feel of the restaurant was very nice and the wait staff was fine . Certain dishes were delicious (the focaccia bread in particular) while others were very disappointing (the tomahawk pork chop). Not cooked thru and I disliked the seasoning of fennel pollen. Will probably not return.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: We loved the food but is not very often resturant to go for bcuz is pricey but overall I will recommend

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: The food wasnt worth the price

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Amaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaazing!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: by far one of the best restaurants in los angeles. the quality and value of food is so perfect. everything on th menu is amazing. especially the salad with bacon vin. and the diablo chicken

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Valentines Day!!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Great vibe. Not sure about quality of steaks

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Had the pleasure of dining with Lidia Bostianich as she shared recipes from her newest cookbook.  Great food, great wine and great company!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Loved the special event on Feb 10

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Too much Salt.......I didn't think the food has maintained it's level of taste.  It's not the same ChiSpacca as it was and I've been dining there once it's opening!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: The overall experience was okay but not exceptionally great. We asked a member of the staff for help with taking our photo and he responded that he was busy and did not stop, come back or made an attempt to help us however when they were setting up a new table next to us with new guests they gave them all their attention. felt that we were not valued as guests, disrespected and we will not be dining here again.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Great Dinner due to Eduardo. Great service from him. He was so knowledgeable and efficient. All food was delicious. Would definitely return. Duck was on point.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Fantastic!!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Fantastic as always.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Outstanding meal!!!!  Wow!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: This place is next level. Sit at the counter for a great experience and to interact with the chefs. Sometimes you might get a little surprise tasting. food, menu, service, ambiance are all top notch. Cant wait to be back here again.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: The BEST Italian food in LA. No one makes Caesar Salad better than chi Spacca. It's right there with Tricolore Salad at Pizzaria Mozza.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Simply outstanding!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: WHAT A GREAT EXPERIENCE. SET UP A RESERVATION WITH AN EARLY 6PM TIME. AND EVERY DISH WAS ABSOLUTELY DELICIOUS. ORIGINALLY CAME FOR THE TOMAHAWK AND ENDED UP BEING BLOWN AWAY BY EVERY PLATE THAT WAS BROUGHT OUT. THE SALAD WAS FRESH AND ZESTY AND A GREAT SPIN ON A CEASAR. THE SWEET POTATOES WERE SURPRISINGLY SWEET IN THE WAY YOU WOULD HOPE THEM TO BE. THE TOMAHAWK WAS DELICIOUS AND HUGE, COOKED AS THE CHEF PREFERRED AND THAT DID NOT DISAPPOINT. THE STARTING OF THE SAVORY BREAD AND BURRATA WAS A CLEAR SIGN OF THE GOODNESS TO COME. I WILL HAVE DREAMS OF THAT BURRATA.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: well service is always excellent!!, food outstanding!price very good!we love it!thanks!angel

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Our favorite restaurant. The food is phenomenal. Its expensive but worth every penny. Run dont walk to chi Scappa

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: The best pork chop I have ever had. Sit at the bar!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Best meal ever!!!!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Top 5 restaurants in Los Angeles. Maybe even better than Sonoratown. (Crack at LA Times food critics)

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Excellent birthday dinner!

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: One of the best restaurants in L.A.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: The chicken is Magical

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: One of the few restaurants that we can say is authentically enjoyable to eat as the food is prepared so well and so fresh with taste unbelievable and so enjoyable.  People are laid back and natural, we do not get the feel of coming to a place with attitude.  We will rank it as in our top 3 to go in LA.  And we have been around many of the top places in Europe.  Totally recommendable.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Chi Spacca was one of the best restaurants that Ive ever been to. From service to food this restaurant was outstanding.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: I really wanted to like this place. While the food was about what was expected, the entire experience was a huge let down. First, we were seated 45 minutes after our reservation, and then it took another 30 just to get service. The restaurant has about 5 tables total, so the fact we RARELY saw our waiter the entire TWO HOURS it took to eat was also extremely unfortunate. The courses came out 30 minutes apart, which was very strange to have a bowl of mashed potatoes sit there for half an hour until the first meat came out. Our waters were never filled, and I think I only got one beer the entire meal because our waiter literally never came back after we ordered our food. Except one time to apologize for how long everything was taking. I will say they gave us complimentary sorbet at the end, probably because it was now 11PM and we were just eating. While the food is tasty, I really don't believe the restaurant is as fine as it seems to have convinced itself it is. For how much it costs, I would definitely go for a more exemplary dining experience elsewhere ie: Bavel.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Too much lemon in all the salad (Caesars salad), stuffed squash flowers, and broccoli.  Roast chicken was not well cooked - the meat near the bone was pinkish/a little raw.We were overcharged for the water... US$3.00 per person but they charged for 7 guest to my table of 6.They brought a happy-birthday dessert for the celebrant at the table, but charged us for it.The waitress/sommelier was obviously pushing us to order too much for the table. For the table of 6, we had a roast chicken, a lamb shoulder, and the US$220 steak, aside from various vegetable dishes.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Our dinner at Coppa was magnificent!  Their outdoor seating is nice and we felt like we were in Europe, which is always fun.  The staff was on top of everything - food, covid, drinks, etc.  They have a good system in place for accessing the restroom.  The food was outstanding.  We shared the celery caeser salad and tuna sashimi as starters, and we had two pastas - one with a chicken sausage sauce and one with lobster.  Both were great and kept their heat and we ate every last bite.   We each had a cocktail and a glass of wine.  I highly recommend this cute and yummy spot and we hope that there will be heaters so we can dine outside when the weather gets cool again.

Name: Coppa
Comments: The pizza and pasta were great, wine was excellent.  Arugula corn salad was outstanding:)

Name: Coppa
Comments: Outdoor seating was a bit uncomfortable, seems Coppa bought same blue metal chairs as many local restaurants as they scrambled to respond to Covid. Only downside of the meal. We were seated promptly at our reservation time, service was friendly efficient and knowledgeable. Started withzucca appetizer, great suggestion from our waitress, light starter for hot summer evening. We had the bucatini with lobster and red sauce; excellent, fresh tomatoes in sauce, spicy but didnt totally overwhelm lobster. Also cavatelli with chicken sausage; not as spicy as bucatini but billed as more so. Overall an excellent meal and would definitely return

Name: Coppa
Comments: Lovely food, excellent wine selections with amazing service.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Food is always spectacular. Patio during Covid felt very safe. This will forever be our favorite South End restaurant.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Had a great time dining outside here.  Great location!

Name: Coppa
Comments: Good experience

Name: Coppa
Comments: Everything was so delicious and service was friendly and attentive.

Name: Coppa
Comments: We ate here during Covid and had an awesome experience celebrating my wife's birthday. Outdoor seating was quite nice, albeit we sat on the Shawmut St side, so not as private (we felt stared at by cars stopping on the stop sign).Food was fantastic as usual. I just wish they had more options for wine by the glass.Regardless of where you go during COVID, go with patience and an open mind. Everyone is trying their best. With that, you will have an awesome experience and not get bothered by the little things (which I won't note here for this same specific reason).There were no COVID related hygiene issues as all customer facing staff had masks and gloves on. Also very strict rules around using the bathroom. Be ready to put on gloves and wait.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Loved being about to 'dine out' again at Coppa. It's one of my favorite restaurants and didn't disappoint! This was my first experience eating outside and the whole Coppa team managed it beautifully.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Food was delicious.  Serving sizes were perfect: left totally satiated without feeling overly full. Staff was very polite. Only negative was that our waitress kind of ignored us after our initial order, e.g. didn't refill our water; had to flag her down to get another drink. We would have loved one final drink, but she just dropped off the check and left us to be. Slightly expensive - for pasta - but that's expected. Overall a nice Sat night, al fresco dining experience.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Perfect spot on a hot summer day in the South End.  The Frose was perfection!

Name: Coppa
Comments: Great food. Great service. Great job with improv setup outdoors.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Great food as always.  Outside dining area top notch

Name: Coppa
Comments: Great food, perfect atmosphere, attentive and knowledgeable staff

Name: Coppa
Comments: Service and food are incredible - love this restaurant!

Name: Coppa
Comments: First restaurant meal in 4 months. Outside tables well-spaced. Very professionally and safely run. Excellent food and polite service, as always. Monday meatball sub is outstanding.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Excellent food, excellent service

Name: Coppa
Comments: Food was very tasty but service was bad overall, but the cherry on top of the cake was that my partner's main dish arrived 10 minutes before mine (!!!), so he ended up eating his food before me.

Name: Coppa
Comments: The staff and service was excellent...attentive, professional, super friendly, and socially distant aware.  We really enjoy the new deck and the unique ambiance it creates.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Thank you for an amazing first experience dining out after four months. The food is still tremendous and the staff and service was still top notch even under these challenging conditions and times. Big thanks to Ryan and everyone on the team for continuing to crush it everyday.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Outdoor seating was great, plenty of space between tables, nestled on a quiet side street. Food is amazing, service is fantastic.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Everything was fantastic. Great service. The food was phenomenal

Name: Coppa
Comments: Amazing dinner outside with the absolute best server in Boston. Dining made easy, especially under the current COVID-19 restrictions and circumstances. Cannot wait to go for the delicious pastas and pizzas!

Name: Coppa
Comments: Rigatoni was on point. Nice relaxed spot to eat on a Sunday.

Name: Coppa
Comments: It was wonderful to return to Coppa whose extended patio made it a pleasant summer evening dinner. As always, sterling service and delicious food.

Name: Coppa
Comments: The food was deliciously flavorful and the service was excellent!!Also, the tables are well spaced.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Fantastic!! One of the best restaurants in Boston.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Awesome outdoor setup

Name: Coppa
Comments: Outdoor setting is well done and the food is always just right.

Name: Coppa
Comments: The corn/maise pizza, octopus pizza and celery ceaser were scrumptious! Wine pairing was perfect.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Everything was great. Went there for pizza. . Good food good service and noSurprises. Enjoyed will return.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Amazing as always!!

Name: Coppa
Comments: Never fails. Always delicious!  Theyve done a nice job with outdoor patio and social distancing.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Food was great and the outdoor patio area gave a great atmosphere

Name: Coppa
Comments: During these trying times for all of us, eating al fresco at Coppa was truly a breath of fresh air.  The service (Jen) was very friendly and at just the right tempo.  Pizza and pasta were delicious.  A beautiful way to spend Monday night.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Wonderful meal and great service! I was very impressed with what they have in place in response to COVID.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Thanks for being so covid-conscious and safe!!

Name: Coppa
Comments: great food!

Name: Coppa
Comments: First dining after 3 months of restrictions. The outdoor seating was awesome in a semi_quite South End neighborhood. Limited selections on the menu. Nothing extravagant. We ordered a pasta dish with clams which was decent. Drink menu very limited (maybe due to the situation). Tiramisu was not good at all and it was a waste of money but otherwise was a good experience. Loved sitting outdoors and the staff were really nice and super friendly particularly with my little doggie so for that reason along I would go back!

Name: CRUST
Comments: We had a great time at CRUST for my sister's birthday. Chris our server was really nice and did a great job! The other stuff and the owner who was there made us feel really welcomed. The food was AMAZING and the plates were huge. Great combo of quality and quantity. We will be back! Thank you for such a great experience!

Name: CRUST
Comments: It was amazing as always. Great food and the staff is super friendly and attentive. We went for Fathers Day dinner and couldnt be more pleased. We are long time customers and Crust is our favorite.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Fathers Day

Name: CRUST
Comments: Couldnt wait to try this place out,, the owners are awesome and the Pizza was amazing,, we traveled all the way from PA and will definitely tell everyone about this place when we get home.. Fantastic!!!

Name: CRUST
Comments: Absolutely loved it! We celebrated our sons 20ish birthday and it was spectacular. We had a party of 6 and each one ordered something different, all equally delicious I must say. Our server was very attentive and recommended some dishes and wine. Anita the owner checked in on us to make sure we were ok, as she did with everyone else in the restaurant. We had a fabulous time in an amazing restaurant that did not disappoint. We will definitely be back.

Name: CRUST
Comments: One of my favorite Italian restaurants. Always excited to visit as I know the experience will be awesome.  The environment is very relaxed, plus they always go above and beyond to accommodate; never any complaints on the food.  Definitely a must on anyone's list of restaurants.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Wonderful Excellent service. Food was incredible

Name: CRUST
Comments: I always receive an online request to give my feedback about my experience at Crust. Its honestly never a chore because I love telling everyone how awesome it is. From the moment you walk in Anita or someone welcomes you and makes you feel like youre at a family dinner. That kind of hospitality doesnt end with the welcome but continues on with the service until youre saying goodbye, until we see you again. On top of the amazing hospitality, the food, it is absolutely delicious. Never had a bad dish here. Explore the menu and enjoy something you dont normally have or stick with a favorite classic. No worries everything is great!  Hands down one of the best restaurants in Miami.

Name: CRUST
Comments: We ordered several things , the problem was the salad it had old walnuts, when we called the manager, she from the first moment affirmed that it wasnt like that, that the chef was her husband and that he had to try it to confirm our complain. Then she returned with sarcastic attitude denying our claim. She brought a punch of complete different walnuts and asked to us with the same attitude what we wanted another salad or discount the older one from the account. Very disappointed an arrogant attitude to be honest.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Great Italian food.  Good service.  Will return.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Always a pleasure to dine at Crust. Anita welcomes us like family. Highly recommend!

Name: CRUST
Comments: Food was great service was meh

Name: CRUST
Comments: Flew to East coast just to eat at CRUST before driving to our destination on west coast. Its that good!!

Name: CRUST
Comments: It was as it always is  GREAT. I love the food, owners and there servers, as they always make you feel at home, my only complaint is that they are not closer to me but whenever I am somewhere near I always book my table at Crust.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Very personable staff. Work very well together. Was extremely impressed by the teamwork and happiness shown by the employees.

Name: CRUST
Comments: We love Crust.   Went for my birthday with another couple.  totally enjoyed by all.  Portions are generous and food is delicious.

Name: CRUST
Comments: The staff was amazing the hostess was over the top and so friendly and nice. We had a cranky 2 year old and the staff was super nice bringing coloring books and interacting with him to calm him!  Best Italian and so much food!!

Name: CRUST
Comments: It was fantastic.  From the hostess to the servers.  The food is amazing!!!!  This is our place when we want to have great Italian food!

Name: CRUST
Comments: Always an extraordinary experience!

Name: CRUST
Comments: Great food just to much

Name: CRUST
Comments: Great restaurant, best pizza in miami, the risotto was even better!!

Name: CRUST
Comments: I cant get enough of the place. The food is consistent. The staff is impeccable. The food is D-E-L-I-C-O-U-S!!!

Name: CRUST
Comments: Excellent!! Must make a reservation .

Name: CRUST
Comments: The food is amazing! The service is really good. If you want a quiet place for a date, this is not the place to go. It is very lively and has a very energetic ambiance.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Great food, great service

Name: CRUST
Comments: Great food and incredible owner!

Name: CRUST
Comments: We went for my moms 85 th Birthday before going to Hamilton at the Ziff.  So were greeted by the owner with birthday kisses for mom. The portions are huge and wonderful. Sharing is a great idea!!! Definitely on my favorite list. We will be back soon ( after I finish my left overs which have lasted all weekend ).

Name: CRUST
Comments: Great food but portion size was to large my pizza would have been much better with half of the ingredients on top and seen  some of yhe pasta dishes getting delivered and the were huge. Very off putting

Name: CRUST
Comments: Nice. Good service and great food!

Name: CRUST
Comments: Truly an incredible place every time I go! Food, service, decor, ambiance to name a few is always on point! Thank you for making it such a DIVINE place to dine!XOXO...Belkys Sanchez

Name: CRUST
Comments: Amazing as always!  Hope to keep celebrating anniversaries there for many more years!

Name: CRUST
Comments: So enjoyable. Worth the long drive from boca raton!

Name: CRUST
Comments: One of our favs

Name: CRUST
Comments: As always, food was delicious.  Service was a bit spotty, and it was a bit noisier than usual (even though we went very early!).

Name: CRUST
Comments: The owners warmth sets the tone for the whole experience. Everything about this place is an embrace  from the plentiful menu choices to the robust portions to the special touches that make you feel like a treasured customer even when youre not a regular (yet! we will be after this).Really an exceptional, special place. These people are doing what they were called to do, and its all about love.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Wonderful! Portions are large though! The eggplant parm serving feeds 4! Service is great, food is fantastic!

Name: CRUST
Comments: More Italian food for your money than I have ever seen any restaurant ever serve.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Great food atmosphere was fantastic definitely recommend sitting outside on a nice day.

Name: CRUST
Comments: Love this restaurant!  The meal and service were spectacular as always!  We will be back soon!  Thank you!

Name: CRUST
Comments: If you're into great spaghetti sauce, this is definitely the place. The portions are ridiculously gigantic. More than enough to feed 2 people if not 3. I was disappointed that I could not swap out the pasta I wanted with my main choice. But they did tell us in the beginning that they wouldn't do what I wanted them to do. The prices were reasonable, but I want a place to give me what I want to eat.  I had to change orders to get what I wanted in the sauce.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Was overall a great experience but it was my boyfriends birthday and I even called before and nobody remembered:( it was an overall great experience despite the fact. Great servers.

Name: Daniel
Comments: My wife and I saw the article re the reopening and booked a table to change the routine of being at home.   It was a stormy night by the staff worked tirelessly to adjust so people could enjoy. Our meal was fantastic.  Loved the cold melon soup (wifes) and my pate.   Mains were fantastic as well.  Really great evening!

Name: Daniel
Comments: This was our second visit to Restaurant Daniel in 2 years. The food was still "ok" there was nothing amazing that blew me away like other Michelin restaurants we've been to. There is no taste to the meats except for the sauces which they are doused in. The staff was good.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Eating outside at Daniel was a unique experience. But it was a pleasant one. People worked hard to make it as restaurant-like as possible, and, frankly, being deprived of a decent restaurant experience for so many months, it was wonderful. Go enjoy!

Name: Daniel
Comments: Fabulous service. No rush. Wonderful assistance in explanation of every course. As always our did our explanation

Name: Daniel
Comments: First class throughout.

Name: Daniel
Comments: My daughter and I visited Daniel while on a spring break trip to New York. We ordered the tasting menu, which was a nice way to sample various items. The service was impeccable and the atmosphere was lovely - quiet but not stuffy.

Name: Daniel
Comments: The experience lived up to the legend and hype. The beautiful location, wonderful staff, and incredible food made an impression on all our team during a constructive trip to New York.

Name: Daniel
Comments: I love Daniel but haven't been to this restaurant in years.  Some of the food was "overdone."  Abalone had a sauce on it and I didn't even recognize the abalone.  Fois gras was fabulous.  Duck was grand as well Il flotante overdone, dry.  Wine pairings amazing.

Name: Daniel
Comments: I haved a wonderful and exciting time

Name: Daniel
Comments: Chef Daniel comes out to each table and makes it an incredible personal experience! Beautiful dining room, delicate and delicious food, impeccable attentive service.

Name: Daniel
Comments: I haven't provided a review in ages.  This was an extraordinary dining experience.  Truly extraordinary.  Every dish was perfectly executed aesthetically and mind blowing delicious.  The service was flawless.  We had a girl's night in the city and my friend is vegan, and they accommodated her restrictions without hesitation...and I enjoyed a non-vegan tasting menu that was beautifully executed.  The wine pairings were also done to perfection.  We had a lovely and most memorable evening -- this dining experience goes down in our history books.   Five stars, a standout in a massive city with so many restaurants, it's hard to choose.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Absolutely AMAZING experience! If you havent dined at Daniel go now! Wonderful melt in your mouth experience from beginning to end.

Name: Daniel
Comments: The ambiance was pleasant. The service impeccable. The food innovative.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Exquisite is the best way to describe  the food, service, and ambiance.  From the moment you enter you are made to feel as though you are their only guest. We tried the 7 course tasting menu with the wine pairing and it's obvious that Daniel has everything perfected. The tastes my tongue experienced were out of this world. I can say every dish exceeded my expectations.  The bison and mushroom aperitifs were my personal favorite and I'm usually not a fan of mushrooms.  They even provided personal touches that made it a night we'll never forget.  The staff were so attentive and not in any way rushing you.  I cannot wait to return and of course I highly recommend Daniel to all.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Celebrating an anniversary

Name: Daniel
Comments: Wonderful service and amazing food at Daniel. Made a special night even more special.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Perfection

Name: Daniel
Comments: Do you really need a review for what is arguably the best restaurant in NYC?  It is not inexpensive, but really, if you're reading this, you knew that already.  Service, impeccable.  Food, outstanding.  No better place for a special occasion.   Bonus, Chef Boulud was in the dining room.  I don't know, maybe he's there all the time, but it was cool to see.

Name: Daniel
Comments: This was our third year going to Daniel for our birthday dinner. My daughters share the same birthday, three years apart and I follow a couple of weeks after so we have made it a tradition to go to New York to celebrate. Our first time at Daniel was so amazing we decided it would be our yearly tradition and it has never disappointed. Not only is each plate beautiful and delicious the service and ambiance simply cannot be matched!

Name: Daniel
Comments: Food and service excellent as always. They even made a special dessert when I found I couldnt eat what was offered.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Amazing as always!!!  Thank to Elvir for the kitchen tour and chef Will!  Amazing food and service!

Name: Daniel
Comments: My wife and I loved the experience it was superb in every level.I want to give props to the manager Kareem who made sure everything was perfect thru our evening and took us to the kitchen for a photo up.We will definitely be back.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Daniel is amazing! Unforgettable dinner.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Best restaurant in Manhattan,  just amazing food. The service and ambiance are reminiscent of the best Parisian places.

Name: Daniel
Comments: The service was remarkable and outstanding.  The hosts, the sommelier, and the servers went over and beyond to ensure our comfort. We had the four course tasting.  The dessert course was amazing and kept getting better with each offering.  However, the other three courses were very disappointing.  the presentation was good but the taste was not what we expected from a restaurant of this caliber.  It was not pleasing to our palate. Considering the price we pay at this restaurant, we were expecting a lot more in terms of taste.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Incredible tastes and service. They handled dietary restrictions with ease. Very special place

Name: Daniel
Comments: Without a doubt one of the most outstanding meals of our lives. The finest combination of cuisine, service, and ambiance in the United States, if not the world. We were awed by the tasting dinner. Every staff member was superb. Special appreciation to our sommelier who recommended a wonderful wine that was also a good value. Well always remember this great evening at Restaurant Daniel.

Name: Daniel
Comments: First visit to this legendary restaurant and it totally lived up to its reputation.Will return.

Name: Daniel
Comments: a fabulous dining experience. Outstanding Menu , great Presentation and first rate service.A true memorable culinary experience!!!

Name: Daniel
Comments: The experience at Daniel was absolutely AMAZING. Everyone was very kind and thoughtful for our special day. The Chef even sent us a customized "Congratulations" desert made with white chocolate and exotic fruits - we very much appreciated this attention. As well as the fresh and warm Madeleines, a delicious french Canelet and mini home-made chocolates using the finest chocolates from all over world. And Thank you again for the very pretty customized menus printed in grand elegance for us. Daniel restaurant  is a true highlight for people who want to experience something which is truly special and unique. We will come back soon. Merci infiniment.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Thank goodness there is still an exceptional dining experience around. Id almost given up on dining out. Every place was the same uninspiring Upscale gastro pub trying to put a new spin on old recipes. So many places didnt live up to the hype. Daniel is the definition of fine elegant dining. Every bite was creative and perfectly balanced- a foodies dream. Checks all the boxes of what I look for when seeking a new exciting experience. 1. He created things I would never imagine- familiar flavors blended into something new and sensational.2. I could never create this in my house.3. Creates a whole world and experience.
