For three hours I was removed from time and space and enjoyed one Devine culinary sensory sensation after another of taste smells and textures.Hit every note perfectly like a symphony- the room decor, the lighting, the service, the timing, the wine,  and of course the food.If you are a true foodie ( in search of the next great bit- no matter where - fine dining to food cart) then you must experience Daniel and if you miss and are in search of a whole true fine dining experience put Daniel somewhere top of your list.

Name: Daniel
Comments: 30th wedding anniversary meal went 5 years previous and did not disappoint nothings cheap in New York really so well worth a visit for a special occasion with a quality taste experience and very attentive staff

Name: Daniel
Comments: Very classic and nice setting. Was lucky to see the chef and have a picture with him.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Valentines Day; the special menu was astronomically priced even in relation to other fine-dining NYC tasting menus

Name: Daniel
Comments: Absolutely amazing. Better than Le Bernardin.

Name: Daniel
Comments: One of five must go spots in Manhattan for special occasions. Very pricey but you get what you pay for. Our Valentines Saturday lunch was superb with unmatched seating due to the earlier time. From the reception to departure the highly trained staff makes you welcome with knowledge and lack of pretense. All the four courses were elegant to behold and a symphony of flavors. The dessert course is a profusion of riches crafted under the supervision is the Pastry chef Ghaya Olivera and is equal to the best in the world. Drinks are special with a stellar and expensive list of curated wines. Very highly recommended for anyones bucket list. Bravo!

Name: Daniel
Comments: Dinner at Valentines Day.The food was great as always. Price was double due to Valentines Day. Table was close to the entrance door. Rush service. Unfortunately, I felt it was a sloppy night.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Great time with another couple for V day ,

Name: Daniel
Comments: Elvir is awesome!!!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Great meal and experience before everything had to shut down

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Everything was excellent the food, the service, the space. We dined here because our first and second choices were closed due to COVID-19. This was not our first or second choice because there are many other restaurants with just as excellent food and service but much better value.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: The brodo was too salty.  The Sommelier was fantastic and did an outstanding job of pairing our food selections.  The pork was impeccably done -  beautiful taste.   Overall, a great restaurant, but the price is over the top so it is always going to be a treat.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: We were adventurous & selected the chefs table 8 courses with wine. Totally fabulous! We had such a wonderful evening with friends that was fill with conversation & good food. The pasta was so light light & delicious Im envious of the still of those tiny cheese or potato filled delights. My husband loved the flavorful soup course. Best part I stayed on my diet & still lost weight! Gave me new meaning to portion control! Its so relaxing to be be not rushed to next course to turn over the table. Cant wait to go back!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Outstanding meal and service is perfect.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Visited from California for our 10 year wedding anniversary. They sat us late for our reservation. Took a long time to get served wine. Somales was unfriendly, uptight, and not helpful. She accidentally poured my husband a glass of red that he did not order spilling it in the process then when she realized she accidentally poured it she made a big scene of taking it off the table. When I asked her what she did with the glass of wine she said its a wash its just sitting in the back. For the price of the meal you would think she would just leave the glass for my husband to enjoy.  The restaurant is beautiful looks like a movie set but the meal and service was not worth the price of a fine dining experience.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Visited with my college daughter and teen son on a visit to NYC. It was the highlight meal of our trip, as in the past.Love everything about this amazing restaurant!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Overpriced but worth it! Great food and service as well as ambiance!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Mind blowing food experience

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Inventive but excellent food, soothing surroundings, and top-notch service!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Hubby and I went here after dry January to have an amazing dinner and delicious drinks. I mean is Marios restaurant so its gonna be sick!!! Our server (forget his name) was awesome. Loved his Italian accent and when he explained the wine pairing with each course. We did the 8 course menu which every bite was better than the first. The wine was sooooooooo good. Cant wait to go back. Youre gonna pay when doing the wine pairing but its soooo worth it. You only live once.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Amazing dinner. Top three restaurants in the US!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Just perfect

Name: Del Posto
Comments: I took my husband to DelPosto for his 56th birthday after seeing it being mentioned in a Daily News article as one of the best Italian restaurants and confirmation of same by a good friend.  The ambience, food, staff and service were all impeccable from the time we walked in the door until the time we left.  Such a romantic restaurant. Great for date night, birthdays and Valentines Day! We had the 5 course tasting menu.  Every dish was excellent even though our favorites were the linguine with geoduck, the shellfish stew, the branzino and the antipasti with sweet potatoes and pears!!!!  All delicious! The warm bread stick with the clotted cream and olive oil was addicting!  The whole team made our experience memorable especially Damiano and Jaziel! They didnt miss a beat!! They even gave me a small foot stool to rest my handbag on so it wouldnt be on the floor!!! Who does that???  We will definitely go back again!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Del Posto is one of the most elegant restaurants Ive ever been to. We did the Captains Menu where you tell the waiter your preferences and he selects the 8 courses. Every course was delicious. It was definitely pricey but well worth it for a special occasion.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: This is my all time favorite restaurant in the world.  I make sure when I travel to NYC that this place is on my dinner list.  That is a lot to say coming from an Irish guy from Chicago

Name: Del Posto
Comments: This is one of the best restaurants around.  Quality of food and service is top notch.  Youre going to pay for it, but you wont forget it.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Excellent, elegant, extravagant, and extraordinary are just a few descriptive words to express how wonderful Del Posto is!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Absolutely one of the most disappointing dinning experiences EVER. The ambience was dark, cold, sterile. Wait staff, though reasonably attentive was stiff and not friendly. Prices were exorbitant for vert average food e.g. $39 for a tossed salad, tuna entree ( 3 tiny medallions for as I recall $70)Would NEVER recommend to friends.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Everything - food, service, decor, ambiance - was perfect.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: This just wasnt good. Wasnt worth the price. So much disappointment all around. It definitely lost its flare!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Great Restaurant in every aspect. I feel it was better in prior years.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Amazing food and service to match. Deep wine selection coupled with knowledgeable sommelier. Fabulous experience. Wowed the pants off our guests.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: The restaurant was beautiful but I expected much better with regard to the food, especially given the cost.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Great space, great service, and exceptional food.  Perfect spot for a romantic date night.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Del Posto is wonderful for lunch.  The prix fix is a great value for this fine dining restaurant.  The food and service were top notch.  It's lovely for a special occasion.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Absolutely the most overrated Italian restaurant I have ever been too.  Beautiful with great service, but the food was subpar and outrageously expensive. $500 for two adults and a child.  We ordered two salads, two main dishes and one childs pasta with three adult drinks. The main dishes and salad were bland. The childs past was good though and my daughter loved the butter. Lol.  The largest portion on the menu was the butter.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Outstanding service. A very enjoyable last evening in New York.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: New Years Day

Name: Del Posto
Comments: I had a high expectation. When I got there nice specious entrance and dining area. Service was good and attentive. Wine and salad was ok. But 2 pasta was unacceptably salty. I mentioned it. Then main dish Branzino was again salty. Tuna for my wife was as well. I dont mind to pay 600.00 but not for this. Very disappointed.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Family of 4 wearing jeans and sneakers seated in main dining room for New Years Eve Lunch. I recall once in the summer i was wearing a suit with dress sandals and not allowed to eat...No longer serving cocktails at the bar, only food service (the bar was empty) no one came to take drink order in the  lounge seating, decided to just go to tableLive piano music no longer at lunchSeveral dishes not up to previous standard, lasagna tasted like burnt tomato pasteLunch Prices raised.Bathroom towels and hand soap no longer superior.Table service excellent as alwaysAmbiance- stellar as always

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Best deal in NYC for a pre-fixe lunch....wonderful setting, superb service compliments what is a fantastic tasting lunch menu.  It's not inexpensive but it will be a memorable meal with one of the most extensive wine lists in the city.  Enjoy a classic Italian meal in a sophisticated and inviting setting.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Most of the dishes were too salty.  I ordered waguy beef which was so tough.  The steak knife was so dull.  with the tough beef and the dull knife, it was not an enjoyable meal.  I have dined at Del Posto a few times in the past and I would not return again.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Excellent service dining experience combined with an amazing meal and wine pairing experience We did 5 course tasting menu

Name: Del Posto
Comments: It was wonderful and one of the best meals ever!!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: The host should of been more welcoming. I had to interrupt them so we can be acknowledged. Everything after that was amazing. I will give them a second chance.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Mike was a great host and server etc.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: My boyfriend and I had a fantastic experience dining at Del posto.I would definitely recommend this restaurant to my friends and family

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Incredible evening for a special occasion. Unique dishes, endless wine list and great atmosphere.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Food was superb! Service was excellent! It was a bitter cold grey day that was warmed and brightened by the caring attention we received. We look forward to our next visit.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Perfect in every way!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Wow! My guest(s) and I couldnt get enough of the Chefs tasting menu until we were full. Definitely a special occasion/date night experience to be remembered.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Exquisite sushi, robatayaki and other Japanese dishes, well plated with friendly but not obtrusive service. Would be very happy to return once it is safe to eat out again!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Double Knot is situation in an intimate location downstairs from Sampan and the bar area.  Ambience is hip and a bit darker, so perfect for a date.  Noise wasn't too loud, so I could easily hear my date across from me.We did the tasting menu, which is excellent value at $60 given the amount of food we got (we had a lot of leftovers for more meals afterwards!).  The quality of the food was great as well and I'd definitely recommend this to others!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: I went to Double Knot with some colleagues and we not only found the food superb, but the service and ambiance were delightful as well. Great for girls night out, larger groups or sexy time with that special someone. Great vibe overall.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Unfortunately, I found the food bland.  And while the ambiance and drinks were good, it wasn't worth the money.  I will not go back.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: This is our second time visiting and we love the atmosphere and the food.  Everything was great.  The service was outstanding and the food was delicious.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: It wasnt clear that the bar reservation wasnt eligible for happy hour specials

Name: Double Knot
Comments: This place is top 5 in Philly easy.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Our second visit. really love everything about it. all the small plates so interesting. Evening menu has nine sections!  Incredible variety and assortment can be a bit overwhelming! First visit we did the tasting menu but this time we felt confident enough to order a la carte. Unfair to call it a sushi restaurant since it is much more than that. You may wish to peruse the menu online before you go. In the cold section we loved hamachi and avocado salad. I was not a fan of the king oyster mushroom but partner liked it. It's too rubbery for my taste.On the  "crispy" menu, the wings were wonderful. next time I'd like to try the Japanese fried chicken. We had the beef dumpling in broth that was delicious. My menu said beef soup dumplings which they are not. Partner's menu just said the correct "beef dumpling." Crab udon delish but not much crab. My favorite offerings at the restaurant are the Robotayaki especially the ribeye and Kobe beef. You may want to order double and triple of those. The lobster claw was also great. No room for dessert. Schulson does a great job with decor and fun experiences which enhance the whole experience and also manages to hire staff that are really friendly, professional and knowledgeable. They seem to be having fun even tho they are working.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Dinning at Double Knot was definitely an experience. We had a reservation and ate at the counter downstairs. We had the chefs tasting menu and they accommodated my shellfish allergy and it being lent. My one complaint is that we felt rushed and like we needed to eat as fast as possible. At one point we had four plates arrive at the same time.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: The upstairs bar area where you wait smelled horrible.  A mixture of bleach and feet.  Nearly left while waiting.  Its not a good way to start and end the evening Food and service downstairs was excellent.  Sad that the experience was tainted

Name: Double Knot
Comments: This was our 3rd time coming to double knot and we enjoyed it just as the last one. I had the lovers knot cocktail which was amazing. Me and boyfriend ordered the Japanese fried chicken as something new to try. Flavour explosion in our mouths. It was the best thing ever.  Our waitress was Caydie and she was a sweetheart. Very informative on the items on the table and attentive to us.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Service was excellent! Food was excellent except Brussels sprouts had too much balsamic vinegar.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: While the food was good, as always, this time we had a new server/bartender who didn't understand that soy is in all soy sauce. In fact, she argued with me about it until one of her colleagues that explained to her, very patiently, that soy, by the very nature of the thing, is made of fermented soybeans, and is not related to its gluten content. With my soy allergy, this is rather an important point. Still, she meant well, and other than this, we had a good time there.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Omakase chef's tasting was delicious.  Server and female manager were rushing our table, clearing plates before we were done; the manager even took away my empty water glass after dessert without bringing it back (or refilling it). It was so obvious that they wanted to flip the table.  Unprofessional and not appreciated; our party of 3 spent $400 on dinner.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: best sushi place in town considering location ambiance and food!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Happy hour was good cooked food apps are good  sushi was very meh.  Waitress was great.Would go back and only get cooked food.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: I forget our waiters name but he made the night with his wine and food recommendations.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Excellent, as always! Its on our rotation for business and pleasure!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Omakase is a great way to go here - trust the chef.  Service was very helpful is selecting different beverages to pair with all the different courses

Name: Double Knot
Comments: On the pricey side but some of the best sushi Ive had in quite some time.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: We love to come here. Its a great date spot. The staff is very knowledgeable and attentive and they make great recommendations. We always order a bunch of dishes, and have the server recommend at least one of them so we try new dishes on each visit. Yum!!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Six of us went to Double Knot at the recommendation of a friend while we were in town for the Flower Show.  It was a fabulous and fun dining experience!  Our waiter, Manny, walked us through the menu since it was our first visit.Everything we ordered was delicious from the Edamame Dumplings to the skewered  Octopus.  The tapas menu allowed us to try many different menu items and everything was great!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Awesome dinner! We did the Chefs Tasting menu and each course was better than the last. Cocktails were great, food was amazing, service was top notch.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Went here for my boyfriends birthday. We did the chefs blind tasting menu along with a few extra courses of sushi and a couple round of cocktails. Everything from the drinks to the multiple courses were amazing. Our server was very informative and every clean plate was almost instantly cleared from our table. I must recommend: octopus sushi, duck scrapple, any robitiaki item, and their mochi ice cream. Overall, it was a great experience for a special occasion

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Our server was great at providing recommendations based on our preferences!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Definitely my new favorite date night spot! We decided to order A La Carte instead of the chefs tasting menu and everything was amazing. Everything was prepared fresh and deliciously. Will definitely be returning!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Always enjoy our time at Double Knot! Service is top-notch, the downstairs area is great for a date night, and the food is spectacular. We did the tasting menu and chose our selections. Everything was delicious and it let us try things we wouldnt normally order. Food came promptly as it was ready, and, as fast eaters, we appreciated the pace. I believe the portions were smaller with the tasting menu but we did not leave hungry. We sat at the bar and the bartender was super helpful and patient as we made our decisions. One male bartender was a bit loud and I heard him complaining a bit, but other than that, we very much enjoyed the whole experience. Definitely a place for a special occasion or to take visitors!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Great food but was way too dark inside

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Exceptional! We had the special menu and were extremely pleased! The cool vibe and original design, the impeccable service, and the whole experience make this our regular go-to in Philadelphia. The hard part is getting the reservation.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: It was good! Pricy but good!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Excellent staff excellent food

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Everything was amazing. The attention to detail was great as well. Was worried about our seats at the counter downstairs but it was cool seeing the cooks do their thing behind the counter. The sushi quality was some of the best Ive had in a long time. Definitely looking forward to coming back again.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Carissa was amazing at the sushi counter. Was disappointed to have made a reservation to get there and wait for 10 minutes to not have a table ready. The food is superb so that was the least of our worries.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Excellent food, good service

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Happy hour upstairs was fantastic!  Delicious choices from the HH menu, but also had to have an order of the tuna rice crackers from the regular menu.  Brussels sprouts are so good, we ended up ordering two!  YUMMY!  (Only thing we were not crazy about was the roasted broccoli, which seemed steamed. ) Great dinner before a show at the Academy!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Always a great overall experience

Name: Double Knot
Comments: The service is top notch along with the stunning atmosphere. They really make you feel like youre in an old speak easy. We did the chefs tasting which was fabulous. Definitely cant wait to go back.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: I just cannot say enough about Double Knot - reserve a table and do the Chef's blind tasting - you will NOT be disappointed.   Service was superb! Ambiance great!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Excellent job on outdoor dining during the age of Rona.  Very thankful to have FWD here in Manhattan Beach providing excellent raw seafood, and innovative seafood dishes!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Great ambience. & food for a social distance dinner!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: We were a party of 3 celebrating on of our birthdays. The staff was wonderful, taking every precaution during this pandemic. Our waitress never re-touched anything that was opened, there was a separate bus staff. The food was amazing. We had oysters, grilled octopus, the Halibut ceviche and all split the lobster roll. All so good. The staff even brought out a complimentary dessert-Key Lime Pie that was equally amazing. Thanks FWD for a wonderful evening!!!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: 30th birthday! FWD always does a great job with each aspect of our experience. The food, the presentation, the feels, the drinks, service and recommendations. 5* all the way.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love love love this place. The food is delicious and the service is wonderful.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Great atmosphere on the new patio. Food is definitely over priced  but the quality is good and its great to support our local businesses.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Always excellent.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love the outdoor dining. The food was phenomenal as always.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Fresh seafood, amazing cocktails and key lime pie to die for - what else could you want?!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: I took my son for a special dinner to celebrate and we had a spectacular time. Our reservation was for 645pm and when we checked in with the hostess she let us know that our table would be ready soon but that they were waiting for the prior reservations to clear out. After waiting about 15 minutes the hostess brought over  a delicious Peruvian scallops appetizer as a treat for us having to wait for our table to be available. We felt this was a very nice touch and the kick off to a fantastic evening filled with scrumptious food and great service. Due to the Covid all of the seating was outside now which was actually amazingly comfortable especially when it cooled off a little in the evening and the heater lamps were brought out. We felt the service and the food were fantastic and we will definitely be back soon.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love this restaurant but they are struggling with service and wait time right now. I understand that times are tough at the moment but we were seated almost an hour after our reservation time and our food took FOREVER to come out. Our server was not very attentive either. I guess Ill have to wait until things are back to normal before I dine here again.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Vacation with sister

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Wonderful dining experience! Our server, Michelle V was phenomenal and the food was delicious and imaginative. Kudos to the chef for the outstanding Peruvian scallops! The oysters were fresh and flavorful. Hubby had the soft shell crab, son had the lobster roll and I had the fried oyster roll and crab chowder. It had lots of clams in it, still in the shell!! The key lime pie was just the right tartness and ended our meal perfectly. Our first time here and will definitely return soon.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Need a boost to your mood?  FWD!  Late lunch on the new patio was fabulous!!  Breezes, sunshine, and amazing food.  Had BOTH specials!!  Santa Barbara Prawns and Grilled Hamachi Collar.  I ate like a cat, they were so good!  Virtual hugs to Rachel, Sal, and Chef Alice.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: My favorite restaurant in Manhattan Beach is now even better with amazing outside seating!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: The Lobster Roll is AWESOME. Oysters are very fresh. Great outdoor dinning experience.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: They did a very nice job considering the circumstances....the wait staff was great, and I commend therefor wearing those plastic masks. The food is always great...and the seafood so cold and fresh. The chef take a lot of pride in his profession.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: FWD is top 3 in the South Bay! Food and service is always outstanding.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Bartender server from Boston awesome presence and food dynamite. Highly recommend oysters.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love the al fresco dining experience!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Great afternoon lunch. Food & service were excellent

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Such a great experience!  Fabulous cocktails and delicious oysters and Peruvian scallops!  We had the hamachi too which was perfection with a little touch of heat!!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: My husband and I celebrated our anniversary here. Everything was great and Kacey took exceptional care of us!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: I wish I hadn't taken so long to try this place! The seafood was spectacular - so fresh! And the drinks were heaven.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Great raw food. I know it's weird right now, but please for the love of god clear dirty dishes before dropping more food onto an overcrowded table then make us wait awkwardly for two minutes for someone to clear while food is sitting.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Always great loved the oysters and crab platters as well as the hamachi. And there social distancing and cleanliness was spot on.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Our first outing post-lockdown so everything is weird. We sat on the patio, which is really the street, and there is not much separation from the people on the sidewalk. But the food is as good as ever and service was attentive and unhurried. We will be back, even with our masks.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Excellent food and service.  Everything was executed perfectly.  Alice, the chef, is every bit as friendly and sweet as she is magnificent in the kitchen.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Awesome service. Great food.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: We had a great date night, the staff was wonderful the food was even better than we hoped.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: FWD has the total experience. Great food, super service, and delightful ambiance

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: It was great to finally experience this sister restaurant to MB Post, which is just next door. As the name suggests, the cuisine is seafood oriented, which was fresh and delicious with influences from around the world and domestically.  We ate the grilled octopus, soft shell crab, and lobstah roll.  All were delicious, but we thought the stand-out item was the soft shell crab, which kind of looked like a spider roll meets brioche bun.  Lobstah roll only comes cold, and was tasty.  I prefer it hot, but not many restaurants prepare it that way. We were seated at the high top sushi counter, which was a nice location, but would be nice to try the new al fresco dining option next time, which is reclaimed street parking.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Kitchen was out of crab and other seafood no special rolls-   Did not tell us when we sat down did not tell us when we ordered. Came out later and said oops  -  really disappointing  Fathers Day surprises.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Awesome. Best seafood in the South Bay and one of the Top 3 seafood restaurants in all of LA County

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Always fabulous! Best raw seafood in Los Angeles.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Wait staff was great.  We made a reservation and table wasnt ready for about 10 mins, but they felt bad about that and brought out a few oysters and a round of cocktails, on them! We sat outside and they moved heater for me as soon as I asked.  Octopus appetizer and crab cakes were incredible! Highly recommend! Also had the halibut entree, but didnt like the tomato corn salad, we didnt finish it, unfortunately.  Other than that, atmosphere, service, aesthetics were all great.  Recommend!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: So good we will be back again soon!!!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Delicious as always!! Thank you!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: My friend was concerned about her first dine-in meal during the COVID-19 pandemic, so the restaurant seated us in a less busy corner of the restaurant (that was really nice of them).   The service people were very nice, and wore masks and gloves.  The seafood was very fresh, and the lobster sandwich was delicious.   I highly recommend the bread pudding for dessert.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Amazing food and cocktails!!

Name: Frances
Comments: Delicious food in a lovely, intimate environment.

Name: Frances
Comments: We got the tasting menu for $65 per person, best value!  Each dish unique and with many layers that complimented each other in the dish - 8 different plates that each stood on its own!

Name: Frances
Comments: Great service, and one of our dishes was outstanding, but overall the food quality did not match up with the high prices.

Name: Frances
Comments: Simply the best! Frances always delivers.

Name: Frances
Comments: Very friendly service. Always love the bacon fritters. I had a delicious fresh little gem salad with crab and a cauliflower soup with date pure.  Delicious.

Name: Frances
Comments: Frances never disappoints, one of my favorite places in the city for a nice date night. The house wine was great, and make sure you save room for dessert!

Name: Frances
Comments: First time at Frances and we'll be returning! The food was flavorful and delicious. The service was warm and knowledgeable, and the ambiance was cozy.

Name: Frances
Comments: After coming to Frances for over 8 years--typically for my birthday or my partner's birthday--I've never been able to get the coveted window seat...until the 22nd! We got lucky. Stars aligned.  We ate family style which was a value for us and our friends who eat smaller portions. And did I tell you the service was extra special? It was.

Name: Frances
Comments: Amazing, definitely will return.

Name: Frances
Comments: Love this place.

Name: Frances
Comments: Had been here before and it was amazing.  This time the food was good, but the server was dismissive and not very nice.

Name: Frances
Comments: We always love going to Frances.  Its our favorite casual restaurant in the Bay Area.  Frances never lets us down, and actually seems even better every time we go there!

Name: Frances
Comments: Still lovely spot with excellent food and service. Definitely get the lumber jack cake!

Name: Frances
Comments: lovely intimate cozy restaurant with quality ingredients and nice portions.

Name: Frances
Comments: Perfect great food and friendly service  and we went for Valentines Day which can often be a tough night for restaurants.  But Frances pulled it off perfectly!  We always particularly like to sit side-by-side at the spot right next to the window fun to watch the world go by.

Name: Frances
Comments: Frances continues to be my favorite restaurant in the city and one of my boyfriend's favorites as well.  Between the carefully curated menu and wine list, and the neighborhood feel of the venue, it was perfect for Valentine's Day dinner this year.

Name: Frances
Comments: My favorite restaurant in the city. From the quality of food to the cost, it is my favorite spot.

Name: Frances
Comments: Options for vegetarian and vegan food were not plentiful and not great. Ended up not eating entree-not special at all. Good wine list. Somewhat inattentive staff, by the time they asked if my food was okay or if I wanted something else, it was time to leave. Disappointing anniversary experience-not what I remembered in the past

Name: Frances
Comments: excellent service! love everything!

Name: Frances
Comments: We had the nicest person helping us! Food was delicious and ambiance was so perfect.

Name: Frances
Comments: Frances is always a terrific experience.

Name: Frances
Comments: Everything about this meal was special.   The wait staff was very friendly, helpful,  & attentive. The food was beautifully presented and expertly crafted by chefs who clearly know their ingredients & love what they do. Although it's a bit off the beaten path it's well worth the effort to get to this hidden gem.

Name: Frances
Comments: Excellent service, food, wine - looking forward to returning!

Name: Frances
Comments: Chickpea fritters and bacon beignets with dips were amazing! Housemade bread and lumperjack cake are also not to be missed. Our server was very attentive and easy to talk to. Do the tasting menu so you don't need to make an decisions becuase it's impossible to anyway ;) Everything is outstanding!

Name: Frances
Comments: The overall dining quality hasnt changed. Weve dined there since its opening and the food and wine choices plus preparation remain top drawer in SF. The service excels: the wait staff is warm but discretionary, and knowledgeable about the menu preparation and wine list. The diners are a good representation of the City, while still retaining its neighborhood feel. Still, the standout  food is the star!

Name: Frances
Comments: Frances is the perfect spot to start an evening out to the theatre, symphony, ballet or opera. The skilled and thoughtful staff will work with you to get you on your way on time. The fun, vintage F-Market trams are only steps out the door that take you on a nostalgic ride down market to your entertainment destination. Every dish that came out of the kitchen was perfectly prepared. Hint: order an appetizer or two, and a couple of side dishes, instead of an entre.

Name: Frances
Comments: We hadn't been to Frances for a while but we are SO happy that we returned last week for this very special dinner. Everyone was very welcoming and gracious and the food was amazing!We will be returning soon and often!!

Name: Frances
Comments: I love everything about Frances.  Tasting menu was an incredible value and I left stuffed.

Name: Frances
Comments: Wonderful restaurant.  Would highly recommend.  Not particularly child friendly but I took my 7 year old daughter  (it was my birthday dinner).  She is well behaved...not loud, anything like that.  I had never been there, it is a very small and you are very close to the other tables (the staff literally pulls the table out for you to get in the booth seat against the wall).   The staff was very kind and did nothing that wasn't "child friendly".  But, if I had known the ambiance of the place, I probably wouldn't have brought her.

Name: Frances
Comments: The hostess told us our table was needed for another reservation before we got to dessert. It was really, really disappointed.

Name: Frances
Comments: Love the food, the staff and atmosphere. Such a gem.

Name: Frances
Comments: Frances is back on top form. We shared a variety of bouches and small plates. The favorites (smoked bacon beignets and the chick pea fries) were still outstanding - the beet side accompanying the chick pea fries could have had fuller flavor. The sour dough bread was very tasty. The brussel sprouts with tahini sauce were tangy and delicious and the pasta excellent. The only miss was the grits-consistency polenta - I would have preferred something less runny. Service was quick, friendly, and attentive.

Name: Frances
Comments: Lovely dinner, delicious food, attentive staff, a very enjoyable first time experience at Frances.

Name: Frances
Comments: The food was delicious and the service was great. Highly recommend this place

Name: Frances
Comments: A continuous favorite with exceptional, small, curated menu and amazing team both in/outside the kitchen.

Name: Frances
Comments: Our favorite special-occasion restaurant, the vegetarian main-courses are great, and the music is always great too.  Small and cozy and not too loud.

Name: Frances
Comments: Always satisfying, high quality, comfort food.  Ample quantities.  Fixed price chefs menu is an excellent value.  Professional staff.

Name: Frances
Comments: Excellent food, great service.  A great treat.

Name: Frances
Comments: Magical as always!  Such a special place to dine in San Francisco.

Name: Frances
Comments: The sampler menu is great.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Great. But have more attentive waiters. Improve coffee making. In total, I had a great experience with my boyfriend.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Very  nice restaurant, amazing food and service but , very very expensive.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: We selected the six course tasting menu. There wasnt one dish that was disappointing. This is easily the most refined cuisine I have experienced in NYC and is probably in a class with some of the top restaurants in the world. Good luck in these turbulent times.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: We had eaten at Gabriel Kreuther before and the food and experience this time was excellent. We will be back!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: This was a surprise birthday dinner at Gabriel Kreuther.  It was a Monday night and tables were at 30% (perhaps due to the coronavirus?)  There was sophisticated jazz piped in and low decibel level.  The plethora of staff was professional from greet to exit.  GK has two tasting menus: nine course Heritage at $195 and the nine course Chef's Carte Blanche at $245.  While the restaurant recommends you allow 2 hours for the Heritage and 3 hours for the Chef's Carte Blanche, the prior lasted 2:35.   Do not be fooled by the food : time - we left quite satisfied by the portions.It was an amazing dining experience with our favorites being an early course Pistachio encrusted Foie Gras and the Grilled Dock to Dish Tilefish.  Choose from Grilled Berkshire Pork Culotte or Aged Long Island Duck Breast Smoked in Hay as your meat entree.Cocktails of various categories consistent with neighboring Bryant Park range from non-alcoholic, to classics, and signatures.  Pours of wine by the glass were short.As a nice touch, we were presented with a printed menu of the day on exit.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: I prefer to relay my experience at a later date via email.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: I've been to GK several times both in the main dining room and lounge.  Both experiences are always special and a cut above other high end restaurants.  We love coming back.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: I picked the Heritage menu and it was incredible. Foie gras Terrine, pasta with truffle, caviar mousseline and tenderloin were to die for. Wine pairing was very good, it didnt blow my mind (except for a surprising German Riesling and a phenomenal Chateauneuve du pape) but went very well with food. Price in line with the quality and the Michelin stars, very high but worth it.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Delicious and creative food , superb service but very noisy.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: 2 Michelin quality food, service, ambiance, cadre... Perfect for business lunch, ideal for romantic dinner or dinner with friends. Amongst my fav restos in NYC.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: What a special and wonderful experience!!!  The chefs came out to meet us and the service at every level was outstanding!!!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: It's an incredible space with outstanding food, and exemplary staff. I would wholeheartedly recommend this fantastic restaurant!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Great experience!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: This is a one-of-a-kind experience.  From the moment we walked in and checked our coats until we left - there was not one misstep.  The room is lovely, understated, with a nice bar for a pre-dinner drink.  The service was impeccable.  We had the Long Island duck breast and all the many courses that came before it (loved the langoustine tartar and fois gras) and then the sorbet that followed.  A really lovely touch is the little box of chocolates that you get on your way home!  Yes it is expensive - but s worth it!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Wonderful preparation tasting menu but problems out front. Wine service late with courses. Near end help was leaving and transition left us temporarily forgotten.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: One of the most elegant and incredible dining experiences in New York.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: We had a lovely romantic dinner. It was our first time trying out a tasting menu and had the best dining experience.  From the moment we walked into the restaurant, we felt welcomed. The service was exceptional. My partner has a shell-fish allergy, and our server was attentive and accomodating to his dietary restrictions. I was impressed with the plating and overall presentation of each of our dishes. The ambiance was romantic and lovely. Overall, it was an incredible experience and can't wait for the next time!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: One of the best meals I ever had!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Amazing flavors and great wine pairing !!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: One of very best restaurants in the US.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: we were surprised that the service neither did ask if we would like to order a 2nd bottle of wine nor if we would like to have Cafe or Espresso to 'conclude' our dinner.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Amazing dinner. A sensory adventure. Every bite makes you feel more alive. All beautifully, meticulously presented in a welcoming atmosphere.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: amazing plating with equally amazing taste. Impeccable service with an amazing dining experience make this a truly delightful place for all occation.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: We ate at lunchtime.  Everything worked well.  However it appeared that the smoothnessdid not conceal the obvious comparison of LeBernadin--same price, both have excellentwine lists. Food good but not exceptional--and cost-cutting was obvious.  One kind of senses that Gabriel Kreuther will be closing soon. Definitely not in LeBernardin's class forservice, atmosphere and food.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Let me get right to the point - this was a very disappointing experience for us. For the amount we paid for this special Valentines dinner (we were celebrating my husbands birthday), the 7- course menu (excluding the amuse bouche and petit fours) was just ok. I didnt want to use mediocre to describe it, as there were some fantastic elements like the Dry aged duck and red apple consomm en gele.  Everything else fell flat in my opinion. I just didnt think it was worth that kind of money. For a very steep price tag of $1K, every bite shouldve elicited a wow!, but it didnt. Not to mention from a Michelin rated restaurant at that. To add insult to injury, our server announced at the start of dinner that they have added a dish to their menu which is Risotto and black truffle for an additional $50 pp. We declined, as weve anticipated a wonderful evening ahead of us. We couldnt have been more wrong.  Spend your hard-earned money elsewhere. Per Se, Jean Georges, and Le Bernardin would be considered reasonable compared to GK, with amazing food to boot. Alinea in Chicago is very much worth the price tag - from start to finish. You would leave on cloud 9 and have the fondest experience ever ( we still dream about it to this day). And if you are ever in Oslo, Maeemo is top notch.  We will not come back.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Exception food, wonderful ambience, terrific service.  Couldn't have been better!

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Amazing !!! Nothing else to say ! Couldn't be better.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Not enough foodA tasting sit down should not last 4 hours Left the restaurant very hungry For what I paid for dinner 1,300 all of the above comments should of been addressed Portions were extremely small only to have to wait a minimum of 30 minutes between each course.If your are to charge these prides, all of these issues should of already been addressed.Overall, the salvaging grace was that the food although  not sufficient was in fact very good.Dissatisfied customers should have an reinvite to correct the wrong with some type of a courtesy reduction in order not to lose a patron.Dr. Malpeso,

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Our trip was

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Excellent food and service - what more can you ask.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: The food and service were outstanding. The setting was lovely: a subdued, pleasant ambience that allowed for quiet diner conversations.However, as with many high-end restaurants, the portions were very small. Certainly not satisfying for anyone with a hearty appetite.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Good but too expensive compare to similar fine dining restaurantes.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Second time here in the last year. Not to be missed when in NYC.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Lets start with the fact that the restaurant was virtually empty, but once I received the check and saw that my guest had two scotches at $50each, it started to click. This restaurant has some brilliant moments of epicurean magic, and the wait staff is superb, but the expense relative to the actual food and wine is ridiculous. We ordered on the low end of the wine spectrum and it was still $500/ person. This is absurd and nothing about the dinner was remotely memorable.This was my third and last time dining here.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Quite an excellent meal. The main dining room only has a multi course price fixed meal so make sure you leave enough time or eat in the bar area.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: Fantastic as always

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: It was a dining experience.  It was expensive, but you don't go to a place like this without expecting to spend.  It was lovely all around.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: My first time at this restaurant. It was absolutely fantastic! From staff, who accommodated us in the dining room but with lounge menu option ( we were in a rush for the show), thru meals and desert. Food was incredibly tasty, well prepared, fresh ingredients, fantastic combinations of flavors! Really really liked it. Ordered tuna tartar, sturgeon appetizers, beef filet mignon, sea bass, chocolate desert... super delicious!Super pricey. We really enjoy our dinner. Thank you.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: This place was as good as it gets.  The food was incredible and service stellar.  My mom took me for my 60th birthday.  We had the 9 course tasting menu and walked out in awe of the whole experience.  Definitely will be back.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: This was my third visit and it was by far the best.  We chose the Chef's Carte Blanche menu.  We had an 8:00 reservation and time was not an issue.   If you choose this menu, be aware it can take more than four hours, which may be too long for some.  We felt every course was exquisite and the service impeccable.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Geronimo did an amazing job building an outdoor dining space!Food was delicious as usual.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Amazing taste you may only experience a few times in a lifetime.  The party was in my mouth for over 1hr.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: We had a lovely evening of safe outdoor dining. Geronimo always serves excellent food with very attentive staff. Its a place we enjoy frequenting

Name: Geronimo
Comments: As always a wonderful night at Geronimo! Food was terrific, Craig our favorite server was over the top, the best there is!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Celebrated my husband's 60th birthday at Geronimo.  We were impressed with the friendly hostess & waiters, presentation of our dishes and the food was delicious!  Highly recommend the Meyer lemon crepe for dessert!  Valet parking is available...the most friendly valet gentleman you will ever meet!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: It's a great fine dining experience as you'd expect; good food, good wine, attentive service. However, our server's mask kept sliding down below his nose when he was talking to us or bringing food over, so we were really on edge the whole time about sanitary concerns.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Great outdoor dining experience.  Superior service and food.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Great job of creating an outdoor dining space in the parking lot. Nice ambiance. I had the Caesar salad which was very over dressed - a big surprise. Also had the salmon. The waiter didnt ask me how I wanted it prepared and it was overdone to my taste. Overall the food was a disappointment.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Beautiful outdoor setting and exceptional service!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Geronimo is just ridiculously good. The menu and the execution of it. The wine list. The unobtrusive but always there when you need them service. The kind of place that makes me love Santa Fe. Outstanding on every level.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Excellent set up for COVID outdoor dining. Food was very good, but not as outstanding as the price tag suggests. Steak was sold strongly to us but was underwhelming. The carpaccio was the best!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Excellent!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Once again a great dinner on the patio.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Superb in every way. Great menu options. Lovely setting. Peaceful. Outstanding service.  We are foodies and would recommend to the same.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Best food and best service, EVER! No more need be said.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: what a wonderful evening!  We sat outdoors (per the gov) on the portal.  It was lovely.  Began with wonderful drinks.  Moved on to appetizers, entree, etc.  The food was delicious, service attentive but not hovering.  Valet was personable and so helpful.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: We had a wonderful evening at Geronimo .We asked to sit on the portal and we had a quiet table at the end.We were greeted with some Gruet which was lovely .I had the tuna tartare and my husband had the wasabi Caesar .My friend and I split the lobster tails and they were very good .We all split the ice creams.I would have had three scoops of the mint .It is always nice to be at Geronimo .I am so sorry it has to close again today except the patio .They are a treasure in Santa Fe .

Name: Geronimo
Comments: The Elk is amazing. The food is professional quality and very very good.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Geronimo is the best in Santa FE, NM.  I love and adore Geronimo's.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: this was our third time to Geronimo, and we again had an outstanding meal! The service, the food, the atmosphere was wonderful and so enjoyable! We will be back!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: 40th anniversary, we celebrated our 20th here and found it very fitting to return for our 40th! Joseph did an outstanding job making it special!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: We enjoyed another birthday dinner at Geronimo's. Even with the current restrictions, the service and ambience was flawless. We started with the ravioli appetizer followed by the elk and sea bass entrees. And, finished the evening with the banana cream pie.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Our servers were timely, polite, interesting and knowledgeable.  The food superb though the lobster tails were a bit dry. the dining room was nicely socially distanced.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: It was an outstanding evening! Service wasPerfect and the food was wonderful! Great experience!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Amazing as always!!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Service, menu depth, dish presentation and quality all excellent.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: We travel a lot and this was a referral for us which was the best thing that has ever happened. There were four of us it was a birthday celebration and the service from the minute we walked in was impeccable. Franc ( Frank) was outstanding. I had the rack of lamb which was cooked perfectly and so delicious. We also had the elk tenderloin, and the New York strips. Everything was perfect and the attention to detail and presentation was amazing. It is a must to experienced this amazing establishment. A very romantic, relaxing restaurant to dine

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Outstanding! Even better than expected.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Best fine dining in Santa Fe!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Exceptional food and service. We were hot and tired after a long day of hiking and came so close to canceling to eat at the hotel instead. But from the moment we walked in, were glad we changed our mind. Our server directed us to a few favorites (elk tenderloin and sea bass) and I have to agree with his assessment that the sea bass is the best seafood dish in town. Perfectly balanced umami with a light hand of truffles. So pleased to see an innovative way to prepare sea bass using ramen and mushrooms. The elk was closer to traditional with mashed potatoes and button mushrooms, but so tender it made me a fan again after so many previous tough experiences. Make sure you start with the Curry Cauliflower Bisque (velvety rich but not too much) and Sashimi appetizer. Ambiance was warm with gentle lighting. The prices are on the high end for this town but Id go back for the food and service in a heartbeat.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: We had such a lovely evening! From the start with our Valet, The Hosts that greeted us, our Server and all personnel we interact with. Exceptional all around! The FOOD!!!  Beautifully plated and each bite amazing! We will definitely return. Hopefully very soon!!!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Service was excellent; food was very good. We had elk tenderloin and salmon, and they were both very good. The cool atmosphere, top notch service, and unique dishes make it a fine choice for a fine dining experience.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: This restaurant is a must. The food is sensational. Truly deserving of international recognition. We ordered 10 dishes they were all exceptional. The service was also impeccable. The staff's knowledge of the food and how to cater to us made the experience even better. I would give this restaurant a 10/10 as they delivered at every step of the night. I recommend people to plan a trip to Santa Fe, NM just to visit this amazing place.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Wonderful always! Over 10 years. Not one bad meal, not one bad preparation. Kudos. THE BEST in Santa Fe hands down.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: I must say we were a bit disappointed. We do not live in Santa Fe, but always hear great things about the dining scene. While the food was good, it was not special. My husband had an appetizer and main dish that he said tasted very similar. We feel each dish should be distinctive and memorable at any restaurant, especially fine dining. The best part of the evening was the lovely outdoor table and spectacular service by Reginaldo.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: This is the 3rd time Ive been to Geronimos in the last 6 years and the Elk Tenderloin is still incredible!   We took our teenage kids this time and they loved it.   Thanks for the amazing experience for my family!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Fantastic presentation, spot on service. Best in Santa fe

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Food and service was outstanding, even valet gave us good recommendation.  Dress up a bit, its a little more upscale.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Always a great dinning experience even with COVID precautions in place.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: This was the best meal Ive had al year. Every aspect was incredible. We were greeted with such friendliness. Loved everything about the evening.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Outstanding as usual. We love this place and are grateful to the servers and everyone there for a spectacular first meal out for us since the first shelter in place. We are so full of gratitude!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: We enjoyed a lovely evening on the patio feeling safely distanced from other guests.  The staff politely asked us to wear our masks as we walked to the table and our server was mindful to stand away from the table.... now to the food!Delicious, beautiful flavor and attention to detail in each preparation.  Our favorites were the crab rangoon squash blossom and the pan roasted halibut.  We enjoyed a lovely Savior cabernet blend that paired nicely with our small bite orders.So refreshing to enjoy dining out again during this pandemic.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: We came to celebrate a birthday and had a fabulous experience. The ambiance and service are great, and the food will not disappoint! Highly recommend!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: This is our second time in Chicago and we had to come back to the Girl & The Goat, the food here is just on another level. Menu is different and they really go above and beyond with food creativity. Everything is always so tasty you want to scrape it off the plate.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Every morsel put in front of me exploded with flavor and mind blowing deliciousness. I highly recommend the sauted green beans and pork shank.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Amazing food and service. This was a birthday dinner for my wife and they made it amazing.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Great food and place!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: It was below average. Theyre not adapting to covid and dining restrictions well. Their seating capacity is pretty weather related, so adjust accordingly. Were all adults, we understand the current pandemic, if you dont have the seating available call an hour or two before and cancel the reservation. Dont act like the guest has a problem when they arrive to the restaurant.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: I loved that the seating was spaced out, before I always felt like I was sitting on top of the table next to me. Having one more room between tables made the experience even more enjoyable!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Go go go right away with no delay

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Delicious as always!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Good food ! But due to covid AC was off so it was hot inside. Great service overall

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Everything at Girl and Goat was phenomenal! The food was gorgeous and delicious!! And the front of house staff was so gracious and hospitable. One of our favorite places in the city!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Fantastic!! As usual. Delicious, friendly. Our favorite restaurant

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Has to be in the top 10 disappointments I have ever had at a restaurant.  The food was mediocre.  The service was pretentious.  We could not have been more unhappy with what was supposed to be a great restaurant.  There are certainly challenges in todays world and restaurants are especially impacted.  But even if the food was a disappointment there is no excuse for the service, both at the front door and server.   I hate it when people act like they are doing you a favor by taking care of you and doing their job.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: It was 92 degrees outside and incredibly humid, we had reservations and sat indoors and the ac was not running, we were sweating through our clothes and extremely uncomfortable the entire time, almost ruining the experience. Food was wonderful, but nobody from the restaraunt acknowledged the intense heat and humidity that the wait staff and clientele had to suffer through. All windows were shut and it was extremely uncomfortable for women and men, no circulation. Food was amazing though, its too bad.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: There is no wow factor. Food is very good but not great.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Great Job Girl & the Goat! This was one of my first times dining out since COVID and it was a wonderful experience. Everyone wore masks, gloves, and kept their distance. The food was great and loved the add ins of local in-season ingredients! Thanks for making us feel safe.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Me & the lady went out for a nice little date night. Everything went smooth from start to finish with our reservation. They even bring your food out to you from lightest to heaviest which I liked. We got the shrimp & gotham greens salad... FIRE! We got the goat empanadas... AMAZING!!! & we also got the Kalbi style short ribs... ON POINT!! For dessert we got the caramel corn & malt balls & the Berries & creme which were both equally SUPERB! It was also very comforting that all the employees were wearing masks & everyone was spread apart. Im definitely going back without hesitation

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Good food. Great service but SO HOT INSIDE it made it difficult to enjoy our food.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Too hot inside restaurant- no air

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Girl and the Goat is a spectacular restaurant and like all restaurants in the city, they are having to make changes that effects the experience. They deserve our support. They are doing a good job in difficult times and when we go back to normal they will be flawless again, no doubt!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Outstanding, amazing, one of a kind. Definitely worth it for a date night or special occasion with unique food and ambiance. 10/10

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Food was great - ordered the crab rangoon, halibut and branzino.  Everything tasted great - one minor issue was that the skin on branzino fish was overcharred. We were celebrating a birthday and got dessert on the house as a special treat.  We expected to be seated outside but got only inside seating.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Mis handling of a reservation and being verbally attacked by a random waiter ruined the evening. Unprofessional and indifferent interaction.Dismissive managers of the situation and careless handling of customers makes it difficult to support this local restaurant. Specially when there are many more that need support.A $250+ dinner for two people was ruined by lack of respect and care.The food was really good!But due to the poor customer service will not be returning.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Everything absolutely a mouth watering delight!Loved the mixture of flavors and variety of choices.  It was absolutley delicious!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Went here for husbands birthday dinner. Glad they were open during this pandemic! I liked the safety measures they took to make sure everyone was alright.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Great! Very chill and felt clean and safe!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Amazing! Food atmosphere and service alway spectacular

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: We were so lucky to dine in right before Chicagos lock down! Definitely coming back!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Beyond pleased with the food and service... the unique flavor combinations are unmatched!!! Highly recommend this dining experience... goat empanadas!!! Enough said...

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: The server was amazing and really helped us understand the menu! He had amazing recommendations - we were not disappointed in anything that he helped us order! The service was the best Ive experienced in a long time and not to mention the food was outstanding!! Highly highly recommend!!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Server at first was quite cold, but warmed up eventually :)Everything I had was outstanding, from drinks to desert !!!Will be back next time im in Chicago :)

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Amazing everything. Staff food atmosphere could not be better. Great experience!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: So incredibly good.  Unique dishes but not with things so far out there I didn't know what I was eating.  I can't wait to go back.  I will plan a trip to Chicago around when I can go to Girl & the Goat!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Everything I had was amazing.  Would definitely recommend to anyone.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: AMAZINGGGGG EVERYTHING 10/10 holy moly I cant even believe how deliciously amazing that was

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Great food and service! Will definitely be back

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Great creative food made to share.  Good cocktails as well.  Highly recommended for all foodies!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Every bite was delicious and our waitress went above and beyond to make sure our anniversary was special. Loved it!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: This was a wonderful dining experience only marred by the absence of outdoor seating in spite of the barriers clearly available for that purpose.Still, it was wonderful to at last fine at this restaurant.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Love this place! They did a great job at making us feel like we were not taking a risk i dining out!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: As always, excellent refined food with a comfortable neighborhood feel. We love this place. They did an excellent job with safety and health measures. So glad this was our first indoor dining experience in 5 months.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Food was delicious except the bucatini was a little overdone. The sauce was very good and you can tell it was made in-house. Drinks were well-made. Service was great and everyone was very nice.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Probably the best dinner weve had in Cambridge since Covid hit Michael the chef and Trevor the host do an amazing jobDon and Diana

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Normally not so quiet but we enjoyed it. Food as always is terrific but due to fewer patrons we enjoyed a relaxing dinner with great food and service.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: No air conditioning made it uncomfortable.  Won't return until that is resolved.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Great to see Giulia back on its feet during pandemic. Missing some of the staples, like bartenders, but food fantastic as always.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Ambiance was a 3 only because the AC wasnt working. The food and service were amazing!!!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Great food. Professional service. Really enjoyed the meal.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Shockingly delicious. Still talking about some of the dishes days later.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Amazing meal as usual!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Was amazing! Such a fan of Giulia. Kinda, friendly serving staff. Amazing food. Lives up to the hype, and well worth the money.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Really good dinner here our server was wonderful. Very knowledgeable about wines and the food. Gem of a place on Mass Avenue. We will go back.!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Great food and service, thank you!!  Loved all the dishes and flavors. Noise level is a little high--maybe some sound mitigation?

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Really enjoyed my first and much anticipated visit to Giulia.  Everything was outstanding.  Had the signature pappardelle with wild boar with the fresh black truffle add on (such a treat!), veal pasta special, housemade sourdough, burrata with lentils (so good), live scallop ceviche with fermented muscat grapes (so so good), octopus and squid with chickpeas, and an excellent primitivo at the server's suggestion.  Pricey yes but not out of line with the quality/creativity of the meals.  The pasta was perfectly cooked.  Got a last minute res via open table.  Will def be back.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: The pasta here is not to be missed. Always try something new.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Terrific small Italian great local food and friendly service

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Excellent food, wonderful service. It was worth a visit. Wouldn't say it's in my top 5 but definitely top 8. A word of warning - parking is TOUGH. If you can Uber or use public transport, do it.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Hands down one of the best in Cambridge, if not Boston. Beats the north end by a mile. Tough to get a reservation at a normal hour, which is frustrating, but youll forget what time it is when youre inside enjoying the incredible food. The menu seemed to be heavy on homemade pastas (which were amazing), so not sure if they have many gluten free options - though I didnt ask.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Amazing as usual! The top handmade pasta in MA. The bar sometimes has the best seats for interactive experience.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Fabulous!!!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Fantastic!!  Worth waiting for a reservation.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Our waitress was incedible... she was extremely knowledgable with the wine list and her service to our table was awesome.. the food was some of the best we have ever had in a local restaurant.... would definitly return...

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Its very deceptive.  The opening  photo of the restaurant on Open Table is NOT of Giulia Restaurant.  The atmosphere is quite pub like and not an elegant restaurant with white table clothes.The food was a B+ but not worth the cost.  Service was exceptional.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: The fixed price menu was not disclosed on opentable. This information is critical. Dinner was much more expensive than expected as a result

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: This Has to be the most unwelcoming restaurant I have ever been to! If any of the bartenders smiled Im quite sure their faces wouldve cracked! The food is good but I wont go back because of the service. The ambience is not that great either and the chairs terribly uncomfortable.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Extraordinary food, extraordinarily knowledgeable and helpful service.  An extraordinary dining experience.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Reserve WAY in advance !  Food is fantastic, space intimate, wait staff friendly and knowledgeable.  Wine and drink selection excellent.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Kerri was one of the best waiters Ive ever had at any restaurant, highly recommend requesting her!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Came for the pasta, but thought the apps were going to steal the show after having a taste. They didn't. The pasta was even better. Probably could have cut back on the salt by about 15-20%, but still one of the absolute best restaurants we've been to in Boston.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: First, everything was perfectly cooked ... to the point where the smoked octopus/squid was in my top 3 ever.  Our server was knowledgeable, friendly, and added to our overall experience.  We thought that, given the difficulty of getting 6 pm to 8 pm reservations, that the food would be more memorable .... undoubtedly an expectation that is somewhat unfair. I would return, but would limit myself to octopus and pasta,  the two strength areas, which would also keep the tab at a more reasonable level. Wines were delicious and worth the price ..... particularly liked the aglianico and nebbiolo.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Wonderful as always!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: The food was off, rosemary in all the dishes, food salty and not edible/

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Fantastic appetizers and a bit too greasy and heavy entrees. Anyway thats is the best restaurant in Boston (so far)

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: What a wonderful restaurant! My boyfriend LOVED absolutely everything on their menu, and even though I have some dietary restrictions, our waitress kindly offered an adjusted dairy-free version of the dish I wanted. The starters, the mains and the desserts were delicious. It is one of our favorite spots in Boston, and we are definitely coming back there again!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Excellent appetizer, entrees and dessert. Wine selection is great but expensive per glass. Great service. Difficult to get a table without reservations.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: This the second time we have eaten here and it did not disappoint. The drinks, food and service were amazing.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Outstanding, as ever. My husband and I struggled to narrow down our choices of tempting offers and were helped by our terrific server to choose a pasta and the Branzino with some apps. That paired with cocktails and the trebbiano wine was the perfect meal. Guilia's always hits it out of the park!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: This was our third visit at the restaurant. The food quality is well above the North End Italian restaurant. I had the celery root gnocchi and it was very rich with seafood and the souse was very tasty. My spouse ordered the whole grilled branzino and this was a very generous portion and made very well. the sfizzi and antipasti portion on the other hand were relatively small. We will return.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Fantastic!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: We enjoyed our starters and desserts. Didnt love our main dish, chicken and veal

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Wonderful birthday dinner.  Exceptional food and service!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: We had a reservation in the main dining room and decided to do the seasonal tasting menu, one with the wine pairings, one without.All of the courses were varied, expertly prepared and delicious. We especially appreciated the spacing between courses, which allowed us to not only enjoy the flavor of each course, but also the overall ambience of the restaurant.The service was outstanding from beginning to end and they easily accommodated special requests.We highly recommend the Gramercy Tavern!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: One of the best there is.  Service is impeccable, unobtrusive, and extremely professional.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: This was one of mine and my husbands best dining experiences we have ever had. (And we have dined in some great places.) We would definitely return.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: One of our best fixed price meals ever!  The seasonal six course dinner was great!  And the service is the best of any restaurant!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Good was just okay. Nothing special. Overall feels like a tourist restaurant that has seen better days.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: As good as advertised. Food is superb, service is outstanding, wine list is imaginative. Well be back.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: We ordered the lunch tasting menu with wine pairing at Gramercy Tavern. What a fantastic value! The amount of food and wine we received for the price (which already included tip) was impressive. The food was wonderfully prepared and presented and the staff were very flexible to accommodate dietary restrictions and make substitutions as necessary. For the price for the wine pairing (about $50 a person for 5 courses) we were expecting lower-end wines, but the wines were the same quality as that used for their much more expensive dinner wine pairings. I would definitely recommend going to Gramercy Tavern for lunch for a memorable meal at a great value.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: delightful indeed Thank you very muchChris

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Birthday lunch

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: How Gramercy Tavern earned its reputation for good (or great) food is beyond me, my husband and our two dinner guests.  The chefs/cooks appear to have dumped nothing other than salt on all the food.  My entre was so bad that it got sent back.  My appetizer (pasta with Bolognese sauce) was drowning in oil; it was disgusting.  At the end of the meal our waiter did the right thing; she took the cost of my dinner off the tab.  If someone gave me a gift certificate to this restaurant, it would be thrown in the trash.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Great combinations on the tasting menu.  Look to return soon.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: The food was excellent and the staff was amazing, especially our server Toni who made our experience memorable and added her personal touch of hospitality.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Way too expensive!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: The food was superb. The service was first rate and really attentive. The deserts were impeccable. Gramercy Tavern will remain in my fine dining rotation for many, many years to come!!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Great choices on the menu. Outstanding service. The wine list is outstanding. Arrived early and had a drink at the bar. Very well organized as they transferred my bill and sat us easily.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Reservation honoured 20 minutes late. Place was so busy that main courses were served a bit less than hot! Hostess was dour and overstressed. Could not handle the pressure!!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: After reading your cookbook and all of Mr. Myers books I had been  so looking forward to GT and you lived up to and exceeded all expectations.  Our enthusiastic server was a delight!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Our dinner experience at the Tavern's dinning area was nothing short of spectacular. The food was excellent, but even better was the service. I was there with my son and daughter celebrating her birthday. Our server made sure everyone was happy, he provided excellent recommendations and was very friendly. The food was fantastic and the dishes were both the right potion and executed to perfection. Would love to come here again.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: We came to celebrate my daughter, Meghan, birthday and  it was wonderful.  Carolyn, our waitress, was terrific.Thank you for making her birthday a treat.The Grosso Gals

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: I particularly enjoyed the tasting menu at lunch.  Considering the reputation of the restaurant, it was up to expectations.  Interesting dishes at a reasonable cost for the kind of restaurant it is.  Excellent service, friendly and helpful in a comfortable setting.  We liked the idea of the no tipping policy.  We will return.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Ridiculous mealout of sight amazing! Service was impeccable. Our favorite restaurant on our trip!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Good food, beautiful presentation, but did not blow me away. For the price tag and the Michelin star, I was expecting more.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
