Comments: This restaurant never disappoints. The dining room is staffed with lovely people who are attentive, kind and love the food they bring to you. And everything is delicious. This is cuisine in a great setting.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: We loved the atmosphere and beauty of Gramercy Tavern. The staff was friendly and genuine. The restaurant was beautiful and the food was just perfect.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Great place to eat worker are super friendly and a great experience

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Second time here with my wife. Probably our best dining experience

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Just wonderful in all respects. Kelsey is a gem!Thanks to all for a great experience.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Very welcoming. Lovely service and great food.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Sad to report that after many years going to GT standards have dropped. The food was Average at best on the seasonal menu. The duck was hit but the portion size was tiny. The pasta was sausage and clams a complete miss quality you get at a bad diner. As mentioned portion size are so tiny that my kids left starving - which make it expensive given the 184 for the pre set dinner. Hopefully a one off miss.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: We had a most enjoyable late lunch. Everything we ordered was delicious including the relatively inexpensive market lunch menu and the complementary salad.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Great lunch! Delicious food! Kind service!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: We are carnivores but look forward annually to the summer vegetable tasting menu.  Chef Michael Anthony is known for his prowess with vegetables.  The creativity and deliciousness of this tasting menu is testimony to his genius.   Not to be missed!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Food and service was impeccable as always at Gramercy Tavern, however that level of expertise does come at a price! I like the "no tipping" policy, but was a little disappointed to find that the only options in the dining room were a three course or six course prix fixe menu. No a la carte options available. I'll be back at GT, next time might dine at the bar where there are more options.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Still remains one of the best! Food is phenomenal and service is fantastic.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: The food was good (the chef likes it spicy), but ridiculously high prices for beer and wine by the glass, 3 - 5 Dollars more than Michelin three rosettes restaurant Le Bernadin; staff is strained, maybe because they do not get tips, that's why the prices for beverages are so high - they say.

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: I loved my evening at Gramercy Tavern! The food was incredible, and the service was terrific. My only critique was the noise level, but considering the architecture and room size it wasn't surprising that it got a little loud. On the upside, the general cacophony covered the borderline pornographic sounds I made while eating the tilefish course!!

Name: Gramercy Tavern
Comments: Double birthday

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: The last night they were serving food in Florida. What a beautiful way to eat our prior to quarantine. Filet mignon, mushrooms, luscious chocolate cake and the bread. So fortunate to enjoy a wonderful meal in such a surreal time. Stay safe, healthy, and well. Thank you the grill!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: The whole experience from the food to the wait staff was absolutely 5 star!! Scott is a true professional server and made my family and I feel very special! Hats off to the entire team at The Grill-Ritz Carlton Naples!!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Not just exceptional, beyond five stars to the entire staffs, Cheft and facility!  Very grateful to have a place (Cheers fans)where everybody knows your name and glad that you came !

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: We chose the Grill for our anniversary dinner and it was a wonderful experience from the moment we were greeted to when we left.  The service, food, and ambiance were great.  We were not rushed as we enjoyed our meal.  We ordered many dishes from recommendations from the server including the souffl for dessert.  Everything was wonderful.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Fantastic birthday dinner- our waiter Altemar was hysterical and wonderful!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Staff is attentive and food is prepared with a special flair.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Great spot for special occasions - pricey.  Nice presentation.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: The Ritz is a perfect end to our Sunday. Food is always wonderful and it is always lovely to see our friends at The Grill. They are all wonderful people whom we have come to know very well since our first visit.  The Grill is our No. 1 restaurant in town.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Outstanding restaurant. Matt the server was terrific. Only complaint is the noise level.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: First of all we had the best waiter - ever!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Cannot fault the excellent food and service.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: The server was excellent! I especially loved the artistic look of our desserts, and they were wonderful to eat!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Good service, nice ambiance and a wonderful wine list when combined with quality food is always a winner! Nice job by the Ritz Carlton

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Food and service was great. Would highly reccomend.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Birthday celebration, it was great.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: We had a beautiful birthday celebration in the Grill Room at the Ritz Carlton.  All the staff made our table feel special.  The meal was delicious from apps to souffle dessert.  Thank you Ritz for a very special birthday dinner!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: It was our annual stop, and the reason we keep coming back is that we are never disappointed from our high expectations. Cant wait for next year.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: One of the finest dining experience in Every way!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Amazing as always. David is the best waiter. We always ask for him

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: amazing service and menu!!!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Excellent food and service.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: I told the waiter three times that I didn't want the salmon MUSHY - it had to be prepared well-done,and it was served MUSHY!!!  I tried to explain but we got nowhere.  We were seated next to the kitchen, and it was very annoying.  We had an older couple with us, and they were equally distracted.  It was difficult to talk with all of the traffic.  We look forward to visiting this property when we are in Naples, and this visit was extremely disappointing.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: The meal was a huge disappointment.  Nothing was outstanding.  My Delmonico steak was tough - even though cooked to proper temperature.  Wedge salad was bitter and under dressed.  Rolls we just ok.  Foie Gras was marginal at best, not cooked properly and taste was off.  Sauturne wine offered with it was good.  For a $300 meal for two the very nice atmosphere did not make up for a marginal meal.  Would not recommend for the food.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Wonderful service and food.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: All servers are outstanding and Lamar is an excellent wine sommelier

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: The food,  drinks, service and ambiance were all terrific!   It will be our new go to spot in Naples.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: It was lovely to see all our friends at The Grill. Wonderful food as usual. Always our go to spot when in town.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: While everything was good, it was not great, primarily due to the side dishes.  Lobster mac and cheese nowhere near as good as Capital Grill and much smaller.  All sides are small (we also had creamed spinach and au grautins) and just not that good for the prices.  All steaks were very good and cooked to perfection.  Breads are good but should be served warmer.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Excellent!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: food and service was great however the kitchen was extremely slow over 3 hour dinner too much time between salad and entree.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Aldemar, our server was outstanding!!!Ritz very accommodating to my food allergies (gluten, lactose, preservatives)...which is saying a lot!Fabulous gluten free French fries, chocolate souffl , foi gras.  Delmonico was disappointing but when I mentioned, taken off the bill!  Loved the Ceasar salad.  French fries done in separate oil to perfection!!!

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: We arrived 20 minutes before our reservation and they seated us promptly. Unfortunately the table was in a busy traffic pattern for waiters and customers. My main course arrived cold, and it took them a long time for them to bring another replacement, and I was still eating after my husband was finished with his meal.  My food was delicious hot. Overall, we felt the waiters were not as attentive as previous visits. We saw other ladies receive a red rose  and small sampling of sweets, and we were over looked. Finally, when we were ready to leave, they finally brought it Felt like an afterthought......

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: We were celebrating Valentines Day. This is our 3rd time there. It never disappoints.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Excellent menu and very good wine list. Ambience is excellent and quiet enough for good conversation. As part of the Ritz-Carlton, the service was predictably superb.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Overall good. Service was slow. Filet was warm and slightly over cooked. Ambiance excellent.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Great service and an excellent menu and dinning experience. Highly recommended.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: This was our second year in a row at The Grill.  The space is pretty good for a hotel but the food is great and the service is exceptional.  Def. dine here if you are staying at the Ritz Carlton.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Very elegant with delicious menu options,  The service was excellent, just as you would expect it to be at a Ritz Carlton.  I had the shrimp cocktail which was delicious, the shrimp were large and very tender.  My husband had the burrata which he said was very good.  We both had  the bronzino which was deliciously prepared.  We split a chocolate souffle, which came with hot chocolate and whipped creme to top the delicious chocolate with.  It was to die for.  Highly recommended if  you are a chocolate fan.  They had other souffle flavors  and you also could order them in a sampler with all three flavors.   A very delicious dinner in a very nice setting that we both enjoyed.  Highly recommend the Ritz Grill for a special dinner.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: We had an excellent and patient waiter named David. The service was very good. There  was follow up to make sure everything okay, even for more bread. It was a wonderful meal and made us feel special. Highly recommend this place for special event dining. Although not required a sport jacket was most common.

Name: The Grill - The Ritz-Carlton, Naples
Comments: Beautiful service , great food. nose bleed prices. Great venue for an anniversary

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: great steak house , elegant good wine list one of the best

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Service was superb, food couldnt have been better, value was exactly what you should get

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Great location! Exceptional food and service. This place is must visit if in Charleston.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Best in Charleston and maybe in the USA. Food-Service Perfection

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: We decided to try Halls for dinner since everyone said it was so good and man it was AMAZING!! I would definitely come back to this restaurant and recommend it to everyone. The filet was awesome and the best side was the creamed corn! I got the Filet over mushroom risotto. Everyone that was with us enjoyed their meal and did nothing but raved about it all weekend.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: A very enjoyable experience from start to finish. Tyler and Shawna were both awesome.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Absolutely amazing food and staff! Cant wait to take my wife back! Get the bone in filet if available.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Just incredible-we loved our evening there!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Unbelievably the best restaurant weve ever been too! From the greeting at the door to the wonderful service from our waitress Megan we were blown away!!! The steaks are amazing and cooked to perfection! Bread pudding is a must for dessert! Cant wait to go back when we are back in SC!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Our meal was superb and the service was outstanding. Loved the special birthday dessert which was generous, delicious, and came with champagne for all! A perfect family celebration of a special birthday.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: The meal was exceptional! Even received a hand written thank you card in the mail afterwards! Didn't like that you needed to Valet park and the it very noisy but the food was out of this world. We would go back in a heartbeat!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Our server was delightful and very helpful. We were 2 women, and didnt want to overeat, so w truly appreciated her guidance with the menu selection.  We started with a Pomegranate martini, and it was delicious. The veal chop was perfect, as were our sides.  It was our first time in Charleston, and Im sure well be back, and definitely come  back to Halls.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: This was our second visit to Hall's Chophouse, but our first for their brunch.  We both enjoyed a cup of she crab soup, I had the crab cakes benedict and my husband had a bone in rib eye with mashed potatoes.  Both dishes were outstanding!  I wish I could eat there every day.  Loved talking with the owner and the staff.  They made us feel welcome and they were glad we decided to join them.  Oh, and the gospel singers were out of this world.  We had a great time.  We'll be back.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: This was our first time and the waiter was very helpful.  He asked us what we like and then made suggestions based on the information we gave.  It was my birthday and I do like the fact I didn't have to pull my drivers license out to prove it.  I look forward to the next time.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Full disclosure: I never made it to dinner.Restaurant staff informed me that they would call me and let me know if they would be open following a recent hurricane scare.  Never got a call and missed what I had hoped was going to be great birthday for my wife.  Things get crazy on the coast during a hurricane event and things like forgetting about a reservation you promised to call are going to happen at even the best establishments.  I really want to like this restaurant, as they have plans to open a location near me, so I will wait another 3 months for a Saturday night to open up and give it a second chance.  This review will be updated at that time.  In the meantime, I would recommend other diners be vigilant and double check reservations and conversations with restaurant staff.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Absolutely an amazing experience!! The food was out of this world and staff was exceptional. This is an absolute Charleston MUST!!!!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Birthday dinner was phenomenal

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Excellent food and service.  We love this place.  Best food and service around.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Awesome every time a must stop while in the area Great bar dining as well

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: HANDS DOWN THIS WAS OUR BEST RESTAURANT EXPERIENCE EVER!!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: We are Charleston locals and finally made it to Halls to celebrate my husband and Is Birthdays. The service was impeccable and our dinner was perfect. We had very high expectations going in and they were exceeded! We will definitely be back to Halls!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Went above and beyond to make it a very personal experience for a recent engagement

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Visited after relocating from Texas to Charlotte.  This was the best meal, service & steak that I've ever eaten - EVER.  The owners are people friendly, and love to mingle amongst their guest.  GREAT JELLY BEANS!!!!  This is a restaurant you will not want to miss!!!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: When in Charleston dining at Halls Chop House and other Hall Family owned restaurants is a MUST!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Billy Hall is a legend . Went down for my Bachelor party with a group of 12. Outstanding steak and great service. The owner ( Billy) shakes everyones hand as they walk in and visits every table. The personalized dining experience is a lost art.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: The place was phenomenal.  The food was spot on.  Would recommend for dinner.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: We consider Hall's Chophouse Charleston to be the finest restaurant in Charleston.  Plain and simple.  We walk in the front door to be greeted by Billy Hall who immediately makes us feel like family!  We are always greeted by genuine smiles by the entire staff.  The waiters / waitresses are routinely right there when we need them and inconspicuous when we don't need them.  The food is cooked to perfection (once delivered to our table, the waiter always makes us cut our steak to check the cook of the meat).  The waiter's knowledge of the menu is extraordinary.If I had a complaint, it would be that our dinner is always so delicious and filling that we never have room to try your desserts.  We're gonna have to work on that!Thank you Hall Family and Hall's Chophouse for always making us feel like part of your extended family.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: We had a fantastic meal, visiting for a special occasion. For starter, I had the best onion soup I have ever had. It had the addition of onion rings piled on top and I have asked my wife to add it to her own recipe!I then had a delicious steak whilst my wife had the succulent lamb. I finished with a yum bread pudding with a whiskey sauce. Not a cheap meal but absolutely delicious and I would highly recommend a visit.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Great time with visiting family. Folks were great with our 3 grandsons!!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Our favorite Charleston spot by far!   The staff and the family of Halls are incredible.   Food is always amazing.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Have heard of Halls for ages, but never had indulged on one of my frequent trips to Charleston. The reputation is for excellent food and outstanding service. My son, on an earlier visit with friends, proclaimed to the world that he had enjoyed the best steak hed ever eaten. My two friends and I concurred that the service was superb and the steaks among the best ever. However, there was one shortcoming: the onion rings!!! I consider myself a connoisseur. The onion rings served that evening were very large - fine - but coated in a heavy, doughy batter. The batter must be light, flaky. Overall perfection is so close. Let the onion rings lead Halls to its culinary apotheosis!!!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Best Restaurant in the US!!!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Food and service were absolutely amazing and the handwritten thank you note that followed was definitely a special touch.  Probably the best restaurant I've found in SC.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Service was amazing! Worth every penny! Dina was our server and went above and beyond!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: BEST EVER!  We went for the gospel brunch and decided to go back for dinner the next day.  We never repeat restaurants when on vacay but this was a must!  The owner was extremely hospitable and made us feel like VIP guests and looking around the restaurant, everyone was treated that way.  Best food and service in Charleston and probably the US.  I will visit every trip and tell all my friends!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: If you know you will be in  Charleston on a Sunday morning, please make reservations for the Gospel Brunch at Halls.  The food was fantastic, the service was flawless and the music was great!  Billy Hall was there the moment we walked in the door with a lovely greeting, and he even checked in a few times to see if were were enjoying our meal.  I have never experienced customer service like this.  True southern charm.  We will be back the next time we are in Charleston.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Waiter was very attentive. We had reservations and got seated promptly. Or steak was cooked a perfect medium rare just like we requested.

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Literally the best dinner of my life. The customer service and quality of food were amazing! Mr. Hall was there and was so kind and took care of two of the guys whos birthdays we were celebrating. We got a thank you card in the mail after. I would go back in a heart beat and plan on it!

Name: Halls Chophouse
Comments: Excellent service as always.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Love coming to HB, they make great drinks and have an amazing atmosphere.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Went on Friday & had a great time. The ambiance was on point. The old fashioned and the wine was delicious. We did a half meet & cheese tray and found it was very good. Minimal with the cheese, but delicious. Plan to spend what you would on a "fancier" date night. We will definitely go back.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: The food and drinks were excellent, but our service was pretty lousy. We were seated in a booth and our server rarely checked up on us (we only got our water refilled once, I ended up taking my glass with me when I went to the bathroom). My boyfriend had trouble getting in because the host didnt hear him knock, which was really awkward. Also, the pen they gave me to sign the check completely exploded over my hands. I think itll be ok for drinks - they really were fantastic - but I wouldnt come back here for dinner.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Such a unique and enjoyable environment - staff is always courteous and engaging. Unparalleled cocktail preparation and presentation. Perfect late nite spot

Name: Harold Black
Comments: This is our fav date spot in DC. Its not pretentious but lovely, dark, and romantic. Its well run, attentive, but weve never once had the awful experience of being deep into a conversation only to be awkwardly interrupted by a server who could care less. I also love that its not loud. The drinks are wonderful and they can make anything you like.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Great place. Friendly service. A little pricey but they certainly know what theyre doing. Highly recommend just giving the bartenders some guide rails and seeing what they come up with.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: I had an amazing time at Harold Black on a Tuesday night.Speakeasy rule -- sit at the bar if you can. You see the art of creating your drink. You hear interesting tidbits and stories. You bond with your bartender and your imagination won't run wild with ideas that you're not important or that this speakeasy is too pretentious. It's not.While the drink menu was a little more limited what I had was great. A truly spicy cocktail with smoky mezcal? Sign me up. Best part? The bartender can customize to your tastes and needs. My friend thought her old fashioned was too sweet. 'No problem, allow me to make you something like a vieux carre and here's exactly why I am using what I am using.' And then thoughtful bar bites which weren't an afterthought for the drink but actually tasty? Gimme that Chicken Tinga Sandwich and an order of the lamb chops for my homegirl please! The R&B music (yaaasssss! to that) had me swaying, the drinks had me relaxed and the convo had me joyful--  this was a laid back speakeasy experience (And trust me, I've tried many in the area).Four stars because it was great time but it truly was a LITTLE too dim and there could be more drinks but I loved this place. Will be back!

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Great cocktails. Pricy but great atmosphere. Not too loud. Great service

Name: Harold Black
Comments: It was our 22nd anniversary and I thought wed do something a little different. Found this gem on a top places to go list and immediately placed a reservation. The ambiance was amazing, food was excellent the bartenders kept us entertained. Seating, well....for an anniversary date, Id rather not have to sit at the bar but we made due. I wouldnt suggested it for a special special occasion. Great for a nice date night or outing with friends.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: this is one of the best bars in DC. a hidden gem in the heart of the city with the best bar tenders, service and ambience

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Outstanding experience. Beautiful atmosphere and every drink was delicious. These guys are experts.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Bartenders not friendly.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: This place was the perfect date night spot. The ambiance was perfect. The music was on point. The food and drinks were amazing and the bartender (Denasha) provided excellent service and great conversation! We will be back for sure!

Name: Harold Black
Comments: LOVED our time at Harold Black. It has such a cozy, cool and chill vibe. The drinks are delicious. Loved the dark ambiance lit by candlelight. Good for conversation. Service was great - a balance of attentive vs. letting you be, to enjoy your time. Cocktails were delicious. Awesome music too. I did not want to leave!! Take note of their house rules too - most importantly tables are for two hours since the joint is small.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: We enjoyed everything about it!  Great, attentive staff.  Delish small plates.  Creative cocktails.  Fantastic, intimate 'date night' spot.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: This place never fails for good drink and intimate settings.  They have light fare menu--which is great to have while drinking.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Good date. I have spoken

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Ambiance was nice but the host asked us to leave after we had got done signing our bill. We were also seated where guests are placed when they dont have a reservation - in the back corner. But we did have a reservation for my 30th birthday. Disappointed in the treatment by the host but it is what it is

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Food & drinks were good. Waiter very friendly. However, a food order & a drink order never made it to the kitchen or bar. But waiter very apologetic & gave us a complimentary very good cheese board.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: I thought the ambiance was fantastic and the bar tenders were really friendly. My only criticism would be that the bar tenders did not dress according to the theme of the establishment. It would have added so much more had the bar tenders worn something of the period. Suits, hats ect... to keep the vibe persistent.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Fabulous in every way, except no one told us there was a two hour time limit due to another reservation after ours, and they asked if I wanted a third drink with 10 minutes left. I would have liked more time so as to enjoy the drink instead of gulping down a $15 cocktail when we were told our time was up.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: This place is a joke. Save your money.  Service is poor. Staff is rude. I would never go back to this establishment.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Great drinks in a cool atmosphere.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Very cool place! Will definitely be back!

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Just a very chill vibe. Relaxed. Great cocktails.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: This is a great speakeasy for a date-night. The menu isn't extensive, but the execution is solid and they don't skimp on you. We got the cheese plate, meatballs, and brussel sprouts and were quite satisfied. The cocktails we tried were also really nice.  One thing to keep in mind is that the music is kept fairly loud even when the restaurant is not very full, which may not be the vibe you're looking for.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Cool speakeasy venue. Stairway dark. Cool hidden bathrooms    Fun atmosphere. Limit food choices.  Pricey. Wont take cash

Name: Harold Black
Comments: As usual HB delivered great atmosphere and wonderful drinks!

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Excellent ambiance, service and people! Perfect for a date

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Fun speakeasy in Eastern Market.  The third time we've been there and we bring different friends each time.  The drinks are great, and to really take advantage of their mixology skills you need to give them a few hints and let them create something for you.  We didn't get any food this time.   It is expensive but the experience is worth it.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: One of the best speakeasy bars in the city! Loved the drinks and the ambiance.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Terrible service. Sat there for two hours and was only served two drinks

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Fantastic ambiance! Cocktails were fine but honestly nothing special special about them. Service was meh. Worth it for the ambiance though!

Name: Harold Black
Comments: As always, absolutely amazing experience. Great service and talented bartenders.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Unfortunately one of the bigger disappointments Ive had in DC. Wonderful atmosphere and decor, but the worst bar tending experience Ive had. The bartender asked order, made several drinks in front of us, and then after 15min, asked our order again. 15min later, she asked us again. Then after another 10 she brought us one drink (there were two is us) that wasnt remotely what we ordered. So 45min after we first ordered we got our drinks. There were only about 12-15 of us in the entire bar so it was rather surprising. Throughout the night the bartender also repeatedly spilled iced on the bar and therefore us. Heard so much about this bar, but unfortunately this wasnt its night.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Great speak easy with an old world vibe. Walk in a secret entrance and knock on an unmarked door to enter a candle lit, quiet, rustic bar.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Service was not great, as usual, there and in Aqua al Due, its owner.  Hoping it will improve soon.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Harold Black is a great speakeasy.  Exceptionally good cocktails, fine bar snacks, and super service.  To illustrate: the bar snack we ordered was a bit too highly seasoned for my companion.  So the server arranged for the kitchen to produce another version of the dish without the spice!  Amazing!  I shall return to Harold Black!

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Very cool speakeasy, enjoyed myself thoroughly and it was a huge plus for my date (who is a bartender) who said that she loved it. Earned me bonus points for finding such a cool bar.

Name: Harold Black
Comments: Awesome cocktails, delicious lemon-artichoke hummus (Ill be back for the chocolate cake) and flawless service. The bartendress was very engaging and made us feel most welcome. We had such a great time that we had to reminded to leave after 3 hours to let the next reservation come in ;)

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Husbands Birthday!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: I'll begin this review by saying that I had been looking forward to, and tried to find an occasion to visit Heirloom Cafe for a very long time. I've lived in San Francisco now for a year and have had dozens of dining recommendations, but I found this one on my own and was excited to visit a local gem in my neighborhood of the Mission. When one of my hometown friends visited, I wanted to bring her, and my local friend in SF for a ladies' dinner on a Saturday night. The food - delicious, presentable, a great portion. We had the fettucine and salmon and both were divine. The wine selection - abundant, knowledgeable, perfectly dry white and ros to our taste preferences. The ambiance - candlelit, dim, great for close colleagues, friends, or a date. What completely turned us off however, was one of the servers.1. She seemed to be under the influence. Her words were slurred, and she approached our table in jerky movements.2. Our third guest arrived a bit after us, and about a minute after sitting down, the server came to our table and said "What's the gameplan" without asking to see if she had a chance to review the menu and decide  3. She accidentally knocked over the entire water decanter onto my friend's seating area, lap, and jacket. she didn't apologize but instead said "it can be refreshing". she continued to wipe it while not noticing that she was carrying 2 more decanters in her arm that continued to pour out - luckily a few other servers came to dry up the area 4. We left a nominal tip instead, and she came to the table while we were sitting there, stared closely at the receipt, and marched away to show her manager. Heirloom cafe: your other servers, from what we could tell, seemed to provide good service. We also spoke a few times to who we believe might be an owner and he was great. You should re-consider this server that has left an incredibly bad taste in our mouths and we will not be returning, nor recommending it.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: We introduced our friends and neighbors to Heirloom the other night. They were very impressed with the menu and presentation and overall excellent repast! I am certain they will be back to experience the restaurant again.  We, of course, visit as frequently as we are able. Thank you - Heirloom crew - for always providing a terrific dinner for us and our family.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Great neighborhood restaurant. We had the halibut ceviche and the pod salad.  Entrees were the Salmon and steak babette. Added the oatmeal chocolate cookie and bitter sweet chocolate budino.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Low key and excellent, fresh food. Service was also excellent! Cant wait to go back!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: I ordered the halibut ceviche and the bean salad while my partner ordered the chicken with corn salsa looking thing...the bean salad was exceptional. His chicken was good but too salty. Overall, a solid B+.  My ceviche had some big pieces of fish and when I pointed it out, the waitress said that is the way the chef likes it...Duh...I was not born yesterday and I do know how to make better ceviche.   And the waitress was either drunk or high on something the way she moved...not cool for her or the restaurant.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Service was excellent - friendly and knowledgeable- made good recommendations.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: We had a wonderful dinner and service was spot on. Bacon and onion tart was flakey crust and perfectly seasoned topping. Salad pulled from the prix fixe menu was refreshing and had some unexpected ingredients, probably listed on the menu but forgotten in the interim. Roasted king salmon with veggies was delicious but trs petite. And dessert of berries with polenta cake was tip top. Loved the French-sourced sauvignon blanc. Restaurant was loud but it's hard these days to find one conducive to conversation where cuisine holds no surprises, however well prepared it may be.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: We love eating at heirloom the people the food its all outstanding!!!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: We were disappointed.  Portions were very small.  Overpriced.  Noise terrible.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Heirloom brings a sophistication to comfort food that makes it a great weeknight choice. A summer evening with corn chowder and the (off-menu) burger is a delight.  Service is friendly and attentive.  Tables are a bit tight, and noise can be a bit of a distraction, particularly when seated next to a couple of folks convinced they are about to conquer the world.   While not regulars, we have returned to Heirloom regularly over the years and never been disappointed.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Best servers. I want to be friends with them. Food is always on point.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Always very special hospitality. Fantastic wine list!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: The  succotash was tasty but the chicken was very dry and not good

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: We loved the Heirloom Cafe! The food was excellent. Our waiter was so nice to us. We thought he was exceptionally so. We would definitely return but it would be a special occasion destination for us considering the cost.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Amazing, always great. A little pricey, but nothing out of the ordinary for SF. Enjoy!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Lovely food snd lovely service

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Excellent food! Great service! It was noisy and hard to have a quiet conversation.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: A waiter that wasnt present and pretty incompetent and since the restaurant was loud could hardly hear what he was saying. He spoke so softly. And didnt seem to have a knowledge of the menu. Also not a lot of personality or attention to our table.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Went to dinner after a show; the food was SO delicious and what wonderful service. Have come to Heirloom Cafe several times and have never been disappointed.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: As always, great dinner.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Very good food; generous portions.  Matt, the owner is a pure delight and the wait staff was excellent.  Wish it wasnt so noisy for us seniors .

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Mussels were so good that I ordered it twice!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: I love Heirloom Cafe and dont dine here often enough.  The neighborhood feel, friendliness and competence of the staff, and the sumptuous authentic food keep Heirloom at the top of my list!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: The waitstaff was underwhelmed to see me and I them. The burger and salads were quite tasty but the fettuccine was undercooked. Plates were small and not elevated enough to be worth the price. I cant recommend this restaurant.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: I really enjoyed my overall experience at Heirloom Cafe and would be somewhere that I return. All the dishes were quite tasty and incorporated flavors that you can't just simply make at home. Nothing was too salty or bland. The wine suggested was superb and paired well with the food. The waitress was warm, funny, sweet. The ambiance was cozy and romantic (dim lit with candles, wooden tables).

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Food and service was simply fantastic. It has an old feel with modern food. Felt like a great modern community feel.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: We had a number of guests in our group of 8 with specific dietary needs. The staff went above and beyond. Highly recommend. They even have a large table that easily fits parties of 12 which a real find in the city.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Heirloom Cafe is the best. Food, wine and service are top of the top. Love it.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Dining at Heirloom is one of the great pleasures of living in the Mission -- or of visiting it.  Once the most tagged corner in the neighborhood, this sweet little spot now serves fresh, beautiful food with a simple, elegant aesthetic.  The staff is lovely and the meals are beautifully prepared.  The seasonal menu is complemented by a thoughtfully composed wine list -- and to say the atmosphere is charming doesn't begin do it justice.  Behind the gauzy curtains, the hubbub of the City fades away in a grand, open room that quickly fills with a pleasant crowd of diners who've dressed a bit for the occasion, and whose convivial conversations punctuate what always turns into a memorable night.  Even if we didn't live on the same block, we'd love it just as much as we already do!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Great place before a show(Beautiful- Carol King). fun art deco vibe and bar drinks. meal was superb. parked a couple blocks away and had to negotiate sketchy street scene but worth it once arriving.  amazing kale salad!  will return.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Great place that's reasonably priced for the quality of food. Not a lot of selection, but everything was delicious. The wine paring is great with pre-fix menu.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Delightful neighborhood spot for celebrating our anniversary. The food and wine were exceptional. The house made fettuccini is a must order (I don't even like mushrooms and this was a standout dish). They also let you share a single order of the prix fixe which is a fantastic deal as it includes generous individual pours and the perfect amount of food to share when you add in an entree. We were both full, but not uncomfortably so. There's no way we could have eaten more! Especially pleased with how perfectly the wine complemented the food (really smart pairings) and how we got to try wines we wouldn't have otherwise known anything about. Will definitely recommend Heirloom to friends and family and look forward to the next occasion that brings us back here.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: The food and service were absolutely solid. I eat here fairly often and have had almost no misses. This time I brought a friend with me who had never eaten at Heirloom - he was impressed!

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Lovely, per usual. Beautiful setting and the food is always simple but perfect.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Great service Delicious food

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: This was our first time dining here and really enjoyed a midweek birthday dinner. Service was so warm and welcoming and every dish was delish! Looking forward to a return visit soon.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Nice restaurant. Good service from quality people. Excellent wine list.  Could use a broader menu selection.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Neighborhood gem, but timing was a bit off. We were served our dishes randomly so no one ate together. They were aware, and apologetic. Im sure it was just one of those things that happen. Great place otherwise. Wine menu is fabulous. Highly recommend.

Name: Heirloom Cafe
Comments: Service was very good, we were seated promptly at our reservation time. Our server was warm and friendly. Background noise was quite loud which made it difficult to hear and the lighting was very dim. The food was beautifully presented but the tuna tartare was bland. The duck salad was slightly dry but had a nice flavor. The burger was definitely the tastiest. The wine was awesome and reasonably priced. Overall the experience was pleasant but with so many other places to choose from, I don't think we'll return anytime soon.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: One of the best pizzas we've had (we had the margherita XXX)! The friendly staff made sure to follow strict guidelines to keep us safe during COVID. Amazing experience!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: We sat outside.  This is one of Baltimore's best. Everyone should support it during these difficult times.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Love Hersch's! Always a great time with great food and friendly people!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Excellent pizza and dessert. Would recommend to everyone!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: good food - nice atmosphere - really liked the cliff diver cocktail

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Our favorite place! best food and ambiance! fun cocktails

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Great food as always!Great food as always!Great food as always!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Glad to see Hersh's back.  It is an important part of the food scene  in Baltimore.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Hershs continues to exceed all expectations in cuisine and service. The drinks and food were outstanding and they took every measure possible to make things safe and comfortable during the pandemic. Should you call, Chris gets right back to you and his team is consistently impressive.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Our first restaurant dining experience (beyond takeout) in four months. Pre-pandemic, we had dined a Hersh's on a fairly regular basis and for the last few months, we've been enjoying their takeout. Since the start of all this, the owners have seemed so mindful of the health of  their staff and guests that it was a no-brainer for Hersh's to be our first meal out. Overall, it was what I expected: spaced out patio tables, disposable menus and dinnerware, masked servers who were conscious not to socialize too much and to stay a respectful distance away from the table. The sidewalk traffic that passed our table was minimal.  Pickup orders were around the corner, which allowed for a quiet and safer dining experience. The food and drinks were outstanding as always.  I miss everyone's smiling faces, but this is as good as it's going to get at the moment. Thank you!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: what an amazing place. absolutely delicious plates! get the crostini and youll fall in love. my favorite is always their homemade pastas, the flavors are on point, exactly. calming ambiance for lovers and friends. youll never be disappointment here

Name: Hersh's
Comments: They made so many changes to make us feel safe.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: This was our first date night since opening up post (more intense) quarantine, and it was the perfect situation. I felt so safe. All disposable cutlery etc, distancing between tables, all outside dining, staff wearing masks were all factors that contributed to our experience. Great food and great experience. Highly recommend!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Always great!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Great service. Amazing food. They never disappoint.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Always great food - meatball appetizer and margherita pizza - really good.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Service was outstanding, pizza was amazing - highly recommend! Def. need a reservation, walk-ins  esp on weekends are unlikely.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Their food is absolutely delicious. Love coming here for cocktails or special occasions.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Every time we go, it is the best food Ive ever eaten.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Awesome. Period.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Hersh's is  a great date night spot! The pizza is delicious as well as all of the apps. We tried the Il Rubicon pizza and loved it!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: A bit on the expensive side, but definitely worth it for a special occasion. I'd definitely go back!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Magical as always - Hersh's always delivers with a fantastic meal

Name: Hersh's
Comments: One of THE BEST pasta dishes Ive had in my life. Server was great and knew the menu well.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Never had anything but a 5 star experience here!  New people we brought were just as impressed.  Never lets us down when bringing new friends.  Best pizza, frehsest homemade pasta, and those meatballs!  Mmm...Josh and team kill it every. single. time!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: We love Hershs. Food was excellent as always. Service excellent as always. Really fun date night spot.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Hersh's is the best overall restaurant in Federal Hill, without doubt. Consistently great food, service and atmosphere.  You can always count on a few menu staples, yet they mix it up just enough to keep it interesting. Special shout out to long-time staff member Shannon!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Love this place! Food, wine & service are consistently very, very good.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: A wonderful meal once again.  New item on the menu, pork belly with shredded brussel sprouts and almonds was amazing.  Also loved the arugula salad and scallops with cauliflower risotto.  Hershs never disappoints with an amazing chef and a super efficient, friendly staff.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: We love this place! It is consistent and delicious. Their happy hour drink specials are a good deal - we go at least once a month

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Great! My new favorite spot for cocktails and high-end eats. I recommend the chopped salad!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: There were 5 of us so they put us upstairs. The decor is quite minimal. The drinks were good. We all liked the meatballs, the Brussels sprouts, the octopus, La Salsiccia pizza, the Atlantic cod. We didnt like the clam pie, too salty and the Tagliolini had a lot of sand in it and lacked flavors. For dessert, we shared the Haze Bomb which was just ok and the donuts which everyone liked.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Always excellent!!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: We love this place! We go for special occasions, everyday dining and family get togethers. The food is quality and always on point. They have a great happy hour on fridays and if u like wine or beer this is the time to go. Its pricy but so worth it. It is literally our favorite restaurant In the world and we have had pizza in Italy! It is better here. Trust me

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Outstanding as always!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Fantastic meal start to finish!!!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Never disappoints! Try the eggnog! Chopped Salad had a great spice to it.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Great food!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Hershs never disappoints!

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Good time with family- food was good a bit pricey and small portions- service not as good as other reviewers experienced

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Best romantic I ever had with my wife. It was everything I imagined it to be and more.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Wonderful ambience. Impeccable service , fabulous food!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Foods and services at this restaurant are excellent.  Very nice and cozy decoration.  Highly recommended!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: The atmosphere is exceptional.  The food portions were perfect.  There were several offerings compliments of the chef.  We consider ourselves foodies and have dined inside and outside the U.S.   The chefs selections were delicious.  However, the price for the dining experience, especially the wine pricing was unnecessarily exorbitant.  The wine we ordered was $40 per glass or the wine pairing was $170.  These prices could not be justified.  It was a once in a lifetime experience and not to be repeated.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Sommelier and waiter we're fantastic. Met chef O'Connell when asked. Great experience and food.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: We visited the Inn last night for our 5th wedding anniversary. This was our first time at the Inn and we appreciate the opportunity. I am going to be honest with my review and please keep in mind that this is my personal opinion. It might sound nitpicky but I think that you earn the right to nitpick if you shell out this amount of money for food :)I have been to one other restaurant with a similar structure and that is Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier in DC. We went there for our 1st wedding anniversary so I will compare both restaurants.The quality of the cuisine is similar at both restaurants and there is very little that sets them apart. The wine pairing and selections was outstanding at both restaurants. Marcel's provided multiple "entremets" between courses and the Inn did not do so. When it comes to table service, the only area where the Inn performed better than Marcel's was the enthusiasm and interaction we received from the waiter, Andrew. However, the waiter at Marcel's was still very good. He performed all his table service at a higher level of technical service. The table was cleaned thoroughly and properly in between courses by Marcel's while at the Inn the table was just not cleaned and cleared properly. The waiter at the table next to us dropped used utensils on a customer which is a massive offense for a 3 star restaurant. Additionally, the sommelier at the Inn poured the incorrect for the wine pairing at dessert. While the experience at both restaurants was very good, Marcel's provided a slightly better dining experience. We certainly did not leave hungry from the Inn and are glad to have the opportunity to dine at an acclaimed restaurant, we think that these little things are worth noting when dining at a restaurant of this level.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: This restaurant is a true gem.  The quality of everything is amazing.  A good place to splurge on a special occasion.  But you must make reservations as far in advance as possible.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Our evening at the Inn at Little Washington was exceptional! They made my husband's birthday feel so special. The food, service, and ambiance were all delightful and memorable. Every dish was perfectly composed and delicious. Service was perfect, we never wanted for anything but were left alone so we can carry on a conversation. Everything felt intimate, romantic, and serene. The highlight was being able to see the kitchen and meet Chef O'Connell. My only small criticism is with the wine pairings. I didn't love a lot of the selections and especially did not like the Riesling. It was so sweet I didn't even drink it. The server who was pouring the wines noticed and commented on my full glass yet never offered a replacement pairing which I would have appreciated.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Interesting place and very odd staff.  Food is excellent.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: From the moment we arrived until we left this was a unique and incredible dining experience. Food and service are impeccable. Thank you for a great experience both dining and lodging. We will be back.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Delicious food although a tad inconsistent. We also had to wait wayyyy too long for the cheese and dessert course. To their credit they comped the cheese course.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Birthday & Anniversary

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: The best meal of our lives. The food is worth  a trip from any corner of the globe. Wine lovers are better off pulling a gem from their cellar rather than the pairings which, while varied, were somewhat pedestrian.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: From the moment we crossed the street and were greeted with an dapper seer-sucker dressed man with an umbrella, to the moment we left, with all staff wishing us farewell, it was an amazing experience. Thank you for making our first anniversary as special as it felt. Keep up the excellent work!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: The experience was exquisite replete with visual beauty, heavenly aromas, in captivating textures and blissful flavors. This is the best dining experience in the New World. Thank you for the memories!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Disappointing, considering it is a three star Michelin restaurant.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: No words can describe how wonderful our visit was...every little details were tended to from the beginning to the ending of our meal. We will have to come up with more reasons to celebrate at the Inn...soon!!!!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Splendid experience, as I had expected.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Best meal ever!  Elegance around every corner.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: We had an extraordinary time at the Inn at Little Washington! The server Jessie was wonderful, and made great beverage recommendations. All of the little details!! Customized menus, goodie box of treats to go. It was unbelievable. Each course was amazing and flavorful. They were extremely accommodating to my gluten free dietary restriction. 10/10 would recommend going here for a special occasion.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: What can I say about dining here that hasn't already been said. I'm always afraid that I'm hyping this place so much that those who join me will be let down but the Inn consistently exceeds my expectations and those of my guests. I cannot get enough of Cameron and the Moo Cow cheese cart. He is the maestro of cheesy humor. I'll be back again and again.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Creative, perfectly seasoned food paired with excellent service.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Fantastic experience from start to finish.  Amazing food, wine pairings, and staff.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: A wonderful time was had by all. The food was delicious and the staff was wonderful. A celebration of birthdays was made even more special by a wonderful and attentive staff. The young man at the front door who welcomed us and parked my car, the welcoming hostess who showed us to our table, Chris who oversaw our dinning experience, the wine expert who suggested a fine bottle of wine, and everyone else who had a hand in bringing food and drink, they all made the experience special. We were seated in an area with five other couples which made for an intimate dinning experience. It was really nice, it made you feel special with all the attention and care.It was really wonderful.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: World class!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Beautiful experience! The food was beyond amazing. Words do not do it justice.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: It was our 31st Anniversary dinner.  A once in a lifetime dining experience.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Everything was wonderful.  The food, the wine pairing, the explanations, the cheese cart! This was my partner's 60th birthday and they created a keepsake menu.  I had called ahead and paid for a copy of the cookbook and it was waiting for him.  Lovely evening in every way.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Five stars all around. Theres a reason this is a three Michelin star restaurant! Absolutely the finest dining ever! Patrick OConnel is a genius!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: The Inn at Little Washington is a world class experience in every way. It doesnt get any better. We are so fortunate to have it in our backyard. Its worth the trip it every time, no matter how far you are traveling to get there!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Its a very nice place but just not a good value. For what it cost it should blow your mind and for me it just didn't. To be fair, its not really my kind of experience. That said, I have been to some highly rated and very pricey restaurants around DC. i.e. Bourboun Steak, Bond 45 and others and was much more satisfied. The service is top notch of course I will give it 5 stars there. But negatives were the seating is close quarters; we were sandwiched a foot away from tables on each side of us and more than once an obnoxious woman next to us jumped into our conversation univited.  Food was good but not mind blowing by any means. Not exactly what I expected for a dinner for 2 at about $750.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Everything from valet service, to meal service, to quality... all excellent! Staff made us feel like family for our Easter gathering. The selection of menus provided excellent choices for each of us. The wine pairings were spot on and each wine was described in detail, as were the menu items. I really love this place and will go back as often as I can!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Fantastic. This is a jewel.  It has been 20 years since our last visit. We decided its worth a visit a couple of times a year. On the way out we were greeted by Luray, the owners Dalmatian. What a treat.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Truly deserves our 6hr drive from NY to enjoy the 5 course meal at The inn at Little Washington. Every service staff from the door man hold the umbrella when we got out of the car to our server and sommelier, and the manager who kindly gave us a kitchen tour are all fabulous. Food was fantastic, truly an amazing experience.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: The Inn is always consistentamazing food, creative presentation, excellent service. Always lives up to our expectations and never disappoints.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Cannot find a better location for comfort, ambiance, great food, and attentive staff.  Can't wait to return.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Worth the hype. Worth the money. Just do yourself a favor and go!

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Overall the food and experience was good. TLDR is, it's not worth the price, and DO NOT get the wine pairing. Wine pairing was $170/person. It didn't add anything to the dishes, and you only got 2.5 glasses. Getting a cocktail instead of the wine would have saved us at least $200, and would have had the same food experience. Not only did the wine not add to the food experience, but some were just bad. Some of the dishes were amazing, but for those prices I was expecting every dish to blow me away. Can get similar food/experience for 1/4th the price at nice D.C. restaurants. Portions were small, which is to be expected. But when the tasting menu works out to about $60/dish (before tax and tip) you expect more than one scallop.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Simply outstanding.  Dining at The Inn at Little Washington is a life experience.  It's not for the shy of pallet nor wallet, but that should be expected for a restaurant with _three_ Michelin Stars. The service is exceptional and extremely accommodating; ask and it shall be provided.Plan for as much as three hours for your dining visit.  Lots of courses and many little extra offerings in between.  Dress your best and take your special person for the night of their life.

Name: The Inn at Little Washington
Comments: Delicious and very good but not one of the best meals Ive ever had. Not necessarily worth the price we paid, but a great experience.  Worth it as a bucket list thing.  The ambience and the service were impeccable.

Name: Seafood
Comments: My wife and I both ordered 6 oz. fillet and 10 oz. lobster tails. Our daughter had the petite fillet. We all shared sides (spinach, mac & cheese, mashed potatoes). My family frequently dines at fine dining establishments, and this was easily the best meal we've ever had. It is quite pricey (with tip we spent $300), but as the saying goes...you get what you pay for. During the COVID-19 pandemic, it's not like we could go to a show or concert or anything, so we decided to spoil ourselves through a topnotch dining experience. Absolutely delicious! The ambience was nothing special, but the servers were very polite and attentive. I would certainly go again. Date of visit - 7/25/20

Name: Seafood
Comments: We frequent Joe's because the food, the staff and the atmosphere always meet our expectations.  It is our favorite place to bring friends because we trust that all will be perfect!

Name: Seafood
Comments: Our birthday celebration for my husband was outstanding! The food was wonderful and the service was exceptional.

Name: Seafood
Comments: You MUST dine here if you love the person your with!! Awesome service and the food is unbelievably delicious!!!!

Name: Seafood
Comments: Went there to celebrate an anniversary and was a fantastic experience.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Wonders staff. Excellent food.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Excellent experience all round. All dishes excellent, superb wine list plus very experienced & knowledgeable service. All COVID precautions well followed. They dont give the food away here but neither should they. Everything super fresh and nicely presented. Will be back soon

Name: Seafood
Comments: Nice experience. Very expensive, service was excellent outstanding. I willBe back

Name: Seafood
Comments: We were out celebrating a Birthday and was greeted with warm welcoming people. The food was excellent!Did not care for our waiter. He was pushy for us to order more cocktails, sides and desserts.I think Im this time of our world you should just be happy people are going out to eat. Our bill was over $500 for the 5 of us, so I think he should of just chilled and appreciate the customers

Name: Seafood
Comments: NYC price for Chicago location. You got what you pay for. Theres something for everyone. I was with my mom and my sister, got a last minute reservation here. Food is top notch. Well done fillet mignon that is really soft and easy to cut with a knife. Usually I get a dry or rubbery steak for a well done, but their steak takes the top spot. Crab cakes and chicken were also outstanding as well. It is well worth the splurge if youre feeling fancy or need to celebrate a special occasion.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Everyones food was absolutely wonderful. I cant wait to go back!

Name: Seafood
Comments: As always stwlkar food, stellar service.  It was sad seeing a once vibrant place so empty due to covid, but its a legend for a reason

Name: Seafood
Comments: The service was good, didn't have to wait long although I got there a few minutes earlier. The waitress was nice and respectful, and explained the menu well. My guest I brought with me enjoyed it and we was able to talk, eat, and have a nice conversation with the music at a nice level. I will be back, and I will recommend this place to friends and family.

Name: Seafood
Comments: I had called ahead of time and asked about social distancing and wearing masks.  I was more than amazed to hear what they were doing for customers and for their staff safetyWe ate there and never felt unsafe or anxious during our meal.  Would recommend it to anyone and I have .

Name: Seafood
Comments: High quality stone crabs and steaks. Awesome service!

Name: Seafood
Comments: Love everything about joes From the service to the food it it all top notchOne of my familys favorite restaurantsWould highly recommend

Name: Seafood
Comments: Excellent food and service!  The ambience was excellent.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Our family has been going to Joe's for many years & the service and food  always good.  Joe's always seems to make our visit feel as something special from entry to the restaurant thru dinner and always a thank you for visiting their restaurant

Name: Seafood
Comments: Good food. Really good food. The service was great my first time and spotty this time.

Name: Seafood
Comments: I cannot say enough about Joe's.  Even after recovering from the shutdowns related to COVID, they came back better!  Service was amazing, the GM Paul Ritchie went out of his way to make our experience phenomenal and they added several new restaurant items.  They are very successful and people will come, yet Joe's goes out of its way to thank you as the customer for coming!

Name: Seafood
Comments: Every thing was amazing food,the customer service just everything

Name: Seafood
Comments: No outside dining but they massively social distanced the tables. It feel odd and sort of depressing but we salute the effort. The food was fabulous as always and our server Denise was perfect.

Name: Seafood
Comments: This place is excellent in terms of taste and service. The only place in Chicago so far where we felt comfortable dining in. tables set far enough apart (like about 20 feet rather than just the 6 foot minimum). Servers were on things immediately. From filling water glasses (without making any contact with anything), filling wine and always setting the bottle down carefully and label towards us. checked back when needed but not so often it was irksome. Really knew when to be there and when not too.The collection of seafood is fresh and outstanding. We sampled Shrimp, Lobster, Crab, & Scallops and everything was good. Wine list is extensive and had unique choices for pretty fair pricing. Know up front that you will probably spend a couple hundred for a good meal here, but it WILL be good and you WILL feel treated special and safe from start to finish. There's a lot of classy seafood places in River North, but this one scored all the way through for us.

Name: Seafood
Comments: My ahi tuna was over cooked and bland.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Annual birthday dinner for my daughter and her boyfriend.  This has been our tradition for the past 3 years, and it's their favorite place to come and celebrate.  We came during Covid and they took all the necessary safety precautions which included masks, gloves, social distancing, 25% occupancy, etc.  Was a little strange, as we are used to seeing it very busy and having tables crammed together, but the service and food were as outstanding as always.

Name: Seafood
Comments: We have been Joes diners for years. This meal was best ever. Steak, sides and crab legs perfect. Service was terrific.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Everything was cooked perfectly and explained very well to help with my perfect Halibut selection.

Name: Seafood
Comments: We felt very welcome and safe while dining at Joe's, with the COVID-19 requirements. As always the food and service were outstanding. Looking forward to our next visit.

Name: Seafood
Comments: I can't say enough about Jennifer at Joe's.  She was a knowledgeable, pleasant,  and has awesome customer service.   I am so pleased about my experience. This was my first time there and I will be going again.  Awesome experience

Name: Seafood
Comments: We are Lettuce Entertain You regulars, and Joe's is one of our favorite places.  We are always extremely satisfied with their excellence!

Name: Seafood
Comments: This is my favorite  restaurant  in Chicago.  The fried chicken is the best in the city.

Name: Seafood
Comments: We love Joe's and we were so happy to be able to spend our anniversary there.  It was strange to not have the usual crowds.  They did everything they could to keep us safe, and the waitstaff was charming and joined in on our celebration in this strange tme.

Name: Seafood
Comments: 40th birthday

Name: Seafood
Comments: Service was excellent ambience was excellent food was mediocre

Name: Seafood
Comments: We went with the whole family and it was very delicious food and service was great. We had in Miami and this was better despite covid restrictions.Highly recommend. And Denise was outstanding server.

Name: Seafood
Comments: The food we had was excellent. The bottle of wine we had was also VERY good.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Outstanding meal! Great place for a celebration. And we felt very safe during this pandemic. Tables were well spaced. Glad to see they enforced the wearing of masks by all customers until seated at their tables. And, of course all waiters and staff had masks.

Name: Seafood
Comments: The limited seating due to COVID-19 actually made it an even nicer experience.  Great meal - as always.

Name: Seafood
Comments: The service was fantastic, Our waiter was great and very knowledgeable about the menu. Joes is one of my favorites. Our dinner was delish.

Name: Seafood
Comments: I will definitely return! The food and the customer service was exceptional! A great restaurant; my experience was perfect. Thank you!!!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Great food as usual. Very attentive

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: It is a good place to celebrate birthday and the environment is good and food is delicious!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: very good love the experience

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: The food, service and ambiance were all exceptional.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Outstanding.  Across the board.  Maybe the best NYC restaurant experience in 25 years.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: spectacular food, lovely service, quiet atmosphere a perfec tplace for a special occasion

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Our Third year wedding anniversary

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Absolutely phenomenal. It was a unique experience of creativity with delicious plates, with atypical takes of high-class dishes with a Korean flair. Would definitely recommend and go again

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: We dined at 4 other 3-star Michelin restaurants. This one is on par with our other top one in San Francisco Quince. If it was our decision we would give it that final third star to elevate it the highest level. Wonderful presentation, beautiful execution of flavor profiles, service  was well-educated and descriptive while providing attention without interrupting the intimacy of the meal.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: A delightful experience, beginning to end. Thank you for an amazing evening!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Incredible tasting menu! Tim was really fun! Thanks great experience! Will be back

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Great hospitality, couple unique things they did such as a name on the menu and piping happy birthday on one of the desserts.Black truffle cone was out of this world

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: As always, Jungsik lives up to its two Michelin stars and demonstrates that it deserves a third star unlike Eleven Madison Parks oversalted food. The balance of flavors and textures of each dish were spot on, including the cook on the proteins. While the depth of flavor this time was a little bit lower than usual, thats more if youre nitpicking and know how good the dishes are usually. Tim, our main table handler, lived up to the standard I have with regards to service, a high bar that was already set by Oscar. The staff is always very personable and welcoming and I look forward to coming back when they make more changes to the seasonal menu and potentially bring dishes over to the NYC branch from Seoul!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: The food was really good and creative, the service was great and atmosphere very calm and pleasant. I felt it was a little overpriced, but in general it was a great experience and would recommend it for sure.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Everything was superb! One of the best dining experiences I have had in years.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Excellent. The food, the service, the atmosphere, all excellent. Every bite makes one pause to savor the amazing combination of flavors. Each course brought a new favorite after thinking the last couldnt be topped. It was a 2 hour drive, a train ride and a cab to get there from home and we would do it again without a second thought. Truly a memorable dining experience.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Amazing !!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Easily one of my favorite meals of all time.Excellent food. Excellent service. Great wine menu as well.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Amazing Michelin two star restaurant thats quiet and perfect for dining with your loved one or a group. The Korean food was unique and a memorable Experience

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: It is very special when you can walk in to a restaurant and feel like youre dining surrounded by family..that is the feeling we get every time we walk in to Jungsik. Our meal this evening was wonderful, as usual. Every course was delicious. Finally getting to try the truffle cone was the highlight of the night. Now I cant wait to have it again. Many thanks to George, Catherine, and Tim for another memorable evening.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Very amazing

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Great dining experience. We opted for the Chefs tasting menu and it was outstanding !

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Staff were really nice there. People are talking about the dishes in a great passion. The food tastes more like a French cuisine than a Korean one, but they do use some Korean spice and sauce to tune up the tastes. The desserts were also good. Most of them were not sweet so that I can finish them even if I was already really full. The Pinot Noir grape juice was awesome!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: The food was amazing! Attentive waitstaff, nice ambience, but the food was the star of the show.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Loved our evening at Jungsik. The food and the place were incredible, with the service very pro.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Awesome experience!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Amazing! Enjoyed every moment

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Food is really good

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Great experience in NYC!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: A bit too much introduction to food

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Amazing service - everyone was attentive but not overly so. The food was thoughtfully put together, with some surprising flavor and texture combinations here and there. We were celebrating a special occasion, but Im planning on bringing my parents next time they are in town because they need to experience something like this.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Very good tasting menu, just overpriced by about double what it should be.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: We thoroughly enjoyed our dinner. The banana dessert was my favourite part!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: The Overall food quality is great. Yet some dish are bit salty. Love their dessert!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Outstanding experience!  Food and staff are amazing!  Oscar is wonderful!  We loved the evening!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: We were celebrating my boyfriends birthday and the entire staff treated him very special unlike anything Ive ever experienced.  The waiter was very charming and attentive.  Totally recommend!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Fantastic experience - beautifully orchestrated courses delivered by talented staff. A definite destination while in NYC.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Beautiful food with creative flavors inspired by Korean food. Best way to describe it is French-Korean.

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: I selected Jungsik for my birthday dinner in NYC with my mom and wife. I couldnt of been more pleased with the selection. The service was best in class if not better than some of the finer restaurants that Ive eaten out in Europe. The ingredients were extremely fresh, very different than your standard fine dining food, and I couldnt of been more pleased with the selection. The service was best in class if not better than some of the fine restaurants that Ive eaten at in Europe. The ingredients were extremely fresh, and very different than your standard fine dining food without being strange.  The staff was so friendly and extremely attentive. We had the signature menu and I am so glad that we did. I would recommend this restaurant anyone anyone who is looking for a unique fine dining experience that is extremely memorable and fun!

Name: JUNGSIK
Comments: Great food. Highly recommend

Name: Kinship
Comments: Went here for an anniversary dinner a few weeks ago and it was a terrific experience.  We used to live in Manhattan and couldn't help comparing the experience to the likes of Le Bernardin, Babbo, etc.  It was definitely up there in all aspects- attention to detail, knowledgeable wait staff, perfect execution.  The actual dining room itself was okay but we were there for the food and I was definitely glad to be surrounded by 30+ age group diners.

Name: Kinship
Comments: A very special restaurant!

Name: Kinship
Comments: kinship is a calming, soothing, elegant oasis where the food is taken seriously but the people are down to earth. it is a lovely dining experience.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Our evening at Kinship ranks up there, with memorable dinners at the two or three top restaurants in the Washington, DC area.
