Our visiting out-of-town friend, who regularly travels around the world (literally),was awed, as my spouse and I were, with the consistently superb quality of every dish, the perfection of preparation, and the elegance of presentation. All of this was enhanced by correctly recommended wines, highly professional service, and a "classy" ambiance. We can't wait to return!

Name: Kinship
Comments: Food was great and service was exceptional

Name: Kinship
Comments: The experience here was fantastic. Our server was knowledgeable, astute, and friendly. Food was all fantastic, and my boyfriend's drink was the "best old fashioned he's ever had." We had a small food allergy and they were more than accommodating about it. We will definitely come back for more special occasions!

Name: Kinship
Comments: The food is simply exquisite.  We enjoyed the flavors of each dish very much.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Excellent service and very accommodating. We had a baby with us and they were more than willing to help in any way possible.

Name: Kinship
Comments: I was pleased with my experience at Kinship, but I don't believe that I will be going back. I enjoyed about half of the dishes that we ordered, including the tuna appetizer, the grilled shoat, and the Vietnamese banana fritters. However, I was underwhelmed by some of the other dishes. I enjoyed going to Kinship as a one-time experience to check off the list, and I'd recommend it for adventurous eaters willing to take a chance and potentially be disappointed. Service was really amazing, and the ambiance is exquisite.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Sam AND his barback/assistant WERE AWESOME!!! Had a great Sunday, we mentioned we would be back EVERY SUNDAY.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Lovely, cozy setting with very attentive staff! Sunday dinner so we were all going for a lighter dinner, so order several apps to accompany a shared entree. Sea bass to share was lovely, came with roasted cauliflower, mini-porter house rolls. We enjoyed also the crispy taro root appetizer, too. We also enjoyed the Vietnamese banana fritters for dessert.

Name: Kinship
Comments: One of the best meals I've ever had! The Kinship chicken is a must.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Remains one of the very top restaurants in DC.  Beautiful setting, great service, excellent wine and amazing food. And Chef Eric having red chile chimichurri on his menu?!  Definitely try the piri piri beef.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Great birthday experience with my boy friend. I will definitely be back again!

Name: Kinship
Comments: Birthday for wife

Name: Kinship
Comments: Our waiter was incredible and the food was even better. Is it a bit pricey? Sure, but it's also worth every penny. The Chicken is as good as everyone says it is.

Name: Kinship
Comments: A perfect dining experience.Food, service, ambiance...  5 stars

Name: Kinship
Comments: What I can say about Kinship is....... it all makes sense. From the walk through the door you are welcomed by people who care and want to make your experience an exceptional one. It was our anniversary so when sat at the table there was a card to congratulate us and I knew we were in for a great meal. The service is almost robotic in a way where it doesnt seem fake but a guie care for the customer. Food pace is perfectly executed while the service team replaces and replenishes your water, silverware, and bread. Food is being prepared in the back awaiting for the arrival.The food is just as amazing as the service. The sunchoke with Avocado and Aj Dulce peppers is a must try. So is the quail. Entres of Duck confit and Braised Shoat shoulder really sent it over the top. Eating here you really understand and see what a great restaurant is about. The team here has all bought into the concept and work like clock work. Its a pleasure to come here and I will continue to sing the praise of your team and your restaurant. Very well done Kinship! Thank you!

Name: Kinship
Comments: Great server.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Great good, great atmosphere, and great (very friendly) service. Well be back.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Impeccable service with genial and well-trained staff. Food was incredible. Small plates with distinct flavor profiles that reflect the skill and talent of the chefs. Each waiter is also sommelier trained and had excellent wine recommendations with each course. Very accommodating with allergies (gluten free bread is unreal!) and thoughtful touches for birthdays. We are definitely coming back!!

Name: Kinship
Comments: Amazing!!!

Name: Kinship
Comments: the taste of food is a little bit heavy for us

Name: Kinship
Comments: Celebrated Valentines Day dinner at Kinship.  The customer service was wonderful. The cocktails were great.   As for the food, am not sure if I am happy or disappointed.  I mean, it was great overall. However, comparing it to other fine dining restaurants and/or one starred Michelin starred restaurants, I dont think they are at par with them.  For example, if I haven tried Marcels boudin blanc, I would say its great. But, I have to say Marcels is better.  And, I would stay away from their Moulard Duck Foi Gras Confit.  I love foi gras and never had a bad one. I have my favorites and not, but I would say theirs is the worst for me.  Overall, its a great restaurant. I just cant say its the best one out there.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Food and service was excellent! Really enjoyed our dining experience.

Name: Kinship
Comments: I would absolutely and have already recommended Kinship to multiple friends and colleagues.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Some of the best food I have had in DC, the menu was exceptional, the lobster french toast was out of this world, and the service and ambiance were something I would expect from a much more expensive restaurant. I would go back in a heartbeat, the staff decor and food were an experience unto themselves. Will recommend to anyone looking for an elevated food experience in DC

Name: Kinship
Comments: We thoroughly enjoyed our meal at kinship. The portion size was just right.  The quality of the scallops and the overall venison dish were superb. The Jerusalem artichokes and pommes anna were very tasty starters.  The 4/5 stars was because of the chocolate tart with lapsang souchong; very smoky taste.  Maybe others love it, but we found it a bit odd. Service was outstanding.  We will be back often.

Name: Kinship
Comments: I specifically selected anniversary under special occasion when I made the booking, but nothing was done differently for the occasion. We found that surprising and disappointing, epecially the fact that the two tables next to us received cards, complimentary desserts and were wished a happy anniversary.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Very well taken care of and everything was timed out at a nice pace.

Name: Kinship
Comments: service was great - food was a little better than average given the price point.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Incredible service, amazing innovative food, all-around fantastic experience. Top 3 must try...lobster french toast,  Maine scallops, chocolate souffle cake.

Name: Kinship
Comments: This was our first time to kinship, but not our last. The menu is creative and organized in columns of "style/feeling" with a couple of starters, a couple of entres, and a couple of desserts in each. The food was first-rate and well priced for the quality. There were a number of locally sourced meats and produce. The wine list was smart with a good variety. Especially noteworthy was the list of very good 375ml bottles.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Kinship is simply outstanding. Great place to celebrate a special occasion. The food and service are terrific. Can't wait to return.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Amazing and creative dishes with excellent service

Name: Kinship
Comments: Excellent meal at Kinship. Service was polished, food was spectacular.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Fantastic experience. Service was amazing. Food was amazing. Just go.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Great meal!  Loved the lobster appetizer and roasted chicken.  Service perfect!  Thank you.  Ill be back soon.

Name: Kinship
Comments: Exceptional in every way though you cant have the 4# chicken unless you can commit an extra 80 minutes to the cooking process. The sausage and cod were our second choices and they didnt disappoint

Name: Kinship
Comments: Truly enjoyed your unique dining experience.  Loved the booth we sat in for the 4 of us.  Food was fresh, flavorful, eclectic, right size portion, that allowed each of us to taste/enjoy each others dishes.  All of the staff was most helpful.  Recommendations for tasting multiple different dishes was great!

Name: Koi
Comments: Loved my first experience there. Went with my girls for early dinner. The food was just amazing and the service was wonderful. Drinks ... AMAZING! I will be back. Thank you so much for this cute little spot with the friendliest staff. The toro and Shes so LA roll, worth every penny. Definitely recommend this spot.

Name: Koi
Comments: What a great place! Ambiance, service, food - everything was top notch!

Name: Koi
Comments: Enjoyed the patio COVID safe experience. Same great service and food.

Name: Koi
Comments: We have been to Koi on numerous occasions and  normally enjoy our experience. This was not one of them. Began by staff member deciding to answer a call without first attending to his guest standing in front of him. We were ultimately seated by another staff member while the previous staff member remained on the phone. Service was non existent unless you were the seated at the table of 6. Food was slow to come out and server blamed it on kitchen. Oddly enough another table of 2 seated next to us was experiencing similar If not worse service than we received. Anyway just a really bad night for Koi and a birthday dinner for my wife that was  memorable for all the wrong reasons.  We will probably go back because we do like the food but it will definitely be a while.

Name: Koi
Comments: Amazing place and everything is so

Name: Koi
Comments: Amazing service and great food! Highly recommended

Name: Koi
Comments: We overall had a great experience at Koi, the service and the food was fantastic. The seating was ok, but it was good given the current circumstances of COVID. We definitely would go back another time!

Name: Koi
Comments: Surprised my boyfriend here for dinner and he enjoyed the food and service. The waiter was sympathetic and patient with us. I would recommend coming here.

Name: Koi
Comments: Amazing service, great food, one of my favorite restaurants!

Name: Koi
Comments: Good food and service.  Ambiance was good as well.

Name: Koi
Comments: First visit to a restaurant during Covid pandemic.  Great food, great service.  Tables were separated well and staff all had masks.

Name: Koi
Comments: Tried this place out after they re-opened due to covid.  Miso black cod was a great dish, the rest of the dishes including the sushi was mediocre.  Service was pretty sad, I ordered a dish and asked to change it ONE MINUTE later, and was told by the waiter Im sorry I already put the order in.  What stupid service and restaurant doesnt let you change your mind?  He should have said - yes Ill change the order immediately.  Doubtful Ill go back given the poor training of the servers.

Name: Koi
Comments: Everything from the moment we walked in was outstanding.  We have just found our favorite LA sushi place.  We ran 20 minutes late due to PCH traffic and they still seated us right away.  Our server was exceptional and the food was terrific.

Name: Koi
Comments: There were signs up notifying of mandatory masks that need to be worn when entering the restaurant. Many customers were not wearing masks as they walked in, or whilst speaking to host, nor whilst walking to their table. Several tables are NOT 6 feet apart (ours at most was 3 feet from the tables next to us, and the booth). However, they did a great job with the booths providing Perspex dividers to separate the booth seating. The servers/waiters did an excellent job providing a service that is very difficult now with gloves and masks, they provided a top notch service to us, food was excellent as always, and if they can figure out how to distance tables we will keep coming back

Name: Koi
Comments: Great place to go on a date

Name: Koi
Comments: Koi has their act together as they reopen. Sign of a professional organization. Food ambiance service all great as always. Drinks were delicious too. Will be going back regularly.

Name: Koi
Comments: Tony was an amazing server! There were guys smoking in the patio next to our table which was gross. The bartender with the white hair was rude; when my friend wanted to order a drink with Mezcal he asked, Have you had that one before? to which she replied no. He responded Then get something else. Luckily we were able to order them through Tony at our table. Do better.

Name: Koi
Comments: Excellent food and service. We're a regular and happy to come back time after time. You have to try the crispy rice with filet mignon.

Name: Koi
Comments: Thank you for great experience! Friendly service, delicious food!!!

Name: Koi
Comments: A must, when you are in LA.  Only negative is the high noise level.

Name: Koi
Comments: Things are always great at Koi.  Food and Vibes are perfect.

Name: Koi
Comments: Always a treat. Exquisite taste and service is great

Name: Koi
Comments: Server messed up a couple times after asking for specific things but not the end of the world

Name: Koi
Comments: Spectacular food. Creamy shrimp is pure heaven on the plate; sizzling rice takes this item to the addictive level; and, the sashimi is fresher than any youll find anywhere. Brilliant.

Name: Koi
Comments: Exceptional attentive complete. service with outstanding food and good advice from waiter.A tiny setback was slight rudeness from valet Parker but this was quickly forgotten

Name: Koi
Comments: This aint real sushi.   Overpriced for run of the mill pieces of fish.   Meh.   Very loud lots of kids playing video games loudly without headphones .

Name: Koi
Comments: Bad service long wait for drinks

Name: Koi
Comments: Amazing!!! We booked Koi to celebrate my daughters 21st birthday and we loved it!!! The food , service and ambiance were outstanding!   Highly recommend this restaurant.

Name: Koi
Comments: Had a reservation at 9:15.... wasnt sat till 10:30

Name: Koi
Comments: Absolutely horrible. We had a reservation but still waited an hour and ended up just sitting at the bar. The service was terrible they were very rude to us.

Name: Koi
Comments: We had a reservation for 9 PM. We werent seated till 10:20. People who came after us with no reservations were seated before us. When we asked about the wait it looked like they forgot about us.

Name: Koi
Comments: The host was understandably frustrated and was trying his best as all reservations were behind but we werent seated till 9:45pm with an 8:30pm reservation. There arent enough seats at the bar so people have to sit outside where it was cold. I understand that Valentines is a busy night but to wait over an hour past my reservation time was a bit extreme. Plus the bartender didnt know how to make a paper plane, bummer since they have such great whiskeys available. At least the food came out quick and was delicious but it would have been a better experience had they comped some edamame or something for making every reservation wait such an extreme amount of time.

Name: Koi
Comments: Food was great but waited 45 minutes to sit down

Name: Koi
Comments: Kiiro roll is A+

Name: Koi
Comments: Perfect spot in LA for any occasion

Name: Koi
Comments: Thank you and the team for always making us feel special and welcome. Also the food is always insanely great!

Name: Koi
Comments: Great food and service.

Name: Koi
Comments: Great birthday dinner celebration

Name: Koi
Comments: Amazing food, fantastic staff and beautiful space. Rich the bartender was wonderful!  Our reservation was for 8:45 and we waited a bit at the bar which was fantastic. The gentleman who seated us was so apologetic that we had to wait a bit and we truly didnt mind. The evening was wonderful!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Always a fantastic experience. Seth was our waiter and we really appreciated his attentive and engaging demeanor.  Food was spectacular as always.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: I suppose we could have moved, but the party behind us was very loud. Millennials dont understand the idea of using their inside voices.Excellent food. Strong cocktails. Amazing service.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: awesome place.  great service, great food, a little noisy.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Family dinner prior to our daughters wedding...

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Excellent, as usual :)

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Simply the best restaurant in San Francisco. Consistently fabulous, great service, and a lively and happy crowd.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Our waiter was amazing!  Food was excellent!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: We always enjoy Kokkari and Sunday was no exception. We shared spanokkopita, avgolemono soup and the wonderful Greek salad, followed by the lamb shank and a bottle of red wine. Our meal was topped off with baklava and icecream. Couldn't be beat in our opinion!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: The kataifi ekmek was a delightful dessert.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Had a wonderful meal with friends. Service and food were excellent.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: It was our first date since having a baby! They gave us a great table, we had great service and food! They went the extra mile to make it extra special for us.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Experience was amazing its our go to place for special occasions or really nice datesThe food is amazing the ambience is great

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Really consistent amazing food - worth every dollar!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: One of my favorite places to dine. Ambience has you wrapped in white table clothes and the true aroma of Greece.Excellent service and polite employees.What more would you ever want!!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Of course this place kills it on every level. Ive been coming here for special occasions for at least 15 years and its consistently amazing. Always try the kataifi dessert if its on the menu!!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: The lamb and octopus were as amazing as my friends described it would be. However, everyone in our party commented that the host was very snooty. I think stoic and unfriendly would be better descriptors.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Fantastic food paired with exceptional service made for a fantastic evening.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Super delicious. I really enjoyed the appetizers. Definitely recommend for a date night.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Love the food offerings!!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Great quality creative kale salad loved the octopus chicken was a bit dry great wine selection loved the Greek white wine we had

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Wonderful place great food ,service and ambience  very well prepared chicken, lamb, beets, and broccoli sides. We will return

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Always a great dining experience at Kokkari. Nice special occasion restaurant.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Food and server were great!  Noise level so loud can't hear people talking at the table.  We had a special birthday celebration, and we all had a wonderful time.  Thank you so much!  Holly C. Kully

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: One of the finest dining experiences San Francisco has to offer. Quality of food is exceptional, and service very professional.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Great food, as usual. Valerie couldnt have been any better as a server. Knowledgeable and sweet and always there when we needed her.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: In spite of arriving 40 minutes before reservation time, they were 10 minutes late in assigning me a table .Food was delicious

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Everything was super tasty and I loved the ambiance. Ill definitely have to go back so I can try more items on the menu!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: First time in San Fran. Came on the recommendation of a friend. Food was perfect, service was warm and friendly but professional and knowledgeable. Very helpful. Everything was fresh and perfectly cooked. Loved it.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Muy agradable lugar al que no suele llegarse como turista.Excelente comida

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: I wanted to hail, I believe her name was Alana. She couldn't have been nicer and more helpful. Both of my guests had never been there before so it was a real thrill for them.Thank you.Katie

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Lovely ambiance and wonderful food. Always enjoy Kokkari!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Amazing food and amazing service. Very authentic and makes you feel like you transported to Greece

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Enjoyed the dining experience.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Great meal and terrific service!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: The grilled octopus was out of this world and Id go back just for that! The Greek salad was under seasoned and the tomatoes were mushy, and we had to send one of the lamb chops back because it was very rare. Greek potatoes and saganaki were definitely impressive with the cheese still sizzling on the skillet, delicious!!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: All was very good. Hostess was very accommodating offering us a choice of seating

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Lovely food, staff knowledgeable on the wine list. Will be dining again

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: My favorite restaurant in San Francisco for more than two decades!

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Kokkari never disappoints!  This time they outdid themselves. Not only was the food excellent but the service was incredibly thoughtful with just the right balance of friendliness and distance.  A standout was the fresh plump squid stuffed with feta and olives on a bed of watercress. Sublime. The coffee is the best I have tasted in ages - even the decaf. And they brought out a scoop of baklava ice cream with a candle for my friend;s birthday even though we did not order any other desserts. The decor and atmosphere are of a class and elegance it has become all too hard to find in San Francisco or anywhere else these days. Kokkari is a wonderful experience whether for lunch or dinner.

Name: Kokkari Estiatorio
Comments: Waiter wasnt very friendly but the rest of the staff was great. Food is very good and the place is really charming.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Perfect as always. Even in a pandemic, Chez Francois manages to shine bright. The menu was limited, but should be expected during these times. Perhaps so much abundance has been taken for granted in the past. Cheers! Looking forward to another fabulous visit soon.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Remains a top 10 DC place -- the food, the service, and the atmosphere are superb -- proved to be a wonderful place to break from the quarantine in a serious and gracious manner.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Always a delicious meal and excellentservice.  Glad to be back at our favorite restaurant.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: This was my first meal at a restaurant since the COVID lockdown began and it has set a very high bar. I had a late outdoor dinner here last night and it was amazing. The service was impeccable, as usual. Ive been several times in the past and this meal was the best (get the tenderloin!). A large high-ceiling tent has been set up which seems to cover the whole patio. It rained throughout the meal, but we didnt even notice. Tables were spaced widely apart and theyre set in from the edges so no rain is dripping or blowing on you.  It was so nice to have so much space between tables so you could easily have a quiet conversation.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: It was our 50th anniversary and the staff were unaware until dessert arrived and our neighbors had a gift card delivered to our table.  The staff then delivered champagne to our table.  It was a lovely evening

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Excellent food and very warm, friendly service. This is the ideal place for a special occasion.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: One of the best restaurants anywhere, and one of the most welcoming. For us, it has been the go-to special occasion restaurant for decades.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Excellent meal with wonderful service.  Fixed Price menu on paper due to COVID, but no loss in their excellent cousine.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Wonderful meal even in world wide pandemic, service was excellent and food was great

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Always a special dinner at L'Auberge.  Excellent food and service!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: A truly special meal. We went for our anniversary during COVID season and sat outside. The food was exquisite. The service was impeccable. The setting was delightful. And they were COVID-safe. We had a 3-hour lunch that we will always remember.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Always a great place to go for fine food and peaceful meal with great service.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Covid has limited the menu selection to Fixe-Prixe items.  Although Duck a l'Orange, fried frog legs, or steak tartare, etc weren't available, the overall experience was still good. We had the Chateaubriand de lAuberge (for two) for entree and grand marnier hot souffl for dessert. They were both excellently done. Since it was my wife's birthday, they brought an extra dessert with candle. Lots of nice touches throughout and we weren't disappointed.  Great place to go for special occasions. (We felt safe eating inside: there was table social distancing, all staff/employees wore masks, they disinfected everything (table, credit card, and even pens) before use.)

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: It was a great experience! Great food and awesome staff

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Lunch under a giant tent was a fine (if very traditional) dining experience under Covid restrictions

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: The restaurant did a great job in the lockdown by setting up tables on the tented side patio.  Even with a limited menu and wine list we had a great meal with great service.  Will be back again soon

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Kudos to the restaurant and staff. In this era of COVID they know how to serve and make one comfortable.  I would go back again without hesitation.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Love LAuberge - highly recommended for a fantastic meal and service.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: They did a very nice job of dining outside under a tent at 90degree heat

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: we have dined at L'Auberge Chez Francois many times before. This was our first restaurant dinner since we began to stay home under the Covid pandemic. The restaurant took all necessary precautions to protect staff and diners.As always the service and the ambience were excellent. The only disappointment was the heirloom tomato salad which Was drowning in dressing and the tomatoes were less than satisfactory.Otherwise the four of us were very happy with our dinners and of course we will go back.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Had a wonderful lunch for our first time visit. We can't wait to go back again, (when its not so hot outside),  to sit in their beautiful outside seating.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Amazing setting - wonderful ambience and service. And of course the food is top notch. Feels like being back in France!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Excellent. We will  be back. Very happy to see the whole staff being very careful with masks and gloves.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Wonderful but not what its always been the 36 years Ive been going. Im sure the impact of Covid is a key factor, from reduced menu offerings to too spaced apart table arrangements and very good but not exquisite fare. I know Jacque is working harder than ever to preserve the family legacy and I greatly appreciate him. Ill keep coming back for certain.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Food is still excellent, but the general well cared for , extras, we've grow to expect were lacking.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Four of us ladies thoroughly enjoyed the afternoon in the garden under a canopy. It was a warm afternoon, yet we remained quite comfortable. It was an outstanding luncheon for a special occasion.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Always a lovely meal and the patio this evening was a joy

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: A wonderful lunch on the tented patio!  Multiple fans cooled us off a a day with the heat index nearing 100.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Another wonderful lunch with family for memories

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Superb meal. Lunch in the beautiful outdoor garden. Wells paced tables under a large tent provides shade and rain protection. Excellent service as always!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: This is one our favorite restaurants in the area. The food, service, and ambience will never disappoint.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: This is our first return visit since the start of the pandemic and it was better than ever!   The restaurant has installed a large canvas pavilion over the outdoor dining area,  Tables are at least 8 feet apart and servers wear masks and gloves.  Menus are only used once and then recycled or destroyed.  We felt safe and relaxed the entire time.The food was outstanding.  Try the duxelles crepe appetizer and the heirloom tomato salad.  The beef Bourguignon and the Halibut with buerre blanc were both perfect.  We are so glad you are back.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Chez Francois is simply the best.  The restaurant has taken precautions to make dining safe and enjoyable. The patio dining was perfect!  Our favorite!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Always a treat to come here & I always order the chateaubriand!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: It was a birthday celebration

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: The service was great, many accommodations in place to meet social distancing requirements which made us feel comfortable being there in this crazy time.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Superb service as always and the food was great as well.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: My wife and I had a very pleasant dining experience for our anniversary.  The food was superb and the service as usual was great.  Highly recommend this restaurant - especially for a 'special' meal.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: If you want spectacular food in a delightful setting with great service you want to go to L'Auberge. It isn't cheap, but it's worth every penny even now when the menu is relatively limited as is the wine list. Still a great night out. And, no I don't work for the restaurant.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: We had an amazing lunch, as usual, at L'Auberge Chez Francois. The food was impeccable - everyone in our group enjoyed their selections. But the service was really the outstanding part as we were a larger group with a number of children. Our waiter was very attentive and made extra efforts with the little ones (who can get a bit impatient during a long meal). We appreciated the staffs efforts immensely. And again, the food was amazing. Always get a souffl!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Delicious Dinner

Name: La Grotta
Comments: My wife and I went to celebrate our 3yr wedding anniversary, and the end of my medicine residency. The food was absolutely incredible. We had the BEST pasta dish that either of us have had in our lives, the 2nd best beef carpaccio we have ever had (with freshly harvested black truffles - amazing). We had a beautiful beet salad, and a perfectly cooked filet mignon.  The wine list is impressive (7+ pages), with a great selection of Italian wines hitting many of the major regions like Tuscany (with a focus on the super Tuscan varietals of Bolgheri - hitting most of the big names), montalcino, montepulciano, Chianti, etc etc), as well as lists of wines from other prominent regions of the world. Not only was the list large and inclusive... it was also remarkably affordable, with less of a $$ markup than you typically see at a fine-dining restaurant. To top it off, the service was great, with attentive wait and support staff.Would absolutely recommend.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: La Grotta is an outstanding Italian restaurant with a beautiful outside patio and with delicious entree choices.  My wife and I have been regular customers for over 30 years and have never had a bad experience.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Excellent place! Went there for my wifes birthday!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: It was a special occasion indeed and LaGrotta made it so! Dining in the elegant dining room with such attentive service and delicious food is always a pleasure!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Came here with my wife for our anniversary, and everything was perfect. The food was very delicious and very affordable.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: 5 star experience and great value for the food and atmosphere. A classic Atlanta restaurant that we love to visit!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Incredible restaurant!!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: My wife and I have been going to La Grotta for special occasions since the 1980's when we were in high school and college.  I don't believe we have ever had a bad meal!  The decor is old school and most people dress up.  Our appetizers and entrees were very good.  We are planning to go back in a few weekends for my mother in law's 80th.  Can't wait!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Our waiter just wasnt that good.  But he thought he was.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Best service of any restaurant. Food was tremendous.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: A fantastic choice! We love to come here for special occasions- food is delicious: beggars purses, sole, lobster pasta- just excellent. The service is great too  one of my favorite restaurants in Atl!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Amazing as always.  The Lobster Pasta is simply amazing.  Best Italian in Atlanta.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Excellent as usual.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Fantastic! There isnt better Italian in Atlanta!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Everything you can ask for a restaurant is in La Grotta!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: We had a great experience. The food was phenomenal and the service by Billy our waiter was excellent. Highly recommended

Name: La Grotta
Comments: We had cause for an impromptu family celebration, but wanted to feel safe outside and socially distant. The lovely courtyard at La Grotta was perfect for us. The wait staff was attentive and charming. Thank goodness La Grotta is still here, withstanding the test of time.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: THE BEST food, great service, beautiful ambiance, and our favorite dinner we have had all year! La Grotta is outstanding on all fronts!!!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Fine food and excellent service in a delightful ambience.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Once again the food was excellent. Three of us ordered a dish not even on the menu and it was cooked perfectly. They chefs and staff happily accommodated our off menu request. We can't wait to make reservations and come back soon.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Our family had a wonderful service and experience!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Wonderful experience.  Can't wait to go back. Amazing food and amazing service.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: This is our second time dining at La Grotta and the experience never disappoints! The food is superb, the wine list is extensive, and the service is unparalleled! Weve had Juliano and Danny as our servers and they are true gems!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: This was my first experience at La Grotta after many recommendations. The food was phenomenal and the staff was extremely friendly. It took almost 30 minutes past our reserved time to be seated because COVID related reduced capacity.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Delicious meal great service! One of our most favorite places to eat! Treated like family.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: La Grotta never disappoints. The service and food was outstanding. The best mussels and lamb chops in the city. My only complaint was that were were seated next to a very loud party of four outside.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: The experience and food were great. Billy was a great waiter and made sure all of our needs were taken care of.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Well be back!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Excellent food and service!!!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Amazing Great food. Great service. Superb experienced staff

Name: La Grotta
Comments: This restaurant has been around for over 30 years, and there is a reason for that. Simply put; the best Italian restaurant in Atlanta.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Just was not as good as it has always been Disappointing

Name: La Grotta
Comments: We enjoyed a wonderful meal on the patio.  Both the service and food were excellent.  La Grotta remains one the best values in Atlanta, if not the very best.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: I was extremely happy with my service, food, and atmosphere at La Grotta. Everything was delicious!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Fabulous restaurant. Nice to dine in after months of pick up

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Lovely evening with excellent service and delicious food. So glad La Grotta has reopened. Had the escargot appetizer. Wonderfully creamy and tasty. Cannot wait to go back.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: My favorite restaurant in Atlanta by far!!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Amazing meal. No sign of corona virus here!!  Packed at 8:30 tonight. Everything was great except the service was awful.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Awesome food!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Absolutely incredible in every way. A must go in Maui.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: As always, they did an amazing job!!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: We had a wonderful time. Everything was enjoyable from the cocktails, to the delicious entrees, and the dessert. The waitstaff were superb. You can tell that they have been well trained.  Kudos to the management.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Awesome meal and fabulous service!!! They treat you like you are the only ones there. Very welcoming and accommodating.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Hands down the best food we had in Maui! We loved it so much we went back for dinner two consecutive nights! They confidently handled my Celiac safe dishes and had numerous GF meals available. LOVE!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Our 4th time coming here in many years...this is the second time we have been here for an anniversary dinner. The fish special was AMAZING.  The wagu ravioli for an appetizer is always good but the sauce is too curling good....get extra bread to clean up every drop of the sauce.  The beet and goat cheese salad was good as well.  Atmosphere is great. Lisa M our waitress was just delightful....great smile fantastic personality.  Just a wonderful experience AGAIN.  Be back next March and do this again.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: I am fortunate to travel to Maui every 2 years. While in Lahaina  I enjoy sitting @ the bar at Lahaina Grill because I am single and the bartenders are very friendly and remember me. At my last visit on 3/16/2020, the owner was there. He made a point to introduce himself as the owner to the couple who sat next to me @ the bar. It was their first time @ the restaurant   He continued visiting many many of the customers at the bar and restaurant area. However, he made no effort to approach me. I felt I wasnt a valued patron because I was a single woman.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: The food and service were excellent. Unfortunately, they have crammed too many tables into the space causing excessive noise and very tight seating areas.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Lhain Grill is terrific. A special experience and amazing food every time. Service by Jillian was top notch.  We are happy to recommend this place, if you know the pricing going in.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Its always such a treat to eat at Lahaina Grill. The staff is wonderful! The food is always exceptional!! And even if we eaten too many rolls( the herb butter cant be beat!!),we cant pass up the triple berry pie!!! The wine list and cocktails are exceptional too!! Lahaina Grill is one of favorite restaurants on Maui!!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Always Fabulous!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: We could feel the wonderful ambiance from the minute we entered the restaurant .  The service was outstanding as well as every bit of the food we ordered.  We will definitely go back!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Great restaurant.  One half block off water - no ocean view - but excellent food and artwork in dining areas.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: As usual great food and great selection of fine wines. The service was outstanding .

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: The food was amazing and the service all over was the best!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: We were celebrating a birthday and couldn't have asked for a nicer experience. Server Michael, the food, the wine and our birthday pie ... Amazing!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Love the ambience of this restaurant!!Food was delicious and cherry berry pie very good!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Exceptional restaurant with exceptional food and service. We were seated in the quietest area, which was helpful. Otherwise, we would not have been able to hear each other. However, we will be going again this week, right back to table 34!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Wonderful experience as always.Everyones meals were fantastic and Lisa our server was spot on!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Michael our server was phenomenal!! Everyone working there went out of their way to chat with us and assist us. Michael even gave us the recipe for the berry pie as well as the penne and meatballs!!!  We cant wait to return soon!!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: This restaurant is charming, and the service is perfect.  We each enjoyed a delicious drink (one alcoholic, one not) and a seafood entree.  Although the food was very tasty, we each felt it should have been warmer.  We were warned that the plates were extremely hot, which they were.  Unfortunately, the food was not.  It wasn't cool enough to merit sending it back, especially since we were there at 5 pm and it was already really busy.  For the high price, however, the food should have been excellent, rather than just very good.  I still rated the restaurant as excellent, however--everything else was terrific.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Great service and best food we had our entire vacation. We are both vegetarians and the options did not disappoint.Highly recommended!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Wonderful dinner! The food is excellent. Prepared perfectly and presented beautifully. Our server and other staff were super attentive.  Noise level is a bit loud. We will be back!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Another wonderful meal from LG. It's no wonder I come back every time I'm on the island. This time I started with an amazing seared tuna and foie gras plate followed with the opakapaka special. So goooood!! Buddy was a wonderful server, she's a blast. There is just so much warmth about the place.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: The food was outstanding.  We had the special red snapper, it was absolutely delicious.  The service was excellent as always.  I dine here every time I visit Maui. Highly recommend!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Enjoyed the food and atmosphere.  Staff were excellent.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: The meatballs and the short ribs were awesome and Maui onion soup andMy special birthday berry pie!!!!And Buddy was a character/awesome person took good care of us!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Unquestionably,  this is one of the finest restaurants we have ever dined in. And we have eaten all over the world. Everything was superb - wait staff, food, ambiance, decor, etc.  You are taken care of from the time you enter the restaurant to the time you leave - and if you leave something behind at your table when you leave they will come running after you to make sure you get it back (in my case my hat). The owner goes to each table and introduces himself and makes you really feel at home. This is a top notch organization and the results show it. A real gem!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: 50th anniversary

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Scottie was a wonderful server. Type of place that focuses on the details and treats you with class. Wonderful food.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Wife and I went here after receiving a $100 gift card from my sister.  To be fair, we would never have gone here if not for the gift card after seeing the prices, we just don't dine at expensive restaurants.  Wife had Pacific Salmon ($49) and I had Boneless Short Rib ($46).  Neither of us drink alcohol.  Wife's Salmon was to come with Asparagus, came with String Beans instead.  Waitress and table assistant did come by a bit but nothing special about the service (I would imagine if we got drinks and an appetizer they would have come by more often but not much of a need with just us getting the dinner plate with no desert).  Her Salmon was OK as was my Boneless Rib but nothing special tasting.  Inside was nice but nothing special and a bit noisy even though we weren't in the main dining area.  No place to park close and plan on $10 or more paid parking unless a few blocks away ($5).  Gift card covered the meals, gave a $20 cash tip.  If you like expensive dinners this place may be good with you, check out the cost with the online menu. We much prefer the Okazuya & Deli Honokowai at 3600D Lower Honoapiilani.  If you've never been there go (take cash, they do not accept credit card and closed on Sundays).  Average dinner price is $17-18, the Mahi Mahi (includes two sides) is unbelievably good as is everything on the menu, it's TAKE OUT so it's perfect for beach dinning or at a condo lanai.  Wish sis had given us cash for us to use where we wanted, but her thought was in the right place.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Amazing food and service

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Awesome place. Food and service was amazing.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Have been to Maui several times but this is the first time eating here..... everything was awesome! We will be back for sure!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Dont miss the Lahaina Grill.  A must while on Maui!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Went for our anniversary dinner and had asked for a special table, we ate in the middle of the dinning room. The waitress was nice but had a very odd personality that didnt seem like she really cares to be there. The tomato in the tomato and mozzarella salad was hard, underripe and had been blanched to peel. Odd. Cant believe they can charge so much for one tomato and some cheese! The entrees, one being the special for the day, were a let down as well. Not sure what all the hype is about this place.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: We've enjoyed many evenings at the Lahaina Grill and everyone is special.  Among the many fantastic restaurants in Lahaian and on the island - the Lahaina Grill is our favorite and we believe the best.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Great food and staff

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Ask for a table away from the bar. Very loud.Wish they could get a better parking experience. There is no handicapped parking near by.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Excellent food and service

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Always a Home run of a dining experience. Food and wine are excellent and staff is knowledgeable. My only call out is the server seemed a little annoyed we ordered dessert/dessert wine. Understandably she wanted to close out her tables and go home but otherwise great experience.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Consistently excellent. We brought people who hadn't been there and they were very happy. Service was great, seated promptly, food came out in an orderly and timely manner.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Outstanding as always! Love the new expanded brunch menu and excited that you'll be open for brunch on Saturdays too!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Both the food and the service are consistently good.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Great place. Awesome pasta.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The food tasted very nice, only the serving size could have been bigger

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The crudo  was outstanding, the wait staff professional, knowledgeable and friendly.  I was disappointed in the Branzino  it was overcooked and over sauced  and Brussels undercooked; but my husbands Halibut  was excellent!  Wine list and wine excellent!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: We had a nice brunch, nothing life-changing but good  - the portions are huge though. We ordered way too much - wish the waiter would have told us?!!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Start to finish, the service, suggestions, and presentation were tremendous.  And as for the food?  Again, never missed a single beat, the quail, tuna tartar, spaghetti, there was not a crack in any of the dishes. Finishing with the olive oil cake with creme fraiche was the perfect closure. Bravo to this restaurant that again came through.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Amazing. So hard to get a reservation but lartusi was amazing

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Amazing brussel sprouts and french toast. The pasta was good, but a little over priced.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Went for Brunch. Not many true Italian options, not sure anyone on the staff even spoke Italian. Restaurant decor was dated and sloppy. Despite all the stellar reviews we were underwhelmed by the whole experience. Food was good but, pretty standard.  Service was OK.  Didn't make us want to try to get on the list for dinner.  We talked about how disappointed we were the rest of the day.  We'll be going to Rafele from here on out.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Service was a little slow, after the food was delivered - it felt almost like our table was forgotten. It took awhile to get a check (we had to flag down our waiter after the first time we asked for it) and once we put down our credit cards even longer to get back the check to sign. To be fair, they may have been short staffed. It was fairly busy. However that said - when we did get service at the table, everyone was friendly and accommodating. Food was outstanding.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Excellent brunch! The pastry basket was filled with delicious homemade treat. Our service was stellar.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The food was excellent but was very disappointed with the service. Dined here once before and thought the food was good but was blown away by what I thought was the best service I had ever had. Then this time I went, waited over 20 minutes past my reservation time, server was inattentive and the gap between appetizer and entree was far too long. Food was good but poor service overshadowed it this time.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: We had a reservation at 8:30 and they sat us at 9. They gave us a glass of champagne as an apology which was nice. Otherwise the experience was great, server was knowledgeable. Food was good but did not exceed expectations.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The food here is amazing, especially the pasta, but the ambience and service have suffered from the popularity of the place. Still overall one of my favorite restaurants in Manhattan.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: We have been several times to this restaurant for dinner, this was our second time for brunch and we were so displeased with the service and how much they rushed us through our meal. It was a late brunch reservation and they cut off service because they had to get ready for the dinner crowd. My recommendation is not to allow customers to make late brunch reservations if the service level is diminished  because they have to turn over for dinner.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Great service and an even better meal!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Delicious as always - highly recommend sharing the Lemon Ricotta pancakes on the side :) Were very accommodating when we were late for a reservation despite a busy brunch time!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Excelente Service! Amazing food!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Food was great, service was awful. Got orders wrong, took a long time to check on us. Would still go back though!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: My boyfriend & I LOVE LARTUSI !!! We always are trying new spots but this is a place we will forever love and continue to return to regularly

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Everything was delicious and the service was great. The spaghetti was really light and fresh. Roasted potatoes are a must as is the olive oil cake!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: It was our first year anniversary each plate was delicious

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Amazing pasta. Delicious meal. Cant wait to go back

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Wow  stellar food and service and not a fortune

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Lovely restaurant and food but difficult to get a reservation

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Amazing experience from the service to the food. If you can get a reservation I highly recommended.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Clearly this is a very popular restaurant but to my mind, it is overrated. The dishes we ate that night were overseasoned with far too much emphasis on chili in every dish. The steak was ordered medium rare but was served rare and I know we could have sent it back but this would have disrupted the evening. The tables are too close together and the noise level was rising even though the restaurant had only just opened.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: One of our favorites!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Always incredible.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Phenomenal food and absolutely amazing service. Our waiter went above and beyond to make our first lartusi experience amazing. Food is insanely good.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Love love love L'Artusi. This place knows what it's doing. It has amazing food and the best, nicest, most competent waitstaff and management. In a city with so many good restaurants, this is the one I go back to again and again as my favorite.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: It still seems de rigeur for city restaurants to court noise level beyond the ears of most human diners.  That said, LArtusi was a wonderful culinary experience, with a thoughtful sommelier who was touchingly unaffected, and a waiter with a sense of irony.  The butter lettuce salad was a marvel, the pasta (kale pyramide) far from the pile of greens its name tends to imply to Americans.  That we were the oldest diners in evidence is certainly not a complaint...just a regret for lost dining innocence!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: We came for our anniversary and the service was amazing! We had a 10pm reservation but popped in around 7 and they were able to seat us early right away. They provided complimentary champagne at the start which was special and thoughtful. Our waiter Dan was perfectly attentive, helping with recommendations and kept the speed of the meal at a relaxing, welcoming pace. The experience overall was one I cant wait to recommend to others! We will be back!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Was very good! Food was delicious. Minus 1 star for the noise level

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The food is always great here! It is a special place because my fianc and I ate here before he proposed to me in April. The food is so good that we have come back just because and to bring visiting friends and family.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Unfortunately the hangar steak this time was not up to the usual lartusi standards. It was tough and not just one piece but all of it. So disappointed. I have been here 5 times before with no issue. Plan to go back again and try it. Made the whole dinner a fail for a new guest.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: The food, service, and ambience were all fantastic.  The services provided by the professional management and staff are the main reasons that we keep coming back.   The old world elegance is a rare thing, and we value their focus to make sure that everything about the dining experience is excellent.   I highly recomend this restaurant.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: We had another fabulous meal last night at Le Bilboquet. Thank you as always - great food, great service, just one of the best dining experiences in Dallas.  Wonderful menu. We enjoy sitting outside on the patio. Service was wonderful, yet quiet and respectful. Cajun Chicken still one of the favorites in our family. Worth the trip. You will not be disappointed.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Its one of my top three restaurants in town! Never disappoints.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Le Bib is one of our favorite restaurants.  Edward and Stephan deliver a top notch dining experience every time.  Highly recommend!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: 50th Wedding Anniversary celebration! Excellent everything!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: The food was okay, not worth the price. Service was very slow and not very attentive. We eat out at least 7 times a month all around the metroplex. We probably wont be back.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Very fine dining experience.  In fact, the best in Dallas.  Professionalism at its finest!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: We have eaten in restaurants 2 times in the last few months and we have chosen Bilboquet both times. We felt very comfortable with the set up and service. The food was delicious as always. A real treat to be out.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Great as always!  A neighborhood gem!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: One of my favorites! Wonderful place to dine, food is great, friendly service and beautiful atmosphere.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Dallas institution

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Le Bilboquet is wonderful: from the  delicious and consistent food quality to a relaxing and yet chic ambiance!!! Highly recommended !!!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: It was just an off experience. Not usual for bilbqouet. Fish was extra fishy and was not eaten- still charged for the plate and didnt offer to change it.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: The food, service, and ambience were all fantastic.  The services provided by the professional management and staff are the main reasons that we keep coming back.   The old world elegance is a rare thing, and we value their focus to make sure that everything about the dining experience is excellent.   I highly recomend this restaurant.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Home away from home. Always warm and friendly greeted msg and staff.Accommodating, as well.Thank you Jan

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Again, we always feel comfortable, here. We enjoy the staff and choices for dining. I didnt want to be critical so just explaining value one star below excellent due to wine price. Well still drink wine, there.Jan

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Always nice. Indoor patio was a little warm.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Our serving was amazing! He gave us great recommendations and honestly needs a pay increase for the amount of attention he gave out table. Really appreciate the service and quality of menu items. Muscles, beeet salad, crab and tuna tower all sensational.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: The food, service, and ambience were all fantastic.  The services provided by the professional management and staff are the main reasons that we keep coming back.   The old world elegance is a rare thing, and we value their focus to make sure that everything about the dining experience is excellent.   I highly recomend this restaurant.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Service was attentive without being intrusive.  Crab avocado appetizer was delicious.  Perfect for a great date night or special occassion.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Excellent service and food as per usual.  Our favorite French.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: First time back after the COVID shutdown... SO good to be home!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Had lunch outside with two friends and it wasgreat

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Lovely and excellent cuisine!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: I love their brunch. Poached eggs are always cooked to perfection.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: A great place to get a taste of French informal dining in Dallas. Service is impeccable and the menu and beverage selection is great. a very nice date location.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Its always a pleasure. The staff is perfect and the food outstanding.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Finally after pandemic Place sparkledFood tasted better than ever

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: The food, service, and ambience were all fantastic.  The services provided by the professional management and staff are the main reasons that we keep coming back.   The old world elegance is a rare thing, and we value their focus to make sure that everything about the dining experience is excellent.   I highly recomend this restaurant.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: It was wonderful to dine in at Le Bilboquet. I was celebrating my 70th birthday with my husband and another couple, friends of ours.The staff was excellent. Accommodating in every way. We were never rushed and really enjoyed the ambience.I had the crab and avocado salad for my entre and it was delicate and lovely to my palate. My husband was thrilled to see the Frog Legs were on the menu and indulged. I had gazpacho soup for my starter and he had the grilled endive, which I kept eating from his plate. It was prepared beautifully. The restaurant gave me a complimentary peach tarte a la mode dessert for my birthday which had a brilliant sparkler on top. Our dinner was a perfect experience.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Great food and great service. Even under threat of incoming riots, the staff was extremely professional when making the emergency shutdown of the restaurant.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Gracious staff and the food was delicious

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: The dinner was delicious and the service was outstanding. Our waiter was so helpful. I look forward to returning soon. Thank you, Beverly Franckhauser

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Le Bilboquet is always an incomparable Dallas dining experience in all respects.  It is something that everyone should experience at least once.  However, it is far better to make it a regular personal event!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Great servicePatio is quaint Quality / price on the food is the issue The  foie gras is a Demi cuit but had no taste ..... the brioche that came with it was on the other hand excellent The escargot where small and  overcooked The halibut was fresh but the dish itself boring The scallopini where good well prepared The profiterole were okThe flotting island with the creme anglaise was a 7The waiter was great

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: One of my very favorite restaurants in Dallas!! Cajun Chicken is the best! Beautiful place and great food and service!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Excellent service, food and social distanced tables.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: All tables were spaced.  All servers were masked.  Our table outside was perfect.  Even the weather cooperated.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Great service and delicious food! The chocolate mousse is a must!

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Food, service and ambiance all excellent. Problem was my Italian leather gloves were picked from my pocket at the coat check. Management promised to make good on this and they never did.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Fantastic food .good service.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Lovely space - food was fabulous. Took a little time to get any service/ welcome at the table, save water delivery. Nice wine choice via sommelier. Well be back. Love the Paris-based Spring.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Everything was spectacular!  Among the best dining experiences any of us have ever had.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Waited too long to be seated. Especially when we were seated at a mediocre table. Right next to the entrance. Cold draft every time someone opened the door. The kind of table one gets when theyre a walk in. Asked to sit in the main dining room and they told me that would not be a problem if I wanted to wait another 30 min. This is NOT the type of service one is supposed to get at this level restaurant. Food was ok. Service was very good except they left the crumbs on the table too long after the plates were taken away. Not impressed.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Great and creative food. Impeccable service and a great and cozy ambience. A bit pricy though.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: El mejor lugar para comer en todo NY sin duda

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Not a single complaint. Everything was spot on and we will be back.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Superb! 4course tasting...out of this world

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Delicious French food in a charming and beautiful setting.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Too many workers standing around just chatting with each other. Best employee was the water server. Way too many staff with nothing to do. Food was above average but nothing exceptional compared to other Michelin restaurants.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Le Coucou was outstanding in every way. Beautiful space, with great lighting and generous spacing between tables, which allowed for easy conversation (at normal volume) at our table. The food was traditional in style yet creative and perfectly executed; truly delicious. Save room for dessert, which was exceptional. Service was superb: attentive and professional, but not hovering. With wine, this is an expensive evening, and easily worth it.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: My favourite NYC restaurant, they really treat you like gold when you visit.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: By far, our favorites dining experience in the states.  From the moment we walked in until we left every moment and every detail was impeccable.  It was like art watching the staff, both front and back of house seamlessly attending tables, food and beverage.   We thoroughly enjoyed our table as the view of the kitchen was front and center.  My boyfriend ordered the quenelle de brochet and duck.  It was as good as any Ive had in Paris.  Thoughtful and approachable wine list exciting novices and aficionados alike.  And then there is dessert... DO NOT SKIP.  A big thank you to Guillermo for taking us through such a beautiful afternoon.  We cannot wait to return.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Beautiful and excellent  restaurant ! Love it! I recommend this restaurant

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Third visit to le coucou, wonderful as usual with one caveat. The table behind us was extremely loud. It was apparent to us that the staff was unhappy with their behavior as well. I continue to give 5 stars in the hope that reservations will be monitored to maintain the pleasant atmosphere we have experienced in the past.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Le Coucou is so wonderful- great ambience and fantastic food & service. Great for all occasions! Very civilized and elegant!

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: It's still a fine restaurant, and I think we'd go back, but it's not the really wonderful experience we had in November 2018.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: In a word: EXTRAORDINARY!

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Great experience! Service , food and vibe! Highly recommend!! Top 10 restaurant in my list.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: I dont know if I would recommend Le Coucou for breakfast. It was such a huge let down with some breakfast dishes not being available.Two weeks prior I had gone for dinner which was an amazing meal and experience. Breakfast was the total opposite of dinner.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Unbelievable!!

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Exceptional

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Just awesome. It was amazing.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Le Coucou is a perfect place to relax and enjoy a lunch or dinner in a beautiful, pleasant atmosphere. The service is impeccable, very friendly, attentive and discreet. Needless to say that the dishes served here are wonderfully prepared.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: A perfectly beautiful restaurant with charming service and delicious food !

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Everything was amazing from start to finish.I just wished our server was a little happier that day and at least try to smile. The food was delicious and ambiance was just right.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Flawless French cooking accompanied by superb service

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Amazing atmosphere and the service is impeccable. Food quality is top notch with a lot of deep flavors.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Wonderful dining experience.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Outstanding restaurant in all areas. My new firm favourite in NYC.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Food was delicious, service amazing! We were expecting brunch, but we realized there wasnt brunch, only lunch. It was amazing either way

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Overall the restaurant was very good . I was disappointed that I couldnt get a later time . The food was delicious , dessert could have been better . The decor is beautiful! . It is very pricey.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: I came here for my birthday about a week ago. Everything was absolutely perfect!! The whole experience was amazing- everyone was super friendly and attentive, the ambiance was stunning, and the food was amazing! Cant wait to go back!

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Perfection

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: What a wonderful dinner. Delicious food, stunning presentation, enchanting space. Erin the sommelier was amazing. Cant say enough good things about Chef Roses latest jewel (I was a big fan of Spring in Paris). Cant wait to come back!

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: One of our favorite places. Never disappoints.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Our first date night since the birth of our baby son!

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Food and service were excellent.  Restaurant is lovely.

Name: Le Coucou
Comments: Outstanding

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: I am a former restaurant manager/server/bartender. My comments come from experience in many restaurants. Our original server was very reserved, but soon transferred us to another server. The new server was very attentive at first, but became more distant as tables were transferred to him. I understand. I tried to keep my ordering short and precise. We finished appetizers and were asked if we would like anything else? I was confused by that question, as we had only ordered one course. Nonetheless, we ordered our entrees. Remnants of the first course remained as entrees arrived. I had expected the table to be framed for the next course, but COVID restrictions may have changed that hospitality norm. Food was spectacular in presentation, flavor, freshness, and timing. Overall the dinning experience was great, and I made sure to take care of our waiter. Unfortunately my friends and I were limited to soft drinks, which have a marginal affect on check averages. Reflecting on my experience, I ponder the influence of lack of alcohol consumption on the overall presence and mindset of our waiter. Just food for thought. Thank you for a great night!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Always make a reservation, as walkins will be 1hour or more wait, even during the pandemic.Got the foie gras, oysters, clams, crab cocktail, cheese plate which were all solid. Service was fantastic and food came quickly. Indoor vibe is better than the outdoors vibe, as can get quite hot during the summer.Good social distancing and sanitation measures in effect.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Their covid-19 precautions were reassuring.  Outdoor seating was shaded and comfortable.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: I had a wonderful time and the service was excellent!!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Old fashions were too bitterCreme brle was cold but tasty. The hosted attempted to refuse us service by lying about the last reservation time. The waiter polite and kind.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Le Diplomate certainly lives up to the hype! We got a table for brunch after hearing so many good things about it and it did not disappoint! Everything we ordered was spot on and the service was excellent. Really would recommend this place to anyone looking for a unique meal that goes with a perfect atmosphere. Thank you Le Diplomate Staff!!!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Delicious food. Great service.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Excellent service and excellent food. My wifes favorite restaurant in dc.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Top of the line. A premier experience in every way.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: The tomato salad was the best part of the meal. The service was great, and the drinks were amazing.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Tried the lobster risotto and it was delicious!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: This was a birthday lunch for my business partner. It took quite a while for a waiter to greet us, and did us to get water and a bread basket. When our meals arrived, one of the orders was the wrong entree. Unfortunately. This resulted in my business partner having to wait 15 minutes to receive the correct order.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Ctait phnomnal, javais le loup de mer et les profiteroles aprs, les deux sont parfait.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: We had a wonderful bday lunch with 3 of us. We sat inside due to the heat. There were clear directional markers on the floor and all staff were wearing masks properly. Menu and payment were done contactless. We had a delicious meal starting with apps including escargot, onion soup, and beef tartare followed by yummy steak frites and veal plus celebratory desserts. I felt really safe dining here too - tons of space between tables.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Food was very good, this was the best Le Dip burger I have had. French onion soup, Mac gratin, steak tartare, foie gras cream were all on point. I thought the charcuterie plate was weird and could have used some cheese.Service was a huge disappointment, waiter didn't give us a menu walk. Had to flag down for missing items and to ask to order drinks. Felt like he was doing us a favor waiting on us.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Great Experience.  Excellent food and drinks!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Very classy - the absolute BEST bread  basket  in town!  Sooo happy that Sunday night special is soft shell crab

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Greeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeat

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Excellent food and service, as always!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Food was great. We were sitting outside on 14th so very very hot, so if you would like to sit outside, make sure its not on 14th!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Great! Food,service, ambiance

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Been here many times was so excited reopened for dining and will never return absolute worst service and mediocre at best food sad to see them reopen and be shell of what they were

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: They dont have even disposable face masks for people who forgot their own - made us go buy one. For their price points thats a bit greedy.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: We were celebrating a friends last few days living in DC. Not only was the food delicious, our server went out of her way to accommodate he group. She surprised us at the end of the meal with a plate of profiteroles with Bon Voyage written in chocolate. What a great evening and nice surprise. 5 stars!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: I'm glad that I called to make sure I had a table outside - there wasn't anything noted during the reservation process - because I didn't. I had to move up my reservation by 30 minutes for an outdoor table, which was fine. The table I asked for sat with the previous diners' glasses for 15 minutes before staff cleared and disinfected it. We were not seated until 10 minutes after our reservation time. Food was delicious as always, but service was a disappointment.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Sat way in the back, not used to that, but I guess someone has too. Waitress very sweet but a bit too chatty! We wanted to talk amongst ourselves.Food is always great!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: This is hands down our favorite restaurant in the DMV. As always, the beef bourguignon was outstanding and my husband loved his steak frites. Service was excellent, with us in and out in an hour (a plus when dining outdoors in the DC summer heat and humidity). I'm sure we could easily have lingered longer, but we passed on dessert because of the heat.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Good social distancing and Covid prevention steps that I saw being taken. Had the gazpacho and warm shrimp salad, absolutely delicious. Glad Le Dip is open again, will return.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Really appreciate all the safety precautions the restaurant has taken without compromising the consistently excellent service and food/drinks were accustomed to from Le Diplomate. Our server made sure our daughters birthday was a special one. Many thanks!!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: For several years we have made this an anniversary event.  The petit tower has been the main attraction. This year that was not the case and it was disappointing.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: The atmosphere and food was fantastic - they were great about my food allergies and the service was very attentive.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: The food delivered as it always does and they took extensive steps to ensure a safe environment while maintaining the ambiance.  Some menu items ran out early but that's to be expected given the current operating constraints.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Very safe !! Tables with social distance

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Terrific food and environment.  Will visit again soon.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: The staff are easily the best in the city. The spacing of the tables felt very safe. Food was delicious as always!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: We ate outside, great weather, good social distancing.  Food was really great. We had the lump crab appetizer and the Monday special, Dorade Royals en Papillote.  Id forgot how great this restaurant is.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Excelente!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Our dining experience was very good. The waiter was very helpful in helping us to decide what to eat when we could not decide between several options. He also offered the best way to get our steak cooked.  The restaurant did have their tables set up for social distancing and every staff member was wearing a mask.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Had my bday there - the waitress was so nice and courteous. the food never disappoints

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Sadly, the once excellent seafood platter has much less seafood but the same price in post-covid reopening...

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Sunday Brunch was delicious.  Great variety of meal options.  Eggs Benedict was done to perfection.  Very pleasant atmosphere.Would highly recommend.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Simply the best restaurant in Palm Springs.
