Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Great 5-Star restaurant with a very knowledgeable, considerate and caring staff. Outstanding menu selections, many unique to southern CA.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Outstanding, one of the best in the world..

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: This is not only our favorite restaurant in Palm Springs, but anywhere.  It is expensive and a special occasion kind of place.  We make it a point to dine here whenever we visit.  Highly recommend!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Every aspect of the meal was wonderful. The patio is gorgeous and the wait staff is top of the line. The chef is as good as it gets.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: The food was sublime as always, and Marcella was a fantastic server!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: The brunch menu is terrific. Although a fixed price, including wine and champagne, they offer quite a few choices for each course. Desert was great. I am especially fond of floating islands which my grandmother used to make. I haven't found any other place that match hers. Services was outstanding.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Brunch was superb. Service first rate, correct and friendly. A pleasurable mid-day occasion.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: We typically come here on special occasions like anniversaries, birthdays, or Valentines Day. It is truly an outstanding dining experience in almost every way.  My wife always feels special when I take her here.  Sitting in the courtyard under the ficus trees and lights is classically romantic.  For food lovers, the menu is unique and diverse, youre guaranteed to find something special, quite the food adventure, and Ive never had a dish that isnt delicious.   The wait staff is very courteous, prompt, friendly, all the things you want.  I would highly recommend to anyone looking for a special night out.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Wine by glass very expensive but a great wine list

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Lovely courtyard

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Le Vallauris is probably the best 'fine dining' restaurant in Palm Springs.  I actually like having lunch there more than dinner because during the day you can see the beauty of the patio.  We got the 3 course lunch for $44.50 and it was worth every penny.  The staff is lovely and they know that to dine there is a special treat, so you are treated very well.  It is not cheap but then it wasn't made to be that way.  Truly an incredible restaurant.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Simply the best Palm Springs has to offer.  The food is spectacular and the outdoor garden area a very beautiful place.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Intimate Birthday dinner. Charming romantic interior courtyard. Old school classic style but not stuffy.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: This is an elegant old Palm Springs place, great outdoor patio eating.Lobster bisque was gorgeous. Not the cheapest place, but fantastic wine list and excellent food.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: La Vallauris does not disappoint.  As always, the entire experience was remarkable - the food, service, ambiance.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: A plus every time!!!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: This is my favorite restaurant in Palm Springs, if not anywhere.  The service is attentive without being overly pretentious.  The outdoor dining patio is lovely...almost makes you forget you're dining under the stars.  The menu is imaginative while not taking unusual flavor chances.  The pre fix menu is a bargain for what's included.  I always look forward to returning!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Our entire experience exceeded our expectations. From the friendly and fun reception to the lovely alfresco dining room the setting was superb. Our server Christine was on the finest weve encountered, she made spot on recommendations for wine pairings and was a delight to chat with.The experience was elegant without being pretentious! Loved it.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Always perfect...Perfectly cooked...perfectly served...perfectly perfect!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: It was a real treat to dine in a beautiful resturant with class and elegance!  The waiter was wonderful  and we enjoyed the evening and it is now our favorite resturant in Palm springs

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: We dine here every time we are in PS.  Beautiful patio, perfect service and wonderful food.  The Degustation menu was not only delicious, but very well paced.  Delightful dinner.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Always great food and great service. We love the beautiful patio setting.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Our favorite restaurant in the world...from start to finish, everything is superb. A beautifully paced dining experience!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Excellent food, setting, ambiance.  Worth a special occasion

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Celebrated my wifes birthday accompanied by her older sister, who was a little slow getting ready and we were going to be 15 minutes late. Called to let them know and they held our table, no problem. Service was wonderful and attentive, moving heaters to keep us comfortable. Escargot was very nice and garlicky. Wife and I had duck that was nice and crispy as advertised. Sister loved her lobster salad. Martinis were acceptably priced at $15, but the least expensive wine by the glass was $18, which I think is way too high. Thats my only complaint. Otherwise, an enjoyable meal and evening at a beautiful venue.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Charming, gracious and lovely in all catagories!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Wonderful Sunday Brunch, Would recommend going. Make sure you sit outside it is beautiful .

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Sunday brunch with lovely free flowing champagne is wonderful experience. Staff ver6 att3ntive despite busy time and sitting out amongst trees very pleasant.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: I had one bite of my entree and knew it would make me sick if I ate the whole thing, it was too greasy. I tried to send it back but the manager came out and told me that no one else had complained and they charged me full price for the disgusting dish. Never had such a rude waitstaff.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Wonderful experience as always.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: We were most disappointed with the service. Our waitress was aware that wed asked to speak to the sommelier to order a 3rd growth Bordeaux but still placed our food order   Our first course arrived before wed ordered our bottle of wine as we were waiting for the sommelier. It was unacceptable. We should have returned the food, but most importantly she should have postponed our first course. What was to be a beautiful evening became a most unpleasant evening as our first course was cooling off as we spoke to the sommelier. We were rushed which is unacceptable when you spend over $400 on an evening dinner for 2.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: From the moment we were greeted by the maitred we knew this was going to be a memorable experience. The wait staff was over-the-top attentive and the waitress engaging and knowledgeable. We have dined at Alinea, Le Bernadin and Daniel to name a few of our most remarkable experiences and this ranked with the best.While a bit more expensive than the standard Palm Springs/Palm Desert fare this was worth every penny of the additional cost. Starting with escargot and finishing with a dark chocolate torte, every dish was delicious. Dont miss this wonderful PS experience.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Great fine dining in Palm Springs. Old school classy restaurant.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Top notch all the way. Management is present at the tables and everyone is friendly and professional. We ate there two nights in a row.

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Our first night in Palm Springs and we had reservations for 6pm.  Got there and no patio seating, they put us in a walkway and we said no, they moved us inside and after 5 minutes it got hot and stuffy so we decided to leave.  The owner/Mature D came out after us and asked why we left, he offered to seat us in the patio!!!  It was a really nice experience!  The sea bass and lobster were fantastic!  We would recommend this fine dining experience!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: Delicious, great service and wonderful ambience! Well be back !

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: I took two special friends to Le Vallauris to thank them for their help. This is ALL of our favorite restaurant EVER!! We all feel very special when we dine there. Everything is first class and the staff always makes us feel special. Of course, we are!! If I could afford it, Id eat there daily! Its that good!!

Name: Le Vallauris
Comments: I always feel that I,ve spent an afternoon in the south of France when I have dined at Vallauris.Merci

Name: Linwoods
Comments: All was amazing

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Everything was great from appetizer to dessert! I look forward to going back.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Be here many times but this time was terrible. Service was very poor and food was very average.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Not impressed. Crabcake was dry and and substandard, Mahi Mahi was small little piece with what tasted like thousand island dressing poured over it.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: The best dining experience around Never disappoints!

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Annie is my favorite server in Baltimore! Linwoods is consistency excellent! The best chicken Ive ever had anywhere!

Name: Linwoods
Comments: It was my wifes birthday and we went to Linwoods  to celebrate.  From our arrival at the beginning through the end of the meal, we had an excellent dining experience.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Linwoods is consistently an outstanding restaurant in all aspects particularly the creativity and quality of the food as well as the superior service. Their staff is so well trained!  I had two soft shell crabs (whale size) sauted in a lemon butter sauce served over kernels of sweet corn and tiny tomatoes. I may not be describing the meal correctly but it was a WOW. I had decaf cappuccino and I like a dark rich roast. This was not but it did not mar the experience. Great restaurant!

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Lindwood's did a great job with outdoor social distancing, even with several bouts of rain.  Food and staff excellent as always.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Truly such a special evening. Thank you so much!

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Everything exceeded exceptions and I have come to expect only the best from this restaurant. They have done a wonderful job with the outdoor dining experience. Such a wonderful evening.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: The blueberry tart was outstanding!  The portabella mushroom pizza was pretty good as well.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Amazing food and service outside. I'm definitely going back soon.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: stopped in while  passing thru , what a great place , outstanding chef

Name: Linwoods
Comments: As always Linwoods food & service was exceptional. Because of the pandemic they have set up our door dining which was well executed & still had the same great ambiance! They added a few new item to the menu which were delicious, everyone should try the lasagna!! Our server was upbeat & kind. I always love my experience there.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Crab soup was the best start from appearance to taste!! Sea bass was delicious. We are going back as soon as possible.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: You can always count on the food at Linwood's to be perfectly prepared.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Hands down the best restaurant in the Baltimore area

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Everything great as expected by a five star restaurant. Waitress was exceptional and food was delicious.I would definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for the best there is,

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Birthday  celebration. Very nice time out ...first time since March.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Fantastic dinner. Fantastic staff. We go here allot. We would highly recommend dine here. The Sawyers

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Linwoods is always my favorite go to. I can always count on a great meal every single time I go there.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: I am a regular customer at Linwoods.  On this visit, the service was very slow.  Imagine looking at an empty plate with crossed utensils for 20 minutes before wait staff appears with the bill.  The restaurant was not super busy, but I was forgotten with beverage service, then between appetizer and main course.  I know that the wait staff can do better.  The BBQ salmon was excellent and the crab gazpacho did not disappoint.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Always good. Glad that the menu is expanding, too.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Slow service. Portions of food smallNot up to pre-COVID standards It will take time

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Excellent as always.  Outside tables were spaced apart nicely and staff was courteous with masks on at all times.  Was a little disappointed in cosmo which was way too strong and not good.  Love the way Linwoods splits entrees for people.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Food and service always outstanding. Linwoods has made outdoor dining upscale. Annie provides excellent service every time!

Name: Linwoods
Comments: The food is amazing, drinks delicious. If I have to find something negative , it would be the fact that their watermelon salad isnt on the appetizer menu at this time.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: The staff at Linwoods is phenomenal

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Amazing food and service.  Octopus app was best I ever had!  Crab cakes all lump no filler!  Great seafood tacos.  Bronzino was cooked to perfection.  Service is impeccable and not overbearing.  They are doing a great job of making you feel comfortable during the pandemic.  Everyone socially distance.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Everything was wonderful!

Name: Linwoods
Comments: We dined outside at well spaced tables. It was a pleasure to be able to eat real high quality restaurant food again. The bronzini was delicious, the atmosphere was very casual and well thought out and the service was excellent. A nice return to civilized dining.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Many years and many dinners with todays challenges Linwoods still never disappoints.  All dinners and appetizers were great, tuna tartare, sea bass with crab, Brussels Caesar, all were great.  Pro service and acceptable ambiance considering.Loved our evening at Linwoods.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: We were seated as soon as we arrived, but our server did not come to the table for 15 minutes to greet us. When she did come to the table she apologized and stated she is getting familiar with the new routine since reopening and would be right back after closing out the table next to us. She did apologize for the delay, but she walked pass our table at least two times before greeting or recognizing us. During our dinner service we asked for bread and she shared she would get it right away. Again, apologizing for not bringing it out. A few minutes later she returned without bread and informed us that they ran out of bread. Really??? People are still being seated for dinner service and you run out of bread.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Perfect as always

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Excellent food and service

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Annie is wonderfulGood deliciousPerfect

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Great food, great service, great ambiance in outside patio area. Linwood is taking all precautions to keep diners safe.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Linwoods is our favorite restaurant, has been for a long time. Never disappoints. Great food, great cocktails, and GREAT service.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Linwoods is always great!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: They didnt tell us its closed. We get e-mail the day before reservations that the dinner is confirmed. We get a Taxi from Lahaina to Paia and then we see its close.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Macadamia nut crusted fish stuffed with crab might be the best thing Ive ever eaten.  Cocktails were perfect.  Beautiful place and the view of the ocean/beach is a perfect touch.  Great ambiance.  Server was amazing.  He was very knowledgeable, friendly, helpful, and energetic.  Complimentary bread was ok, but i couldve had a gallon of the complimentary Clam-and-mushroom bisque.  Black pearl oyster dessert was beautiful and elegant, but I definitely think we probably couldve gotten a better tasting dessert based on the other options we saw.  No problem if we get to back though!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Incredible food and beautiful view!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: 4th time at Mamas Fish House and it, of course, never disappoints!!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: It was our first time at Mama's Fish house and the food was amazing and so was the ambience.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: The food and atmosphere are amazing. I had a vegetarian option that was not on the menu, it came with a banana curry sauce, which was absolutely to die for. I highly recommend going here at least once. However, the price is a very steep. Drinks are $20+ and food is $50+. I would expect to pay a premium for the quality of the food, but unfortunately the price is so high I do not see myself coming here more than one time per vacation.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: We had a wonderful experience at Mamas the day before they had to shut down.  We almost put it off a day and I am so glad we did not.  Theyre Mai Tai was the best Ive ever had.  We ordered every appetizer on the menu and they were all outstanding!  Our server was so wonderful as well as all the staff.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: A legend for dining in Maui. This place is always a treat - everything is done right. From the valet to the end of the meal - it all flows seemlessly and seemingly w/o effort! Yes it's expensive - very - but worth every penny.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: We've been to Mama's many times in the past and have never been disappointed.  Everything was exceptional, except that somehow we got missed with soup and bread appetizers, however the server apologized sincerely and sent us home with a goodie bag with bread, butter and soup.  The meals were excellent

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Food was delicious and presented well. Our waiter was wonderful as well. We were seated along the coastal view area which added to the wonderful experience. We will be back!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Wonderful day to lunch at Mama's and celebrate our granddaughter's upcoming 12th birthday while she is here on spring break from Colorado.  Attentive, thoughtful service by Will along with wonderfully flavored mahi mahi and yummy creme brle.  She felt very special and we enjoyed the moments at Mama's with her.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: This is by far the best place to eat on the island! The food is prepared beautifully and the servers are right there to help you with anything! The atmosphere is romantic and if you dont want that it still is incredible!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Awesome food and service. We always enjoy our vidd sad it.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: I sent my daughter and son-in-law to Mama's Fish House for their anniversary.  My daughter texted to say it was the best meal they had ever had and that the waitress was really great to them.  I gave the restaurant my credit card ahead of time and they did everything right, including having an anniversary card from me all typed up and ready to give them.  Really impressive as I did all of the arranging from California!  Thank you, Mama's for making their anniversary REALLY special!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Outstanding atmosphere!  Great food and history at this place. They should bring back the old menu with more fish and preparation options.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: The food was amazing!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Mamas House is a Must Do when in Maui.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Probably the best restaurant on Maui and possibly one if the best in the USA. Setting, food, service and ambiance are excellent. This is a very unique place. Just go. Make reservations.....

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: had to wait 20 min. with reservation   with plenty of open tables

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Amazing food and service!! Be sure to save room for the Black Pearl.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Worth every penny!  Coconut ice cream and coconut cake were more amazing than words could describe.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: The staff as always was exceptional and made my birthday special.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: As always - MFH was outstanding from the moment we arrived to the time we left. The ambiance is without compare - service & food more than that! Will always make MFH a must whenever on Maui!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: I have heard great things about Mamas Fish House so thought Id give it a try.  It far exceeded my expectations on every level.  Food was outstanding, drinks were quenching, service was attentive and friendly and the ambiance was what you would expect for a Hawaii atmosphere.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Horrible service from bar and hostess stand. Food and server were great though!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Not a better place to have Dinner in the world. Food is the best bar none.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Amazing restaurant. From the beach and views to the wonderful service

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Hubby and I got a beautiful scenic spot by the window in this open air waterfront restaurant. The service was amazing and the food was pretty good. Will return again.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: It was excellent in all aspects!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Everything I expected and more! Food, service, and view all top notch.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Mamas was great as usual. The setting is gorgeous and the food excellent.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Excellent selection of fresh fish. Beautiful restaurant, attentive staff.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Absolutely our number one favorite restaurant. Best Hawaiian setting, atmosphere ,on Maui..Everything is excellent.Dave Baker the day manager is perfect....

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: great food and atmosphere.  second time eating there and was great both times.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: ALWAYS a great experience!  This time was no exception. Gluten Free options great as well!  My compliments to all.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Always a must destination for us when we visit Maui and never ever disappoints.    Service is great.   Food is spectacular.  But the ambiance is like now other.   Its like a movie set its so amazing

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Our server Mike was awesome, the food delicious and the ambiance spectacular. Would definitely recommend Mamas!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Wonderful experience! The food is truly the best on Maui. We visited for our honeymoon and they staff made us feel so special and cared for!

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: I'd highly recommend Mama's fish House to any visitors to Maui. The service was unreal and the staff made sure every aspect of our dining experience was perfect.

Name: Mama's Fish House
Comments: Wonderdul location!  Great food!  Fabulous service!  Felt a bit gouged by the prices.  $20.00 for a glass of fairly inexpensive wine

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Wonderful food and service, they always deliver!

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Everything about MF is amazing. The food. Wait staff. Ambiance. I cant say enough about it.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: The food was excellent especially the Halibut en Croute, which was exceptional! I really wanted to try the very popular Chili Lobster with Texas Toast too, but my friend couldn't have lobster . Next time for sure! Our server was the best as well. She went above and beyond to hook us up with little "extras" during the course of our meal, which made the experience that more wonderful. I look forward to my next dining experience at Marc Forgione.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Outstanding as always!

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Service very poorHalf way thru wsiter just started ignoring usOrdered coffe capucino etcIt never came but was on the checkBig let down from prior visits

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: I have enjoyed several birthday dinners since the restaurant first opened in 2008 (I think), and as of Tuesday night the quality of the cuisine, service, and experience has not been diminished in any way.  That almost never happens in NYC!  Thank you for another delicious and fun evening.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Great upscale-casual atmosphere, amazing food, and the staff went above and beyond to help us celebrate.We had the halibut and the black cod, and I couldn't imagine how to improve either dish.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Above and beyond anything that could have been expected. After visiting Peasant, and meeting and talking with Chef Forgione (and being absolutely blown away by the food) only a week ago for my first dating anniversary with my boyfriend, I decided to take him here for his birthday. We were treated like royalty from the second we walked in, and the food matched the service. We ordered the chicories salad to start. It may sound/seem simple, but that was one of the best salads weve ever had. We were also given the Hiramasa tartare dish, which my boyfriend declared the best tartare dish hes ever had. I had the half chicken (cooked under a brick), and he had the halibut - both outrageous. We had the carrot cake for dessert, but we were also given what the waiter called, The Egg. He basically told us to move back in our seats a bit as he proceeded to toss a white chocolate egg filled with passion fruit into a plate ... it was as hysterical as it was delicious, and my boyfriend does not like passion fruit. There are no words that can properly describe this experience. From the card my boyfriend received when he sat down wishing him a happy birthday from the restaurant to the desserts to the sparkling wine to the everything bagel amuse bouche to the amazing atmosphere, this was a one of a kind experience. Simply outrageous, and we will be back.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Amazing as always!

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Bad service and the food is over priced for what it is .

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Incredible food from start to finish !

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: This is a superb restaurant.    The chicken is spectacular!

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Good place for a business meal. A bit overpriced.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Outstanding!!!

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Always terrific !

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Great food, service.  Expensive but worth it

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: This place never disappoints. The food and wine were perfect.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Consistently some of the best food  and service in NYC. One of our favorite restaurants to go to for special occasions.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Good was excellent and so was the service. Server was very knowledgeable and offered great advice about certain dishes. A little pricey but worth it for a special date night/occasion

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: For my first NYC dinner I was blown away! Will definitely revisit

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Great service and food. Restaurant is extremely loud with no sound dampers. Go early for the food and miss the noise volume.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Love this restaurant Wonderful staff Great food

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Absolutely amazing service and delicious food!

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Terrific all-around dinner.  Love the chicken for two, as well as a pear desert.  Service was attentive and efficient.  However, some of the appetizer portions were a bit small.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: We LOVE this place, and dine at least once a week here.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Every year we sneak down to this beautiful and cozy space eagerly awaiting the Singapore Chili Lobster, Halibut with Sauce Proposal and the brick chicken.   Loved the Laotian sushi during our last visit.  So thoughtfully prepared and lovingly executed each and every time.   One of our very favorite beacons for a perfect meal.   When we havent made it down to NYC in a while, our home bar can always pour the iconic banana Jameson, yet that always seems to make me ready to plan our next visit.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Ive wanted to go to this restaurant for years. I went for my birthday and it did not disappoint. Highly recommend!

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Working in NYC for a month, I decided to have my own restaurant tour mostly chefs that Ive seen on the Food Network. Its also my birthday month, so I am going all out! I am thrilled this was one of my top picks! Everything is amazing! The staff, ambiance, food, little treats between courses, everything! I tried food I do not typically like venison. Being from Louisiana, someone is always cooking venison, and is not something I like. However, it was recommended by my waitress that it was her favorite. I figured if anyone was going to change my mind about venison, this maybe the only hope. Oh my, it was delicious! I cant believe how much h I enjoyed it! My friend had the steak. We would giggle every few bites because the food made us that happy! Thanks for an amazing experience!

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Exquisite from start to finish. Exceptional service. Delicious and creative food.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Food is very good. Trout was perfectly grilled with Chanterelles and gnocchi with butter and sage. Ive dined here several times and will come again.The servers are efficient and discreet.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: We had an excellent experience; great food and service.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Servizio eccellente ma cibo davvero nella media, mi aspettavo molto molto di pi nella qualit.Prezzi esorbitanti, dolce buonissimo.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: This is a perfect spot for Christmas Eve dinner with close friends and family. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, the food superb. Our waiter was well informed and efficient. There was one thing that really had a decidedly negative impact on our experience: the presence of a waiters helper who paced back and forth constantly during our entire stay. I could feel eyes upon me as if watching every bite. When I put my fork down I was instantly approached Are you finished? Im just sorry I did not ask the waiter to have this person removed. I understand the need to turn the tables on a busy night like Christmas Eve but must say that I will think twice before returning and, if I return, I would request to be left alone by the waiters helper.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Not impressed at all were waiting to eat here for months and when I did I only liked dessert and I couldnt believe that theres such a hype over this place. Ive been eating everywhere from NYC to Miami Michelin started restaurants and mom and pop shops this was not good. I would not go back many other awesome places to eat right around the corner.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: My favourite restaurant in all of New York City - never disappointed and I make sure I go every time I visit

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Fabulous experience from start to end.Knowledgeable professional staffIntriguing / manageable cocktail menu and wine selection.Amuse established the mood for a creative competent kitchen.Shishito peppers simply salted and grilled ...Chicken under a brick - crisp skin floated over succulent half a chicken served 2 with sizzling halved potatoes.Two chocolate chip cookies did not benefit from the purposely melted ice-cream ...certainly abortion meant for sharing ... but why.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Great food, excellent service! The tasting menu was very good.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: I Love this place. The ambiance is amazing, food is great, drinks were phenomenal service impeccable. One of our favorite NY restaurants.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Our second visit here was a bit of a disappointment.  The place was very full and very loud.  The menu is quite limited, which we knew, but the starters and appetizers did not have much appeal, and the peppers were considerably more spicy than described by our waiter.  Many people, ourselves included, seemed to be there for the chicken for two.  It was fine, but roast chicken can accumulate a bit too much pan juice, which makes it seem greasy and less appetizing, which is what we experienced this time.

Name: Marc Forgione
Comments: Our fabulous server, Lise made the whole evening extremely enjoyable!  Food was amazing and we loved Marcs signature perfect bite on a spoon!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: A classic dining experience, starting with delicious drinks at the bar and an excellent jazz pianist. The Tasting menu offerings are exciting and choices are flexible. Excellent spot for a special occasion.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: My husband and I had dinner at Marcels before attending a performance at the Kennedy Center. We opted for the theater menu. It was one of the nicest meals we have had in DC in a while. The service was impeccable  they even provided a selection of reading glasses so my husband could read the menu. Service was attentive without being intrusive or rushed. Service was great, and not just by DC standards. The food was excellent, as well. They even have a complementary car service to the Kennedy Center. I would definitely go back again, and we will certainly make this our go to dinner spot before heading the KC.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Fabulous as always!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: It was such a pleasure to go to a restaurant where you are taken care of so completely. The QUIET dining room allows for normal and even whispered conversation. The wait staff are extremely professional remembering everything youve order and examining every plate prior to serving your dinner for quality control. I can not recommend Marcels too highly.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Our entire evening could not have gone better.  They were out of our selected caviar, so they upgraded us at no charge.  The scallop starter and the squab were outstanding.  The staff was impeccable, warm, knowledgeable, just the right amount of presence.  The decor sumptuous and restrained.I know we will return again and again.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Terrific meal.  Each dish was special. with a unique blend.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: the restaurant met our expectations in terms of food that was delicious, elegance and  courtesy of the staff

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We had a fabulous evening at Marcel's. The service from the front of the house was perfectly balanced between attentiveness and discretion. The food was beautifully prepared and presented and delicious in every way. Marcel's is elegant and we enjoyed the evening very much. What is Musak everywhere else is a the gentle jazz piano in the bar at Marcel's. The perfect atmosphere for a special evening. Recommended.Two items that detracted somewhat, but never interfered. There appeared to be some tension between the wait staff and the support staff - maybe just the usual search for perfection but we overheard more than one impatient comment. Second, for a prix fixe menu offering we were surprised there was no option for wine pairings and when we asked if one could be provided received a frustrated response that sure, we could do that if you wanted. That said, the pairing were from the wine-by-the-glass menu and were splendid!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Always an exceptional experience. We had the 4-course menu option and sat at the bar before our show at the Kennedy Center. We loved all our dishes - I had the black cod, salmon, and lobster timbale. The poached pear dessert was delightful. Highly recommend!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Lovely dinner, we were well taken care of, and the food was outstanding.  We'll be back!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We had a great experience. And they offer a car service to the Kennedy Center, which was an added bonus.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This was our second time; it won't be our last. Jonathan is the epitome of five-star service, perfectly paired with Chef Robert's exquisitely delicious and beautifully presented dishes. The dining room is an oasis of peace away from the noise of this area. Gentle jazz and live piano play softly. Sight, sound, smell, taste, texture - Marcel's perfectly attends to every sense. There is a reason Marcel's is in Tom Sietsema's Hall of Fame for DC dining. We look forward to our next experience at Marcel's.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Another enchanting evening at Marcels - a wonderful dinner with great service.  The creativity never stops.  There is always something new to try.  And Marcels will always accommodate food allergies without compromising quality.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This was our second time here, and it was equally good. It is a new favorite for special occasion/Kennedy Center evening dining. What a nice dinner out should be.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Great food and amazing service.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Great for special events.  We celebrated our 28th wedding anniversary and our son's acceptance into the MD and DC Bars.  We chose the 5 course tasting menu.  Everything was perfect.   Great job by Vinny and Staff.  Kudos!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Soup to nuts, outstanding in every way -- perfect service; beautifully plated; lovely wines; and correct portions for me!  We loved the food, the service, particularly our waiter, and the seamless experience of dining, having Real French Food, with nouvelle twists, and the car service to and from the Kennedy Center is a terrific perk!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Always fabulous.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Food and service were impeccable. The three course pre theatre menu is full of great choices and a good value. The chicken in tarragon buerre blanc was amazing.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Vinny is a fantastic server. Highly recommend

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: One of the best restaurants in Washington DC now and form many years. Great food, quiet lovely ambience and attentive and pleasant service.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Phenomenal food, great service and nice ambiance. Good wine list but overpriced. Easily 4x market prices.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Meet an old classmate you haven't seen in years

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We had an excellent time - food, presentation, service, atmosphere all exceeded expectations.  It was one of the few top-notch restaurants where you can have a decent conversation.  Yes, you pay for that privilege (tables aren't crammed together) but it was surprisingly reasonable given the quality of the experience.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We are coming back within two weeks of our first visit. It is rare to have a nice place live up to expectations, but Marcel's did. My husband said this was his favorite meal since we went to French Laundry, and that was about a year-and-half ago of regular restaurant going (West Coast and DC).  We go out to eat a fair amount in all price ranges and in this range, once expects more than just good food. We got great food and great service executed by professionals, not just folks who want to wait tables for a couple years before they move on to their "real job". And, yes, it is not a bargain dining hall, but we felt it was a good value for the quality, portions,  presentation, and vibe (great jazz pianist in the lounge, complimentary swank ride to the Kennedy Center for show). Plus, the wines by the glass were priced very accessibly and tasted like much more expensive price points. If you appreciate a more traditional fine dining experience with professional, adult staff and are tired of dropping a couple of bills only to see everyone around you dressed like slobs, make your next date at Marcel's.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Excellent special occasion location. Great food and service.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We have been dining here for 5 years. Always had a great meal.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: I took my wife for our 29th anniversary and I wasnt sure what i was get into.But then. The show stared. Amazing food. The unique taste of each plate, was unreal. Henry the waiter. 5 stars. And then i had the honor to meet David. Not just an amazing chef. A true gentleman. I dont know when i will go back. But for sure i will

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Food was delicious and service, exceptional.  We were within hearing distance of the pianist in the bar; loved that!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We have been to the fine dining room a number of times and love it.  We were eager to try the Bar special menu.  Our reaction was that the food was fabulous.  However the amount was  on the small side and the wine pairing was minuscule.  There was no dessert included.  We were sort of in and out in a short time.  Generous on the bread service.We would not go back for the bar experience but would go back to the fine dining room.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This wasn't just dinner out--this was a dining experience. Go when you can take your time and enjoy being pampered by the service, wowed by the presentation and flavors and relaxed by the elegant ambiance.  It'll be the  kind of evening that you'll talk about for a long time.  I can't imagine rushing through dinner here to get to the theater but I guess people do. I didn't want to leave. The food was amazing. There used to be a Washington Post food critic, Donald Dressden (goes way back) I think his name was--when he went to a great restaurant he said the "food sang" yep, the food sings here, like Pavarotti on a plate, or something.  You have to go, save up your birthday, anniversary, special occasion or just 'cause you deserve it and spend it here.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This restaurant is without doubt one of the top in the DC area if not the country. My only regret is that I did not try it earlier. The staff - from the owner to the waiters to all who assisted us - were kind, punctual, caring, and welcoming. The chef and cooking staff really know what they are doing and the food is sourced fresh and of highest quality. We ordered from a tasting menu from which one could choose four, five, or six dishes. We chose four, which was more than adequate. Among the three of us we had salad, fish including shellfish, venison, pasta, and several desserts, inter alia. The vegetables were fresh and the cooking afforded succulent, wonderful tasting options. The wine selections ranged from reasonable to pricy, and we were able to get a bottle of a recommended red wine by the glass that was excellent, from a vineyard and vintage that we knew. Expect to pay twice what you would a most high end restaurants but the result will be more than twice as good. I was reminded of an Inn in the countryside in Virginia that has great food, but Marcel's is  better and less expensive. We'll definitely be back!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: A perfect evening from the impeccable service to the menu choices to the presentation and taste of each course.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Wonderful complete dinner- all aspects were first rate - Vinny took exceptional time care of my wife and I

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This is a wonderful French restaurant with smart service, a creative and skilled chef and a lovely wine list. Each dish has deep roots in traditional French haute cuisine that have been married expertly to our time. It is the perfect place for a special occasion.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Highly recommended.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Marcel's has always been one of the best dining experiences for us. We were there for our Anniversary last weekend. We told our waiter/host Mark that we wanted a picture with Chef Wiedemier for our Anniversary and he came through for us. Mark took great care of us ... very professional, attentive, good natured. Like talking to a friend. Mark loves his job and it shows. We especially enjoyed the Foie Gras, lobster appetizer, sea bass, but everything was a foodie treat. Ambiance is classy and even though restaurant was almost full, it was not noisy and you could enjoy having a nice conversation in a soft voice (a rarity nowadays in restaurants).

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: The service was top notch, which you would expect for a restaurant of this caliber.  The presentation of the food was wonderful and the flavors were distinct and exceptional. The tasting menu was right-sized and  perfect for the amount of courses chose. (Four).  The wine pairings were well thought out.  Overall a wonderful experience.  A call out to our head waiter Adam.  Spot on service.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: One of the top French restaurants in Washington.  A traditional, delicious menu--no foam-filled balloons.   Just great food beautifully prepared and served.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Impeccable service and a wonderful wine list. The best parts of the menu are the starters ( scallops, boudin Blanc consomm) but the duck entre was average.This restaurant is heart attack expensive and I would have expected better.

Name: Marea
Comments: Great all around!

Name: Marea
Comments: I wish I could give it 6 stars. This place is a gem.Food and service are outstanding. Excellent wine list.

Name: Marea
Comments: We had a fantastic evening. Staff were gracious, professional and attentive. Dishes were excellent. Looking forward to returning soon.

Name: Marea
Comments: Fabulous gluten free pasta   I loved the truffle and anchovy sauce. Perfection.

Name: Marea
Comments: As always amazing!

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea is an elegant restaurant from the decor to the food to the service. Great attention is paid to every detail to make the experience luxurious and special. We were there for a birthday lunch starting with excellent cocktail and wine (dont miss the delicious bread as its brought around) into appetizers of a variety of crudi (thinly sliced raw fish) and entrees of halibut and steak. We ordered sorbet for dessert then were pleasantly surprised with a special birthday dessert plus cookies and small tiramisu portions. All were excellent and beautiful. Adding to the overall atmosphere is the elegant china, cutlery, glassware and serving pieces. Dining here made it an occasion.

Name: Marea
Comments: Always perfect! Best place in New York

Name: Marea
Comments: My husband and I enjoyed an amazing dinner at Marae last Sunday. We treated ourselves to the five course tasting menu with the wine pairing. Everything was delicious, especially the halibut and the Tagliatelle with a sauce made from bone marrow. The chocolate dessert balls were also scrumptious.  Each wine paired nicely with its dish. The service was exceptional. We shall definitely return and hope the Tagliatelle is on the menu that night.

Name: Marea
Comments: It was perfect and my 2-yr old daughter really enjoyed the food as well as the setup.  Really appreciated it.

Name: Marea
Comments: The atmosphere and the wait staff are absolutely stupendous! The food however, ranges from good to very good. Nothing reached a level of excellence. At these astronomical prizes, I would expect to be blown away by every morsel.Certain dishes were cooked perfectly and we're quite tasty, however others seem to be overcooked. (Not a good thing with seafood.) Parts of the grilled octopus we're just downright dry tough. Regarding the Brodetto, The broth, while absolutely delicious, was served warm to start with and cooled to room temperature by the end of the dish.If you are looking for calm, culture, civility, this place is it. If, however, you were looking simply for amazing food, you may find yourself a little disappointed. Overall, a lovely dining experience with a phenomenal wait staff, but I just wish the food had lived up to the rest of the experience.

Name: Marea
Comments: 3rd visit and every meal outstanding! Pointless to explain just to! Not stuffy like most restaurants of this caliber

Name: Marea
Comments: Great place for lunch!  Great menu and beautiful space!

Name: Marea
Comments: Excellent food, service and ambiance.  Going back very soon.

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea keeps getting better and better.  The setting and the service are magnificent, and the food is extraordinary, every time.  The service is so smooth and predictable that it is an easy choice for pre-theater dining, even with 4 courses.

Name: Marea
Comments: The Branzino was awesome. Great ambience. Beautiful room. Definitely would go again.

Name: Marea
Comments: First time on a Tuesday evening and did not disappoint - love this place!

Name: Marea
Comments: Enjoyed another wonderful lunch. Tuna crudo, octopus starters very nice. Sent back a bottle of wine and got replacement equal value - no problem. Mains of scallops and striped bass very tasty. Special thanks to somm! Can't wait to be back.

Name: Marea
Comments: Extraordinary combination of atmosphere , service, and culinary delights.

Name: Marea
Comments: Consistently delicious!  Always great service!  My most favorite place to eat!!

Name: Marea
Comments: Wonderful service, atmosphere and food.  My favorite NYC spot!

Name: Marea
Comments: Very attractive, sleek and comfortable dining rooms.  Warm welcome, excellent service.  Very extensive wine list with a good selection of under-$100 bottles. Prix Fixe lunch @ $67 or will offer a la carte.  Very good tuna crudo, tatare.  Very good pastas ( garganelli, Agnolotti).  Attentive service. Quite expensive for lunch.

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea always is outstanding  wonderful good quality and service.   It is expensive, however.

Name: Marea
Comments: Everything was delicious.

Name: Marea
Comments: I was celebrating my kids first trip in New York and after two days of cramming tourist attractions and activities all day we needed to unwind and relax while enjoying a delicious meal that warmed the heart... though its a fancy restaurant and very upscale I can say my kids and my husband and I enjoyed the best spaghetti with butter we had in our lives... the rest of the more intricate food items like the lobster risotto the steak the halibut the burrata lobster were divine. Definitly if your kids are not too loud ( my son Definitly was so i gave him my phone to keep entertained) its a definit must go restaurant for food, comfort, and that finesse touche.

Name: Marea
Comments: Terrific food and great service

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea has exceptional food, wine & service - always a perfect experience!

Name: Marea
Comments: The food was wonderful and the atmosphere was perfect for indulging

Name: Marea
Comments: it was a really great experience for a special occasion.

Name: Marea
Comments: We went to this fabulous restaurant over the holidays, had a delicious dinner and could not wait to return when back in a Manhattan from South Carolina.  This time I booked an afternoon Valentine meal as we had concert plans for the evening.  We chose the five course tasting menu and had one of the best experiences ever!  We thoroughly enjoyed each dish, mostly consisting of exquisite seafood and specialty pasta, paired with some fabulous wines.  My partner stayed with the white wine accompaniments while I enjoyed the lighter reds that were selected.  Service was outstanding, and there was still an air of romance at the corner booth despite it being 230 in the afternoon!  Marea will be on our calendar every time we visit the Big Apple!

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea made my husband's birthday very special, giving us a wonderful seat and bringing a festive dessert, on top of the amazing food!

Name: Marea
Comments: Valentines

Name: Marea
Comments: The food was superior.  The service was superior.  The staff was efficient and appropriately friendly.  The best meal during our trip to NYC.

Name: Marea
Comments: Perfect spot for our birthday celebration!!!

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea never disappoints, it was amazing as always. Michael provided excellent service.

Name: Marea
Comments: We go every year for dinner on our anniversary and few times during the rest of the year for a special occasion. Never fails to exceed our expectations!! We love this restaurant!!!

Name: Marea
Comments: It's one of our favorite places in New York. Food ,Service, location, ambiance is always excellent

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea Continue to provide a restaurant with pleasant ambience relaxing atmosphere excellent cuisine and attentive but obsequious service.

Name: Marea
Comments: The food is outstanding at this restaurant.  The service is top notch also

Name: Marea
Comments: One of the top restaurants in the city.  My wife and I were saying afterward that it was literally one of the best meals we have ever had.  Amazing restaurant start to finish.

Name: Marea
Comments: Food was amazing. Servers changed often and didnt inform us. Nobody offered another glass of wine until ours had been empty for over ten minutes. Seemed like our table was forgettable. Probably wont return.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Always an amazing meal at Market! We go every time we are in San Diego. Its worth the ride!!!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Very innovating dishes with great taste. You won't get bored here. There is something for everybody and all dishes are expertly prepared. Great wine list and exceptional service. Well run machine

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Food was outstanding maybe as good as I have every had and that includes the French Laundry.  Service was not as good as the food a little slow.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Service was a bit slower than previous visits and entres took longer than expected (based on experience at Market) to come out of the kitchen. Food was, as always, excellent. My wife's gluten allergy was forgotten (waiter asked when we arrived as they always do) when the restaurant brought out a cake based desert to celebrate our aniversary - somebody  dropped the ball.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: One of the best meals Ive had. Creative dishes. Friendly attentive wait staff.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We went to Market to celebrate my wife's birthday. Market is one of our favorite restaurants. The food is always great. The decor of the restaurant is lacking (needs a refresh) but the food is amazing. We both did the tasting menu and I have to tell you it ranks up there with the few times I've eaten at Addison. Since the portions are bigger at Market I would say it was my best dining experience in the 5 years we have lived in San Diego. We will certainly visit again but really wish they gave the place a face lift.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Great meal.  Food was excellent.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: The unpleasant part of this evening for me was that the A/C was blowing directly on my shoulders all evening long and there was no way of getting away from it. And believe me I always love A/C everywhere I go.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: The complimentary valet is a confusing concept... you still want to tip the valet, but who carries cash these days? So just be prepared to bring cash so you can tip the valet.Hostess was not warm, as a hostess should be. However, the waiters were exceptional! Thank you. Very friendly. I dont think management should require them to memorize specials of the day, as it comes across very rehearsed, awkward, and off-putting. Save them the embarrassing stress & just write it on a simple menu card. I love a dark, cozy ambiance & this place is that exactly. The food was good but I noticed on the tasting menu the same base sauces and ingredients were repeated a few times. If you dont like salmon, dont order the trout... it tastes identical. The Cabernet braised short rib was insanely delicious. I was accidentally given a restaurant week menu & the manager was kind enough to honor the discounted prices on the menu I was presented with. Thank you. Very generous gesture.Some of the side panel wood near my table was very dusty (attention to cleanliness details always appreciated), and there were a few annoying gnats buzzing around that I had to keep swatting away & this interfered with my relaxed dining mood.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Always an amazing experience eating at Market. Food is truly awesome!!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Just outstanding. The food is the best in town.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Market is in my top two restaurants in San Diego! Always delicious, service is great, a fabulous experience. My only wish is that some of the tables were a little bit further apart so we don't hear every word of the conversation next to us. Of course, this will not keep us from returning again and again for Chef Schroeder's amazing cuisine!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We are never disappointed. The food is amazing matched only by the service.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Food was salty. Our main dish came late.  I will not come back again. It's our 2nd time here.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: PROBABLY THE BEST RESTAURANT WE HAVE VISITED IN SAN DIEGO...AND WE HAVE VISITED QUITE A FEW.  FOOD WAS JUST OUTSTANDING!  WOULD LIKE IT EVEN BETTER IF IT WAS A BIT LESS EXPENSIVE.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: I really think the food is way too salty. Too saucy, drenched in sauce, to be honest.If you claim to use great ingredients, let the flavor shine through.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: This is one the few restaurants in San Diego that we go to if we want a special treat.  We partook of the SD Restaurant Week menu and it was outstanding, beautifully plated and wonderful flavors.  No skimping on quality.  The waiter was respectful and knowledgeable.  Highly recommend.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We were impressed by the way you creat each dish- subtle but colorful balance of the well chosen ingredients! Particularly blue cheese souffl. Only one disappointment was the beef for the main- it was a little too salty and was the sauce, too. Other than that all great and we will come back in future.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: ber Jahre hinweg konsistent bestes Restaurant in San Diego. Wir wurden noch nie enttuscht. Immer innovativ, wunderbare Zutaten und wunderbaren Kreationen. Service regelmig ausgezeichnet. Groes Restaurant mit vielen Gsten und trotzdem logistisch perfekt organisiert.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Dinner for 4 during restaurant week.  Arrived a bit early waited at the bar and were seated promptly at the reservation time.  The dining room is set up nicely and (kudos) for once no stupid tables.  The place was busy but the noise level moderate!!  Food overall was excellent - an interesting take on a tuna tartar,  excellent corn soup with smoked port.  Entres were trout, duck and beef tenderloin - all very well prepared - portions very adequate.  Desserts yummy.  Attentive, efficient and polite service!!!!Bar selection OK - not really great and along with the wine list insanely overpriced.  A clear indication that they are catering to the Rancho Santa Fe crowd. In all a very enjoyable evening and will visit again when in the area

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We really enjoyed the food and the service was excellent. We will return for next restaurant week.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Ate off the restaurant menu with wine pairing.  Great food, and our waiter was outstanding.  Expensive, but still great value.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Always love Market and this was no exception. Delicious.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Amazing food and service, as always at this gem of a restaurant!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Have eaten here many times... thought the food was heavy on the salt as did everyone else.  Two meals were fish, two were beef.  This has never occurred before.  We were disappointed as the the food has always been perfectly seasoned...the desserts and wine pairings were wonderful.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Our favorite restaurant in San Diego! The food was and is always amazing. Service is top notch!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Loved the atmosphere , food, service. Theyre truly professional . Enough waiters so you dont feel left out. My favorite

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Simple put, there is no other restaurant like Market. The food is always delicious and unique. Its our favorite place to dine.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Restaurant week and date night. All was amazing but the tenderloin was too salty. The wine pairing was great. The green apple sorbet and berry dessert were amazing. The pear salad was to die for!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We dined during Restaurant Week and had a great experience.  Nice selection of starters, entrees and deserts.  Our waiter was terrific.  The wine pairings were not quite as well paired as in the past, but were still interesting.  Of course, we'll keep coming back to this marvelous restaurant.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Perfect and delicious

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Birthday - was wonderful!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Best restaurant in the San Diego area. The freshest ingredients, exquisite on the palate, awesome wines.....Market has it all!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Went to the Market for my wifes birthday - overall an enjoyable evening.  We started with the corn soup (great) and burrata cheese & peach salad (good) - we then shared the forest mushroom ravioli (good but incredibly rich & salty) and the grilled beef tenderloin/lobster combo - the tenderloin was again much too salty.  Both my wife and I left with a lingering salty aftertaste and told the waiter as much.  The waiter was very attentive & we appreciated the birthday dessert - just cut back on the copious amounts of salt.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Great staff and food!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: great neighborhood favorite. we order the market salad (off the menu).the fig salad was very good.duck special was excellent.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Good service and staffs, Amazing cuisine!

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We had a delicious meal.  Party of four and we each ordered a different app and entree so that we could try a variety of menu items.  Everything was wonderful. Best meal weve had in a long time.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Food here is ALWAYS amazing!!!We did not love our server this visit though... she was below par the others we have had in past visits.We will absolutely return... just hope to have a different server thats a true representation of this fine dining establishment.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: My favorite restaurant..Recommend it to all my friends

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Best frites, best John Dory, best margarita, best service and best management team. Best, perfect.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Outdoor dining is terrific!!!!!!  Raoul & Henri continue to do everything just right. Even in these crazy Covid days. J Dory fish dinner is so, so good and the best margaritas in town. Consistently the best meal in town.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: We went during the COVID lockdown. They set up tables out front on the sidewalk. It was our anniversary and they treated us special. Great food and service.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Very COVID Friendly !  Outdoor tables... Well Spaced... VERY CLEAN... Food was A.M.A.Z.I.N.G. !! ... Had Gazpacho, Escargot, & Duck Confit.Can't say enough good things about Mistral.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: We had a beautiful evening at mistral on the back outdoor patio.   Well spaced and everyone from the diners to the waitstaff were all friendly and wonderful. I had the onion soup, lamb chops with haricots vert, and the chocolate souffl  My husband had a lovely salad and duck confit. It could not have been a nicer outing!!!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Simply amazing!!!! Ill leave it a that... lamb chops, duck and so many others. All 5 star.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Our first restaurant visit since the shutdown in March-we were thrilled to be there and see Raoul and team and cant wait to go again!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Always a great place to dine.We always leave there feeling grand.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: The food is always delicious!!!  The tuna tartare and the lamb chops are outstanding!!!  It is also so nice to always be greeted by Raul he is the best!!!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: The restaurant was amazing per usual! The staff was wonderful and the food was excellent. The steak tartar is to die for and the the chocolate souffl is the best souffl Ive ever had!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: This restaurant took huge precautions during COVID-19 by ensuring lots of space between tables and the staff completely covered in protective gear. The food is always excellent and we very much appreciated their efforts.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: This was our first dine out since being quarantined for Covid. Such a great experience. Missed it so much!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Great food, great service.Observing all the necessary precautions.You can dine here with complete confidence.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Very good experience overall. The service was great in spite of the social distancing requirements, the food was outstanding for every one of the four people in the party. Would highly recommend this establishment

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: As always, it was such a great experience.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Food is always excellent and love the flour less chocolate cake

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Limited menu upon just opening up but most favorites there, including tuna tartare

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Always a pleasure to dine at Mistral! Soooo glad they're open again!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: I like the French atmosphere. The food is good.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: First let me start by saying its my wifes favorite restaurant. She was so excited for our sat evening reservation, being that its so hard to get in there. service was slow and we had an issue with both lamb chops and steak. Came out in a pool of oil. Was really bad. They did take it right back and off the the check as they should off but nothing else was done and I ended up paying 120$ for soup salad and bottle of wine. Very disappointed. Evening was ruined. Hope they can make up for it

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Food was astounding. Warm goat cheese salad, beautiful fish, juicy pork tenderloin. Great wine. It was a delightful dining experience.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: We love Mistral!!   All our special occasions are celebrated there!!!  Staff and food over the top!!!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Best restaurant in L.A.  Very romantic. Outstanding food and service. A neighborhood gem.  Highly recommended.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: waiters are most attentive and made our evening dining experience very comfortable.  food was delicious.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Best tuna tartar ever, especially with special of added lump meat crab. Bronzino with crust skin delicious. John Dory great too.  Terrific french fries  with their mustard and not ketchup.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: We went for a birthday celebration and had a wonderful experience.I had already had lunch here and enjoyed it but this was my first time dining.The food is exquisite, the staff attentive and knowledgeable. We had a fantastic time and will be repeat customers.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Great as always!  Our neighborhood favorite.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Always feels like being on vacation in a French cafe! Warm and welcoming owner & staff and food never dissapoints

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Friends birthday dinner

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: We have been there before and had an amazing dinner, however....This night, everything just seemed off! The food was mediocre, the menu was different and the noise level was so loud we couldn't hear ourselves talk when this was supposed to be a romantic dinner.  For the price, I would have expected much more. We were very disappointed

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: All around excellent!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Always a treat.   I've never been disappointed with dining here.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Mistral is the best! Everything about this restaurant is first class!Always coming back.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Great service, awesome food. Will definitely return!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Always a special treat going to Mistral's the food and service are ALWAYS

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: I have loved Mistral since it opened. I go back 30+ years. I had my 40th birthday dinner and countless others there. Unfortunately, the expense has made it a special occasion place for me now. Even still, on those occasions, I always enjoy being there. The food, its quality, the service and decor all make Mistral one of the best restaurants to which I have been. I recommend it without hesitation.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: From the service to the food, excellent..I had the lamb chops which were delicious.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Too too loud and table too close.  Not for the price.  Food was delicious and good service.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: My favorite place to go! Henri and Raul (and entire staff) are amazing! Food is delicious!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Great cooking, top-notch ingredients, attentive, fast and helpful service, very friendly staff. Excellent bar and ample and expertly selected wine list.  Street and valet parking.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Dinner was fabulous. I can't wait to go back! Of note was our wonderful waitress. Thoughtful, knowledgeable and just lovely.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The food was a bit too salty. However the presentation of the food, room ambience and service was excellent.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Lovely menu, well-executed dishes.  Interesting wine list and excellent service.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: One of the best Michelin starred restaurants in NYC with zero stuffiness. Incredible value. I am going as much as I can. Need I say more?

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great little hideaway bar with interesting history at Grand Central Terminal.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: my favorite restaurant in NYC these days. go go go go

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: We always love coming here. The atmosphere manages to be intimate and buzzy at the same time. The service/food/wine is impeccable. Since it is a no-tipping restaurant, the price point ends up being well below other restaurants that aren't even on its level. Definitely recommend!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: While the food was very good, the service was NOT attentive (unless you were the wealthy couple sitting near us who had chefs come out from the kitchen to fawn on them).  We had to ASK our waiter for a refill of our water glasses and then nobody actually did it until we finally stopped a suit clad higher functionary who actually did the work himself.  Staff training is needed (as is an attitude adjustment).

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: While waitstaff is polite and knowledgeable, they were slow during a midday rush.  Perhaps too few people for the guest load.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The food and the service was outstanding!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: After so many years, the Modern has maintained its high standard with food, service and ambience! Its a reliable place to go back to!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The atmosphere, the service, and the food make this our favorite place to eat in New York.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great casual place. The food is creative and delicious, the service was great.I highly recommend it.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: I have dined at the Modern Bar room dozens of time-never had a bad meal-you can't go wrong if you decide to eat there and it is also very popular for just drinks.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great food

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Everything was great. The setting, the food and the wait staff. We had a lovely evening. Will definitely visit again

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great as always!!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: With the MOMA renovations causing closure of the art museum temporarily, we had to skip our annual visit. However, the Bar at the Modern was available so we were able to enjoy a marvellous Saturday lunch.  Service was skilled and our waiter was very well informed on the options and preparation details. Every course of our three course meal was amazing in taste and presentation.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: I cannot believe the huge disappointment I experienced at The Bar at the Modern, which has been one of my favorite spots in NYC since it opened...we even celebrated there the day of the birth of our first grandson eleven and a half years ago...and I always want friends visiting us in NYC to meet us at The Bar at the Modern.I brought a friend who had never been to the restaurant for lunch, specifically to try the tart d'alsace.This was a new food for her...when this rectangle that looked like a slice of pizza arrived I was shocked.That is not a tart d'alsace,  I thot...it had a lot of red and green in it...not the creamy white I was accustomed to...and the taste was unidentifiable...my friend said all she could taste was salt.  I did not complain...at least I thot the tart was edible, but could not explain the taste.My baby gem lettuce salad was ok,  but not as lovely as I expiated, to the eye and the tongue.My friend was aghast that the soup of the day cost 24 dollars, but she ordered it as she was not very hungry (we lunched early...ll:45 )...I was so devastated that I considered, and still am ,  writing directly to Danny Meyer.  He would be horrified had he been at our table yesterday Aug 30. I will not be returning to The Modern, unless an explanation is given.  I can get a beautiful tart d'alsace at BENOIT, as I did on Aug l9...the size of the tart was generous and share - able with 5 other people at my table for drinks and small plates...the size of the MODERN's tart was not even enough for two.Ah well..in the big picture of life I can handle such a disappointment.  But this indeed feels like a loss of one of my favorite places in NYC.Patricia Lahrmer Ross on Aug 3l 20l9

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great service, fantastic food, highly recommend

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great dinner!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The overall experience was top notch.  This proved to be a perfect choice for the night.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The food and service at the Modern Bar Room were excellent.  I was also struck by the quality and presentation temperature of the wines by the glass.  Many restaurants in nyc serve very poor wines by the glass kept at the wrong temperature.  This was not at all the case at the Modern - the wine was excellent.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The food is so high quality and the tastes explode in the dish. The crispy salmon was tremendous.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: We had an amazing meal here, and it really made me want to experience the main dining room someday. My spouse and I each ordered the three course tasting menu, choosing an appetizer, entree, and dessert. I had the wine pairings as well, while he ordered a Manhattan.  Every single thing I ate was perfect. My very favorite was the charred avocado with peekytoe crab. The flavors and textures of that dish will stay with me for a long time to come. I cannot recommend it highly enough. My spouse started with the corn soup, which I had almost ordered. It was very tasty, but nowhere near as good as the avocado. The service was very attentive, with our water frequently refilled and being checked in with regularly. The time between courses might have felt long if you were in a hurry or very hungry, but for us it was the perfect pacing. The room definitely has a lively atmosphere, which is nice, though the tables are quite close and it was hard to tune out the conversation at the table next to us.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The bartenders were very attentive and demonstrated great mixology Skills as well as menu knowledge.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Caesar was just an amazing service provider - his suggestions were spot on and so was the service provided by every other member  at this restaurant, thank you for making a huge difference in the way you treat your guests.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Food was terrific.  Staff was very accommodating.  However the room smelled of fresh paint.  That is very unappetizing.  Perhaps the restaurant should close on days when it is freshly painted.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: As always a most pleasurable dining experience. The wine list is extraordinary as are the prices with only a handful below triple digits.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Fabulous restaurant week menu ...we both had the salmon that was cooked to perfection. Service was excellent...waiter/waitresses friendly and professional..

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The ambiance, door and service were spot on. The announcement of each dish was over the top and unnecessary, particularly when some of the dishes were repetitive from one diner to the next. It seemed silly and disingenuous. $18 for a glass of white wine had us passing on spirits at lunch. It would have been nice for the iced tea drinker and the coffee drinkers to be offered seconds for the price of $7.00 for an iced tea and $6.00 for a cup of Joe. Its the little things...

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
