Comments: Perfection!  Fabulous food, great service, lovely ambience.  Can't wait to go back :)

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Was visiting this place twice during a restaurant week.  Amazing a nd delicious food, great service!!! Thank you!!!!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Fantastic! Wait staff excellent. Picked two course restaurant menu for lunch. Amazing salmon and cavatelli dishes. Cocktails sublime. Also, the modern is a no tip establishment but you wod never know it, the service was impeccable.  Only negative was we had planned on going next door to MOMA but its closed until mid October.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: We really like and enjoyed the service and the food! We go to upscale restaurants sometimes. This one is at the top of the list of the restaurants we went in terms of the food taste. Highly recommend.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Service was very nice and sweet. Food is of great quality and value. Went there for the restaurant week but will certainly go back again.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: This was a terrific evening made all the better by the attentiveness of Maitre d' Michele Molier.  I had managed to put our reservation on the calendar for the incorrect date.  We showed  up a day early and could not have returned on the next night.  Michele  led us to the bar and then went to work finding us an  table.  Shortly we were escorted to an ideal table for memorable dinner.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Disappointing from start to finish. We have come to value the Modern on our A List of fine cuisine. We selected the Restaurant Week offerings. Servers lacked adequate knowledge of the vintages. Short pours dominated. The Main course was bland and tasteless. Two slices of bread were an additional charge. Rather insulting. Wine pairings were delayed with food arrival. The meal was rushed although there was ample seating. Our servers were not attentive. The only redeeming part was the support table staff. The Modern has been always exceptional. Unfortunately this experience falls into the ONE STAR category ... at best.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Wonderful time. Everything is perfect from start to finish.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Exquisite!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Outstanding food and service.  If you like tasting menus it doesn't get much better.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Absolutely fantastic. Food and staff were both amazing.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: What a great experience. Nice staff, amazing food, and a good wine pairing.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Absolutely amazing experience. Highly recommend it if youre looking for a treat. The atmosphere is lovely.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: The entire experience from start to finish was excellent. We were there celebrating a special event, the staff made special arrangements for us and brought in some items from outside vendors for us. Food and service was top notch, chefs were engaging energetic, friendly and professional. I cannot emphasize enough how on top of their game this group, both front of house and chefs are. Actually what comes to mind when thinking about our experience is how impressed we were with the entire team. Tasting menu was off the charts as were the drink pairings. We are not from the New York region so do not know when we will be back, however the evening is one that we will always remember. A special thanks to the entire crew for a magical evening!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Great food, great service. Highly recommend doing the wine pairing. A great night :)

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Excellent all around. It deserves the 2 Michelin stars that it has.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: The entrance was hard to find, but located in an alley. Astoundingly delicious meal. Service was top notch. We would gladly return.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Goes without saying. This place is among the most amazing tables in the world. Eating at Ko is equivalent to receive a doctor's prescription, have a major update about taste and receive a masterclass about service, all in the same time.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Super!!!!Ich liebe es!!!!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Amazing food and amazing service, what more could you ask for?!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Wonderful food paired with excellent wine.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: The most memorable tasting menu experience! Excellent food, non-pretentious and focused on intense flavours. Loved the relaxed setting and impeccable service. #PartyInMyMouth

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: We had a fantastic dinner. The flavor combinations were innovative and incredible. The service was wonderful. Not only were they attentive, but they engaged with our questions and made us feel like they cared what we thought. We also went to Le Bernardin and Eleven Madison Park on this trip and Ko was our favorite of the three.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Everything was wonderful.Food and wine pairings were excellent.My only gripe was the lack of detailed explanations on one or two courses of the tasting menu. But at that point, I'm just splitting hairs.Overall, I had a fantastic experience.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: One of the greatest eating experiences I have ever had. I am a loyal listener and follower of David Chang and this was my very first time to experience one of his restaurants.My sister took me for my 60th birthday. I truly was not ready for such a great experience . The staff was so engaging and connected with my sister and me beyond anything I had ever experienced before in a restaurant. I tell everyone that I would not order anything we had on a menu , but everything was delicious and so much part of the experience.  We had listened to the pod cast that day about Ko and we had so many questions (need to meet Sean and Sue) . The person who worked with us truly connected and kept adding to our experience.  We asked about the Japanese Cheese Cake mentioned in the pod . She told us she could not get it for us - They it appeared with a candle in it. You should know that we posted on Face book and you are going to get a lot of new people . If its David Chang we are in

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Momofuku Ko was an incredible experience.  We got to sample things we most likely never would have eaten if it wasn't for this night.  Service is exemplary, and the food is Incredible.  We also enjoyed the Alcohol Pairing.  Be prepared for an expensive night out, but one you will never forget.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Great food  and pairing

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Everything was perfect from start to finish.   Loved the playlist

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: I had a great time with my girlfriend celebrating Valentines Day week.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Food was okay. Wine was great. Service was good. We went for the tasting menu and it went on for 3 hours through no fault of our own, and they asked to move us for the next people. That was absolutely wild to me. Not worth the $1,000 we paid.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Impeccable food and service! Well worth the splurge for a special occasion. We look forward to returning for our next anniversary, and will be visiting the bar in the meantime!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Loved it!  All of the good things about a pretentious tasting menu (impeccable service, delicious food made with great ingredients) with none of the pretense. It was casual, fun, and laid-back but definitely still something special. Highly recommend!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: They were trying to do sushi and wagyu yakiniku, but when it's so easy to find authentic Japanese restaurants in NYC with chefs from Japan with years of experience, I felt like their attempts were not quite successful. Given that the majority of their courses were very much focused around the Japanese cuisine, I would probably just go to a Japanese restaurant.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Great ambiance. Nice to sit at the counter and watch the meals' preparation. Very interesting creations/compositions, most of the 12 dishes are a success  (sea urchin and chickpea puree, what?!) and only a couple of "disappointments" (seabass only "so so" / "whatever" ...). Enjoyed drinking sake too. No surprise with the bill with the unique menu (and service is included)

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Semplicemente tutto TOP...Grazie ragazzi di tutto.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: A wonderful experience - a combination of creativity, great service and a comfortable ambience.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: such thoughtful and imaginative food in a welcoming ambiance. I go once a year, but was greeted as a regular, my champagne choice was remembered, had enjoyable, non fake chats with chefs and the manager. Such fun to watch the chefs and wait each surprise. Nearly always perfect balance of tastes and texture. Umami often, acid balance, little spikes of salt. My favorite NYC meal!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: The 4 hour lunch was a fabulous gastronomic adventure - priced a bit higher than where I think it  should be, but still quite an experience!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: An exceptional dining experience. Got to try foods and wines that I'd never have had access to otherwise. The preparation and experience were elegant but didn't alienate me as the guest. A must-do for anyone that takes food seriously.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: One of the best meals Ive ever had. Granted I dont eat like this often, but if I had the money Id do it again. It was a once in a lifetime opportunity for me and Id do it again, in an instant.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: David Chang does not cook here. Its the farm team - everyone is working hard and professionally - and seems about 23 years old.Specified a pescatarian menu in response to managements solicitation some days in advance.  At the resto a chef asked What do you think of duck?  I think duck is not a fish.The place is maybe fine for tourists but not for NYC locals looking to be wowed.  It delivers neither the wizardry of an Alinea nor the solid reliability of a Le Bernardin.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Amazing. If youre thinking about going - dont hesitate just do it

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Very personable and knowledgeable staff! The tasting menu is an intricate blend of flavors, decadence, and most importantly texture. A must visit!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: One of my best dining experiences! Thank You so much to the team at Momofuku KO for making me fool so at home and looked after me sooo well! I HIGHLY recommend a meal here!!!! The Rice Cream should be permanently on the menu... just saying!!!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: This was one of the best meals I have ever eaten!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Unbelievable experience. Amazing food and attentive and warm service. The people there are the best!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Amazing meal every time. Must do "wine" pairings, which includes other drinks besides wines. Sit at the counter. Cooking can be a spectator sport.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Absolutely wonderful experience throughout.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Yule present to each other.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: As always it was perfect !

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Family man.  Brought wife and two teenage daughters

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Food quality is outstanding and service impeccable.  Always a fun and tasty take on dessert.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Wonderful birthday dinner - the spacing made us very comfortable and the food was as awesome as ever!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Our first date night in Dallas since COVID and couldn't have had a more enjoyable experience!!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: This is one of our favorites  in Dallas! Always consistent and delicious

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: excellent food & even better service!  entire staff was friendly & energetic.  food was delicious as always.  music is too loud in my opinion, but i'm noise sensitive.  very safe & clean & covid aware.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Excellent food. Very safe. Everything is very spaced out and clean.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: We loved our evening at NHS! From the green chili crab dip to the halibut special to my husband's cheeseburger, every single food item we ordered was delicious. Service was great, pacing of food was appropriate, and it wasn't too loud. The only fault we found was no highchair for my 7 month old niece.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: It was a birthday celebration and they said  happy birthday! Thought they should have brought out a dessert....

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Marques was the best, total professional and so personable. Food was fantastic. Thanks.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Always the safest place and best of food, service and drinks!!!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Great job with socially distancing and masked staff.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Our server was fantastic!  Wish our table wasn't right in front of the kitchen though.  We had a great time and the food was amazing.Looking forward to our next visit.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Fabulous as always, from the ambience and service to the food. My favorite!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Best food! Best service!!  Love this restaurant!!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Everything was outstanding. The service & food were fantastic

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Excellent service and amazing food!!  The staff made us feel very comfortable. We cant wait to go back!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Been eating here for years and EVERYTHING is delicious!  I always go for the fish special because its always fantastic.  Hubby loves the Fish & Chips.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: First time back since the re-opening and it was very good. Staff and service was excellent, they followed safe distance and hygiene protocol as required.  All the food was terrific, one exception being the pasta special, which had overcooked sauce with a burned bottom of the pan taste to it and the noodles were undercooked-to the point of being a bit stiff. Overall very pleased that one of our favorite places is open and will only get better!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: We were there to celebrate my husbands 35th birthday. Everything was spot on, from the service to the food to the drinks. We really appreciated how seriously they took social distancing and Covid precautions. Will definitely be back again soon! Have already recommended to my friends who are leery about going out to restaurants right now.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Favorite place in Dallas!!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: We had an amazing night here this week! Cant wait to go all the time now !

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Food was delicious as always, and wonderful service.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Fun atmosphere, great service, and outstanding food.  Will definitely make this one a regular stop.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Knocked it out of the park in the new norm with safe environment, service and best food in the city-dare I say world right now!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Always a favorite!  Food and Service was outstanding!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: When we arrived they were closed yet we had a confirmed reservation. Its a great place. We will try again.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: It was closed when we arrived. weve eaten here many times and it is Excellent!  But so disappointed to arrive to a locked door and no notice.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Last time we were at NHS prior to the stay at home order and it was as good as it always is. I miss it so much! GM Julia is always so helpful and accommodating with my dairy allergy and we had Marcus as our waiter who kills it every time. My boyfriend and I cannot wait until our next visit! Miss you guys so much.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: As always, the best place in Dallas!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: The schnitzel, fried chicken and fish were all delicious. Good drinks too.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: A wonderful dining experience each and every time! Make sure you book your reservation early as this hot commodity books up! Though you can always eat at the bar where Rob and Alex will take excellent care of you!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Great vibe and great food.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Food and waiter were very good.  Felt rushed as the restaurant became busier and they wanted to turn the tables.  It is really the only negative I would say about the restaurant.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: The hostess Emily makes every visit special! We will be back soon!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: A wonderful dining experience!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Always great food, service and ambiance.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Same as usual - excellent.Waiter was outstanding and had everything covered without being intrusive.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: We were celebrating our friends recent engagement (havent seen them since) and we chose NHS to treat them as a surprise. Id put in the comments of the reservation we were hoping for a nice table or booth to celebrate this night out. Instead, we were placed right in front of the noisy, highly trafficked kitchen. We felt that the service was rushed the entire time, from when we first sat down and were asked if we want to put in an order for food before our drink orders were taken to when our water glasses were stripped from the table. Also, we had very little time to enjoy our cocktails before being rushed to order a bottle of wine with our dinner. Overall, the food was very good, but when we chose to pay a premium and spend our money on a special occasion I would expect better service and treatment.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: We have tried various "high-end" restaurants in Cincinnati, but none compare to the  Plam Court at the Netherland.  From the elegant environment, personable and knowledgeable wait-staff, to the unparalleled cuisine, one is never disappointed!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Wonderful dining experience. From the moment we arrived we were treated as special guests. The food, service and ambiance was all excellent. The room is one of a kind and sets the stage for a wonderful evening. One of Cincinnatis very best restaurants.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The service was attentive without being overbearing.   The restaurant is beautiful with a feeling of elegance.   The food was superb.  Overall a very memorable dining experience.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: It was our 25th wedding anniversary and we had a lovely time! The hostess, bread server, and our server, Chris, all wished us happy anniversary, as well as as a card from the restaurant! The food was fun and delicious!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: We've had lunch buffets (Easter, Mothers' Day, etc. at Orchids. They were all very good. Our first opportunity to dine at Orchids was a real experience. Comparing Orchids to the old Maisonette, Boca and Restaurant L (the three legitimate 5-star restaurants we've been to) is a real challenge. Orchids' service staff was above outstanding. Quiet and efficient, the table was cleaned and readied for the next course. The food was wondrous. The seared foie gras, Spanish mackerel, made us want more. The first plates are intentionally small and left us wanting more. Our Monkfish was superbly prepared and surrounded by great food. The chocolate dessert was a wonder. We can't say enough positive about Orchids/ We can also mention that the price was relatively low. Orchids is an unqualified winner.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Service was excellent! Enjoyed our first and second courses immensely, especially bleu cheese beignets and Spanish mackerel. However, we had the monkfish and ribeye entrees and felt that both were lacking and not impressive. Monkfish was dry and seemed overcooked, bouillabaisse was one note and didnt hit the mark for us. Ribeye was cooked perfectly and had beautiful presentation, but the flavor was not great, Ive had much better steaks at chain restaurants.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The Orchids is in a spectacular setting in the historic Netherlands Hotel in downtown Cincinnati. The setting is idea for a relaxing, romantic dinner, or intimate small gathering. Tables are elegant and widely spaced, so very conducive to conversation. No other ambient noise or music. The service is highly attentive and the pacing of the meal was spot on. It was fascinating to watch the choreography of the staff (and the service is clearly choreographed). The staff was friendly, but with a degree of professional aloofness given the more formal dining setting. The prices are expensive although not out of range for the setting. However, the food itself, while well prepared and presented, did not have the distinctive, memorable taste that would befit the prices. I had the ribeye which was well prepared and tasty, but not distinctive. My wife had the flounder which was disappointing in the portion size, taste and accompaniments. We opted to not have dessert, but the restaurant provided some petit fors which were the highlight of the meal. Overall, this is a wonderful place to make an impression and to enjoy a leisurely meal, but is very expensive for the quality and quantity of food. We would recommend, but with caveats.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Morgan, Tate and Oscar are wonderful and made our night fabulous.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The food was good, but bland.  The short ribs had a musty smell initially.   The risotto had good flavor except for the celery root.   The blue cheese salad was good.  Service was impressive and everything came out hot.  The restaurant itself is amazing and the Jazz band was a very nice touch.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Wonderful dinner with a friend in town for a visit.  Tate was amazing as our server, food and drinks were great, everyone we encountered went above and beyond, and it was a special time.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Incredible food and service.  Can see how they recently received the highest rating.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Chris and his team provided wonderful service!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Absolutely amazing food and service. Staff was knowledgeable and very friendly. I am pescatarian, no meat, and they catered to my diet and gave me a delicious chefs tasting that I will never forget. If youre thinking about going, just go. You wont regret it.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Great experience.  The food was excellent and complex, but delicious.  My wife and I each ordered four courses, which over the period of 2 hours was just the right amount of food. Service was excellent, and although the menu might be considered haute cuisine, our waiter made us feel very comfortable and at ease.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The food, service and ambiance are consistently superb.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Wish the meal had been better. Service and ambiance awesome.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: I have consistently had excellent meals here, both at dinner and brunch.  This was an exception.  Service was lackluster, and the food was inconsistently good.  I knew we were in trouble when the bread arrived and was stale.  Overall, this experience did not match the price level.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Fantastic food, service, and hospitality in a beautiful environment.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: This is our 2nd time coming here for a special occasion and it was fabulous, just like the first time. The food is exquisite and the service and ambiance couldn't be better!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: This is a great restaurant for a special  occasion or just a very good dinner.  The presentation is especially good and the service is excellent.  I highly recommend Orchids.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Food was quite good.  The bouillabaisse was insultingly modest (filled with potatoes and little seafood [no monkfish as advertised].  For $48, you HAVE to do better!Service was very spotty.  Busing of the table barely occurred.  For a five star restaurant?Seemed like there was no one managing or guiding a VERY young staff.  Simply not impressive.Go to Restaurant L or Jeff Ruby to see how fine dining is done.Music was fantastic.  Ambience?  Fantastic.  Good waiter that had little support.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Everything was great!!  The food was perfection and service wonderful!!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Food and service were outstandingin every way, but the noise from the nearby bar was a little high for our taste. When dining at a restaurant of the quality and price point, a quieter atmosphere would be appreciated.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: This has become an annual tradition for my wife's birthday.  Each year we continue to be impressed with the knowledge and attentiveness of the wait staff.  The food is always excellent and the ambiance unmatched.  Many thanks to Orchids for a memorable night on a special occasion!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: This was my second time dining at Orchids at Palm Court.  The first time I dined here was last year and it was fantastic.  This year was a different story.  To start off, it should be noted that this is a relatively expensive restaurant and therefore comes with certain expectations beyond food, service and ambiance being two of them.  We were seated by a very friendly, knowledgeable, and professional greeter, Morgan.  Our server, Oscar, was also very professional.  However, it took 40 minutes from the time we were seated to meet Oscar.  He was extremely busy and for a Saturday night Orchids was poorly staffed--labor cuts?  In any event, we were looking forward to the actual meal.  My wife ordered the blue cheese beignet salad, popcorn grits, and scallops.  I ordered the beef cheek perogies, maitake/cappelletti, and lamb.  My wife's salad was very overdressed and almost seemed as if there was too much salad dressing on it, then the chefs decided to pour olive oil on it--what a disappointment.  The popcorn grits, on the other hand, were flavorful and delicious and I would definitely recommend this unique and tasty dish!  And my wife's third course of scallops were cooked perfectly.  My order was a different story.  First, my perogies had absolutely no flavor whatsoever-no salt, pepper, herb, or sauce-and therefore was unsurprisingly very bland.  The maitake and cappelletti were terrific and cooked perfectly, and the sauce was a perfect pairing (you should order this).  But sadly, my entre was lackluster.  The lamb was almost rare and had, once again, no flavor.  The entre did come with two bites of lamb sausage and creamy polenta, but the what should have been the star of the plate, the protein, disappointed in flavor and the way it was cooked.Along with service being painfully slow, the staff always seemed rushed and in a hurry to leave the table.  The staff was so hurried that for our second course they gave my wife and me the wrong second course.  Loud patrons.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: A fantastic all-around dining experience once again. The consistency of excellence with food, service, and ambiance is truly amazing and makes Orchids a must-do for any special occasion, celebration, love of life, or a memorable date with your loved one(s). The beauty of the art-deco hotel, restaurant, and bar in general...along with the spectacular ceiling, walls, lobby, and furnishings... make this a world-class venue and a fine-dining opportunity you do not want to miss.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The food, ambience, details, and service at Orchids made the experience very special.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Beautiful surroundings in an old art-deco environment. Good food, not great food a bit disappointing considering the price. Very, very slow service. We were there for 3  1/2 hrs for dinner.   Its nice to make an evening out of a nice dinner but this was just too long.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Everything was handled with great aplomb and the effort to create a very pleasant occasion! Obviously, the staff wanted my wife and I to celebrate our wedding anniversary in exemplary fashion, and succeeded.  The only drawback was the telephone call to our residence to confirm our coming.  I always try to surprise my wife on such occasions, but she answered the phone.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: We hadnt dined at Orchids for many years and decided to go back this past Friday night. We were greeted promptly and noticed a lively happy hour going on at the bar. We were seated promptly at a nice intimate quiet table for 2. Service was flawless except a slight delay getting cream and sweetener for our coffee and tea. An apology was issued and offer to pay for our hot drinks which was very nice. Our food was delicious and well paced with chef surprises to taste along the way. The drinks were tasty and popcorn grits delicious as were our scallops and short ribs. We shared a chocolate dessert and enjoyed the sweet surprises at the end. All in all a lovely experience. Well go back soon!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: I literally couldnt wait to review this restaurant- and I NEVER leave reviews.  Unbelievable execution in service.  The food was great but the beef cheek pierogi was by far my favorite thing.  Tate, Chris and Morgan made the experience that much better as I enjoyed chatting with them.  Cant wait to come back!!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Great aesthetic but the menu was disappointing compared to the level of restaurant it is. For Cincinnati its towards the top of the pile but if youre coming from a larger city with more like options this place falls a little short.  Service was fantastic but the food needs a bit of a refresh and the pricing isnt appropriate for what you got (a bit high for the area and quality). Overall would say give it a shot but coming from Chicago with such a rich food scene this place fell flat

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The food was heavenly as was the overall experience. The entire staff goes above and beyond to ensure your experience is great. They even called the valet to make sure our car was there waiting for us.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The service and experience at Orchid were outstanding. The food was delicious but comparable to other upscale restaurants in town.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: We went for a romantic Christmas dinner, service was lovely and the food was interesting.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: My wife and I celebrated our wedding anniversary at Orchids and had the best dining experience ever! The service was wonderful from the valet parking to the wait staff. We felt well treated. Our waiter Chris was perfect, informative, attentive but not intrusive.  The ambiance is legendary in its beauty. The jazz music provided was very enjoyable.  The food was delicious (we had the scallops as our entree) and beautifully presented. The whole experience was  classic fine dining.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Tate was amazing!!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Outstanding food & service

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: We have dined here several times before and it has always been a memorable experience.Not so much this time. Service was outstanding but the food was mediocre for some and uninspired for others.  Not one, in our party of five, said their meal was great. I might try it again but with reservations.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: We had a wonderful dinner to celebrate the Christmas Season. All of the food was delicious and the service was impeccable

Name: Oriole
Comments: We absolutely loved Oriole! The food was so tasty & the staff was very welcoming and accommodating. Ask ahead a few days for the vegetarian menu, you won't be disjointed!

Name: Oriole
Comments: I dined at Oriole in 2016 - the year they opened - with a friend. We knew then that they'd receive a Michelin star. Surprise, they have 2! Anyway, I finally returned a few nights ago to celebrate getting married. I did a pescetarian menu, though I am aware that the Wagyu dish is life-altering. Everything about the journey is perfect - from when you arrive, to the recommendations, to the food itself. We thank the staff of Oriole for a memorable evening. And also a huge thank you to the wonderful table next to us, who we found had left the best gift ever, when the bill arrived! Still a top 5 dining experience.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Food was 9.5+.  A bit small on portion but really exceptional Wine paring was a 10Service was a 10It was our first time. Really great for a special occasion.

Name: Oriole
Comments: As good an experience as we have had in any restaurant, in any city, in any country

Name: Oriole
Comments: Great inventive menu and wonderful service. Good for small numbers and foodies. Menu and wine is expensive, but on par for their status.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Outstanding as always.  Cannot wait to return and see what magic Chef Noah and Team can create.

Name: Oriole
Comments: The most unique Restaurant I have lately been!!!Intriguing entrance, ambiance- on point, team- is TEAM :) Menu :) OMG admired every course like exhibit  in art museum at first and only then turned into Ratatouille to indulge the unique combination of flavors and imagination!thank you for being there and don't ever loose your imagination and passion!!!Will return!!!

Name: Oriole
Comments: Had a fabulous experience.  Loved almost everything that we ate.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Simply amazing way to celebrate a 20 year wedding anniversary.  We were taken on an effortless food journey paired with amazing wines.

Name: Oriole
Comments: A truly beautiful culinary experience!  The staff was passionate and knowledge, and they welcomed our questions.  The food was by far the highest quality and best prepared we've ever had, and the beverage pairings were perfect.  Thanks to everyone at Oriole for an unforgettable evening!

Name: Oriole
Comments: I had never experienced better service than we received at Oriole.  Will definitely return. Everyone was amazing from Marylin to the entire staff. At times it almost seemed that I was watching an amazingly choreographed ballet. Extraordinary experience far beyond what was expected even for a Michelin Star restaurant

Name: Oriole
Comments: The best meal of my life! Also the best service! Highly recommended. Plus its byob ;)

Name: Oriole
Comments: Oriole is a very special place and a wonderful way to celebrate a special occasion.  The food presentation could be in the art Institute.  Thank you for the great experience.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Amazing!  Some of the best food Ive ever eaten. And tremendous service!!  Perfect night.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Absolutely SUPERB.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Perhaps the best meal I have ever eaten

Name: Oriole
Comments: Great place for a night out with someone that is extremely special to you!!

Name: Oriole
Comments: Wonderful experience. We celebrated our anniversary with our son.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Very expensive but very delicious. A wonderful birthday night dining experience.

Name: Oriole
Comments: The most amazing and delicious dining experience. Their food is art and carefully crafted to bring flavors and textures together for the perfect bites. The service and stellar and you feel welcomed from the moment you walk into their cool, low key side alley. It almost feels like a secret club. Worth it!

Name: Oriole
Comments: The best meal in Chicago and the US! Worth every penny

Name: Oriole
Comments: It was a singular dining experience. Easily the best meal of my life. The service showed minute attention to detail. Each course was well timed and a perfect amount to enjoy. Thank you so much for a memorable evening.

Name: Oriole
Comments: The food was delicious. The customer service was outstanding. I would definitely recommended. Parking was easy to find also.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Wonderful. Everything was delicious! The only negative thing worth mentioning is that they priced the vegetarian tasting menu at the same rate as the omnivore tasting which I feel isnt comparable cost wise. The vegetarian tasting menu should be less expensive. As an example, during one of the courses my husband had A5 wagyu steak and I had a beet...not nearly the same price, yet paid the same? Other than that, the ambiance was lovely and the staff was very friendly and attentive.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Outstanding service, delicious food, beautiful presentation. Absolutely worth the money!

Name: Oriole
Comments: Oriole is one of the top restaurants in my mind. We spended a wonderful Valentine's Day here. Excellent food and drinks. I highly recommend to have the non-alcoholic beverage pairing, which are perfectly matching with the food. I will definitely visit there again in the future.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Sper recomendable. Todo riqusimo y la atencin excelente. Volveremos a nuestra siguiente visita a Chicago sin duda

Name: Oriole
Comments: Without a doubt the most expensive meal I've ever had...but the waitstaff was something to behold and the foold was sublime. Worth the splurge.

Name: Oriole
Comments: The food is really good as I expected. The dish with foie gras is fantastic and delicious. Great environment with professional and friendly service!

Name: Oriole
Comments: Very attentive service and nice ambiance. There were surprises with every course.

Name: Oriole
Comments: This was my 17th time there, so Im running out of ways to say how fabulous Oriole is (and I like to think I have an expansive vocabulary).  Incredible, as always.  Cannot wait to return.

Name: Oriole
Comments: The best service I have ever had at a restaurant. It was an amazing experience.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Food is so bad as a Michelin 2 stars

Name: Oriole
Comments: Wow, wow,wow !!!! From beginning till the end everything was delicious, rick in flavor. Service wow, cocktails wow, atmosphere wow!!! Highly recommend!!! Words can not describe, you have to taste it, hear the story of each dish and feel its deep flavors of very interesting ingredients.Its  12 dishes course and Hope in future they will have options to choose menu with extra courses 14 or 16 dishes.Art of food experience was amazing , looking forward to eat there again soon!!!! Very soon!!!!!! Especially when they adding new dishes and changing menu seasonly,cant  wait to try new stuff there !!!!!

Name: Oriole
Comments: Amazing food and service. Had the reserve wine pairing which was delightful.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Extraordinarily good food, genuinely nice and engaging staff, wine pairing spot on.  Will return.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Impeccable and exquisite. An absolute delight. Chef Sandoval and his wife Cara have created magic. Cant wait to visit again soon!

Name: Oriole
Comments: This was simply one of the best meals I have ever enjoyed, and I select that verb since in high end restaurants, quality doesn't always come with such enjoyment. The amount of food and wine was just right; we had eaten enough and were not drunk, even with the wine pairing (standard). It is impossible to say any dish was inferior to any other; all seemed perfect (and were presented on beautiful dishes too). The service was attentive but not intrusive. The space was elegant and comfortable and we scarcely noticed anyone else. Oriole equals Alinea in quality but is a very different experience, not theatrical, not startling, but full of pleasing surprises. I hope to find an excuse (and the means) to return  we're truly fortunate to have such a restaurant in Chicago.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Incredible food and outstanding service. Pricey but its worth it for a special occasion.

Name: Oriole
Comments: Excellent food and service!

Name: Parc
Comments: The wait staff, the ambience, and the food are always outstanding!

Name: Parc
Comments: In the times of COVID-19 it is hard to expect a similar level of quality and service from restaurants, but Parc did just that.  Even though all seating is outdoors and distanced, even on a 90+degree day, they did their absolute best to keep diners happy and comfortable. The service at Parc is always excellent, and our server, Darwin, was no exception. This was my first time dining out since COVID-19 hit, and I felt secure in the measures taken by Parc to keep their employees and patrons safe. Additionally, the food was absolutely delicious, the Frose was exactly what we needed for a hot summer brunch, and the staff even saved a baby quail that was found wandering the street outside! If you're considering going to Parc during this odd times but are worried about safety, I think you will feel comfortable with the safety measures being taken. Temp screens were done at the door when checking in, masks and gloves are worn at all times by staff, guests wear masks to and from their tables, all surfaces were wiped down and cleaned thoroughly between seatings... I would happily return here anytime!

Name: Parc
Comments: Outside dining was great and socially distant.  The salmon was delicious and I ate a LOT of their bread.

Name: Parc
Comments: Im really impressed with Parcs efforts for safety and social distancing during this time. And the food and drink was excellent, as always.

Name: Parc
Comments: Wonderful outdoor experience, even with the rain!  Parc is still pumping out amazing food, service on point and tables 6 feet apart.  Thank you for making me feel comfortable enough to come out and dine with you all!

Name: Parc
Comments: Perfection-  as always

Name: Parc
Comments: Always Great & Never Disappoints!!!

Name: Parc
Comments: Since we have to dine outdoors, it would be more comfortable if they-along with other restaurants-to have any type of air conditioning setup.

Name: Parc
Comments: Good restaurant. Overpriced food. Burger was good though.

Name: Parc
Comments: Dinner menu was limited. No Duck Confit or Lamb, which is why my party went to Parc in the first place. Server seemed disappointed that my party was seated at his table, until he realized the bill was going to be large. Once I asked for the bill, it took 15mins and me asking twice for the server to bring it over. The food was great. Back of the house and the hosts get 5 stars. The server gets 3. Overall, 4 stars.

Name: Parc
Comments: Great food!! Great service! Great outdoor dining!!!!

Name: Parc
Comments: Edwin was a great server; prompt & professional service. The food was great! I had the tuna carpaccio which I found to be light and so so good . My fianc enjoyed the chicken club. He said the chicken was very flavorful. Parc is a beautiful setting & we had a great lunch to get our visit in Philadelphia started .

Name: Parc
Comments: I ordered the gazpacho soup. It was average and very overpriced for a very small portion. My friend ordered the chicken club, it had been sitting because the bread was discovered to be soggy on the bottom, so only one half was eaten, and the rest was not taken home. I love parc - Ive been going there for years, I know Covid has had a deleterious effect on restaurants in Philadelphia, however, The cost Of the food for what is delivered is not what I can continue to endure.

Name: Parc
Comments: Had the tomato Basil salad with mozzarella and the Basil cocktail. Both amazing and refreshing. Perfect for a hot summer day. The serving staff were attentive and kind. Would definitely recommend.

Name: Parc
Comments: This is a great restaurant, but you can't fully appreciate it when you have to eat on the sidewalk.  The food is excellent.  The service is good, but they have to hustle you out of there quickly  (90 minutes).  If you're doing a major business transaction,  it's difficult because you have to rush it a bit.

Name: Parc
Comments: Fantastic as always! Thanks for the macaroons as a treat to our graduation. You guys are the best!

Name: Parc
Comments: We were there this past Sunday for brunch. Our waitress and the other support staff were so great despite the fact that it was about 100 degrees outside and all the tables were occupied. The restaurant seems to be doing a very good job of implementing social distancing while still providing a great experience.

Name: Parc
Comments: The staff was in a hurry to turn the table, and it was rude to do so while enjoying our food, a bottle of wine and an otherwise pleasant evening.

Name: Parc
Comments: The food and service was great.

Name: Parc
Comments: We loved it. Food was amazingly delicious. Service was excellent.

Name: Parc
Comments: Everything was wonderful from our drinks to our service.

Name: Parc
Comments: Zach was the best server we've had in a long time.  Courteous, fun, friendly.  Wonderful!

Name: Parc
Comments: Our server, Zach, provided us with literally the best service I have ever received dining out before! He made us feel very welcome, knew the menu and preparation of the food to a T, made recommendations for us and how we were going to go about our meal, and was just overall so fun and kind. Seriously, he was the best!!!

Name: Parc
Comments: Great experience Little disappointed they currently do not have cheese boards

Name: Parc
Comments: We ordered the escargot, which was excellent, for an appetizer. For dinner, we got the shrimp salad. The salad was fresh and the amount of shrimp was good but I didn't love the dressing. My boyfriend got the steak frites and thought it was amazing. The only downside was sitting outside because we were in direct sunlight, which got very hot. Otherwise, the service and food was very good.

Name: Parc
Comments: Great service even better food and wine

Name: Parc
Comments: great spot...looking forward to them opening the doors... street is getting old now.

Name: Parc
Comments: We enjoyed our experience at Parc! The food was great but it was our wedding anniversary. I let them know at the momento of the reservation but they didn't give us any special treat...

Name: Parc
Comments: The service and food at Park is wonderful.  They have always had out door dining available, but they have expanded on that space to give more distance between diners during this crazy time.

Name: Parc
Comments: Fantastic place. Parc remains excellent. That said, the service during the COVID pandemic is NOT what it usually is.

Name: Parc
Comments: Great food as always but bring back veuve clicquot by the glass!

Name: Parc
Comments: Garage validation should be considered if spending greater than 100.00Staff needs to be more astute about moving the homeless along that r bothering people eating outside

Name: Parc
Comments: We thoroughly enjoyed our meal at Parc.  For a brief second we forgot about the pandemic.  Everything around us seems to be changing.  Except nothing has changed about the food and service at Parc - - still excellent.

Name: Parc
Comments: Very pleased with the service ESPECIALLY considering the covid restrictions - the restaurant is always A+ and a favorite of ours.

Name: Parc
Comments: Great Service! Food was delicious.

Name: Parc
Comments: Great Sunday brunch on a gorgeous afternoon. Staff was very hospitable and food was delicious as always. Nioise salad, warm shrimp salad, assorted oysters.

Name: Parc
Comments: Food was great  as well as the socially distancing set up. We felt safe and were able to enjoy our meal as usual

Name: Parc
Comments: Outdoor COVID-19 seating.  It was a lovely night.  Our server was fabulous and very careful. Wore his mask properly.   Delicious food never disappoints.  Best bread in the city

Name: Parc
Comments: Every server wore a mask and every single employee was kind, on point, and attentive.

Name: Parc
Comments: Ate at Parc in July during COVID-19 and still had an amazing experience. We were seated outside near Rittenhouse Square and enjoyed mimosas while people-watching the Saturday Farmers Market. While it does get hot and sunny with only outdoor dining, the restaurant continuously provided water. They served their standard brunch menu with excellent cleanliness. Definitely still recommended going but you need a reservation!!

Name: Per Se
Comments: Best dining experience Ive had. Excellent quality and very tasty. The service was attentive and personable. Just a perfect experience.

Name: Per Se
Comments: It was the best birthday ever! The staff was so enjoyable they definitely were apart of making my experience a pleasant one. The food was magnificent!!! Highly recommended. Per Se knows how to make a girl feel special

Name: Per Se
Comments: 3 days later, and I am still thinking about the food. It was everything you would expect from a 3 Michelin star restaurant. We went for my birthday, and the menu had my name printed. I received a signed menu, along with special treats at the end of the dinner. I have been recommending Per Se to everyone!

Name: Per Se
Comments: The food was excellent, if not particularly creative. The Wagyu beef was out of this world. Service was seriously disappointing, ie: I had to request the same glass of wine twice, and when it finally arrived, food sitting on the table, it was the wrong one. No apology, but rather an excuse that the wine was probably married with something else(!) was given. Seriously. The waiter was a touch smug and casual bordering on unprofessional. A thousand dollar meal needs to be perfect. This was not. We have eaten at other 3 Michelin star restaurants and this one didnt hold up.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Absolutely one of the best dining experiences. Everything was impeccable!

Name: Per Se
Comments: We were delighted to be able to get a reservation at Per Se for dining on our wedding anniversary.We arrived early with a view to having a pre-dinner celebratory drink but were told in an off hand manner that there was nowhere for us to sit and that there was another bar outside of the restaurant we could use so thought it could have been handled better. Since our last visit the bar area within Per Se has been turned into tables for dining so they have increased their covers.When we did get in we still had to wait for our table and so sat at a high bar area. The tasting menu was great with a lot of choice and standard of the food was excellent again so we weren't disappointed. The staff were very professional and happy to chat - getting the balance on this is quite difficult in my opinion and after a rocky start  they certainly succeeded.This is a very special restaurant and although expensive a place for celebrations.

Name: Per Se
Comments: It was excellent from start to finish.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Absolutely amazing! Best date ever!!!

Name: Per Se
Comments: It was my husbands 40rh birthday. They surprised us all the time. Amazing.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Per Se exceeded my expectations. The experience is worth the price. I hope to dine at Per Se again sometime.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Just Fabulous  in every way! A huge treat and well worth it!

Name: Per Se
Comments: For me this is destination dinning. I go to NY  often and its nice to experience the top restaurants once in a while. This was semi short notice so the only time available was for Lunch on Saturday. Everything about the restaurant was super outstanding, especially the service, which is becoming rated these days. Unfortunately we were next to a table, theyre not that close, of four that included a 12-13 year old boy. Its not that children are bad, its the failed parenting strategies that have forgotten about the seldom seen and never heard theories of children in upscale public places. I wish they would have a grown up only policy.

Name: Per Se
Comments: This is a dining establishment beyond compare. Prepare to be pampered while you take in view of the NY skyline and relax in the glow of the fireplace. All waiters are graduates of a culinary school who will help you create the dining experience of a lifetime. 12 plates and an assortment of desserts are served to order at your leisure. The cuisine is original, and diverse with flavors that coax and tease the taste buds. The quality of ingredients is unrivaled; so much so that "Bread and Butter" is an entree - "A smoked Paprika 'Parker House Roll' served with Diane St Clair's Animal Farm Butter." Diane has 10 cows that she milks and hand churns the butter. No detail is left to chance. All chairs that are not required are removed from the table (before you arrive) so as not to disturb the intimacy. There are as many servers as there are guests who move stealthily to present your next palate-stimulating tasting.No matter your requirements (allergies, vegan, etc) Chef Keller and his staff will ensure that you literally have the meal of a lifetime.

Name: Per Se
Comments: We had easily one of the best meals we have ever had at Per Se.  The tasting menu was incredibly well put together.  Each course seemed to improve upon the one before it.  The service was even better, with very attentive (but unintrusive) staff who took care to explain the dishes and get to know us throughout the dinner.  The pace was prompt, without being rushed and worked through the menu in just about two hours.  Capped off our experience with a kitchen tour and personal compliments to the chefs. Cant recommend Per Se enough!

Name: Per Se
Comments: Amazing! There are Michelin restaurants and then there is a Per Se.

Name: Per Se
Comments: It is quite refreshing to enter a restaurant in NYC and have it meet your expectations. Per se did exactly that. The staff made us feel comfortable from the beginning, there was nothing rushed. The view of central park was simple and beautiful. Now the food, memorable, had a range of flavors in every dish, and also thankfully left us full and happy.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Outstanding personalized service combined with incredible food. We were treated like royalty throughout the meal all capped off at the end with a tour of the kitchen escorted by the maitre d, who couldnt be more friendly. Not just a meal but a memorable experience!

Name: Per Se
Comments: I need to say Awesome service, every lovely server treat us like a friend!awesome food, both me n my husband love it, hope coming back again!

Name: Per Se
Comments: One of the great experiences in my life that I will remember for evermore.It exceeded my expectations and I am so happy that I was able to get areservation.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Lovely food, ambiance and service

Name: Per Se
Comments: Dining at Per Se is really beyond words.  It's an experience where 12 or 13 delicious, delicate and melt in your mouth courses are presented in a huge variety of plates, bowls and vessels of all kinds by young men and women who seem to appreciate being a part of the experience with you.  The fabulous three-hour treat was not stuffy but very fun.  Taking a tour of the kitchen and wine cellar afterwards was a double treat!

Name: Per Se
Comments: It was amazing. Food, service and ambiance were 5 Star.

Name: Per Se
Comments: With 3 Michelin Stars and already haven visited French Laundry, another Thomas Keller restaurant, I had high expectations for Per Se.  And my expectations were met!  Stunning, dramatic, yet classy ambience, spotless professional service, creative and delicious cuisine.  Just a very special night and experience with friends.

Name: Per Se
Comments: This was my first experience at Per Se and I was so excited to go! My husband and I are junkies for Michelin Star restaurants and this was at the top of our list. Definitely met every expectation of a Michelin rated restaurant.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Holy guacamole! Chef Keller clearly pays attention to detail as every dish is specially curated. This aint yo mommas cookin! Grab your napkin and hold on to your britches because there aint no stopping when youre on this food train.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Fantastic for a special date or occasion

Name: Per Se
Comments: Besser gehts nicht ! Essen und Service einfach nur perfekt.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Per Se was perfect. My wife, sister-in-law and I had dinner there at the end of a trip to NYC. It was a chilly evening and they put us next to the fireplace which was very cozy. The food was great. The service was impeccable. They were willing to accommodate changes to the menu if a particular item wasn't to our fancy. We were there for three and one half hours and it was among the most pleasurable dining experiences we have had. It is definitely a special occasion place. Go there when you aren't in a hurry and want to enjoy the best.

Name: Per Se
Comments: simply incredible!!!

Name: Per Se
Comments: Still one of the greatest spots in NYC. Bill maybe be a bit high but great memories are priceless! Every dish was a hit and the ambience was amazing. Very comfortable and enjoyable experience. Def get the supplements.

Name: Per Se
Comments: From start to finish our experience was flawless.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Amazing food and amazing service. Truly spot on. I do not think there could have been anything improved upon. Laurel provided a very memorable experience.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Tyler the Maitre d' elevated our experience like no other restaurant we've ever been to. From helpful insider tips on other food NYC hangouts, to staying at the table for casual conversation, to a one-of-a-kind full tour of the kitchen, he was absolutely incredible. We loved every minute of our stay at Per Se and found it even better than its sister, French Laundry. All four of us would rate it as one of the best dining experiences we have ever had.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Celebrating my wifes birthday. Fantastic food and everything along the way. They have everything thought out from drinks to food it was sublime

Name: Per Se
Comments: Excellent food experience, courteous service, quiet and comfortable environment, food is missed. It is worth going to many times!

Name: Per Se
Comments: Loved it.  Top 10 ever

Name: Per Se
Comments: We celebrated our 10 year wedding anniversary with a trip to New York and a degustation dinner at Per Se. Our expectations for the dinner were high going in and Per Se exceeded them. The food was phenomenal, the service was attentive and the whole occasion just truly memorable.

Name: Per Se
Comments: This was by far one of the most amazing dining experiences I have ever had.  The food was just incredible; but, the service and the experience were amazing as well.  Of particular note, was that we arrived with our 12 year old son and the restaurant staff from the front entrance and throughout the evening were so amazingly friendly and attentive to him as well as to us.  It made for a truly wonderful dining experience that we will never forget.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Amazing everything which is not surprising for a Michelin 3 star restaurant but in terms of value I think the vegetarian/pescetarian menus should be priced as high/represent the same value as the standard tasting menu. However overall one of best meals Ive ever had!

Name: Per Se
Comments: Excellent attentive service from beginning to end. Complementary champagne to help us celebrate our special occasion to tour of the kitchen in the end, dining at Per Se is an experience, not just dining.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: One of my favorite restaurants in the city. Not only is the restaurant special, they make every individual feel welcome and special. The food is spectacular and the drinks are wonderful.  The Polo Bar is a must and my go to restaurant for any occasion.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: We always save the Polo Bar for our last night in the City! It never disappoints. The wait staff is always so respectful and friendly. The food was divine. And, as always, its a great place to people watch. Cant wait to return!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Very nice place, unique. Recommended to all people looking for something else .

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: I cannot recommend the Polo Bar enough. My boyfriend and I (not famous in any way) happened to dine at the Polo Bar the same night as a number of big name celebrities. There was absolutely no fuss and we felt equally as important and valued to our servers as anyone else in the restaurant. Food was also divine, I highly recommend the chocolate cake :) Thank you, Polo Bar, for a terrific experience.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Very nice location, very good burger with lots of fries. The cheesecake tastes great and comes with fresh strawberries. Pricing is pretty reasonable. Service pays good attention and is very handsome. A nice place, especially for poloplayers.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Food wasn't that great but worth it to visit once I didn't really like the server who had kinda rude attitude (He was keep trying to make me order fancier meal options..)

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: this place is a hoot! i have always wanted to go, but being there made me wish i was straight edge...can't believe that drinks can be over $30! however, the decor and the popovers help provide a bit more value to an otherwise fun and delicious, yet overpriced, whitebread new york experience.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Wonderful Birthday dinner for our son's 21st Birthday!!!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: I was very disappointed to say the least about my dinner here. The atmosphere was disappointing and I couldn't believe that the family sitting in front of me had their kid playing video game on his iPad at the dinner table. It was horrible and the couple sitting beside me was weird, anytime they coughed she kept apologizing that they didn't have any disease or nothing, it wasn't like I said anything to them.  The food wasn't great, only the cocktail was good. Overall, based that you had to have a reservation to get in here and then you see this, it's appalling. Places that don't require such a strict reservation policy have better class of people as patrons than this place. I wouldn't go back or recommend it.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: The BEST! Love the Polo Bar!!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Just Great! Well be back!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Always a must when Im in New York. I love the atmosphere and the food is good and not too pretentious.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: For such an affluent Resturant, the guy who works at the reservation switchboard is of very low quality and standard and has no etiquette. Just his attitude and horrible telephone skills are enough to turn you off this place altogether. I would pass on this Resturant as there are far better quality places with amazing friendly staff who have people skills training. Def would not go back here!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Amazing dinner. Waiter was one of best in City.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: The experience was great.The food was delicious, well served and the atmosphere excellent!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Great evening with friends. Service was perfect. Bar and wait staff were welcoming and  front of house was super accommodating when we were a tad late. Food quality is excellent. And those bar snacks, delicious.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Good food great atmosphere but very costly-55th and Fifth

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Service was excellent, Michael was the best waiter weve had in the several times weve visited here.  Food was really good and fairly good choices, theyll help if you need to tailor a menu item for specific reasons.  Nice cocktail options, and some varied gin selections.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Amazing service and totally delicious.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Cozy and chic Excellent service and reliably good food

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Start at the beautiful bar on the main floor.  Although expensive, the drink are creative and accompanied by a trio of delicious snacks. Arrive at least 30 minutes before your dinner reservation to relax and enjoy the experience. Move downstairs for an old school dinner.  The staff will be happy to split dishes in the kitchen.  The corned beef sandwich and burgers are exceptional.  It is a great place for a meal with friends and family.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Anniversary

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: I love The Polo Bar. Want to make plans for ny birthday next year!!! I love you Ralph Lauren!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: The food and the experience were both amazing, we couldn't have asked for a better night!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Excellent ambiance and service; we loved our dinner, especially the popovers! A wonderful place to celebrate our 50th wedding anniversary!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Best restaurant, impeccable service, and delicious food. Special occasion, date night, or just for a good meal, its perfect. Excellent cocktails. My favorite is the Vesper Martini!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: While the room is warm, decor nicely done,  & tables well-spaced, the food was very disappointing.  The popovers were delicious, but after one, we were not offered a 2nd, & without realizing it, our bread plates were removed.  We ordered what we were told were"must-haves" --Shrimp Cocktail, Franks in Blankets, Corned Beef sandwich, Roasted Cauliflower, & none we agreed, had any distinctive flavor.  The experience for people around us, seemed to be focused on what celebrity might walk into the room.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: I have waited a year to get in this place. It was worth it! Great friendly, fashionable scene. Very attentive service. The food was very good.  Cant wait to go back.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Stunning decor and atmosphere. Food and service were both excellent!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Excellent, would highly recommend, best total experience over a week of tasting NYC !!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: It was my husbands birthday. He enjoyed every bit of his meal.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: A lovely Sunday evening dinner with friends. The space is beautiful, food excellent and service perfect!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Outstanding service and food. Fantastic cocktails !!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: We love the Polo Bar. Great spot for a drink, and the food and service never disappoints.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Great food and ambience. A little noisy. Staff is very attentive and VERY professional I highly recommend.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: A must go place in nyc!!!

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: One of the most exciting and exhilarating  One of the most exciting and exhilarating experiences I have ever had dining.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Classy restaurant, excellent service.

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Fantastic place. Get there early to enjoy a cocktail in the lounge. Great

Name: The Polo Bar
Comments: Family dining early evening Very enjoyable very good service and excellent food . We had the New York strip and burgers All was well prepared and delicious

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Not much more to say; my wife and I thoroughly enjoyed our meal and evening at BH PL.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: The staff were great.  Food was good but very pricey.  Paying for the garden ambience, which I understand, however, eating inside would not be my thing for the price.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: So classic Hollywood.  (Even though its Beverly Hills.)

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Food was terrible. We all ordered the same salad (4) the McCarthy Salad, and it was served mushed, could barely recognize anything in it, seemed like it was almost blended .  Terrible.The drinks were good though!Needless to say, definitely put a damper on our lunch/afternoon

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Even COVID 19 cannot detract from the beautiful outdoor setting used for their famous Sunday Brunch.  We felt, for a brief few hours, that the world was normal again.  Thank you for the magnificent food, excellent service and perfect ambience for our special occasion.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: The Polo Lounge is always a lovely place to dine. Sunday was very pricey, however, & its already $$$$.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Perfect. Very hospitable and all staff were wearing proper protection.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Fantastic a perfect summer setting, social distancing and hygiene protocols observed. Thank you for a perfect experience!

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Always perfect

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: the service is the greatest!beautiful location! ideal for a special date!

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: We came for brunch and we got seated promptly. The hostess and waiter were cordial and attentive. Our McCarthy salads were delicious. As always, a beautiful dining experience with good service. Thank you!PS. The outside chairs and table were uncomfortable and provided very little leg room.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Great atmosphere. Excellent service. Safety precautions galore.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Still quite wonderful!!!!! Everyone was so pleasant with almost perfect service!!!! Food was great!!!!

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: The service and ambiance was great! The food was a bit over priced but good.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: I've been going to The Polo Lounge for a couple of decades, and have never been less than delighted. It's been around a loooong time, but they're not just coasting on their well-deserved reputation. I often went alone to eat at the bar, they do fab cocktails.It's a beautiful space that's elegantly appointed with flowers and cozy decor. The service is always professional, and the other guests can be interesting. I've seen many actors, musicians, and industry moguls there through the years, at least one per visit.  I sat next to Jerry Seinfeld at the bar about 10 years ago and chatted. It's $$$$$, but the dishes on the eclectic menu are always well-prepared, and portions are always generous, good for a take-home snack at least.I highly recommend it, especially for special occasions and romantic meals - there was a marriage proposal a few booths away, and they got a huge round of applause from the entire place.(Oddly enough, there was also a proposal the night before when we were at The Rooftop By JG at The Waldorf the previous evening, I guess it's in the air in LA!)

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: I dined on the outdoor patioWaitstaff double masked covid prepared Very cordial, helpful accommodating.They delivered everything I requested. The food is consistent I am not so keen on shaved lettuce but the salad was healthy. Dressing could be improved. Bread basket excellent.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Did not notify me about dress code they made me go home to change.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Love this place. I will be back for sure! Food, service and ambience was just perfect.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Personally i would not go back. I appreciate good service and I did not receive that here which was upsetting considering it was my 30th bday

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Really strict dress code. Waiters can be pretty rude. Definitely a pretentious vibe.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Upon check-in, the gentleman at the entrance of the restaurant looked us up and down. We understand that theres a dress code but he couldve been a bit more discreet if he was really checking out our attire. Besides that, the waitstaff was great and food/drinks were excellent.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Delicious. Heavily overpriced but we didnt care because everything was so good!  We will go again!

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Atmosphere and service were fantastic per usual. Food was surprisingly underwhelming, and thats being polite. Chicken entree was almost inedible- very tough and chewy. Club sandwich did not taste fresh and had little flavor. Gazpacho with crab was pretty good, but nothing outstanding. Go for the drinks and atmosphere, but skip the food.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Quiet, Amazing Dine in service, distance away from other guests thats are dining, the staff takes extra precautions and super attentive, they wear masks shields and gloves. The food is absolutely amazing. Great Time.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Lovely brunch and great at following CDC safety guidelines.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Great service as always! Amazing dining experience!

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Good people watching.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Took a long while to get our server to come and take our order.  Bus boys were outstanding and should become servers instead.  We had a late guest joining us and I had to ask for silverware and setting for her.  Half way through the meal our server got replaced (?) and then everything was as I expected from this iconic c restaurant/hotel.   Three main courses and one dozen oysters with 2 rounds of drinks for the three of us, almost $500.  A bit much.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Overpriced for quality

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: our waitress Sidney was exceptional-really made for an enjoyable lunch.  The food the atmosphere were all excellent.  During this crazy pandemic I felt very comfortable and safe dining there.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: It was our first night out in a 3 months.  Service was impeccable, food delicious, and I felt very safe.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: The service was great, the food was delicious. Very clean, nice place

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Date nights are always the best here

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Excellent food and service and the place is absolutely beautiful!  Well worth the cost!

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Always great.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Great brunch with the girls

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Our waiter David was amazing

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Great place for breakfast in the terrace, food was excellent. Service a little slow, but OK.  Price of the menu certainly on the high end category.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Classic LA.  An oasis.  Great food and service.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: The service was so bad which makes everything else terrible. So dissapointed.

Name: PRESS
Comments: I came here for my boyfriends birthday dinner and it did not disappoint. Eric was our server and guided us through the whole menu offering wonderful suggestions (the pig ears were my favorite). Jodi the sommelier help to find an amazing couple of bottles of that went perfectly with our meal. We will be back again soon.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Fantastic spot, one of the best in the valley. Amazing food, first class service, and a never ending wine list

Name: PRESS
Comments: We have been going to Press since it opened, over 15 years. I was a big fan as it was a great steakhouse.  Although it still advertises itself that way, it is not.  Not even a filet on the menu.  The food has become fussy and pretentious.  I can not recommend it.  We left hungry.  Sadness.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Amazing atmosphere, food, and service. It was worth it.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Press is an absolute MUST for anybody visiting the Napa Valley. Every dining experience there is a memorable delight!

Name: PRESS
Comments: The staff were very attentive.  The brunch/lunch menu was super limited and the description for the items listed by staff was not consistent with what came out of their kitchen.  Overall this place was ok but did not live up to the reviews we read or the type of dining experience we paid for.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Yummy food with great service! Came here for the first time with my husband  for lunch and wasnt disappointed. The outdoor seating is beautiful , and our server made great recommendations.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Not enough food for the cost. We came for our 1 year anniversary (a splurge meal) we left hungry and broke. Food was just ok but small portions. I had half a chicken with maybe a handle full of salad and was $37?!  Bread cost extra and fries was $19 a la cart?! My husband had what I would call a pulled pork sandwich (served alone) at $22. Then was lovely patio seating but they need to do something about ALL the flies. It was obnoxious trying to shu them alway the whole meal. We left here and shared a burger at Gotts just to fill up.  Note we spent $175 for lunch. Wanted  to support local business. But unfortunately, wont be coming back.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Press is a great place to go for date night, special occasion, getting together with friends, or for everyday dining. It never disappoints. The food is delicious and presented so beautifully, and the service is always great. They have the largest list of Napa wines in the valley that includes many older vintages

Name: PRESS
Comments: Excellent.  Favorite restaurant in Napa.  Great wine list

Name: PRESS
Comments: Outstanding service - the food was delicious. Loved the outdoor seating. Thank you!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Absurdly overpriced for tiny portions of overly complicated food! FOAM is not a food! No longer serving the chopped salad and delicious side dishes they used to have. Save your money- definitely NOT worth it!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Food was good as always - this is one of our favorite places

Name: PRESS
Comments: Press is serving outside, doing the best they can, considering Covid restrictions. But our simple order, including the temp on our ribeye, had mistakes. They did try to make up for the mistakes by giving us a dessert, a classy move.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Great diner. Dining only outside. Everything was great except the flies.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Press is one of the all time best restaurants in the Valley.  The food was terrific and the service was outstanding.  We had to sit outside due to the covid rules and the tables were cozy and in the shade.  Each table had a oscillating fan (and it was 97 that day) which made it nice and breezy without being too hot or windy.  It was our anniversary and we were treated amazing by everyone there.  I cant wait to go back next anniversary..

Name: PRESS
Comments: Absolutely fantastic food!Great service!  Recommend the steak tartare...its incredible

Name: PRESS
Comments: New outdoor seating was terrific and the service was GREAT

Name: PRESS
Comments: Great place! Highly recommend!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Unfortunately we were let down with this dinner. Over priced. Food was cold. Service outside was filled with flies and overheating. Granted this was outside seating during COVID but it was like we were forgotten in the corner. For a $300+ dinner for 2, big disappointment.

Name: PRESS
