Comments: Superb food & service. Left huge tip

Name: PRESS
Comments: Their patio area is nice!

Name: PRESS
Comments: My wifes birthday, Press is our favorite restaurant in the Napa Area

Name: PRESS
Comments: totally spectacular food, extraordinary conceptualization and execution - superb service including great advice on wine selection from the unparalleled list of Napa Valley vintages - overall wonderful experience notwithstanding the outside dining in very hot weather necessitated by current Covid-19 regulations

Name: PRESS
Comments: Ambience is a bit off as the restaurant has been stripped of half of its tables during this pandemic. Did not alter the wonderful food and service though! Only half of the original menu, but what  is on it is excellent!Unfortunately, they have to close again for another three weeks!Look forward to better times!!

Name: PRESS
Comments: They did a great job having a varied but abbreviated menu in these times.  The bar was open and bartender was very willing to craft some great drinks.

Name: PRESS
Comments: AmaZing food - such a great culinary experience. Highly reccomend

Name: PRESS
Comments: Alway great, across the board

Name: PRESS
Comments: Food was fabulous, but expensive. You have to pay for bread. I mean come on, they can spring for bread when theyre charging $34 for a sandwich. But, theyre delicious sandwiches.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Flavors of every dish were complex and distinct. Service was excellent and restaurant is taking protection of patrons seriously during this Covid time.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Wonderful meal. Perfect portion sizes. They forgot the bread we ordered but we got a tour of the wine cellar at the end. That madeUp for it! And they comped the bread. Although I wasnt a fan of the bread. Lol. The truffle fries were too salty for me.  But we got a few freebies. Overall I would go back. The service was great!

Name: PRESS
Comments: First time visit to Napa Valley. The edible art professionally delivered to the table was exquisite. Expensive, but the value is intact.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Jodie the sommelier was very helpful and gave us a lovely suggestion. Food was average. The steak needed seasoning.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Nice restaurant and atmosphere, good service, and great wine list, but the most important part - the food - was mediocre at best.  Tried a variety of different things and settled on the bacon wrapped filet mignon for dinner.  It was cooked as asked but I can make better steaks at home on my Weber grill.  We wanted to try this restaurant for a while and were disappointed at the output when we finally did go.  There's just too many other fantastic restaurants in the Valley to settle for so-so food, especially considering the price point.  Unfortunately this is a one and done restaurant for us.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Thank You Press from the bottom of my heart. You made our first wedding anniversary so special. The staff was so professional and all were wearing masks. We felt very safe. After having a horrible experience with Auberge who last minute cancelled my reservation 4 days before our anniversary. I was freaking out Thursday night. I looked on open table saw press had room for us. I booked it fast. Friday I called just to confirm with them didnt want another Auberge situation. Not only did the young lady confirm she also saw that one of us had a food  allergy. No lies I cried. I was so thankful that she acknowledged my food  allergy. Dinner was amazing. They even surprised us with a pastry and a candle. Again Thank You So Much to everyone at Press.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Birthday party with friends!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Just incredible!  The steak tare tare had the perfect spice! The steak and frites was amazing.  The wine list is out of this world!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Service was terrific but felt very rushed, I suspect staffing is difficult in today's environment. The Filet was far smaller that I recall, but cooker perfectly. Also thank you for offering to omit the corkage if we also bought a bottle of wine, a nice approach since there were four of us, it worked well. Overall we had a great time, thanks for allowing us to dine!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Press is a special place and the quality of the food and service is always top notch!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Our dinners could not have been better. Rudd wines were incredible as usual. We will eat here twice every annual trip to wine country.

Name: Quince
Comments: The food was interesting/intriguing, certainly more suited to a tasting menu.  The wine pairings were also good, but heavily weighted to whites; I would have enjoyed tasting 2 or 3 more reds.  The service could not have been better.

Name: Quince
Comments: Wonderful food and great service. Hope we come back soon.

Name: Quince
Comments: Wonderful non pretentious  meal and service at Quince. We enjoyed the experience.

Name: Quince
Comments: It was amazing! We had a perfect dinner and the wine pairing was exceptional. They even surprised my wife with a special dining opportunity in the kitchen, which made her birthday even more special.

Name: Quince
Comments: This was the best dining experience we have ever had...and we have been to the French Laundry.  The service was perfect, there when you need it and not there when you don't.  The food was exquisite and beautifully presented.   The noise level was low and the room had high ceilings and was softly lit.  It was awesome.  Our wait person was Kyra and she was a perfect delight.  Very attentive and knowledgeable about the cuisine and wines.  She was awesome.   This restaurant is a high recommend for foodies and/or a romantic celebration.

Name: Quince
Comments: An absolute dream. Every detail on point. A very memorable dinning experience.

Name: Quince
Comments: Overall fantastic experience

Name: Quince
Comments: Whole evening was excellent. Food, service n silverwares to wine glasses n cocktail glasses.Thank you for the special menu with my wifes name which made a little more memorable.  3 However, black napkins can replace the white would for black clothes.Need grab bars in wash room for handicap people.  I am.Lastly just a note to Mike. Betsy would like to have her Tupperware back.  Its bern too long.   Mahalo.Chris and Paul......Betsy

Name: Quince
Comments: Very memorable meal for all of us.

Name: Quince
Comments: Very disappointing,The service and food quality goes downhill compared with last year !!!!!!!!!

Name: Quince
Comments: An exquisite dining experience where every detail is carefully chosen for its flavor,color and artistic intent. A meal worth savoring and sharing with someone you love. Expensive but a bargain considering the labor, discipline and passion put in by Chef Tusk and his staff.

Name: Quince
Comments: Ten delicious courses.   Tried foods I normally would pass on and was so happy with the flavors.

Name: Quince
Comments: The experience was incredible, the service impeccable, the food is from another world to experience the mixture of flavors that explode on your palate and transport in a dream place, a thousand congratulations to the chef is magnificent

Name: Quince
Comments: Quince lives up to its reputation.  Expensive?  Yes.  Worth the price?  I have to say Yes, again.  We went in the middle of the week, so not crowded.  Service was wonderful.  At first, I was concerned that there were too many different servers and wine masters attending to us.  But each had a specialty, and a story to tell.  Juan, in particular, provided insight to and history behind the cutlery and china.  Robert paced us through and described each course expertly.  And the food--well, there was nothing that was not perfect.  Oysters in a cream and nettle sauce.  White asparagus prepared two ways.  Wagyu beef--both American and Japanese bred.  Additional treats besides what is listed on the day's menu.  By the time we arrived at the beautiful dessert trolly, I could hardly eat another thing.  Definitely take your time.  We were there for well over 4 hours, and enjoyed every minute.

Name: Quince
Comments: We have been enjoying a few 3 star Michelin restaurants in the past, and we really enjoyed Quince. The service was remarkable, the food was consistently great throughout the tasting menu and the wine paring was very very well selected. I am not your typical desert lover, but I was blown away with those as well, and the praline cart at the end was an amazing finale! Thank you - you exceeded our expectations with leaps and bounds.

Name: Quince
Comments: We have now been to 8 Michelin 3 star restaurants and the consensus of our group is that Quince is the best.

Name: Quince
Comments: Amazing food and great service. Recommend for Birthday and Anniversary!

Name: Quince
Comments: Really nice

Name: Quince
Comments: Too many sweets after main courses. Unfortunately I got sick later in the evening.

Name: Quince
Comments: Extraordinario todo  nunca haba proba una carne como la de aqui, todos los platillos perfectamente balanceados los postres son una delicia comprendo porque tiene *** Michelin

Name: Quince
Comments: A special place and meal, wonderful staff!  Maybe a few more options on the main course entree such as a seafood.

Name: Quince
Comments: In a word: Overrated.  The service was a good but way over the top and made us feel uncomfortable due feeling like our every move and word was being monitored.  The food was good but for the price? Nah. Out of 10 courses, we loved 2 or 3 of them and the rest were good but not worth the money and prestige imho.

Name: Quince
Comments: Legendary. From greetings upon arrival, to the chocolate to go when leaving. Extreme attention to detail. Exquisite flavors. Unique experience. A must-go

Name: Quince
Comments: Total ripoff , For 2 ppl was charged 950 for tasting menu i really wasnt impressed on.Never come back again.

Name: Quince
Comments: A lovely evening. Fantastic meal. Outstanding service. So many deserts! Was so satisfied and happy!

Name: Quince
Comments: super attentive staffs, wonderful atmosphere

Name: Quince
Comments: From the moment you walk in and are greeted by the dynamite staff to when you leave with a warm cup of hot chocolate waiting for you at the door for you walk outside, Quince just leaves you with the best culinary experience to remember for years to come.

Name: Quince
Comments: Excellent restaurant with great service, however, very pricey.  Buyer beware.

Name: Quince
Comments: Best dining experience of my life. We will be back!

Name: Quince
Comments: Excellent food and services. We were even invited to visit the kitchen, had one course there, and took picture with the chef.  Great experience!

Name: Quince
Comments: Good food but not one of the best, well trained staff offering a well rehearsed service, but not genuine, way overpriced for the experience. There are as good restaurant around for a third of the cost.

Name: Quince
Comments: Excellent service from the beginning to the end

Name: Quince
Comments: Disappointing.  After second course, there was a forty Minute wait for next course.  After that the timing of service was spotty.  Wine selections were spotty and main courses did not wow.

Name: Quince
Comments: Exceptional in every aspect! Amazing experience! Worth every penny! ~Thank you, Chef Musk! Well deserved three-star Michelin!!!

Name: Quince
Comments: Birthday family dinner

Name: Quince
Comments: The food and service are simply exquisite. They were incredibly accommodating. The courses are well paced but you should definitely plan on coming with an empty stomach. Most elegant restaurant in the bay area.

Name: Quince
Comments: The best Michelin 3 star restaurant in the world

Name: Quince
Comments: Elaborate dining with prefix menu

Name: Quince
Comments: Best dining experience in San Fran. Highly recommended.

Name: Quince
Comments: Awesome experience The eating in kitchen was very special!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Very "hip" place - loud, crowded, bar packed.  Food and service were both good.  Couldn't hear across the table, so don't go to have a conversation with your dinner partner.  Started annoyed with 6 texts, 2 phone calls, and 1 e-mail asking me to confirm reservation.  Each one answered.  Over-hyped place - won't go back

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Partner enjoyed the food, then the bar with quite great  characters and conversation which made the night complete.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Fantastic as usual!  Raouls consistently delivers an amazing food and ambiance experience.  Id recommend it to anyone and everyone!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Ever mouthful was perfection!! Love this place its So consistent for great food quality and service!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: This cozy but very loud restaurant is home to perhaps the most outstanding Steak au Poivre I have ever had. The cut of meat was excellent, cooked to a perfect medium and crusted in just the right amount and consistency of pepper... served with a perfectly seasoned sauce of exactly the right consistency... and of course accompanied by a basket of crispy Frites! It doesnt get much better than this! Exactly what I would expect from an Alsace heritage which, arguably produces the best chefs in all of Europe!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Food was delicious, overall great experience

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Food and cocktails were fantastic.  Steak au Poivre was amazing.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: This was an amazing find on this past trip. It had an old school feel given all its history in the city. My son LOVED the burger. This is a kid who doesnt like sauce or much adornment on his burgers so the meat has to be spot on - this burger didnt disappoint AND the pepper sauce was so good, he ATE ALL OF IT!!  All the food was divine and definitely a staple for our yearly visits toNYC from now on!!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: One of my NYC favorites!!!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Loved everything

Name: Raoul's
Comments: The food and lively atmosphere is always fantastic!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great evening to enjoy my nieces birthday!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: All  Loved

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Always a great time at this legendary place

Name: Raoul's
Comments: My favorite place in the city!!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Fabulous burger -- worth the hype! The fries were also a pleasant surprise too.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Overpriced but not remarkable.  The waitstaff was curt. I would not go back.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Exceptional service and food at this well known restaurant. Really enjoyed our evening.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Good food, Poor service; table not ready, then after being directed to the bar were told we couldnt transfer the bar bill to our table. Waiter was slow and inattentive, didnt provide plates for the bread, didnt once check in on the food, had to be asked three times for a drinks refill and provided dessert menus but didnt come to take an order for 15 minutes....

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great service and food! If you note a birthday celebration in open table they remember and add a candle to your desert which is great.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Fantastic night at this iconic new york restaurant.  The steak au poivre was perfectly cooked and delicious.  The choice of sides was great and the grilled broccoli was really tasty.  A huge wine list was also good with a massive selection of french as well as us wines.  Would definitely go again next time in NYC.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great service. Nice wine menu. Delicious food. A true neighborhood gem. Cant wait to go back again.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: YOU WILL BE CHARGED $100 to cancel reservations. Still a great place!!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Wonderful old school French brassiere with classic French cuisine done extremely well.  From the steak au pouvrie to the pomme  frites to the profiteroles you cant go wrong.  Excellent service, as well.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Sexy crowd and the best steak au poivre in town. My go-to spot for a fun night out.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: 80th Birthday

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Beautiful space with interesting artwork. The food and wine were great and the ambiance was lovely. Service was the best.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Raoul's will always be our favorite place. The staff and food (especially the burger) are the absolute best.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great burgers. My neighborhood favorite!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: I LOVE RAOUL'S!  My husband and I meet for late dinners here and always roll home full, tipsy and elated.  The service is really always outstanding.  Everything from the bar/ host staff's greeting to the experience at the table makes us feel so well cared for; I find the interpersonal style of the team to be very direct, professional, and effective, but also always warm.  This place is such a New York institution; it's an absolute privilege to enjoy it from time to time.  Thanks to the whole damn team!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Wonderful meal from beginning to end

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Never disappoints!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Amazing classic French style restaurant.The food is exquisite and the atmosphere fantastic. Its not for those looking for a quiet night out as noise levels are high but I wouldnt have it any other way. Efficient staff, eclectic artwork and food so delicious that my mouth waters at the mere thought of it! Go!! It should be illegal not to!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Raouls is the best. Its our regular go-to because while the food is really great (get the frisbee salad no matter what else you do)- the people are incredible and make you feel so welcome and at home. Plenty of celebrities come to this old school restaurant that has stayed popular for over 40 years but they treat  everyone wonderfully and care more how you behave than who you are

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Best steak au poivre ever, great Cosmo, fab music, cool scene. I will definitely return. Sometimes I look so hard for something new.... so glad I chose a classic to celebrate my husbands 50th.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Tremendous spot.  A+ food, service. Traditional and current. Love it. Rivals the best.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great food, ambiance, service.  Hands down our favorite restaurant in NYC.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: One of the best burgers in town.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: The food is great and good value. I like the ambiance a lot. Dark with a European feel. Waitstaff are all competent but there are big inconsistencies in servers.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent meal & service. Best Indian food I've ever had.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Very tasty, though there are other trendy, high end restaurants where I do feel like you get more bang for your buck than here.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent in every way. Amazing food, service, room, noise level. Only knock for me personally was dessert, but that is more my tastes than their execution.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Great modern take on Indian food.  Looking forward to my next visit.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Once again, we all had great meals and great service. Rasika is the best indian food in town.

Name: Rasika
Comments: The food is delicious. I would recommend the restaurant to others.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Nice place. Good food. Always on our list for when we are in the mood for Indian food.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Outstanding food and service each time I visited.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Exceptional food and service!Outstanding experience.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Creative food, great vibe and service. Liked trying Indian beer.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Nice restaurant, food was good, not great. Didnt understand what all the hype is about, but will give it another shot in the future.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Never been disappointed. Just fantastic Indian food with a modern flair.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Amazing delicious food! Great fun for a night of fine dining!

Name: Rasika
Comments: The food here is amazing.  Particularly the fish dishes (cod and bass).  I would eat it daily if I could.

Name: Rasika
Comments: A must-try if you love Indian food when you're in DC.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Dining at Rasika is an every-year holiday event. The service, ambiance, and food are spectacular. I always order the black cod and I'm never disappointed.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Fabulous food- and I mean everything we've ever eaten here.Great service and the decor!!

Name: Rasika
Comments: Absolutely delicious food!  Great service and lovely ambiance. A DC must!!

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent service and amazing food. Consistent great quality.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Delicious food options, albeit pricey. Nice for a date

Name: Rasika
Comments: Rasika is by far one of the best Indian restaurants in the DC region.  You will not be disappointed.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Best Indian restaurant in the dc area.  Sometimes hard to get in so reserve well ahead.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Hands down the best Indian food I've ever had.  Never fails to impress.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Alway a great place to eat -- you cannot go wrong.

Name: Rasika
Comments: This is one of the best Indian restaurants in all my experiences with Indian restaurants.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Loved the everything on the tasting menu. Nice ambiance.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Great tapas sized servings good for sharing a lot of dishes

Name: Rasika
Comments: I loved the Palaak Chaat. Food was great. Would recommend for a slow dining experience.

Name: Rasika
Comments: I love this restaurant. The flavors are bold and delicious. The service is outstanding every time I go ( I have been to Rasika 3 times now). I highly recommend this restaurant for lunch or dinner in DC (either location is great).

Name: Rasika
Comments: Service was great, food was good but portions were so small and none of the dishes come with rice... you need to order rice and pay for it.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Food was mildly spiced and excellent.  They handled a large party of 20 or so very well.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Many good dishes; however, my experience here, with its modest portion sizes and sometimes too subtle flavors, left me missing the experience I get at a good, traditional, American-Indian buffet.

Name: Rasika
Comments: This is my favorite Indian restaurant. Love, love, love.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Good. Hidden gem. Food was good and so was service. Beautiful place. Not expected.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Delicious! Great service and ambiance. Would recommend for a special evening out.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent, unique, Indian food and lovely ambiance.

Name: Rasika
Comments: A little pricey but the food and service are consistently fantastic

Name: Rasika
Comments: Great meal! Tried the tasting menu so explored many dishes.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent food and service.  An authentic dining experience.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Great ambiance, food selection, and variety. Great service by wait staff and managers. Attentive but not helicopter-ish. Great for intimate groups (4-8).

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: What a fabulous experience. From the moment we're greeted at the door we feel like royalty visiting somewhere else. What an atmosphere in the dining room. Expert wait staff, and the absolute finest food in Cincinnati - and that's a high bar given the alternatives available. Go with the the 3 (or 2) course menu and wine pairings for an unbelievable taste experience.  Not something we can afford very frequently but we get there for the big events.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Excellent food and service. Duck and lamb were excellent!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Always great. The Rabbit is phenomenal. Service and ambiance can't be beat.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Jean-Robert defines elegant dining in his several venues across town. Restaurant's impeccable service is utterly unobtrusive and the servers are well-informed. We have dined there on several occasions, both in the restaurant and in the bar, and have come away pleased. This time we opted for the 2-course dinner with pairings, and while the food itself was well-prepared it was not the perfection we had come to known. The wine pairings, though, were superb, as were the selection of in-house pastries for dessert.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Great slow dining experience to appreciate delicious food and wine.  For those that appreciate fine dining, classy atmosphere and are willing to pay for it.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Wonderful! Menu gourmand was exceptional ! Decor and ambience perfection. Can not say enough good things. A must

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Best restaurant in Cincinnati with beautiful ambiance, diverse menu beautifully presented food offering good value ( bargain compared to large cities) impeccable service,  No one does fine dining better than owners Richard Brown & Jean Rober

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: An awesome menu. Perfect setting. Brilliant presentation. Great tasting dinner. Fabulous wait staff. And...all of that plus Jean Robert de Cavel in the kitchen. I could not ask for more, but I did...all of this in a very friendly. "non-stuffy" atmosphere. PERFECT!Put this winner on your restaurant "bucket list" for sure!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Simply the most elegant restaurant in Cincinnati.  Best food between New York and Chicago.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Amazing food!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Everything was wonderful from staff to food. Nice ambiance.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: L has an attention to detail that is unmatched in the tri-state area.  Outside of NYC, there are few places that I've seen that can execute to this level of perfection.  Every detail of the dinning experience, from the grand bar and service, to the entry of the magnificent dinning room, to dinning service - all done with grace and flawless delivery.  No detail in the dinning experience is trivialized.  The thoughtfulness is seen throughout a perfectly choreographed experience.  Their attention to GF was outstanding.  I'm grateful to have this set of amazing restaurateurs in Cincinnati that can have this level of execution.Thank you, team L for another wonderful experience.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Having had superb dining experiences in the past, there is not much more to say except it is still superb. Service, food, and ambiance continue to be in the top tier in Cincinnati. For a very special evening at, by the quality standard of the restaurant, a very reasonable price, one could not find a better place to dine.We will go back often.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Everything was delightful....music agreeable, but a tad too loud...

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Restaurant L is a very special destination and we had a wonderful evening!  Be prepared to spend time there, enjoy the atmosphere and excellent service, as well as the exquisite cuisine.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: An experience! The ambiance is outstanding and the food is delicious. Service and taste were at a level I've never experienced before.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Just a wonderful experience. This is why it is one of the very best restaurants in Cincinnati. Expensive but worth it. Service was great!!!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Wow!  Tremendous service and food!  The chef was amazing and greeted our group a couple times to explain the menu.  He was fantastic!!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: L is my wife's favorite " special occasion" restaurant.   The gourmand menu was superb as well as the service.  Thank you Max and Richard.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: This is our favorite restaurant for special occasions.  It was great to see chef greeting guests.  Everything was superb and outstanding.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: First time there, met a friend for lunch.Was offered the Friday express lunch in the lounge so we decided on that. First course was soup or salad and second course was a Pho burger or chicken crepes for $12.Delicious!! Will go back again for dinner.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: What a gem in red neck Cincinnati, the place is somptuous, the service perfect although a bit too fast, they wanted to close early, with just three tables that evening. The show is the inventive food of the French chef, at the level of a  star Michelin if the inspectors knew where Cincinnati was! A bemol to this otherwise perfect evening: the wine pairing done with perfectly low quality boring wines. Not acceptable for such gorgeous food.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Love the restaurant.  When I want a casual night out with friends, I go to the bar area.  Couldn't be better.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: A wonderful experience from start to finish!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Everything was delicious. Ambience was great and the staff was fantastic.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Everything was perfect, as expected.  One table of six got a little loud periodically.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Exactly what should come with fine French dining....great cuisine, great wine, attentive and gracious service.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Outstanding preparation and service.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Every visit to Restaurant L is a wonderful experience. The food, service and staff make this a visit to be enjoyed and savored. The presentation is wonderful and the food is excellent. Love the wine pairing option. This enhances the flavor of each course. The room is beautiful and the ambiance special.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: AAAAMMMMMAAAZZZZIINNGG!   It was a perfect date night the food was fabulous!  The staff was great and informative!  We had the Gourmand menu and its was wonderful from start to finish.  The dining room ambiance was great

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: The service was exceptional as usual. Only one error, a colleague asked for more bread which never came. Food was amazing.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: This was a wonderful dining experience ! The food was excellent and the service was outstanding !

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: We each got the 3 course Prix Fixe menu. What a great way to try multiple delicious food.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Beautiful and delicious, a great experience

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: What a great choice to celebrate my wife's birthday.  We have always enjoyed the Orchids but it has not met our expectations in  quality of food and service.  We decided to try Restaurant L this year and were pleasantly surprised.  There were many mixed reviews regarding L, but nothing but raves from us.  The room was beautiful and the service was superb.  The food and presentation outstanding.  We chose the three course dinner with the wine pairings  WOW for both. The flavors of each course were wonderful and the venison hit the jackpot.  The wines worked very well with the food and certainly enhanced the flavors of the evening.  We certainly look forward to return visits.  In our book it is the best restaurant in Cincinnati.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: 3 course prix fixe with wine pairing. 5 star Euro experience from start to finish Chef came to  each table to greet and check in. Staff knowledgeable and very open and personable. Richard Brown is wonderful historian of restaurant industry in Cincinnati as well as NYC and Europe.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Nothing can beat their Friday express linch in the bar.  2 courses for $12.  Of course we included a bottle of wine and desserts too.  The soups here are always heavenly and no one does salmon like this place.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: We went to L's to celebrate my sister-in-law's retirement.  We had great quiet evening where the staff continued to excel in everything they did.  The drinks were outstanding and the menu was better than expected.  I'm looking forward to my next visit to L's, to see what's new on the menu.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: While we enjoyed the relaxed atmosphere and felt no rush, some of the service did lag a bit.  However, we were greatly accommodated and we are happy to recommend Restaurant L to others.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: My wife and I had a wonderful Christmas lunch. The 4 course tasting menu was superb! Always a wonderful time at L. It is a very special place.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: In my opinion this is the best Italian restaurant in the city. I always know I will be greeted like a friend and that I will not be disappointed in the service and food.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Had a great time at Riccardo Enoteca! Due to the current restrictions on dining in Chicago, the only available seating for the restaurant is outside on the sidewalk lining the restaurant. The street is very cute and was not busy. Out server was very friendly and knowledgeable about the food. We enjoyed the Caprese salad and the grilled octopus. I had for my entre the sea bass and it was pretty good as well! Great place for a date.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Great service and wonderful food. I loved the trout, with a nice red sauce and veggies. Lovely ambiance on the patio.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Food was very good but not sure its worth going back again given how many Italian places there are in the city. Service was not great... very pushy and made a super rude comment about us ordering so much food.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Really great food, always fantastic service!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: A gem of a spot. Keep them in business. Please go. MUST order the fava e peccorino. Enjoy!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: The food is delightful and the service is impeccable.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: These guys rock! This is neighborhood dining at its best!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Amazing food and amazing service still one of the best in Chicago.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Riccardo never disappoints. Enoteca is my favorite location, but my experience at all three locations have been consistently exceptional. The food is truly outstanding, and the service impeccable. Everyonefrom the servers, support staff, and managementis personable, friendly, and happy to see you. I highly recommend our server, JP. He is conversational, funny, and delivers excellent service. I have a hard time not ordering my favorite dish: Rigatoni alla Buttera. This time, we also tried the burrata over arugula with pesto and the tortelloni. Both wonderful. As a restaurant manager, I am not ashamed to say this is my favorite restaurant in the city, and I do not work here!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Great to be back on the patio! Food as good as ever!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: The staff is always friendly, accomodating and safe.  JP and Juan are always quick to remember you and help cover each others table if need be.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: What a great night! The outdoor tables on the sidewalk were shaded and attractive, the service was friendly and attentive and the food was great.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Excellent! Great neighborhood spot - we will be back!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Wonderful service, great patio. Will definitely be back!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Dinner outside with two friends, service was top notch with very attendance waiter and food/ wine was fantastic ! We were part of the uncovered patio and when it started raining our server moved us under the umbrella with all new silverware, which was greatly appreciated. Highly recommend this spot for great Italian, nice portions and a wonderful ambiance !

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Absolutely fantastic!   Sat outside and we were covered by the passing rain shower.   The food was delicious and service top notch.   So happy we found this restaurant!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: We had a 9 p.m. reservation Friday evening and it was so nice to be able to dine at Riccardo Enoteca again! We felt the table distancing and precautions were excellent. The service and food were exceptional, as usual!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Amazing experience overall! Fantastic service and fantastic experience.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Old reliable. The most consistently good restaurant in Chicago.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: They have a decent wine collection. Good service too.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: The service was amazing. The entire staff was extremely friendly and attentive. The food was delicious. Loved it and will definitely return.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: This is a very cozy neighborhood restaurant that has a terrific menu to please a variety of tastes. The help is exceptional--friendly, helpful and efficient. I have dined here many times and will continue to do so! It is a bit pricey but worth the $$ since the dishes are so delicious.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Perfect neighborhood spot worth leaving your own neighborhood to visit! Delicious food, great ambience, professional and friendly service.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Very accommodating, will custom prepare a dish if necessary.  Authentic cooking and great neighborhood atmosphere .

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Best Italian restaurant in the city!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Everything was so good; the wine, the complementary bruschetta, arugula salad, prosciutto pizza, and surprise birthday tiramisu. Friend was late for our reservation, no problem. We  shared a pizza, no judgement. Very friendly, genuine service -  attentive and unobtrusive. Genuine Italian fresh, quality food full of flavor- the cooks have the gift! Welcoming, soothing, and lively atmosphere. A real gem. Highly recommended.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Lovely spot with so many great food choices it was hard to pick!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Excellent everything! Would recommend for any event or just dinner. Value is excellent, great wine selection and the food was best Ive had since leaving NJ. Will definitely be back.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Always such a great meal and outstanding service.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Always love Riccardo's.  Friendly staff and delicious food.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Absolutely love this place. Classic italian, delicious food, low key setting.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: I am always amazed at the quality of the food and the excellence of the service.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: This is one of our favorite restaurants of all time.  We live a five minute walk away and always ask ourselves why we don't eat here more often.  The service is helpful and friendly.  The food is outstanding.  Never had a bad time here.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Food is wonderful and the service was exceptional. Made us feel special.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Excellent neighborhood restaurant. Exceptional food and super personable and professional staff.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Food and service were excellent. We came on a VERY cold night and were seated just in front of the door and asked if we'd be frozen out in that location. We were offered a 20-30 minute wait for another table but they said we'd be OK. The restaurant has a long entry between the outside door and the inside door. There is a sign asking people to make sure that the outside door is closed before opening the inside door. A member of the restaurant staff spent much of his time by the inside door to make sure that guests observed the request.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Great pizza, good wine selection and friendly neighborhood spot.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: This is one of my favorite restaurants in Lincoln Park. Cesar, JP, Juan and all of the chefs and staff are top notch  friendly, courteous and always provide great recommendations, superior service and delicious meals. I cannot say enough about how much we adore Cesar! Riccardo should be very proud of him and all who make this restaurant so great! And Riccardo himself is the best of the best of all chefs in Chicago and a lovely, kind, intelligent, amazing person too! I do not know many who have his passion, kind heart and amazing talent!!!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Food and ambiance was of the highest quality.  Highly recommend this place.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Fantastic restaurant with innovative food.  Packed every night.  Tip - go and wait at 5.30pm when they just open and you can sit at the bar!

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Incredible food, incredible service. Would go back in a heartbeat but very difficult to get a reservation.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Another amazing place....excellent food and experience.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Always a solid choice.  Creative menu, smart wait staff.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Absolutely loved the place.  Our waiter was very nice and helped us make good menu selections for it being our first time visiting.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Top notch culinary experience, yet you may come away hungry

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Fabulous.  Great for foodies, anniversaries, theatre.  Just great food and wine

Name: Rich Table
Comments: the food is delicious. ideally located and tolerable noise level

Name: Rich Table
Comments: We rolled in at 5pm without a reservation and sat right away at the bar. We shared a tomato bone marrow butter toast and also split a pasta dish and a chimichurri rib eye as well. It was all delicious. The bartender was friendly and attentive. Try Pep in your Step for a drink, it was outstanding

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Outstanding service and meal.  Always a treat to come here.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: great food small neighborhood rest. need reservation

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Nice hearty food in nice ambiance. we get takeout all the time. try the roasted broccoli !

Name: Rich Table
Comments: GREAT.  Attentive, delicious, innovative.  Save up your $$$ and colories for this one.  Its absolutely worth it.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: This place is worth every penny.  Its creative visually and stimulates the taste buds beyond belief.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Creative dishes, fresh ingredients, service was absolutely fantastic!  The tasting menu was a fun experience, wine paring was a nice compliment.  My partner and I shared the pairing which worked out nicely.  Will definitely return!

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Waitress who had a bad attitude from inception It made the dining experience very uncomfortable

Name: Rich Table
Comments: This place is phenomenal. My only complaint is that maybe the seating could be a little more comfortable but the food and wine pairings are so good that it doesn't really matter.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: The food was very good, the service was outstanding and he atmosphere rustic and enjoyable.  I will return.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Glad we went! The Staff was very friendly and energetic and always helpful. Rich Table is a "must try".

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Husband 40 birthday

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Our server, Dana, was fantastic! When I told her that I brought a big wine  to share with our friends, she immediately offered to decant the bottle. We had a symphony performance after dinner, and she made sure that we were able to leave the restaurant in time to make our curtain. Dana was friendly, efficient and knowledgeable regarding the menu.  She made our evening more enjoyable. The food was top rate. We shared appetizers and each had an entree. We especially liked the porcini donuts, rock cod, and rib eye steak covered with onion rings. Looking forward to returning in the future.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Weve come here for Anniversary a few times now. We always have a good meal. Excellent food. Always tasty. One of our favorites in SF.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Very Imaginative cooking, served very "warmly" professionally, totally non-pretentious totality. Quite enjoyable and special.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Excelllent food and a highly trained staff who know the menu and knows even better how to make you feel at ease.  A fantastic experience from start to finish. We will be back - if we can get a reservation, that is!

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Bday, great atmosphere and vibe

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Yes, this is a great restaurant. We had the tasting menu with the pairings. There were three of us and we basically got the entire menu and each dish was fantastic. The pairings suited every dish and the best part was each of us had a different dish with a different pairing and it was a true in depth and varied tour of mostly local wines and beers and ciders. A very fun evening. Hope to return!

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Loved it! Delicious food, attentive staff, what more does one ask for.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Great night and food at Rich table. Per ballet meal. All dishes were exceptionally good from the signature donuts, to the soft shell crab and the various pastas. The lasagna was unusual and good, the bucatini with peas and mint a nice blend with cheese topping.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: My wife and I were passing by San Francisco, heard great review about this place. The food were amazing, we will definitely come again.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Great night and food at Rich table. Per ballet meal.  All dishes were exceptionally good from the signature donuts, to the soft shell crab and the various pastas.  The lasagna was unusual and good, the bucatini with peas and mint a nice blend with cheese topping.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: First time to RT  we were not disappointed! The buccatini was our favorite pasta dish. Highly recommend. We ordered the hush puppies and perrogies as well, both of which were excellent. Most people around us got the porcini doughnuts though, probably shouldve had those as they seemed popular. 10/10!

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Great food, but overpriced, and wine list is crazy. Starts at $60, and wine wasn't even that nice. Also charged for bread and butter, which is always annoying. Great menu, but you really need a large group to do it justice by sharing. There are too many courses for two to enjoy.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: This was one of the best experiences I have ever had.  There are a lot of wonderful, unique restaurants in San Francisco.....but this one is particularly special.  I recommend doing the chef's tasting menu.  Also, the Rich Table cookbook is a lot of fun.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Our dinner and dessert with Tiffany and her associates was phenomenal - cant wait to go back!  Thanks so much, everyone.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: a little bit salty. The ingredients are all fresh and special.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Food and drinks were amazing and service was wonderful.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: You guys are the best!!! Keep doing it!!!! Thanks!

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Amazing funky food. Fit for foodiesIf youre from out of town, dont miss this spot

Name: Rich Table
Comments: The food was delicious and the service warm and helpful. The servers suggestions were perfect in terms of portions and dishes.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Anniversary

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Love this place.  Safe and service unmatched!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Welove this place!  Dignified.  Our server (Jeff) is the best.  We are happy to bring our friends here for a nice dining experience.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Food was tasty, service was good, and the expanded outdoor space was attractive for this pandemic summer.  A minor negative is that noise levels from the street, from police sirens and motorcycles, was a bit distracting.  Highly recommended.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: We love RL for the personal service the wait staff gives from the minute the hostess greets you upon arrival. Very special place & great food!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: RL is a gem in the city. Dining el fresco is wonderful though be prepared for some city noise from being in Chicago Ave. The staff is top notch. There is an old school elegance that RL offers that cannot be matched.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Good food, always a must when in city drinks or dinner

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Wonderful first time experience. Friendly staff...

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Just the best! Always a favorite.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Birthday.   Its a tradition for us.  We always celebrate my husbands birthday at RL and we have never been disappointed!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: A truly gracious place that makes you feel special for just showing up. Everything about it is wonderful. Beautiful place, perfect food and welcoming servers.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: If looking for a place to enjoy a romantic evening, RL the Restaurant is the place. The service and the food was excellent. Very accommodating making sure whatever I needed was quickly provided. Safe environment considering COVID19 .

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Everything was great. We were outside and tucked away distanced from the other tables. Happy to be back!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: I had a wonderful birthday dinner at RL. The manager Michael went above and beyond to make sure we felt welcomed and attended to. The restaurant decor is truly remarkable and the servers have a plethora of knowledge regarding the vast quantity of wine and spirits they have available. My Ros was light and airy and the steak melted in my mouth.  Overall I had such a great experience and I would go again on another special occasion.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: RL is a special and unique dinning experience! I highly recommend!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Lunch with the girlfriend. We sat outside, only thing noted, mosquitos were really bad. Maybe put out some plants to help with that.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Our server had a special kid item made for us. Menu is smaller. Service is always excellent.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: So great to be back! Aramis is a fantastic server and RL never disappoints!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Perfect restaurant in every way! One of my favorites.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: It's a must stop when you are in Chicago.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Great server and good was unique as well as yummy

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Great food. Nice outdoor area.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Great spot for American dining with all the grandeur.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: RL always gets it right.  Love the consistency of food, service and ambience.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Always love the bar. Am from out of town and its always my first stop.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: It was excellent food, drinks and dessert.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Always a solid and consistent meal. Great martinis, wine ambiance, steaks and service. I love the decor and have not had a bad meal here, in the years Ive been coming. If you havent been here, you are missing a chicago staple...and a real treat.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: RL is starting to loose its panache.   It seems like they are cutting corners on little things i.e No longer a basket of assorted breads but some toast on a salad plate,  the salads are smaller and it seems like all the portions are smaller, plus---there is no dress code (customers in jean shorts and tank tops etc We love the ambience and will still go for meals.  Please do not lower your standards!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Excellent meal.  Had the Dover Sole and it was outstanding.  Great service as well.  Very enjoyable family dinner.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Honestly I was so blown away by everything at R.L.  From start to finish top notch, homerun out of the ballpark. For someone with over 20 years in the industry its beyond refreshing to have your socks knocked off. Stellar hospitality, sexy ambience, and professional execution. What else could you want. Thank you R.L.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Scott McClellan, Curt Rose, Christopher Yum, Danny, Russell, Jaipur, SO MANY talented folks! I writing fast or Id keep listing them!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: ExcellentHighly recommend.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: One of my favorite restaurants here in Chicago.  Great brunch.  Food was fresh, delicious, and the service was excellent.  Highly recommend.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Never Disappointed. ALL LOVE! So glad theyre open again.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: 2 best things in Chicago. 1) Calves liver from RL and 2) Brazino from Saigon Sisters

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: We just went for drinks but the service was outstanding as usual.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Amazing food and great service. We can't wait to go back!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Always love RL!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Absolutely incredible! Despite expectations, we got indoor seating in a swank and distinctly American luxe interior; excellent ambiance and the table dress was impeccable. I had the Caesar salad with Chicken, and the Filet Mignon medium rare. Both excellent, cooked to perfection, particular the filet mignon. It was exceptional! Ordered Calamari for the table and it was easily the best Calamari Ive ever had. My guests had the Chicken Milanese and Hand Cut fries, and the Salmon and grilled spinach which they regarded highly. I was celebrating a birthday and she was brought a complimentary brownie with which was plated beautifully and she remarked Im full, but I cant stop eating, everything is so good here! Absolutely exceptional, and well worth the trip. Lucas(?) my server was exceptional, and responded to my needs like an echo to a sound or like a shadow to a shape. Luxurious and grand, exactly what one would expect from Michigan Avenue dining.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: So glad RL is reopened! The oysters were wonderful and chicken parm delightful. Nice to see so many regulars there even with social distancing. Service was excellent as always!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Fantastic!

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: For obvious reasons we could not make it to the reservation but we did order RPM thorugh Doordash and it was still very good.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Service was great. Food was delicious. We loved everything about the experience.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Very exquisite food and very good quality! Sometimes its nice to splurge once in a while, especially in one of my favorite cities. Side note: when you reserve for big groups, I would suggest two people in the group reserving and then coming in person the night before or a few hours before the reservation to see if theres a possibility to sit together. The hostesses were very accommodating. Thank you!

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: This was my second time going to this location and was an attempt to change my initial poor decision. Service was very attentive and friendly. We started with the focaccia and meatballs. The focaccia was delicious and the meatballs were just not my taste consistency-wise. For dinner we shared the gnocchi and wild mushroom risotto which were both delicious. I would recommend this as a stop for a good meal and beautiful ambience.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: One of the best dining experiences I have ever had. The food and drinks were absolutely amazing and there was a wide selection. Our verbal was extremely educated, attentive and outgoing. The pricing is also extremely affordable and reasonable. Hope to be back soon! Thank you RPM and staff!

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Good food and great ambiance!!!

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Very nice experience, food is excellent.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Birthday celebration

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Dre, was amazing. Best service ever. Everyone ask for him. The food is always dependably great.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: We had a very fun experience at RPM Italian. The dishes were very good. Some of our favorites were the Mediterranean Octopus, Brussels sprouts, meatball appetizer, and swordfish. The cocktails were also very well crafted with a long list of bourbons, ryes, whiskeys.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: It was great!

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Outstanding food! This was some of the best tartare we've ever had & the homemade pastas & ricotta were delicious. We will definitely return next time we're in town.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: We were there celebrating a very special birthday and RPM Italian is the guest of honor's favorite restaurant and he goes here all the time. The girl that seated us had an attitude and had a look on her face that she would literally rather be anywhere else in the world to the point where one of my guests had to ask her if she was ok, I'm not sure if she was having a bad day but it was very visible on her face and she acted annoyed when we asked if we could have another table but there was a woman that I wish i got her name because she was amazing and she found out that maybe we wanted a round table and she moved us to the round table. She also brought us a variety of readers when our waitress only brought one pair that were too strong for someone that needed it so I appreciated her so much because I would not have been happy with our experience at all if it wasn't for her. You could tell she cared about our experience which I really appreciated. Also there was a misunderstanding with our waitress on the salads and who was splitting what so we had to order another salad because the way it was split up (which I appreciated that they split them for us), there was a person that was left out and was not brought out a salad. Other than that, the food was outstanding but maybe it was just a bad night but I think service needs to be taken up a notch because that is also a very important part of the dining experience.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: What an amazing restaurant! The wine list was spectacular and the sommelier was very knowledgeable and directed us to an excellent Tuscan red. I am vegan and there were plenty of options!

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Great food! Great experience and service was excellent!

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: The server was very rude and the food was cold.  She would rush back and forth by our table and never stop to ask how our meal was.  I have dined here many times and have always enjoyed the experience but was highly disappointed by our server.  Not polite or accommodating and rushed us.  Sommelier was excellent and took great care.I had guests from out of town that I have been raving about the restaurant and was embarrassed about the experience.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Pasta was too al dente, but sauce was great and service outstanding

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations
Comments: Wonderful!  Great food.  Matthew was our server.  He was so great.

Name: RPM Restaurants - Multiple Locations

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: As we walked into Rudy and Paco, i immediately knew that the restaurant  exceeded my expectations. The upscale, but comfortable and almost historical feel of the place assured us that we made a good choice. Our experience only got better from there. We were greeted my Paco himself before we were taken to our table by a very friendly hostess. Shortly thereafter our waitress introduced herself and brought us a lovely plate of ribboned plantains with chimichurri sauce and Paco Pico sauce. The light and crunchy plantains successfully served to whet our appetite for the rest of our highly-anticipated meal. My husband and I shared a plate of escargot. The delightfully soft and warm bread that accompanied the dish was quite pleasing. As we were there to celebrate our anniversary, we ordered a Prosecco cocktail that was enhanced by hibiscus syrup with candied Hibiscus at the bottom of our glasses. It was a great Segway into our main course. My favorite thing about Galveston seafood restaurants is that they know how to prepare gulf coast seafood- Rudy and Pacos treatment of the red snapper that I ordered was painstakingly good! It was cooked to perfection and adorned (not overdressed) by avocado, Paco Pico, and lump crab meat...good stuff!  My husband wasnt too fond of the scallops dish he ordered stating that they were cold and not very flavorful. Aside from that, the wine selection was ample, and my tres leches dessert was heavenly! It was swimming in the milks that flavored each drenched and spongy bite! My only critique, if I have to list one, is that the sides are lacking. Although I am a purist, and I like my veggies plain and lightly steamed which they executed successfully, I feel that a restaurant of their caliber should step up their sides game. I loved the brocolini, but I would have appreciated a wider range of sides from which to choose such as a lively beet salad to compliment that beautiful piece of fish. I would, and will definitely return!

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: What a great experience! I spilled some of the sauce on my dress shirt and Paco was over in an instant with club soda to wash it out.  He is attentive and a great restauranteur.

Comments: We had gone to the Saddle River Inn a few times back during the reign of owner and master chef Hans Egg. Therefore, we were somewhat sceptical of what new owners Jamie Knott and Peter Lioia would do in order to sustain the immense tradition of this fine establishment.Well, skeptics no more. The new owners have masterfully sustained legacy dishes (read: Maribar) and interlaced new and creative dinners and appetizers alike.This is to say nothing of their par excellence dining room staff. The wait staff, host, support, and coat check are all extremely professional, lively, and not the least bit pretentious or robotic.Lastly, we always end our visit with a walk around the wonderful grounds and adjacent areas. The pictures additionally prove the resounding point that this legendary spot remains strong.
