Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Very disappointing evening. The food was still good, but not worth the money. Service was noticeably poor, while outstanding service has long been a hallmark of St. Jacques '.We had ordered a special dessert, as has been our habit. Clearly the new chef had no idea what he was supposed to do, yet the order was taken and I was not called about it ahead of time. We will most likely not return.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Lovely!Server was perfectly attentive & professional. Food was divine!

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: French food is not my usual go to but Saint Jacques is definitely the place to go for a special evening, whatever it may be.  The french wine and seafood dishes we ordered were excellent.  My friend ordered the pitterfoiles which she said were devine.  Our server was fabulously informative, friendly, and attentive.  A perfect evening!

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Late lunch with my niece. The great food added wonderfully to the flow and spontaneity of our conversation. Thanks. Katharine

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Dessert was awful. Server was going to take it off of the price but I said no. Should've reconsidered.Dan

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: It was a wonderful experience.  Service, food and presentation was superb

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Service at Saint Jacques is excellent.  Food is delicious.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Excellent service, almost all the food was excellent except for the beer tenderloin.  My husband asked for it medium rare and it definitely came out well done.  We opted to not send it back as to not ruin the evening plus the overall taste was excellent.  Just expected better for a steak that costs that much.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Ive eaten here before..... best French Restaraunt in area ..... was here for Valentines Day.... prefixed menu.... I knew it wasnt going to be the quality of the normal menu, but did expect it to still exceed other restaurants.   I was very disappointed.  Clearly focused on profiting on a special occasions by sacrificing the quality of their product.  Im sure the chef knows since they taste what goes out of their kitchen.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: We've dined here for over 10 years and have never been disappointed.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Sweetbreads were overcooked. Potato au gratin with lamb was watery and had to be sent back.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Cocktails, appetizers, desserts & presentation were outstanding. Entree which was a puff pastry with seafood tasted like the chef made a mistake with the black pepper. I questioned the taste but the server did not offer to check on the sauce. Of course, this was the priciest portion of the meal. Expect to pay about $100 + each for the meal.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Celebrated my daughters birthday there and we had a wonderful time. We lived in France for many years and my daughter was born in Paris so a French themed birthday felt appropriate. The atmosphere was comfortable, noise level was good so we could hear ourselves talk. Not a big place but the tables were spaced well so we didnt feel like we were on top of anyone.Food was delicious, service was friendly and attentive. We all agreed that it was an enjoyable experience

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: We celebrated my husbands birthday here and it was fantastic. Service was prompt and everything was delicious. We will definitely be back and will be recommending to friends.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: We have LOVED Saint Jacques in the past, but I had a bad dining experience over lunch last week. What I was hoping for as an indulgent treat turned into a virtual nightmare. Ambiance: There were three VERY chatty and loud women in the restaurant, to the point where I could hardly hear myself think. I discreetly asked about their meal status (wrapping up, etc.), and the lovely waitress shared that they had finished - not so. I had to endure their political and gossipy conversation for an hour - could not wait to leave. Food: Again, we typically love this restaurant, but my seafood soup was gritty and the entree very rich. My posting is not so much as a warning about their food, but a heads-up to check out how loud the restaurant might be during your dining experience.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Lovely lunch and Birthday celebration!  Quiet restaurant with delicious array of baked bread, nice wine choices, delicious mussels and on the Birthday girls dessert plate- chef had written joyeaux Anniversaire in chocolate- a nice touch!

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: My husband and I celebrated his birthday there and very much enjoyed every aspect of the experience. Highly recommend the lamb and scallops.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: We enjoyed our dinner very much.  We read about the restaurant in Walter magazine.  It was refreshing to find an authentic French restaurant in a strip mall.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Decided to try this place based on other reviews. We were not disappointed.  It is quaint, although located in a strip mall, they have done  good job of making the inside feel warm and inviting.  The attention to detail was nice.  Things like seating us apart from other diners when the restaurant was not yet full (we were there at 5:30) and offering dark linen because we were wearing black were appreciated. Aso,asking about allergies before beginning service, and waiting for our complete order so that the plating of all courses could be expertly timed.   Our favorite was the coquilles st jacques appetizer.  The beef bourguignon was hearty and delicious and my filet was actually medium rare which almost never happens. ( I do wish i had felt more adventurous and ordered maybe the fish special, because I decided I do prefer a good amount of char on a grilled steak, but that is personal preference. ) The butter cookies to take home were a lovely touch.  Overall a wonderful experience and we really appreciated a quiet spot for  conversation at the end of a busy week.  Perfect for a date night.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: As always, food and atmosphere were fabulous!  This is  our restaurant of choice for special occasions!

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: It had been 20+ years since we had been to Saint Jacques. Obviously new owners, chef, etc. Still the best French food in Raleigh. Delicious!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Great atmosphere!  Bar area was very energetic, food was excellent and priced moderately!  Definitely will be back for more!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Shinsei is doing a great job!  Very professional dining experience.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: It was great

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Shinsei did a wonderful job considering the new parameters and wearing face masks.  The staff all wore masks, tables far apart and the food was outstanding!!!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: The service was very slow and the quality of the sushi rolls has really declined.  Just not a meal worth the price tag.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: The whole fish is a must!!!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Always amazed by the quality of the staff and ambiance.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: I made reservations for this past Saturday, the 11th.  I confirmed the reservations as requested.  Upon arrival there was no valet or sign of life, however we drove around the block several times and settled on a parking spot across the street.  When we got to the door there was a handmade sign stating that the restaurant was temporarily closed and would re-open on Monday, the 13th.  It will be a long time before I return.  I even checked the restaurant website several times in search of a favorite dish and there was absolutely no indication that it was closed.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Everything was wonderful!  We went for my son's birthday and they made it very special!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Amazing food and service! Always a good time at Shinsei.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Amazing food, solid service, but a dark and loud ambience!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: We took our niece and her mom (my sister in law) to celebrate her graduation. We had a great table upstairs that was nicely spaced from other groups and not very loud up there. Everything we ordered came out quickly and beautifully and was delicious- truly we ate every bite. Our server was perfect.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Service and food were both great.  The table we had for 4 was large and we felt socially distant enough from the other two tables in the room.  Hand sanitizer on the table was a nice touch.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Always delicious and such a fun environment! Don't skip the oysters!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: My absolute favorite sushi restaurant in Dallas -- well above all the others if you love lots of flavors, menu variety, and fresh fish.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Outstanding food and atmosphere. Exactly what we were expecting based on their website. Will repeatedly go back as well as recommend.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Absolutely the best sushi in Dallas, incredible service, and great ambience. Also, the way they have taken steps to keep the patrons safe is noticeable ... and certainly appreciated.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: My friend had never been to Shin Sei. When I used to live in the area I would go 2-3 times a week.  First time I sat in the lounge/waiting area by the front door and had dinner. Everything was great!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Always one of my favorite restaurants in Dallas.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Our Saturday evening dinner experience was great. From the convenience of valet parking, to the cozy atmosphere, to the friendly and  efficient wait staff and finally to a deliciously prepared meal, all our expectations were met or exceeded. We will be back soon.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Food was great and I enjoyed the ambiance and decor, wish the portions were larger but you can certainly taste the quality

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Great time

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Dont sit couples in the bar

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Favorite spot. Think food wAs not as great as usually is. But Ill be back again for sure

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: We took our family for my daughters 12th birthday. GreAt to get out again and Shinsei was lovely!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: The food was outstanding, but the service was slow. The ambiance - horrible. Too loud and seems cheap. For the same money you can get equally good sushi (or better) at several other shushing places nearby with much better ambiance and service.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: The restaurant was spotless and we were greeted by all of the friendly staff.Tammy guided us through the changes  in menu.Mike enjoyed the swordfish.   I had (seriously) the freshest best tasting soft shell crab. That was a delightful surprise.We enjoyed our evening.Jan

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Excellent food and service!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Always a favorite. This place is doing everything right with extra precautions to keep you safe and comfortable.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Awsome foodThursday Duck Night is our favorite Very safe and clean everyone wears masks and glovesWe really appreciate their service

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: This was our first visit to Shinsei and our first post pandemic foray to a dine in restaurant.  We were celebrating our 30th anniversary and I didnt want to cook. The food was delicious!  We tried several different things and shared everything.  Of what we tried, our favorites were the pork buns, miso black cod, and Alfred roll but everything was wonderful.  The challenge will be deciding what to order and what to reorder on our next visit.  The staff was very conscientious about wearing masks and gloves and cleaning between customers.  We felt totally safe.  I highly recommend Shinsei!  Please support them during this weird time!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: It was great! In a time of necessary social distancing and extra measures to make people feel safe/comfortable, they did a good job. The food was delicious!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Great food and great service! I really love sitting at the bar! The bar tenders are fun and friendly.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: As usual the quality of food was stellar and the staff was extremely friendly and knowledgeable.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Great food and wonderful service.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Celebrating getting out of quarantine

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: First time out since Covid began, and we stayed for close to 3 hours! Food was fabulous (our two favorites are the fried rice and dragon lady pressed sushi) and service was great.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Everything was amazing.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Food was amazing and the service was great!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Excellent experience. They did a wonderful job keeping everyone  at least 6 ft apart (social distancing), most employees had their masks on properly (not all, some had their noses uncovered and delivered food or water). The shishito peppers were disappointing, we ordered blistered but they were only cooked until soft, there was no blistering. Everything else was delicious. Love the presses sushi!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Very good sushi

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: This is neighborhood gem.    Quality is always super high.  Staff is extremely friendly and helpful.    Ask them for help. Daily specials menu is critical.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Shu never disappoints!  The food is fresh and delicious and the staff is really friendly.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Delicious as always!! My favorite sushi restaurant!!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Great food, great service! Very cute location, highly recommend Shu

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Love Shu - the staff, sushi chefs, everyone is so chill & nice for a busy, really great/ solid sushi house. Love all the options and every dish is so yummy - love their dressings on the fish, so complimentary, fresh & flavorful

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: The best sushi in LA! Everyone we came across were hospitable, respectful and kind. We will definitely return in the near future!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Always good black cod. Small portions and need to order side soup and rice for the price it is pricey.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Great location!  Good quality of the fish.  Just the tables are too close to each other.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Better than serviceable. I'd give it 3-1/2 stars. The tempura appetizer was first rate, the spicy tuna was fine, the soft shell crabs were below par (fishy and not delicate).Beware of Saturday parking. There is a free valet but the parking can be a mess. Part of a decent set of restaurants halfway between west side and the valley.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Very small, tables are uncomfortably crammed next to each other. Sushi however is the best.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Consistently great fish and always wonderful, warm service. A classic spot.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: We dined this past NYE 2019.Sushi omakase-style was spot on!Server was excellent!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Best Shusi in. LA AT ANY PRICE

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Overall, foods were overpriced Very noisy and crowded.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: The fish is excellent. Items other than sushi are best saved for another spot. You will certainly pay for what you get but you're getting some of the best sushi around.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Service was exceptionalSushi fresh and great

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Best sushi! Fresh and great quality. All the dishes are unique and delicious. The service is amazing and the staff is so nice. We dine here once a week!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Always wonderful sushi. Fresh and delicious. Solid service. Fun place.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Ive had this waiter before and he is just horrible. Its a young Asian man, and he always forgets everything! Forgets to let us know they are out of certain dishes, forgets to put in to go orders, forgets what we ordered.  The food in general is great and I always leave a good review for this restaurant, but this waiter is just terrible!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Quality, neighborhood, and service outstanding

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Birthday dinner for boyfriend. The brought us a alive, yes I mean alive lobster on a plate that almost landed on my boyfriends lap. A little too much! But we appreciate the innovation

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Best experience!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Chidori is the best!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: We love coming to Shu sushi! Best time

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Great food, lots of choices, wonderful neighborhood gem. Never disappoints.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Excellent service and the food is fresh and prepared to perfection!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Terrific, as always!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Ive never had a bad experience at Shu. The food and service are consistently good.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Love this sushi restaurant!High quality fish. Unique dishes. Amazing and attentive staff.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Noisy and expensive but delicious and fun.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: We have been coming Shu for years, ever since the Drago Group took over.I can honestly say it has to be among the 4 or 5 best in all of LA.Reservations are a must!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Wonderful sushi.  The salmon was incredible.  Very fresh.  The server was attentive and helpful.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Always the ABSOLUTE best and gold standard of sushi and setting in LA!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Love this place.  The food is excellent, the service is first rate and personal.  The ambiance is relaxed and friendly.  Always an enjoyable experience.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Amazing sushi. My new favorite sushi bar.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Always a great experience

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Excellent food and service

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Great service and amazing food!!!

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Great food!!!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Love Sotto and they did a great job distancing the tables, wearing masks, etc.

Name: Sotto
Comments: We had a great time. I was relieved to see the restaurant implementing so many ways to protect diners and employees from spreading COVID. I cant wait to go back!!!

Name: Sotto
Comments: We had to wear our mask the entire timethe only restaurant or maybe just our waitress who enforced it.  We definitely shared all of our platesthere were three of us on a moms night out.  We ordered three pastas, a bread and an appetizer.  The meals are not huge, but satisfying.  Its not that I wouldnt go back, but its not worth the hype.

Name: Sotto
Comments: The epitome of a first class establishment and its inexpensive. A must stop every time Im near Cincinnati

Name: Sotto
Comments: Wonderful meal. Excellent service. Highly recommend.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Sotto
Comments: Fantastic server with lots of friendly energy and absolutely delicious food. The goat cheese honey bread was as crave-able as expected, and the short rib dish was definitely a show stopper for us. Topped it off with the ricotta donuts and a couple of their very drinkable barrel-aged bourbon cocktails.  We will be returning!!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Delicious, as always- we enjoy Sotto as a date night or a dinner for special occasions and the food did not disappoint!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Service was impeccable. Every dish tasted fantastic. Our server talked me into the newest bread, nduja con broccolo, it was delectable.

Name: Sotto
Comments: We had our engagement dinner here. The food was excellent and the staff was so accommodating. They made our night very special. Such a unique atmosphere as well, loved the "basement" setting!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Food is delicious and service was very good.

Name: Sotto
Comments: First time trying Sotto, definitely will not be the last.  Food was fantastic, our server Hillary was even better.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Music did not fit ambiance . Food was delicious, but overpriced for portions.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Good food. Little pricey. Nice staff, but took forever to get our check. Would recommend though.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Nice visit but I would dine another place in the area for the price

Name: Sotto
Comments: Really enjoyed this restaurant. Cappalacci was outstandingGoat cheese appetizer was deliciousDont forget to get the ricotta donuts!Definitely would go backGet reservations well in advance

Name: Sotto
Comments: Everything was amazing.  Top notch from start to finish, being in the industry we appreciated being able to get out relax and have a great night.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Awesome food & service! Music not appropriate for this type restaurant. Too much metal rock, and too loud.

Name: Sotto
Comments: As usual, Sotto was perfection from start to finish!

Name: Sotto
Comments: What an amazing place to celebrate or just go out for a delicious dinner! Get the short rib cappellacci!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Food was amazing!!  Service was good and the atmosphere was very very nice.  Will definitely return.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Every front of house person we met was available and attentive, informative and fun. Food was amazing and we cannot wait to dine again!

Name: Sotto
Comments: All exceptional, noise level in this acoustic deprived restaurant was better than normal due to Covid...having eaten here multiple times my only complaint has been the noise level...otherwise its a really nice experience throughout...

Name: Sotto
Comments: Food was exceptional and staff knowledgeable and friendly

Name: Sotto
Comments: I had a date here the other night and it was a great experience. If youre looking for a classy, romantic place this is definitely the best restaurant to go to. Great Italian food and loved the service.

Name: Sotto
Comments: We love Sotto! From start to finish, it's always a fantastic and tasty experience. This was our first visit back since Covid started, and we were impressed by the service, cleanliness, and precautions.

Name: Sotto
Comments: A lovely group of people to took care of us while we were there to celebrate!  They were super friendly and patient with my father in law who is hard of hearing!  Each dish was amazing - congratulations to the chef.

Name: Sotto
Comments: It was incredible as usual.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Our server was absolutely amazing and professional! He catered to my boyfriend's nut allergy. Just a wonderful experience

Name: Sotto
Comments: Everything was perfect except for the bread. Dry and burn.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Amazing food amazing service cannot recommend it enough.

Name: Sotto
Comments: I didn't feel completely safe in the environment giving the fact that the tables looked way closer than the 6ft. Might be just my perception. Food, service, music, value, all great. THE BEST in the area for sure.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Fantastic experience from start to finish. Delicious food!!  Can't wait to go back.

Name: Sotto
Comments: We had an absolutely amazing experience for my birthday at Sotto. Their social distancing measures made us feel incredibly safe and the food was delicious as ever. This is my favorite restaurant period and Ive never had a disappointing meal here.

Name: Sotto
Comments: First timer - service was excellent and food was to die for! Definitely will be back!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Exceptional as always, Hillary may be the best server I have ever had anywhere! Food execution is always perfect and everything we ate was delicious. Hillarys knowledge of the menu and ab Uluru to pair your likes perfectly with the menu is amazing. Thanks for going above and beyond with the crostatas, be back soon!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Excellent experience as always. Social distancing and very well trained staff made the difference. We love Sotto, but miss a few items from the old menu. A menu refresh would be welcomed.

Name: Sotto
Comments: We celebrated our engagement at Sotto and it was nothing short of absolutely wonderful! We had a great dinner with excellent service and knowledgeable employees who elevated our experience as they explained more about the reasoning behind wine and menu items. Didn't disappoint, as usual!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Sotto is a Cincinnati treasure. This is our most favorite place, we come here to celebrate the things that matter in our life.We have also come just because, and we have never been let down. Everything about the place is first class - food, wine and staff.We had been waiting anxiously to get back, and plan to return again soon(before anything else happens)!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Amazing food & service every single time!!!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: I took my partner here for her birthday. The care and consideration for the small details is what sets Spinasse apart from other restaurants. Everything from their handmade pasta, to their ingredients, and the level of service from the staff. We really appreciated the thoughtful procedures around masks, social distancing, and overall cleanliness for their employees and guests. I

Name: Spinasse
Comments: These are difficult times but we felt we were a bother by coming.. had to eat on the patio which was virtually on the street. The wait staff would come up behind us and then be offended our masks were not on.. it was just too hard to make for an enjoyable evening

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Amazing food and great service. Servers were very kind and considerate also with the social distancing situation.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: As always, our experience was great, if unusual due to Covid pandemic. All staff was careful & made certain we as guests we, as well. Our table was distant from the next patrons. We felt safe & well cared for!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: I have been coming to Spinasse since 2013 and they are one of the most consistent restaurants that Ive ever had the pleasure of coming to. I get one dish practically every single time. Thats right. The tajarin con burro e salvia Ive been having for 7 years. The consistency of that dish is incredible. Ive tasted other dishes when Ive come with friends, and they were wonderful, but to be able to do simplicity in a high-end way speaks volumes in my book. With the world travels Ive had, eating at Michelin star restaurants, and paying upwards of $200+ for myself for dinner, I still come back to Spinasse to have a big or small bowl of pasta that I havent been able to taste anywhere else, some wonderful wine, and experience the wonderful service. You wont go wrong in coming to, and experiencing the flavors of Spinasse.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Charming restaurant with Piedmontese wines, condensed menu with well-executed and delicious food, as well as warm friendly and sincere service.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: The family style meal was a fantastic way to spend an evening with friends. The staff was also attentive and friendly. Will definitely do  again... and again.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: It was for my bfs birthday. The food was so amazing that we were both blown away. Def a good choice for any type of celebration.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: excellent, as always!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Absolutely exceptional! We did the tasting menu with the wine pairing and were in heaven. It was more food than we could finish but we took everything extra to go so we could enjoy the amazing leftovers the next day. Ambiance was cozy, service was superb and the wine paired perfectly with the food. Highly recommend!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Amazing! Some of the best service I've had, ever! Beautiful romantic ambience, amazing food, great wine selection. Highly recommend this spot :)

Name: Spinasse
Comments: The tasting menu was an outstanding choice for our table of four.  We got to indulge in all of the offerings family style and were not disappointed by the variety and flavors.  The amber negroni cocktail and barolo red wine were memorable as well!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: This was our second time dining at Spinasse and it did not disappoint. The pastas were as delicate and delicious as we remember. The service is always top notch and they really went above and beyond this time. The first time we dined, there was a bit of a mix-up with our credit card but it really was no big deal to us. Spinasse provided us with a free appetizer during our dining experience this time which really showed their genuine care for their customers and patrons. By the way, the complimentary poached egg appetizer was AMAZING.All in all, a delicious meal and definitely reinforced our decision to keep coming back!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Thank you for the best meal yet - complete with wonderfully kind service. Always feels like home.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Great ambience, food, and service. The pasta is amazing. Excellent wine selection but a little pricey. It can be noisy.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: We have had dinner at Spinasse 4 or 5 times now and we love it every time. Incredible food that is different from your normal/typical Italian food. They feature "Piedmont" style Italian and it is unlike any other restaurant with top quality. Simple recipes that are executed to perfection.When you go, you MUST have the butter sage pasta. It is worth the trip by itself!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Our server was attentive and courteous. Food was excellent! Will definitely come back.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Great food, great service and ambiance. Never disappoints!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Stunningly good pasta.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Great Piedmont cuisine and wine. Be treated by staff that knows the menu and cares.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: My first time here.  Very impressed.  One of the best restaurants in Seattle.  Inventive menu, great atmosphere and good value.  Definitely will be back.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Food was amazing and service perfect. A little disappointed that hot tea was not available, but hostess was happy to provide hot water to sip after a full meal. Honestly, some of the best Italian pasta on the west coast.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: There are many Italian restaurants in Seattle and I have eaten at many of them, but Spinass's agnolotti (the evening's special) were squisito...tiny, tasty and just plain perfect!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Very good place for a intimate experience, good food and ambience. I recommend their antipasti sampler and the porkchops.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: As always, an excellent meal and service.  Thank you for making our friend's birthday special.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: As good as always. Great food, service and wine. One of our go to spots in Seattle.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Lovely atmosphere and fantastic linguine. Would venture to say the best Tiramisu that I've come across. Will most definitely be back as soon as possible!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Spinasse is by far the best restaurant in Seattle. The food is phenomenal and the service is unmatched. Love coming here!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Remembered my last experience here several years ago as an excellent meal. This time, was not as impressed. Although I very much enjoyed to antipasta dishes- stuffed pearl onions and a well-plated beet salad, my partner's entree pork chop was fatty and rare. And I was hoping to a flavorful pasta that could be a vegetarian entree but it seemed to need more seasoning. Still enjoyed the ambiance and service, but hoping next time I'll enjoy the dinner options more.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Everything was exceptional. The host could have had more of a personality but thats just a personal opinion. The server was great - very friendly, helpful, and efficient. The food was all flavorful and well presented. If youre visiting Seattle this restaurant is a must.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Small portions of food which did not taste good.  My hubs and I each had a cocktail, and they both tasted like mouth wash.  Dessert was delicious, and the service was excellent.  It had a nice atmosphere, but we were a little too close to our fellow diners.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: It was good. One of my favorite restaurant for date night.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: We had the best experience as Spinasse, I would highly recommend to anyone in the Seattle area. We got a last minute reservation, the food was the best pasta I've ever had. Our server was also incredible, so kind and friendly. He let us test wine's and gave us a complimentary dish. Highly recommend.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Exceptional!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Absolutely delicious food! Excellent service!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: This is one of our favorite places we've been!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Went for the best pasta in town and was disappointed . Pasta was glued by excessive amount of parmesan and slightly overcooked... definitely not aldente ...

Name: Spinasse
Comments: It's is a bit expensive and if you are vegan/ non-egg vegetarian there isnt many options.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: The food was absolutely FANTASTIC!  Our server recommended a great combination of dishes which we did.  The pasta just melted in our mouth, and the pork chop was so tender!  Our server was very attentive, we so appreciated her service!  Thank you - we'll be back!!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Year after year, meal after meal, Spinasse continues to demonstrate why they are in the top Italian restaurants in Seattle.   David brings his special touch to every dish leaving the kitchen.  A way wonderful neighborhood restaurant with global reach.   Every trip to Seattle must include a stop at this gem

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Wonderful...as always!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: The food and wine pairing at St Francis is a must when traveling to Sonoma. The care in which the chef paired the food with wine was superb.  The staff walked us through every course at the right cadence and we were allowed to savor each bite and each pairing.  The menu changes slightly every two weeks so I hate to elaborate on a particular dish but know that this experience is worth every minute and dollar spent!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: betty and I have been members for 25 years.  it's one of the most beautiful settings in wine country. new chef and food and wine pairing staff were great.  under the circumstances of covid 19, it was spectacular dining experience.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Outdoors...perfect day. Ive been several times and this was the best time. Already working on booking again

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: AMAZING!!! We have done this food and wine pairing many times! It is the best food Ive ever had! They got a new chef recently and he has absolutely knocked it out of the park! The wine is also to die for! Do yourself a favor and book this pairing

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: The wine was awesome, 2014 Zin my favorite but I bought a bottle of port since it was also outstanding. The chef did an incredible job pairing the food with the wine. The vegetarian dish with the Malbec was amazing. I cant wait to go back. I would have liked to sit outside for this event but the property is beautiful and  I had great view.Hostesses also did a fantastic job presenting.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Been several times. One of our favorite places. Always terrific food and the new chef delivered superb combinations.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Food was amazing! At Francis is so lucky to have Chef Peter!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Wine is always better with food and when accompanied with the delicious cuisine the chef has created makes for an amazing experience. Andrea and Renee are great hostesses and represent the brand very well.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: We participate in St. Francis' food and wine pairing at least twice a year. This was our first visit this year with the new chef. The food was innovative, delicious and beautifully presented, and we look forward to more tastings from this chef. In the period of Covid, they have made adjustments to increase safety. There were only 10 people at the tasting (I think it usually was 18 or 20 in a room that holds 150+); our table was at least six feet from the nearest one, and we were near the doors which were open. All the wines were pre-poured and the food was delivered by masked staff wearing gloves. One issue: because the staff was all masked, it was difficult to hear/understand the staff explaining about the food and the wines; one staff in particular (new, I think?) was very hard to understand. But overall, a very enjoyable experience that felt quite safe.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Always a great experience.   Excellent food and wine!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: The paired food and wine experience at St. Francis is fantastic.  The dishes presented were very delicious and unique.  Definitely things that I could/would never make at home.  One recommendation would be a palette cleanser between the final dish and dessert. Beautiful dining room.  Beautiful location.  Excellent service.  The host was informative and professional.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: I had a lovely experience! It started with walking onto the beautiful estate. I did the lunch tasting menu and the food was fantastic: perfectly seasoned, perfectly paired with the wines, perfectly portioned. It was an intimate experience as well. There were only 2 couples and I signed up on a Thursday morning. Our "guide" for the experience was knowledgeable, funny, and kind. And the chef came out to chat for a bit when we were all done. I'll definitely be checking out St. Francis again!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Wonderful as always. The new chef is amazing!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Outstanding wine and food pairings. A great experience.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Delicious food and wine pairing. Always a special treat and always excellent.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Had missed the food and wine pairing during Covid stay at home orders. Went yesterday with smaller well placed grouping. With a new chef the menu was outstanding-the usual 5 course offering was plentiful and beautifully prepared and the wines continue to more than satisfy.Especially loved the scallop presentation and the duck.Cant wait to return in the fall!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: I recommend this wine and food pairing experience to everyone.  Good food, good wine, great presentation and nice staff.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Great social distancing and safety with food handling and serving.  Highly recommended !

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Both the food and the wine were OIALEs.  (once in a lifetime experiences).   Proper safety quidelines were enforced without interfering with the beauty of the experience.  We enjoyed a beautiful view of Hood Mountain while we enjoyed some of the best food and wine of our lives.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: We have been wine club members at St. Francis for many years and look forward to the annual complimentary food and wine pairing. The food is thoughtfully paired with wine ending the meal with port and a tasty dessert.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: We do this every year for our anniversary and it never disappoints. Perfect pairing of  wines to moan-worthy dishes. Made even more notable this year as we were the last seating before the Corona Virus shutdown. Thank you to all the staff that made this special. Our hearts go out to you. We'll be back as soon as you reopen!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: This wine and food pairing experience is a must if you are coming to wine country!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: If you are in Sonoma and able to get a reservation, do it! The food was incredible, the wine impeccable, the hosts were funny and knowledgeable. It was one of our favorite things we did during our visit. You won't regret it!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: One of the best lunches I have ever had. There were only 16 places at the two horseshoe tables, so intimate and participative. Wine and food pairings were spot on. We completely enjoyed it.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Best experience we had in Napa or Sonoma in combining wine and food.  Can't wait to go back again.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Even though the food was supposed to take a backseat to the wine, the food itself rivals that of many Michelin starred restaurants albeit without a lot of choices.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: The wine and food pairing was fantastic.  Dont miss if in the area but schedule in advance as it is very popular.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Outstanding in every way. Excellent food and very knowledgable staff. Makes learning about wine fun. Gorgeous setting. Our guests were so impressed on this their first visit that they joined the WineClub.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Fantastic food, wine and staff. I would highly recommend a visit.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Celebrating our Anniversary and had to make this one of our stops. Love it here. Food  and wine pairing is just perfect. So enjoy the small venue because you really get to know the other guest for the seating. Every time we come its special. Great value and delicious!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: This is always a new and exciting culinary and viticultural experience.  I highly recommend this experience to everyone, the team is amazing! The food is lovely and so filling! I only wish they were closer to my home, I'd go weekly as it's such a value.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Fabulous food paired with amazing wines, beautifully presented in a most entertaining and engaging way.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Third time and never disappointed.   Food pairings were perfect.  Hosts were helpful, perhaps a little more about the wine and a little less shtick. Could have taken a little more time.  All in all still the best experience in town.  Hope you take the suggestions as opportunities, not criticisms.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: We booked the wine and food pairing and it was the highlight of our trip to the Sonoma Valley. The food was amazing, the wine was amazing, and the staff made the event educational and fun without any wine snobbery. Cant wait to go back!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Mother-Daughter trip

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: This is what a wine and food pairing should be!  More than just a bit of meat or a bit of cheese, these were chef creations that really allowed one to appreciate the wine being tasted.  On top of that Tamara and Andrea were superb hosts that really added to the experience.  We will assuredly do this again!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: This is a great way to enjoy St Francis' wine.  The food is amazing and service always enjoyable!  This was trip number 3 and I can't wait to go back again.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: FABULOUS

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Ive been to alot of food and wine pairing, but by far this is the best one. Big portions with lots of flavor. Both hosts were very knowledgeable and so polite. I will be back!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: This is our go to restaurant for the best food and atmosphere. Always the best!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: This was my first visit to your restaurant. I ordered the filet and added the crab imperial to my steak for the additional $14 (?) I ate less than half my Steak, 1 or 2 bites of the lump crab. Our waiter was good but busy so another server asked if he could box up my dinner. #1. The box was given to one of the other guests at my table , fortunately they came back to my home for coffee and dessert and we were able to make the switch #2 when I opened my box to put the leftovers in a plastic container my crab imperial was NOT included with my leftovers and that really angered me because I purposely saved my crab to be enjoyed Sunday! And the extra that I paid for was waisted! I immediately called your restaurant but of course got voicemail and so  I left a message about my experience. Of course I did not hear back from anyone. Honestly, I didnt expect to hear back ! I had heard so many good things about your establishment and was happy that we were able to FINALLY GET A TABLE! But my experience left me disappointed.Sincerely , Sandra Morlino

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Why didn't I get points for this reservation?The food was great and was matched by the same great service.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Went here to try out their AC restaurant week menu. We had Joanne as a server and she was outstanding! She was super friendly & courteous. We will definitely be dining there again soon!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: No comment at this time. It was a nice time for us

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Always a great time at Steve and Cookies. From the hardworking, friendly, and knowledgeable staff to the amazing food and ambience. Had a wonderful experience.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: It was an enjoyable experience the wait staff was very informative and very very helpful.  Oscar was the best.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Very nice meal, service a little slow.  Took about 3 hours in all.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Everything was great! The pineapple martini was to die for!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: We didnt even realize that it was Restaurant Week in AC and was pleasantly surprised with the options.  Every single thing was delicious!!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: We had dinner on during restaurant week. As always the food was delicious and the service was spectacular. This is one of our places to dine for dinner on the Jersey shore.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Stephanie, our server was excellent, very friendly and attentive.  She couldnt have been more accommodating.  Food was also excellent. Would definitely go back.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Food and service are excellent.  Unfortunately the noise level is barely tolerable. The Restaurant Week offerings, though not inventive, were really tasty. We will return, in the off season of course.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: If you like a restaurant with great food, service, and atmosphere, this is the place for you!  If you like white tablecloths this is the place for you!  What makes it interesting is the fact that each room has its own ambiance.  I cannot say anything negative....

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: as always the experience at Steve and Cookies was excellent.  the food was excellent as usual. that is why we go there and encourage others to do so. other than Smithville Inn  too many other restaurants in Atlantic County are consistently inconsistent

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: The food was delicious and our server was excellent.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Always fantastic!  Get the pork chops!  They are the best I have ever had.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Food and service were great! best meal my friends and I have had in awhile, will definitely be back!!!!!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Everything was delicious! The drinks are pricey and the parking lot is too small but the food was perfection.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Great food and service.   Love the peanut butter pie for desert

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Fantastic, as expected. Love, love , love this restaurant. Everything was great, food and service. They have the best lobster mac and cheese ever. Would dine here on regular basis if it weren't an hour drive.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: The service was excellent as was the food.  The room was packed but the noise level was very low.   They know what they are doing here.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Food was excellent as always!  Service staff was prompt, knowledgeable, and friendly. My husband said the grilled romaine salad with fried oysters was the best salad he has ever had!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Surprising!  Much more of a dining experience than simply not wanting to cook & going out.  Piano music set the tone for an unique night out.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: The food was good, the ambiance was quiet.. but we went on a Monday. We look forward to trying it again in the summer. The restaurant itself was beautiful!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Great food, service and atmosphere. Perfect for a date night or special occasion!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: We went for Atlantic City Restaurant Week and every course was outstanding!!! Every course was the normal size and the service was also on par. We cant wait to go back!! Our new favorite restaurant!!!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Best restaurant I the state! You can't get a bad meal here, service, food and ambiance is excellent.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: We are restaurant week groupies, Sunday is usually Steve and Cookies. It never disappoints. I am always amazed not only at the quality of the food but also the attentiveness of the wait staff, because they are BUSY.  It is a joy to dine here.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: The pork chops melted in your mouth, excellent meal with friendly good paced service throughout the meal.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Consistently great food.  Well presented.  Great service.  Warm and friendly staff and ambience.  Cant go wrong!!!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Once again going to Steve and Cookies was a great experience, window seat for 4, nice view, quiet spot and the food as always was excellent, can't say enough about the stuffed Pork Chops! The service was right there and helpful, I will be coming back again.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: The server was great n attentive and made suggestions on the menu for restaurant week. I would definitely go back just to eat there, because the food was great n the atmosphere.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Went for restaurant week and had Lobster Mac and Cheese, the Pan-Seared Salmon, and the Chocolate Peanut Butter Pie. All delicious, and the ambience made for a perfect date with my fiancee!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: We enjoyed our delicious dinner and desserts.  We appreciated the birthday treat, too! Our service was excellent - courteous, knowledgeable, engaging, efficient, considerate!

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Food was fantastic

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: We went to our familys favorite restaurant toCelebrate our Son and Daughters birthdays.  Although we try to go to Steve and Cookies as often as possible every time we go it is outstanding.  This meal was six of us, and everybody enjoyed everything.  The food and service, as always were outstanding.  The pace was relaxing and enjoyable.  The consistent excellence is the reason it has been our favorite restaurant for many years.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: Food was great but the prices are outrageous! It was $90 per person and we had middle of the road priced entrees, a glass of wine and one cocktail total and two appetizers.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: The theory of rural inflation is proven once again. This is a very good restaurant serving very good food but it cant possibly be one of the best 100 restaurants in the United States. I have eaten in and reviewed fine restaurants around the world and there is no way that this falls into the top class. What keeps Steve and Cookies by the bay from being a five star restaurant? 1) Presentation. It is barely above the dreaded food on a plate category, it is far short of artful. 2) Attire of assistant waiters who all wear printed black tee shirts, fine at the shore but it is not the dress of a 5 star restaurant. 3) Blatant racism in work expectations. Waiters almost all seem to be white work at a good pace and take the time to be pleasant, assistants in black tee shirts work at a frenzied pace of a car wash as if expecting to be fired at any second. Almost all of the sub class appear to be Hispanic. This just isnt seen anymore. Very good meals and very good service in a rather plain atmosphere, solid 4 star stuff.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: My favorite restaurant!  Does not disappoint!  Excellent all around.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: If you are looking to celebrate a special occasion I highly recommend the Stone House! The location is beautiful, and I love the rustic elegance of the Stone House.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We love eating under the Loquat trees! I also cant live without the tortilla soup every so often. The menu is quite limited right now, so entree choices are few. The bread with the seasoned olive oil is excellent. This is simply a wonderful place for the atmospheric alone!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Perfect every time!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We love the property; cant wait to visit again!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We saw a large rat run across the patio.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Great experience, beautiful facility, terrific food, fabulous service. Would like to see some fresher and more creative menu items but everything we got was delicious.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: My partner and I celebrated my birthday on a comfortably enclosed patio, near a heater.  Our meals were beautifully presented, delicious, and the atmosphere was magical. Standout dishes were the halibut and the duck. Frankly, everything tasted great. Dessert was a wonderfully minty chocolate chip ice cream, apparently made on site. The service was quick and amiable.  My partner and I both agree we had a memorable evening and plan to return.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Fantastic dinner!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: This was the perfect place to stay and eat for our wedding anniversary.  Not sure Ill ever find a more beautiful place to share with my wife.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Phenomenal setting with exceptional service, and great food. Very romantic lunch for my husbands birthday. Would recommend to anyone. Very personable waiter who stopped at nothing to make us happy and welcomed. Highly recommended

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Outstanding environment for a special dinner with family, a mate, etc.  Great food, great service.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: ONLY comment, but important!!!! We were in the inside room......SOOOO dark!!!Waiters had to shine a flashlight on EVERY food presentation, that is rather crazy!!!So as you are eating, you are literally guessing what you are picking up on your fork.This is NOT romantic........candlelight of soft lighting would be preferable.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: nice lil place in the hood, cozy and off the beaten path

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: $50 for corkage for a bootle of wine, we think its a little bit too high, I think. And the fact that they put us in the cellar instead of the main restaurant when we made a reservation almost 3 weeks before was t what we expected. Maybe because we were just a 2 people party. All the rest  was great

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Beautiful place with very friendly staff! Food is great but need to pay attention to different menus if you choose to sit indoors or outdoors.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Service, as always, was top notch. Our party was very pleased with the food but I wasn't thrilled with the halibut.  I found it overcooked and the asparagus cold. The chicken, the chestnut soup, the drinks and the desserts were fantastic. I asked at the time of my online reservation to be seated in the courtyard (we are frequent guests) and a little disappointed that it seemed to be ignored as it looked like there would have been seating available. Nonetheless, the ambience of the terrace was wonderful.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Outstanding service, food and atmosphere!Wait staff was awesome and attentive.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Fantastic food and staff.  Service was very nice.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: A magical place to celebrate my birthday. Staff, ambience and food were wonderful.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Breathtakingly beautiful buildings, grounds and views. Food was mediocre, service a bit slow considering there were very few patrons at that hour. Unfortunately, we were seated next to a very boisterous couple that spoiled some of the ambience.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Anniversary dinner!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Mike provided extraordinary service and made our special dinner very special. His assistant, Al was also wonderful!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Everything, from the greeting at the entrance, to the table itself, to the level of service, to the absolute perfection of the meal...I will be thinking of this for a long time to come.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: My fianc and I decided to join San Ysidro Ranchs Stonehouse for an early Valentines Day celebration. We had an absolutely spectacular evening. The dinner, the service and the ambience was truly stunning. Many of our dishes were prepared right in front of us. The entire dinner was a culinary masterpiece. Afterwards we walked the beautiful gardens and were memorized by the truly magnificent property. We will certainly be back as soon as possible to enjoy the rest of the menu.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We went here for the night after our wedding. It was extremely good food and very romantic. 5 stars!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Great meal and service as usual. Busy Saturday evening with well dressed diners enjoying a beautiful night under the stars of Montecito. The scallops and halibut were delicious paired with the Brussels sprouts and the squash. Goats milk cheesecake for dessert with coffee. Wonderful time.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Fine dining at its best. Very attentive staff. Great ambience. A very enjoyable experience.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Amazing location, food, service, atmosphere. Great experience and a magical setting.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Wanted to order caviar, out of caviar.  Please put one steak on the menu.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: This is best restaurant ever  great service

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We had a beautiful night with impeccable service and delicious food.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Marvelous!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: The atmosphere is outstanding, but we go down from there.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Excellent, attentive service in a beautiful outdoor setting.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We went for our anniversary and had a magical experience. We arrived early, ordered some wine and then walked around the grounds, climbing the hill to watch the fiery sunset. The grounds were covered with beautiful flowers and emitted intoxicating smells. There were lights in the trees and people strolling causally and enjoying the sights. From there we went to dinner where we were escorted onto an enchanting patio with a view of the ocean. The service was amazing and our food was some of the best we have ever tasted. We had Brussel sprouts, a nice salad, halibut and filet mignon. We ended up with chocolate souffl and the homemade mint ice cream. Both were so yummy. We both agreed that the entire experience was one we will always remember.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We celebrated an anniversary...the staff were wonderful!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: This is our second time to this restaurant, and both times have been fabulous!  We would come back to Santa Barbara just for this experience :-)

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Beautiful, location, romantic, with incredible food and great service. Recommend getting the classic steak Diane, which is flambeed tableside. Exquisite!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We love this restaurant, but thought the brunch offerings were just okay for the prix fixe.   Lobster Cobb was good, not great.  Chicken and waffles looked really good, but couldnt fathom paying $75 (includes, champagne, appetizer and dessert).  Will definitely be back when its a la carte!

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: Oh my!  What a beautiful night at Stonehouse. The service and the food was outstanding!

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Great service, even better food. The best sushi in New York easily, if not America. Try it at least once and it will change your perspective on food entirely.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: After watching Jiro dreams of sushi and the fact that Nakazawa now has a star, my expectations going into this meal were very high. While many pieces were tasty, for the price there are better omakase experiences in the city. Exceptional attention to detail is lacking. Moths flying around the bar and Ikea cabinetry take away from what should be a refined experience. The publicly in the press seems to draw tourists rather than local regulars.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Best sushi of my life. Cried when it was over

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Took my girlfriend here for her birthday and it was fantastic.  Everything from the food to the ambiance was fantastic.  Cant recommend Sushi Nakazawa enough.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Great food and great experience

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Such a great experience. Service was friendly, attentive, and thorough. The sushi was some of the best I've had. Will definitely come back again.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Melt in your mouth sushi! First class service. Bar seating is a must for full details of all you are eating. Awesome experience. Perfect sushi lover birthday dinner.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Extraordinary

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Lasciate da parte tutto per un paio di ore e concedetevi questa straordinaria esperienza. Il conto  alto ma laQualit non  da meno. Se volete un vero ristorante happiness andateci

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Fabulous in every way. You must love sushi and respect the artist at work.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: it doesnt worth for the price paid, the omakase had no surprise , just ordinary sushi to me & too rush the time

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Our 50th bdays celebration was well noted. We got some extra un and bday candles in our lychee sorbet! Missed Nakazawa San, but didnt expect to see him on a Monday. A great special occasion place that spoils sushi eating anywhere else.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Lugar excepcional . uno de los mejores Susi que he comido

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Food itself is high quality and sake also very tasty. Delicious. But somehow doesnt match my expectation. Chef seems not pay attention enough.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Another super high end experience

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: La miglior cena a base di sushi della mia vita, una delle migliori cene in assoluto.Dimenticate i pur buoni uramaki fusion e colorati di alcune rinomate catene milanesi.Qui c' la pi pura tradizione del sushi in forma di nighiri. Non dovete scegliere nulla, solo sedervi al bancone (possibilmente, perch  certamente pi interessante di una cena al tavolo), guardare i  maestri al lavoro, ascoltare il nome del piatto in giapponese, prontamente tradotto in inglese dalla cameriera alle vostre spalle e poi gustare ad occhi chiusi.OK, non  cheap, ma non  neanche un ristorante qualsiasi. Il servizio  di alto livello e la qualit eccezionale. Nessun serata al giapponese sar pi la stessa, dopo questa esperienza!

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: The sushi bar was a fantastic experience. Every piece of sushi was unbelievable, the sake carefully selected and the service was impeccable. I was worried it might be a bit stuffy but everyone was so kind and welcoming. It was truly memorable.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Exquisite omakase experience, the food & service is excellent and the attention to every detail is truly impressive.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Terrific and unique experience to sit at the bar and enjoy a curated 20-course dinner.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: EVERY SINGLE TIME we come here, we are transported, healed, fed and showered with the best attention.This is food as art in its highest form.We are extra grateful to Chef for remembering us and welcoming us and to Anthony Arvin for the spectacular wine journey on Monday night. THANK YOU THANK YOU! We cannot wait to come back.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Incredible experience! It was delicious. Must visit for Japanese food lovers. The best sushi me and my friend ever had. Will back definitely.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Wonderful. Best sushi experience ever

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Great sushi with acceptable omakase pricing.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Outstanding in every sense of the word ! Felt transported  to some exotic place in some far corner of the world , yes Tokyo!  The sushi was simply delicious, I could go on forever , service beyond stellar , a fabulous evening , will definitely go back

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Could not love the experience more - despite the fact that

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Their food wasnt good, not even compare to other more price friendly restaurant.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Best tasting sushi Ive ever had in my life.  It was Semi mind blowing

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Fantastic Sushi experience! Highly recommend this if you want a five star omakase experience from an experienced staff! We've been here many times and every single time is an amazing experience!  Wish we could post the entire course but definitely get any and all add-ons if you only plan on going here once!

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: As a huge Sushi Nakazawa fan, I was more than excited to take my brother to lunch at the sushi bar for his birthday. I was lucky to eat here last year and had an absolutely fantastic experience - which made me even more dissapointed in my most recent experience. My brother has celiac disease, which can be an issue at other restaurants, but Sushi Nakazawa reassured us that accommodating his dietary restrictions would not be an issue - we made sure to call ahead of time, remind the host, and checked with our waiter twice. But unfortunately, within an hour after eating, my brother was extremely sick. We had the same exact meal and I was completely fine. When you're paying the prices that you do at Sushi Nakazawa, and have been reassured that they can handle customers with celiac, it's quite frustrating when they fail to do so. The next day I called the restaurant to let them know what happened and the host kindly said they would have management follow-up, but 2 weeks have passed and I haven't heard anything - not even an apology. Shocking when you expect high quality customer service from a restaurant of this quality. This truly is an amazing sushi restaurant, but if you have dietary restrictions, eat at your own risk.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: As close to Japan as you will find in New York.  Innovative touches on fabulous traditional sushi.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Mind blowing and Amazing Perfection in every bite, expensive but well worth it.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: I had 7pm dinner at the bar with my husband for our anniversary. Our dinner experience was first and foremost time well spent together, made sweeter by the cozy ambiance, tasty omakase, delightful tea, and thoughtful service. We enjoyed watching the chefs at work and our exchanges with the staff were brief. If this is the kind of thing your after, go for it. Looking forward to our next meal at Sushi Nakazawa!

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: Food was great!

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: I was thrilled with everything about Season to Go (Taste.) Living very close to there, I intend to make it a regular stop. All of the staff were delightful and the service was impeccable.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste

Name: The Table at Season To Taste

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Just the single best restaurant experience in the Boston/Cambridge area. If you can get a reservation, gab it. You will be happy

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: This is our third visit and it is our #1 restaurant in all of BOSTON. As soon as the menu changes we will go back. Name: The Table at Season To Taste

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Such an amazing email, every single course was perfectly made, interesting, and delicious. Our service was top notch. We chose to do the wine pairing, I highly recommend! Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: One of the best new places we've eaten in Boston area! Outstanding service, very knowledgable about al wines...truly excellent!!! Bravo!

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Wonderful 5-course fixe price dinner with paired wines.  Each course elegant with food combinations most interesting.  Great service too.  Expensive, but worth it.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: We had a lovely time at The Table -- the food was inventive and delicious, and the atmosphere was friendly and casual.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Top notch experience from walking in the door to leaving. Service was impeccable and attentive.  All dishes that came out were beautifully presented and a full work out on our taste buds. I cant wait to return with friends that havent yet enjoyed The Table.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Loved this very special restaurant. Not only was the food creative and delicious--it was served by the most well informed, pleasant group of people...Very happy you are part of the restaurant scene here!!

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Excellent food. Several of our dishes were exceptional. The coursing/timing was off sometimes, but they have a small service staff and they are preparing everything fresh so that's to be expected. Otherwise, we thought it was really wonderful. The people were very nice, the setting was intimate and the food was fantastic.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: This restaurant is a gem. On our fifth visit it has never failed to amaze us with inventive and polished dishes which taste wonderful and are excellently paired with wines.  The time spent developing and perfecting each dish is evident in the flavor and presentation. Kudos to Carl and his staff all of which are delightful.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Chef Carl does a great job showcasing high quality ingredients!

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Amazing as always

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Outstanding food and hospitality! Jesse was not only a stupendous host but shared some wonderful wine and knowledge with us during the meal. Max and the kitchen team served up course after course of delicate, ambitious and just extraordinary flavors. I cant say enough good things about the entire experience. Thank you to the entire team and enjoy the night shift tonight!! Cheers!! Your good friend, George

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: This is the best restaurant in Boston. Chef Carl is a genius and Mary makes some of the most creative and delicious desserts I have ever tasted.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Apps and dessert were very good.  Lots of extra 'goodies'.  Entree - both the scallops and the steak, were fairly mediocre for a place charging top-end.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: The Table is a wonderful restaurant for special occasion dinners. The prix fixe menu rotates every six weeks and reflects an eclectic set of courses employing ingredients and techniques from around the world. There are two dishes offered for each of the four courses, so go with a loved one and taste every offering. I've gone twice so far and each of the eight dishes I've tried has been creative and excellent. The noise level is low enough to talk comfortably but the tables are separate enough to keep conversations private. You can tell that the staff team is tight knit and enjoys working together. They are supremely knowledgeable and engaged with each other and the patrons, and with little separation between the kitchen and the tables, you can see the food prepared with care. All in all, an ideal restaurant experience. I will go as often as I can.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Delicious, creative, delicate, but spicy. Interesting takes on fine dining in a relaxed, friendly and comfortable atmosphere. Really special.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Always great food with a new menu every 6 weeks.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Wonderful all around experience. Highly recommended for foodies.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Fantastic food and service. Always have a great evening here, can't be happier this is in our neighborhood!!

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Excellent menu and wine flight- a delightful dining experience

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
