Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Amazing food and amazing service! The staff was very knowledgeable and it made every dish that much more intriguing.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: As always an amazing meal.  Each course surpasses the previous and the wine pairings were sublime.  The desserts blew us away....they have always been good but this time was by far the best.  Already booking our next reservation.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Attention to detail, unique flavors and textures, may be the best food in boston overall.  Very knowledgable wait staff.  Nice extras for a hospitable touch- like amuse buche, and take home granola bar.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Unfortunately a mixed bag here.  The food was very well prepared but the menu is extremely limited -- just two choices.   If you didn't like tripe or skate wing (and we didn't), you were out of luck.  However, the real problem was the truly horrible music and the volume at which it was played.  I like everything from Metallica to Bill Evans.  This was just loud noise with a heavy bass.  My guess is that it was there primarily for the chefs in the open kitchen, but it was blaring throughout the tiny dining room.  It was the kind of loud noise the CIA would use to extract a confession.  It ruined the experience completely.  The value proposition is poor at best at $150 a person with beer, no wine.  The chair are hard, no table cloths, and the decor was essentially nonexistent.  A few plastic flowers.  Overall, a huge disappointment.  Excellent bread and butter though.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Wonderful composition of textures and flavors! Superb!

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: Overall excellent although our table was underwhelmed by the marinated mackerel and I thought the skate-sauerkraut combination didn't work particularly well (although each element was very good separately).  The wine pairings were tremendous and the service was excellent.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: This was a repeat visit and we enjoyed the dinner. The chicken that was served was very tasty but was not elevated to a fine dining experience.  Serving chicken as part of a fine dining menu is risky and this time it did not really paid off. My preference is that the restaurant stick to higher quality meats.  Also, I love bubbly wine with my meal and the only choice by the glass started at $17/glass.  I would like to find also quality sparkling wine choices in the $11-12/glass range too so I can have a couple without breaking the bank.  We will keep coming back always hope for a better experience.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: We had ordered vegetarian dishes.  They were all very flavorful and delicious.  We will be coming back soon.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Amazing! It was our first time but definitely not our last!!!

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: We just love this restaurant.  The food is first class. We were unable to eat in the garden the first time we went because it rained. This time, everyone has to eat outdoors!! The staff are amazing and I can't wait to return. We live in Philly and have been to tons of restaurants,  but this is my favorite!!

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Phenomenal meal... I would give it 5 stars, but the hostess interaction left much to be desired. I was 6 mins late to my reservation, which yielded a 3 minute scolding about turning tables and not holding reservations. The conversation continued to include a mandatory end time, as the table would be needed for another reservation. I understand that covid has thrown a wrench in dining... but basic courtesy towards the guest should always be paramount. If im spending $300+ on dinner, you wont tell me when I have to "free up the table" by. And no, im not "ok with that."Server was amazing, food was mouth watering, dessert was heavenly. Aside from a marred interaction with a less than gracious host... the meal was exceptional. Butterscotch pudding for the win. So sad the hostess sat me in the street and not in the beautiful garden area that had open and available tables when I arrived.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Great service from Peter! We loved sitting outside and the food was excellent!

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: We had an amazing dinner. Tempchecks, masks, appropriate table distances, were all appreciated!

Name: Talulas Garden

Name: Talulas Garden

Name: Talulas Garden

Name: Talulas Garden

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Great job on navigating outdoor dining and safety. Excellent service. Food as good as always. It was so nice being out in Philly on a summer Saturday night. Highly recommend.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: There to celebrate the soon to be marriage of friends and Talulas was outstanding in every way. First, they take your temperature using an iPad like device, which is both cool and futuristic too. We said outdoors in their main outdoor space, and the ambience is fantastic. Will go back time and again!

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Great food and service but seating can be rough during COVID. The garden area is beautiful (and half the reason to come) but we ended up sitting at a table on the sidewalk far away from the garden. It really look away from the overall experience.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: These days, we eat outside at restaurants.  We were temperature scanned as we entered.  The spacing of tables in Talula's Garden seemed appropriate for safe distancing.  The staff all wore masks and minimized the direct contact with dishes etc., during our meal.  I felt perfectly safe.The food was fabulous.  Our group of 4 had scallops, short ribs, and salmon for entres, wonderful beet salad for appetizer. Nice sweets for finish.The weather was very hot, but the garden courtyard in the shade made the dinner fairly comfortable.  We're going back!

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Delicious, fresh food and excellent service. First time at Talulas Garden and Id definitely return.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: We had an outstanding experience.  We felt very safe and comfortable eating outdoors with good social distancing between tables.  The service was excellent and our food arrived quickly - including a side we ordered as an appetizer, which arrived just a minute or two after we ordered it (our daughter LOVES cornbread).  I had the short rib.  It was beautifully cooked and tender, and the portion size was quite large.  The flavorful, hearty sauce really tied the dish together.  We all left full and happy.  10/10, we will be going back.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: I love Talula's! I could eat the scallop dish for dinner every night. Thank you to the whole staff for working during these crazy times, and making it just perfect.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Excellent food and ambiance. Very safe social distancing protocols.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Food was incredible and once again we had a fantastic server. Loved being in the outside garden.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Lovely patio setting. Delicious cheese plate and the scallops and succotash were very tasty

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: great job with outdoor dining and delivering excellent food

Name: Talulas Garden

Name: Talulas Garden

Name: Talulas Garden

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: Wonderful food and service (as usual) and a very pleasant ambiance for outdoor dining during these strange times.

Name: Talulas Garden
Comments: This is the 2nd time we ate here.  It was a birthday celebration and we had reservations.   Because of the limited seating in the garden area, due to the pandemic and social distancing requirements (which we completely get) we had to sit out front on the sidewalk which we were disappointed about as we love the garden area and its one of the reasons we came here.  Where we were seated it became very hot as we were the only table that took a direct hit from the sun and they had no umbrellas to shield us and because it was full we couldn't move.  We couldn't even move our table out of the sun.  It was very hot and uncomfortable.   The food, though, was amazing.   We had the beef short ribs, mushroom risotto and raviolis and the pepper biscuits.  They were all delicious.   We had cocktails, as well, which were very good and we would have liked another one, but because it was so uncomfortable where we were seated we just needed to leave.    I would definitely want to come here again, but make a point of sitting at a different table.

Name: Talulas Garden

Comments: Always outstanding food & ambiance! The Maitre D' greets you at the door with a warm genuine smile making you feel like so welcome. We were celebrating our sons 26th Birthday and our waiter Mark went out of his way to make our night special. A 10 every time!

Name: Toscana
Comments: Even though our reservation was a bit delayed because people were not leaving the restaurant, the hostess was very nice and did her best to accomodate us. Food was amazing and very nice service.

Name: Toscana
Comments: Service was impeccable and the food is so delicious!

Name: Toscana
Comments: Amazing as always!

Name: Toscana
Comments: As always, a terrific experience.

Name: Toscana
Comments: Lovely branzino. Good wine, but quite overpriced. The veal was magnificent, though very very expensive.

Name: Toscana
Comments: Arrived early for our reservation, and was greeted warmly. Only waited a couple of minutes before the table was available. The staff were all great, and the atmosphere was fun and comfortable.  The food was delicious!

Name: Toscana
Comments: Efficient and tasty.

Name: Toscana
Comments: One of our faves!!!

Name: Toscana
Comments: We went to Tuscanos today for lunch. We had great service from the minute we walked in. Our server told us the specials, my husband opted for the seafood pasta which she said was excellent ,I had the orchestra which is small pasta shells with Broccoli, sun-dried tomatoes and garlic. We both enjoyed our pastas& We cant wait to go back!

Name: Toscana
Comments: Wonderful as always!

Name: Toscana
Comments: Everything excellent but noise level too high.  Can't do anything about it but it is distracting

Name: Toscana
Comments: Great food and service.

Name: Toscana
Comments: A new wine list includes man regional wines  in the $50 to $100 range, considerably less expensive than the Brunellos and Barolos, that are exciting and satisfying.  The food was excellent.  I always include a small bowl of spaghetti, with butter and Parmesan, not on the menu which arrives just right, not too large a portion and al dents.

Name: Toscana
Comments: This restaurant is always outstanding!  The artichoke salad is next level, pasta are insane & the dishes all feel clean & light.

Name: Toscana
Comments: One of the best Italian food in town

Name: Toscana
Comments: Love the food! Service was excellent... can't wait to go back!

Name: Toscana
Comments: Toscana has been our favorite lunch place for 28 years.

Name: Toscana
Comments: loved it. Fabulous food and the wine selection was very nice. Great service!

Name: Toscana
Comments: One gets used to the off hand manner of the maitre d if one has been away for a while. We were put at a table smack on the middle of the room. The waiter was charming. Food was good as always.

Name: Toscana
Comments: Good food and great service. What else do you want.

Name: Toscana
Comments: As always, OUTSTANDING. Best Italian food in the west coast.

Name: Toscana
Comments: We felt very rushed and unattended to. We were told certain tables by the windows were reserved, when in fact I witnessed a walk-in seated there. They brought out appetizer at the same time as the entree. I had dined here some time ago, but now I see no reason to return again

Name: Toscana
Comments: Awesome food and service.  As always Toscana lives up to expectations.  Highly recommend!

Name: Toscana
Comments: Delicious food, wonderful service, gracious always

Name: Toscana
Comments: Excellent waiter. Great food. Best table! Loved it

Name: Toscana
Comments: The best!!

Name: Toscana
Comments: Upscale twists on homestyle Italian food. Very friendly and welcoming service

Name: Toscana
Comments: Great food and service.

Name: Toscana
Comments: Welcoming, friendly service, perfectly seasoned and prepared food.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Excellent in the new location. So much closer ! Very young chic clientele !

Name: Townsend
Comments: An excellent dinner. Loved it

Name: Townsend
Comments: Everything was superb. Quiet night with the coronavirus causing folks to stay away from public places, but come on out and eat! Nice wine list, friendly staff. So glad to have Townsend in Rittenhouse neighborhood.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Lovely dinner and wonderful drinks. The staff is delightfully helpful and respectful.  Overall, a great dining experience.

Name: Townsend
Comments: We really enjoyed our recent visit to Townsend.  We both ordered the chef's tasting menu and staff was very accomodating about changing out one of the dishes that was something we don't eat.  Each course was delicious.  We also enjoyed the wine pairings with each course.  A great choice for a special occasion meal.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Wonderful restaurant at a new location, food in top shelf and service is pretty good. A little louder and less intimate then it used to be but still great all around

Name: Townsend
Comments: Wonderful food and service as on Passyunk!  We had a beautifully timed dinner to celebrate and the best temperance cocktail in Philadelphia so far.  Miss the old charming ambiance a bit, but will definitely be back.

Name: Townsend
Comments: We were greeted promptly and seated.  There was a table of 5 men and 1 woman that was very noise.  The men kept trying to talk over each other and getting louder.  We complained to the server about the noise.  She agreed they were way out of bounds but there was nothing she could do.  There was a dying poinsettia in the window sill next to our table; it almost spring.  We had to signal to order cocktails.  The food was very good and the wine was very good.  The variety of food was excellent and they prepared a salad course for my wife which was not on the menu.  It was very good.  Pricing was good.  I would recommend that they spend more training on customer service and attention to details.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Wonderful dinner!

Name: Townsend
Comments: The food was just OK. The Bronzino was soggy indicating it had been frozen too long .The gnocchi was overcooked although I thought the sauce was good.

Name: Townsend
Comments: We ate upstairs on a Tuesday night. We were able to talk and hear each other! A remarkable and delightful surprise in a restaurant these days.We four foodies agreed this was one if the best food we'd ever ate. The experience was further enhanced by our excellent waiter, Harry.All in all, a wonderful evening.

Name: Townsend
Comments: It was lovely and we definitely will return. Delicious!! Excellent service!!

Name: Townsend
Comments: Glad we arrived early on a Saturday, seated right away. After that it went down hill. Waiter not very professional, no offer of fix menu, had to refill water ourselves. Too casual about everything.Overall good was good, not overly salty, cooked correctly. Just not a wow taste anywhere. We had escargot, gnocchi,duck and halibut. Had hoped service improved since opening reviews, once it's was full restaurant we waited for most everything.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Great tasting menu!  The halibut was incredible, the filet mignon cooked perfect, and the soup tasty.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Everything we ordered was wonderful. No complaints, want to go back soon.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Amazing spot, excellent service, food was phenomenal and  truly a dining experience. Cant wait to go back. Chef Todd acknowledged my request to meet him and talk about the restaurant.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Special event dinner for 2 birthdays and my son passing his CPA exam. Great food, delicious wine list, very knowledgeable and friendly service. Pricey and totally worth it.

Name: Townsend
Comments: The whole meal was wonderful. The oysters simply melted in your mouth, cooked to perfection, simply lovely!  Cannot wait to dine there again!

Name: Townsend
Comments: Average compared to the many fine restaurants in the neighborhood.

Name: Townsend
Comments: It was delicious BUT VERY loud.  The acoustiscs need improving as everything else is wonderful !!!

Name: Townsend
Comments: Quality experience on all levels- food, service and ambiance

Name: Townsend
Comments: Simply one of the best meals I've eaten in years and the cocktails were exquisite. The only downsides to the experience is that the ambience isn't great. The food and drink far makes up for that fact . This place absolutely needs to be experienced at least once

Name: Townsend
Comments: Pleasant surroundings if a little stark, quiet and comfortable.  Service very good.Best dishes were the squash soup and the scallops. The foie gras was unevenly cooked, one portion just right, the other  undercooked. Both had an off taste in the sear.  The sweetbreads were very well prepared. The duck was well prepared, nothing unusual but good nonetheless. Overall a good experience . More likely to return to Bibou.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Great ambiance but the portions were to large!  We were told they were portioned for each individual to order each course but by the time the main course came we were half stuffed.

Name: Townsend
Comments: We eat at the bar about once a week, but on Saturday night, we took my mother for dinner, and she liked it so much that we switched her upcoming birthday party to Townsend. Great food on a menu that's always kept fresh. (I had Broiled Oysters, Rabbit Gnocchi, Halibut)   Great service. Great drinks (Manhattans! - thanks Mike and Kevin).

Name: Townsend
Comments: Excellent on all counts. Will definitely return to explore more of the menu.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Everything about our dinner was outstanding. Our server, Amy, was knowledgeable about everything on the menu and steered us In the right direction for each course we ordered. Every person who came to our table to serve us something were also knowledgeable about everything! We loved it and cant wait to come back. Beautiful restaurant!

Name: Townsend
Comments: Fantastic food!

Name: Townsend
Comments: The food was good, but consistent not warm.We felt awckward to send it back to be re-heated, and again it was reallt tasteful, jut not  hot.

Name: Townsend
Comments: This may be a great spot-  but only after they fix some startup problems.Our table was not ready at our reservation time but there is under zero space to wait - except at the overcrowded bar (with others waiting to be seated) so we hung out in a window area. We had a wonderful server who took our order for a nice bottle of wine (from a moderately interesting list). A runner then brought us the obligatory bread basket along with an amuse-bouche of vinegared beets, one of which he  overturned onto the table linens - but made no offer to even cover the large and expanding beet red amoeba shaped stain with a napkin.Our first courses - a nice potato potage and baked oysters with (I recall) Pernod were quite well prepared. Our mains, a duck breast and a fish with a leek and other vegetable pure were both well prepared - but suffered from an obvious many too many minutes late delay in getting from the kitchen to the table. We passed on desert as nothing on the limited selection spoke to us.This is a work in progress. Most of the rough edges we felt were managed around by a wonderful and obviously experienced server (who we well tipped) but its hard to not get the feeling that the front and back of the house need some more time working together.Last - its a fine dining restaurant.  It needs some acoustic treatment as the noise level was close to that of a sports bar until later in the evening when the number of patrons was at a minimum.We will give it a few months and return.

Name: Townsend
Comments: First time at the new location (but several times at the old)- so my advice now is - ask for a table against the wall or upstairs.  The window tables are very cold in winter and the one nearest to the service station is distracting. The food - well, I just don't get the hype!  It's good but not spectacular in any form.  Sweetbreads were overly large and thus contained significant cartilage.  Tuna nicoise was grainy... in general the entire meal was overly salted.  Maybe I'm being picky but for a top place it was disappointing and all this was reflected in prior visits.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Seating was swift when we arrived with our reservation (which we made 15 mins prior); the food was all fantastic - from the amuse-bouche to the sophisticated dessert. Everything was so fresh and extremely well executed. It's a masterclass in French cuisine.

Name: Townsend
Comments: I have never left a poor review. We were really looking forward to trying Townsend as we have heard great things. However, the food was extremely mediocre - some lukewarm, some so hot as if out of a microwave. It lacked any real flavor. The foie gras mousse was gummy like glue and the duck was questionably duck. The only thing actually worth eating were the oysters. Our meal was so disappointing we immediately walked to Friday, Saturday, Sunday where we know we can get a top-notch, perfectly executed meal with staff that dont seem like robots. Just having a reputation for good food wont do much unless you only serve people who would be happy eating at Applebees every night. We wont be returning.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Everything about my evening was outstanding! The food was incredible, the service was spectacular...best meal I've had in a long time!

Name: Townsend
Comments: Outstanding meal and cocktails were divine! It was restaurant week and that can be hit or miss in some restaurants. Townsend was better than expectations! We have eaten at Townsend when the restaurant was located in South Philly and thought this meal was even better. The ambience, the complex yet clean flavorful dishes and creative cocktails should not be missed. We live in the city and have become foodie snobs frequenting many restaurants that have had the 'hype' and were disappointed.   Townsend did not disappoint- we will be back!

Name: Townsend
Comments: We really enjoyed restaurant week menu and portions were generous unlike many French restaurants.  Very nice wine list.  Excellent service and good ambiance.

Name: Townsend
Comments: My new favorite Center City restaurant! Great for any occasion.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Went for restaurant week and both got short rib both were overcooked/tough but one was significantly more overcooked and dry. Wasnt worth sending back cause than not eating at same time. Everything else was good

Name: Townsend
Comments: The food was delicious and the service was fast.  I will be going back to Townsend restaurant in the near future.  Highly recommend.

Name: Townsend
Comments: With reservation I would recommend but also realize this was RW.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great experience at every TFK Ive been to (3 cities).

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Excellent!Fav restaurant in Chicago

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: I love this place. Great, laid back environment; great for social distancing. Great food, service is outstanding!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great experience

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: It was a good experience and was able to sit outside

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Felt very safe here eating during the pandemic. Food was great! I have gluten, dairy, and shellfish dietary restrictions. I felt like I had great options to choose from. I love that the menu is based on an anti-inflammatory diet. Cant wait to go back!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: delicious healthy food in a wonderfully casual but classy setting

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Delicious food and friendly, impeccable service as always.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: We had a great meal and felt safe with the COVID precautions- I feel that this place is doing a great job!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: I loved True Food Kitchen! Awesome menu and the outdoor seating was very quaint. Drinks and dessert were also on point!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Had a good time

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Didnt feel totally safe but Im very careful. Tried a new dish snd didnt like it. Neither of these were the restaurants fault.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: As before  True Food never disappoints.The food is delicious as well as healthy.Great staff cool vibe!Five Star

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Loved the food and safety precautions

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Felt safe dining at outdoor area. Water came in carafe for the table. Contactless payments. Hand sanitizer on every other table.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Service was timely, food delicious and you did not even get any feel of Covid restrictions! Well done.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Dined outside and we could hardly hear our own conversation due to street noise, racing cars, homeless guys begging food from our plates and sirens. Not restaurants fault. We wont be back on a weekend. Food and service was good.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Amazing service. Apps were outstanding. Main courses were decent.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great food and environment

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great customer service, even with covid 19 the food was awesome and staff was friendly.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: The service was great, and the food was outstanding.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: True Food was a great way to social distance and eat outside. They took care to keep tables at least 6 feet apart and had hand sanitizer readily available. The salads are always tasty and unusual.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great alfresco spot with seating off the sidewalk.  Service was attentive and personal. Good and healthy food!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Very good food, on the healty side but with options for every taste to choose.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Food is always healthy and fresh. Staff are always friendly too!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: The quinoa Teriyaki dish hardly has any quinoa.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great vegan options... Delicious flavors

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Always love the food and ambiance. Fresh healthy choices but pretty overpriced for the meat add ons. I feel like you go for the chill vibes with some healthy tasty options. Expect to spend though.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: The service is great and the seasonal drinks were delicious. We only had apps. The flat bread was amazing but the edamame guacamole was not the best.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: We are regulars at true food. My daughter and I both commented we didnt know if there was a new shop or something had changed with the cooking. We order the new appetizer the lettuce wrap made with jackfruit. It was very salty.I ordered the shrimp tacos in a lettuce wrap. There were two small tacos and nothing really on the side  except a small side of lettuce. A far change from their fish taco that used to be on the menu. I feel like the prices have gone up the portions have gone down and so has the quality of the food. The concept of the restaurant is amazing and it used to be one of our favorite spots for lunch or a quick dinner.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Really good and healthy options. Great for Vegan and gluten free options!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: I love true food but this time was not their best effort. We asked for gluten-free pitas and were given regular pita chips. After we asked multiple times the waiter finally came back and said that he did accidentally give us regular. Couldve been a big issue had we eating them without questioning him. Our bill was incorrect, our pizza was not cut all the way through. Lots of issues and Im hoping they work through this challenging time because its one of my favorite restaurants.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Samantha, our server, was extremely professional and  aware of our needs while maintaining new standards.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great service, very clean, social distance guidelines in place

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great re-opening experience. Everything was excellent. Food, service, spacing of the tables. We felt very comfortable.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Great place

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: We enjoyed our dinner with this restaurant, wade selection of Gluten Free meals. I love their Grass Feed Burger and Sweet Potatoes Fries. A must try if ever in the area, we are definitely dine here again.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Always great and attentive service ...drinks and food fresh and tasty. Outdoor option is such a treat.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Unfortunately, the lettuce in my lunch salad was wilted and even slimy in spots. Not appetizing at all. Outdoor seating could have been better with the addition of flowering plants in the planters next to the tables, and street noise made conversation difficult. Overall, not the experience I used to enjoy at TFK.

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Food was good.  Servers and other employees were nice.  Only issue was that hostess had her mask pulled down below her nose at all times and sometimes below her mouth, too.  This is not acceptable during COVID times and especially not when all customers need to wear mask (I am happy to do this) but you are speaking with and seated by someone who doesn't have their mask on properly.  Hopefully mgmt. will correct this.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: I've been wanting to try this restaurant for awhile. Glad we did. Sushi was excellent. Waitstaff had excellent recommendations for food and drinks.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: The food quality and taste were great, service was awesome. So we have a high rating.  Unfortunately, my boyfriend has celiac disease and everything we were ordering was supposed to be done so to avoid gluten, but he had a major reaction the next day, which tells us some of the dishes us gluten in them.  Need to be more careful.  Due to this issue, it will be hard to eat there again.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Great experience with a knowledgeable, quick server who offered wonderful recommendations and really knew the menu.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Food and service are always good at Uchi, but I wasn't happy that I reserved an outdoor table due to COVID, and when I arrived the host took it upon himself to sit us inside anyways. When I inquired he said he thought we wouldn't like the table outside, even though we weren't even asked our opinion. I went outside and asked the waiter if I could move and he said yes so we ended up moving. The point: if someone reserves an outdoor table at least offer it to them before you switch their seating option, especially during COVID because we are only eating at restaurants with outdoor seating.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Great food. My husband and I went here for the first time last week. Really enjoyed ourselves. Megan was our server and she was great for recommendations. Edamame is amazing.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Uchi lived up to the hype! It was an amazing meal, and our server, Bryan, was absolutely fabulous.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: We were quickly seated upon arrival for our reservation. Our waiter, James was polite and welcoming which I wouldnt expect anything less. My date and I ordered the 10-course tasting  ultimate chefs choice and it was nice that James asked questions about our likes and dislikes and what we enjoy more of. James also asked if it was okay to have other people bring out the dish and/or pick up the plates. I was absolutely fine with the question but found it made the dining experience with different servers less personal by the end of the night. The other staff that brought the plates were polite but I wish they took the time to elaborate on the meal(s) instead of making a rushed dull statement; it would have made the omakase experience more polished. James checked on us often but Im still puzzled why there are numerous people to drop off and pick up the plates. Its a small concern since the tip was between 18%-20% on Omakase pricing and Im not sure if its split among those who approached our table or strictly our server; it seems like a team effort. Overall, James is really great. The dining experience is nice; I enjoyed having the lights dimmed for a while then lighting up the room which shifted the ambiance. The lighting seemed to rotate every time a new plate arrived to our table which set the mood for the new tasting. (Not sure if that's on purpose or if it was coincidence.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Delicious meals and cocktails! Best happy hour in Dallas!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Food was amazing but had to wait a little between courses but overall worth going back.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: We had an excellent experience! They really make an effort to customize your experience! The service was outstanding and the food phenomenal!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: They put the priority service to customer who came behind me.Try to push us to the dark corner of the yard even we reversed 1 week before.The outside area is very Dark and leak of light. we did not see our meal at 9.00 pmSushi and sashimi is very fresh good taste.I think 1.5 star is enough for service attitude.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Travis was our waiter and he was amazing. He very kindly explained the process to us as we were first timers. He was attentive to financial issues and recommended great wines. The timing of the food arrival was some of the best Ive ever experienced in America. They allowed us to linger and enjoy the company without feeling rushed and never left us with an empty plate or glass along the way. It was a magnificent experience to have them pick new things for us based on the things we explained we liked. We would go back in a second.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: The food was good however we were disappointed in the service. We felt dismissed and as though we were an inconvenience.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Food is amazing as always. SERVICE SUCKS AND IS GETTING WORSE. I asked for soy sauce and wasabi from 3 people and not one person got me some. For a restaurant this expensive you would expect better service or at least someone get you soy said and wasabi to have with your shashimi.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Food is amazing! Everything we tried was delectable including day boat scallops and rolls and happy hour beef dish. Kara kuyri is a delicious drink but not sure if it has much alcohol though... Will definitely keep coming back. :)

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Santiago was amazing.  Made it a great night.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Uchi always delivers great service and food!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Awesome experience. Signature tasting was well worth it.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Perfect evening with a special person

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Charged us for birthday desert and didnt even surprise or put a candle or anything to make it feel special.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: The food was incredible as always... just do the 10-course omakase and let the chefs cook. Its a pretty good value relative to hunting and pecking for your own dinner. The only downside is structural and always frustrating - no mixed drinks. Would be 10/10 if they would just get off their high horse and start offering liquor.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: The food was amazingly yummy and our waiter was so sweet and knowledgeable. We did the Chefs choice and it was an amazing decision!! We will go back.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Excellent service and food was outstanding!  Felt very comfortable with their precautions during this time.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Great service! My friend and I walked in not knowing what most of the items on the menu were, but now we want to try it all. Everything was delicious and our server helped us pick a great wine that paired well with all of our food. Will definitely be back!!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Great place for sushi and great service! Very pleased and will be back

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Awesome and yummy! Happy vegan! They were super accommodating to my food allergies!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: amazing menu options, my 2nd time there and I chose to let the chef pick what we were eating.  every single item brought to the table was unbelievable! amazing experience. Being a vegetarian, sushi restaurants aren't usually my favorite, but Uchi outdid itself with vegetarian options.  Pricy, but worth the experience.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Ive been to uchi multiple times and Im not sure if the pandemic affected their quality and service but it def didnt feel like uchi. I was excited to be visiting from out of town but overall its still a good dining experience considering the time we are in.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Love love love Uchi! Amazing food, every bite just melts in your mouth with all the flavors. Service is always impeccable and the staff names all of the ingredients which is by far one of my favorite parts of the dining experience.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: The best sushi Ive ever had. My bf and I thoroughly enjoyed our time and the food!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Amazing, they are really offering a safe alternative during the pandemic. The food is next level, we did a chefs selection with our server. Awesome!!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Our Server Mallory was amazing (and so was the rest of the staff)! The food was perfect! Perfect date spot!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Waitress was amazing

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Always a great restaurant with a great atmosphere and a knowledgeable staff. Great spot for anything from a casual dinner to a date. Quality to price is excellent here.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Absolutely outstanding food and service. Ask for Mallory if you can, she was amazing!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Amazing as usual. Never let us down!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Love the place -- just ready for a full restaurant after Covid.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Awesome food!!! They never disappoint. Great not good service. Perfect timing and unobtrusive service. Highly recommended!!!!!!!!!!!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Always the best and an unforgettable experience for my sisters birthday. Love you guys!

Name: UMI
Comments: We had a reservation at 9:00am and had to wait 45 minutes for our table.   This was a special occasion and the  service could have been better.

Name: UMI
Comments: Great sushi and also good options for non sushi lovers as well!

Name: UMI
Comments: The food was wonderful as usual, but it was our first time being there since Covid began - a very special experience!  The art installation mannequins and photographs were amazing!

Name: UMI
Comments: OMG.... this restaurant is absolutely AWESOME!!!! They have come up with a fun whimsical way to enforce social distancing.... with beautiful statues donned with interesting headgear having dinner next to ya.To give ya an idea of how succulent the food was... my 2 year old son & I came here for dinner two nights out of the four we were here for vacation. My favorite sushi items were the specialty sushi like sake aioli and yellowtail/otoro caviar. If you cant decide which to get, I recommend the otoro b/c it just melts in your mouth! The aburi sushi were good, but I have had better at other Japanese restaurants.The wagyu beef was absolutely divine!! Its pretty pricey at $33/oz (minimum 2 oz) but TOTALLY worth it! I think it was better than the Kobe beef I had in Kobe, Japan! The Chilean sea bass was a little dry but great flavor. The fluffy cheesecake was good but didnt like the banana glaze that it was soaked in.This is my new favorite Japanese rest!!

Name: UMI
Comments: It is just a regular sushi place

Name: UMI
Comments: Excellent food!! Excellent Service!! They were very conscious of social distancing.

Name: UMI
Comments: Great place!! Vibes are awesome!! Food is wonderful and fresh!! Attention to detail! A must go place for a date especially if they are a sushi lover!!

Name: UMI
Comments: The best of the best in Atlanta. Favorite staff in the city. Always exceptional

Name: UMI
Comments: Perfect place to unwind for great food and ambience

Name: UMI
Comments: By far the best place for Japanese food. Just amazing.

Name: UMI
Comments: No other place id rather spend my 30th bday.  The night was amazing!

Name: UMI
Comments: Great sushi. Great staff. Great place!

Name: UMI
Comments: Excellent service by Mr Ferry

Name: UMI
Comments: Great place! Even better interior design!i would definitely recommend!

Name: UMI
Comments: Our waitress was great! She was very on top of refilling our drinks and checking on us regularly! Typically the servers at UMI take forever to refill your drinks.. so she was outstanding.

Name: UMI
Comments: Umi never disappoints. The food and service was amazing as always and the art installation to help social distance was a fun touch. Cant wait to go back!

Name: UMI
Comments: Fantastic as always! Love their creativity with the art brought in for social distancing too! Best sushi in the city hands down- always consistent! And excellent service as well!

Name: UMI
Comments: Best sushi I have had in Atlanta (not cheap, though).

Name: UMI
Comments: Unparalleled service, sushi, & ambience.  Theres no spot that can compare in all of Atlanta.

Name: UMI
Comments: Michele is the best!!

Name: UMI
Comments: Second time at Umi and it was phenomenal. Umi staff did an exceptional job of creating an enjoyable environment with the current social distancing guidelines. All food and drinks were top notch. Thanks for the fantastic experience, highly recommend and will be returning.

Name: UMI
Comments: The food is always excellent and of the highest quality. But tonight was unusually special as management had thought of the unique idea of placing mannequins at the tables and bar seats that could not be used because of the Coronavirus. Very clever indeed and the evening that much more enjoyable!

Name: UMI
Comments: Incredible as always!

Name: UMI
Comments: The best place in Atlanta.

Name: UMI
Comments: Never fails to be the best dining experience in Atlanta, and of course the best sushi Ive ever had.

Name: UMI
Comments: Birthday dinner

Name: UMI
Comments: Everything was amazing as always. The food was spectacular and the service was exceptional.  Really dig the art

Name: UMI
Comments: As usual..an excellent meal

Name: UMI
Comments: Every time I go to Umi I fall in love all over again! Michelle is the best service person EVER!!! We never use a menu, just tell Michelle to bring food...and its always amazing!

Name: UMI
Comments: Favorite place to eat in Atlanta.  Jon and Hector are the absolute best.  Amazing food and drinks but the staff is the reason we keep coming back

Name: UMI
Comments: Umi was great!!

Name: UMI
Comments: Incredible dinner. Umi never disappoints.

Name: UMI
Comments: Everything was wonderful and they were very accommodating to our situation.

Name: UMI
Comments: AMAZING. I wish I could come here everyday. Best sushi I have ever had. Great service and atmosphere. Will be back!

Name: UMI
Comments: Great food!

Name: UMI
Comments: From food to service everything was excellent.

Name: UMI
Comments: Excellent service and food. Thanks

Name: UMI
Comments: Love Umi...food, vibe, and service are excellent!

Name: UMI
Comments: Michelle our waitress is always so welcoming and cheerful! She always knows exactly what we want! WE LOVE it at UMI!

Name: UMI
Comments: Food was so great - service was great as well. A bit loud but the food makes up for it. Ill be coming back here for sure!

Name: Upland
Comments: We totally enjoyed our dinner at Upland.  The entire evening was perfect.  The food was outstanding.  My husband never likes the menu when we go out and he loved everything we ordered.  We shared a salad, pizza, pasta and chicken.  Our waiter, Sam, was fabulous and the manger, Jennifer, came over and she was delightful.thank you for a wonderful evening.Susan & Alan Fishman

Name: Upland
Comments: Overrated! Burger ok, pasta came cold... very poor service!!!

Name: Upland
Comments: Great food, great atmosphere. Shame they ran out of the hen of the woods mushrooms!

Name: Upland
Comments: Eh--underwhelming.  Was super excited to dine here but the the menu was just OK.  Not a lot of interesting options.  We had also called ahead to make sure they had vegan offerings.  They enthusiastically said yes.  Their vegan option at brunch?  Potatoes.  Just potatoes.  Many better brunch options in the city.

Name: Upland
Comments: This is a wonderful restaurant!  The food is fantastic and the atmosphere very cozy and friendly.  The staff are responsive and efficient and helpful.  Their is a nice price range.  I had the salmon entree and my husband had the pork -- both were delicious!  Cocktails were perfect.  Upland, to me, seems to have something for everyone.

Name: Upland
Comments: Disappointing.....  barely any lamb in the lamb dish, a ridiculous amount of lettuce basically covered the plate.....  very little seafood in the ceviche.....

Name: Upland
Comments: Excellent food. We had a slight issue with the service - the salmon needed to be cooked through more, and the served acted like we were asking her to summit Mt. Everest - but it got fixed in the end. A good place for a business lunch (which is why we were there).

Name: Upland
Comments: We were there for Sunday Brunch to celebrate my daughters birthday. Upland had great ambiance and good service but all 4 meals (pasta, quiche, eggs) came out room temperature. Flavors were great but no excuse for food not coming to the table hot at this restaurant.

Name: Upland
Comments: The couple next to us was extremely annoying and ruined the experience basically. It would have been just okay otherwise. I probably would not return. It was nothing special.

Name: Upland
Comments: Everything was wonderful except the shrimp and rice dish. It seemed to consist mostly of shrimp shells (creepy) and not much shrimp meat at all.

Name: Upland
Comments: I visit New York around 4-6 times a year.  I am always looking for new places to eat and saw Uplands on a list of brunch spots to try.  This was my first visit to Uplands.  It was in a great location and the restaurant itself is spacious and beautiful - not typical for many restaurants in the city.  Food was very good - we went with the server's recommendations and were not disappointed.  My husband had the fried chicken sandwich and I had the Egg and Tortilla.  I asked for scrambled eggs instead of fried egg and it was no problem.  We had mimosas and Bloody Marys and then finished with the Donuts. We wouldn't normally do that but the donuts were recommended.  Enjoyed the experience from start to finish - we will definitely be back.

Name: Upland
Comments: Loved everything about it. Food service and decor were all absolutely perfect.

Name: Upland
Comments: I went early with a friend.  We ordered a few appetizers and some wine.  Nice sized portions and very fresh food.  Excellent service.  Will definitely come back

Name: Upland
Comments: I have been coming to Upland since it first opened and it has been a consistently good experience in terms of both food and service.  Unfortunately on my last visit our server was SO RUDE and put us on edge for the entire dinner because we were nervous of being barked at!  She tried to take our appetisers away when we were half way though and when we said we werent finished yet, she decided she would change our plates for some unknown reason...then a minute later our mains arrived so we ended up not actually being able to enjoy the rest of our appetisers!  It was quite embarrassing because I had a guest in from out of town and got them to cancel their reservation at LArtusi to come to Upland instead!  I really hope it was a one off be side I really do enjoy Upland, but next time I will think twice before returning since New York is full of great restaurants with great service.

Name: Upland
Comments: Expensive. Noisy.  Pizza was burnt.  My friend asked for a slight modification in her meal (a vegetable instead of the rice) and the waiter didn't even try to accommodate.  Highly overrated.

Name: Upland
Comments: The service was truly terribly. Our server was very stuck up and almost acted like it was a burden to serve us. The food was also overly salty. My favourite thing was the caesar salad.

Name: Upland
Comments: Our server was grumpy and I was surprised because I have usually had really lovely service.   It kind of bummed me out.  I loved our meal despite him but it bothered me a lot, I have been in food service and I know when someone is over it, it shows.   Otherwise Jennifer made it right by coming over to check on us!

Name: Upland
Comments: We agreed that this is our favorite NYC restaurant, hands-down.  Impeccable food and service, both enjoyed in a beautiful and quiet room. We will keep returning.

Name: Upland
Comments: Wonderful brunch, great drinks and very professional staff.

Name: Upland
Comments: We went to Upland for a celebratory engagement dinner with both sets of parents.  This place is incredible.  Every dish is well thought out and you don't need to spend an arm & a leg for a truly great meal like other places in NYC.  Highly recommend the hen of the wood, tomato soup & caesar salad

Name: Upland
Comments: Such a fantastic meal with fantastic service!!

Name: Upland
Comments: Great vibe and great food. Loved that you could have a conversation

Name: Upland
Comments: This is usually a fave but was quite disappointing.  Our waitress tried to rush us and my main dish (salmon) had strange sides.

Name: Upland
Comments: Pizzas and salads are great.  I had the feta spinach omelet, but it did not have much feta or spinach in it.  The slice of bread given the side was truly hard as a rock, so could not break or bite.  Otherwise it is a great place.  Service, ambiance and staff are great.  Will skip the omlette next time.

Name: Upland
Comments: I love this restaurant. The atmosphere is clean and crisp and appeases anyone's taste/style. The wait staff was incredibly kind and my server was specifically awesome. I took two friends and I would highly suggest this as a restaurant to take someone who is in town for the weekend. We shared an order of donuts at the beginning and the jelly donut was the best I have ever had - huge shout-out to the pastry chef :) All three of our meals were pretty stellar - my one and only hesitation is that it can get quite costly but with that being said, the portions are quite large and we all three had food to-go for later. Thank you!!!

Name: Upland
Comments: Such a treat. The food is inventive and great. And a fun vibe.

Name: Upland
Comments: Food and service were great. Two outstanding pastas. Beautiful space with a great vibe. Great meal always consistent

Name: Upland
Comments: Would never go back because of noise level tho good excellent

Name: Upland
Comments: The food is unique and delicious... the cocktail drink menu was very good!

Name: Upland
Comments: There's a reason Upland is always one of my favorite restaurants in the city - they always deliver great food and experience

Name: Upland
Comments: We had a great evening here. Great food and service , and a really lively buzzy ambience. All you want from a restaurant !

Name: Upland
Comments: Great food! Great location! Energetic noise level!

Name: Upland
Comments: We went for a casual meal. The service was great. I spilt my espresso martini and they made me a new one straight away

Name: Upland
Comments: Great dining experience! Will visit again!

Name: Upland
Comments: Great food! Love the decor!

Name: Upland
Comments: Staff was great but the burger was terrible.

Name: Upland
Comments: This was my second time here and both times, I really enjoyed it. I came for my birthday brunch and we were a party of 4. The first table we were seated at wasn't great, but they let us have a booth and it was much better. The hostesses were very kind and accommodating. Service was good - I always had water in my glass. The atmosphere is so lovely and comfortable! The food was excellent. The sausage and kale pizza is phenomenal. Usually I don't like thicker pizzas but this one managed to be thick without being too heavy or soggy. The crust was crispy and the flavor was out of this world. We also enjoyed the burger very much. The fried chicken sandwich was a bit on the small side but very tasty. Overall, great experience and would go back.

Name: Upland
Comments: Enjoyed brunch at Upland this last weekend! Food and service was fantastic!

Name: Upland
Comments: Always the best!

Name: Upland
Comments: We had a great dinner --our usual favorites: the 'nduja pizza, the skirt steak, the little gem salad ... all fantastic.  Also an amazing wine list. Fabulous.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: What a gem of a restaurant!  Truly a fabulous meal.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: I love this place, if it weren't so difficult to get a reservation, I'd go more often.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Food is amazing - difficult to get a reservation or seat at the bar.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: One of the few restaurants that actually gets better with age.  Each service person, from the water boy to the manager, glides around attentively to serve patrons.  The wine list is small but select.  pours are very large.  I loved my duck breast, which is always served medium rare (perfect).  Staff is very attentive, with one staff dedicated to just polishing wine glasses.  All details combine to make this a 5 star restaurant.  Others agree, which is why at 5:15 pm on Thursday it was jammed with couples.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Great local spot, excellent cocktails, vibrant energy and location.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: This was my second visit here and everything was great! I am adding to my list of favorite Philly restaurants. My favorite thing I ordered was the crispy artichokes.  Delicious!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: 25th anniversary I the food was delicious

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Vernick never disappoints!  Everything from the appetizers, to entrees, to wine was outstanding.  One my favorite restaurants in Philadelphia!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: As always, dining at Vernick is a wonderful experience. Very good food, drinks and pleasant ambiance. Looking forward to returning for another dinner

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Loved sitting at the Chefs counter. Awesome experience!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Everything was delicious! The foie gras was probably our favorite of all the small plates we got. The menu was excellent it was hard to make choices because we wanted everything! The cocktails were really good too; strong and refreshing. Cant wait to go back!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Vernick was incredible. Service was outstanding! We had a variety of dishes and were not disappointed by any of them, and some were down right amazing. Definitely worth the wait for a reservation.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Outstanding original menu creations each with their own x-factor. The white truffle tagliatelle special is indeed very special.  Well thought out wine selections by glass or bottle compliment the plates.  Servus is first rate - attentive, comprehensive, but not overbearing.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Everything was incredible food and service Cant wait to go back

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: fantastic service, food, and drinks.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Was just okay. Dont get all the hype.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Amazing experience. Well worth the wait!  Outstanding execution. Terrific service.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: One of the best Restaurants in Philadelphia and absolutely wonderful fare.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Britten was exceptional again.. everything was spectacular top to bottom

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: We just locked the food. If you have mobility issues ask to sit downstairs

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: The pumpkin toast, roasted cabbage, and curry shrimp were spectacular. The ravioli was good but it was weird that it was just one giant one, also for the price it wasnt much. The mushroom toast was good but I think it would have been more enjoyable if it was warm and not served cold. My friend enjoyed the oysters. The service was great! I went to dinner with a friend I havent seen in a year and is in town for Thanksgiving and it was nice that they recommended that we take our time ordering and that there would be 15-20 min between each plate, so we could really enjoy our chatting over the sparkling wine (which I never heard about until dinner tonight!). Definitely will return to Vernick with my husband as I think hed enjoy it.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Outstanding restaurant from the moment we walked in until we left. The staff was exceptional, our server was on point, and the food was even better than I could have hoped for: inventive, exciting, and most importantly, delicious! Well done!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: This is the best restaurant in Philly. The most creative and fresh ideas i've seen. I'm a vegetarian, and there are many options!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Service was amazing. Food was delicious although I felt a few of the dishes were on the salty side (the mushroom soup amuse bouche, sea urchin with scrambled eggs, gratin that came with the sea bass)

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Dinner was excellent, as always!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Loved everything!!! Omg the best!!Cant wait to go back.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: One of our favorite restaurants anywhere! We dine here whenever we come to Philadelphia (we live in NYC) and have even talked about hopping on the train just to dine here!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: The food was very good admittedly a bit pricey for what it was. I did find the food was extremely rich.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Gorgeous menu, beautiful presentation, great wait staff, noisy but worth it!  Well go again!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Fantastic service and incredible food. I cant wait to go back!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Unbelievable experience, food was exceptional and service was too. I've been trying to get in here on previous trips to Philly and it did not disappoint. One of the better meal experiences ive had in awhile

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: This is an AMAZING restaurant.  If you consider yourself a foodie then you MUST go here.  Everything we ordered and everything that was complementary was absolutely delicious and wonderful.  I wanted to keep eating and ordering dish after dish.  I went to philly for a few days and was doing research to find the best place to dine and Vernick is the place!  I live in NJ and eat in NYC all the time and I would definitely go back to Philly just to eat at Vernick (I revisited yesterday and it was delicious). I ate at the chef counter a second time and would recommend eating there just to see the chefs work like a well oiled machine with everyone moving with precision and dedicated passion.I went a second time and this place is AMAZING.  The chefs are rock stars and had another amazing enjoyable dinner.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Awesome all around experience! My wife and I are huge foodies and havent been so satisfied since dining at California Grill, Victoria and Alberts, and Flying Fish. Everything was spot on and perfect. Thank you for a wonderful experience.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: First time visit - enjoyed ourselves very much. Highly recommend.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Excellent service and wonderful tastes! Entrees lacked the luster that I had hoped to continue after our toasts and small plates.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: One would be hard pressed to find a more delicious meal, it was superb! There is always room for improvement so if I could improve anything... well... the service could be a tad warmer.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Been here many times amd have never been disappointed.   Looking forward to our next visit.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Everything was fantastic. The service,the food and the atmosphere.A true  5 star experience

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Everything about Vetri was wonderful. From the service to the granola goody bagwe couldnt have celebrated a 21st birthday any better.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: I was there to celebrate my son and his wife having gotten him through graduation with a Doctorate in Physical Therapy from Arcadia University.  We were all very much impressed with Vetri Cucina.  The food was outstanding (and ample), the service was impeccable, and it was an altogether outstanding experience.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: An amazing evening from start to finish. The staff were so warm and welcoming. The meal was a modified prefix menu. By modified,  I mean that specific foods of interest were included while foods noted to be of lesser interest were not included. The beginning was with a creatively tasty aperitivo, served with fois gras pastrami on a slice of brioche, high temperature baked and charred cauliflower, smoked duck breast and crudities with a balsamic mayonnaise. Then the serious food started.... hamachi crudo with a creative use of citrus to give it sparkle, onion crepe, with perfectly caramelized onion that took 2 days to make. We tried six different pastas, all delicious; however, for me the ricotta ravioli were incredible.... light as a feather, creamy, and, again, set off with a creative use of citrus In keeping with the season. The real showstopper were three perfectly cooked and sauced Nantucket scallops, topped with a generous serving of ostera caviar and tiny house-made potato chips. So good I felt we should eat this dish on our knees. Entrees hadn't even been started at this point. Spit-roasted goat... tender, juicy with crunchy skin and a salt-baked bronzino were secondi. Desserts were equally amazing. We ended up eating on and taking the others home for the next day. Bravo to Vetri Cucina!!!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Seriously delicious eclectic cuisine... we shared many unique courses and wine pairings that we loved! If you love food and unique experiences this is the place

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: I had high expectations for my birthday dinner. I was so not disappointed. From the moment we arrived we were greeted and felt welcome. The food, oh it was sooo very good. I got to try things like froe gras and white truffles. I have eaten at many fine restaurants, but this has to be number one. Yes it is very expensive, the most expensive of any restaurant I have ever visited... but oh so very worth the experience.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Vetri never disappoints!  And their Friday lunch is a treat and a bargain!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Once again, a memorable dining experience.Some of the best dishes I have ever had.Grazie

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: From start, and I mean very start with a personal phone call right after I booked thanking me for my reservation, and throughout the evening, every aspect of the dinner was superb, without any air of snootiness one comes to experiences 5 star restaurants. Very special, yet comfortable and accommodating.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Great service and excellent job with wine pairings. Food was not great. Sauces were all very similar (brown butter based). Also, concept of wait staff picking our menu choices sounds fun in concept, but my wife and I agreed that our experience would have been better had we got to pick our own food. Glad we had the experience, but wouldnt hurry back anytime soon

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Always great! We love bill!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: I'm not sure which was better: the food or the service.  The entirety of the meal was the best I can remember.  Being greater with a drink and snacks.  Amazing service and presentation.  And the quality and execution of the meals was second to none.  Hope to be back soon.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Best lunch experience - always.  Worth taking a Friday off.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: From start to finish our evening at Vetri was exceptional. Of course the food was delicious and beautifully plated but our wait staff made the experience that much nicer. They were attentive without being intrusive and we were impressed by the knowledge of our dietary restrictions. All agreed that this was our best meal in Philadelphia.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: The best dining experience in the city.  Unique flavors, perfect service.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: When people hear about the cost of my meal, they cringe and obviously do not understand "value". When a product or experience is extraordinary, then there is no concern about cost and that makes a great value. This was a dining experience without compare. The food was fantastic from start to finish, and the wine was a perfect compliment. The service was fabulous and the servers absolutely helped to make the experience special. It was my 25th wedding anniversary and my wife and I shared it with my 3 daughters.  I hit a grand slam with my choice of Vetri Cucina! Thank you all for making it a very memorable, lovely and satisfying evening!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Best food in the city, state and maybe northeast!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: This restaurant was a great experience for foodies looking for a fancy night out. It is a great way to try new things and the homemade pasta was perfect!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Excellent experience. Outstanding, detailed, creative, delicious food with an Italian focus.  It also is a home-y unpretentious setting which is perfect. The desserts were the best we've ever tasted. Would consider again for a very special occasion.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Delicious meal, service so over the top that it was a bit much or uncomfortable at times, felt a little robotic/insincere, but it is a very formal place. Great experience, something to try once and the food was phenomenal. Price tag a bit extreme. For dinner for two and bottle of wine on the less expensive side of their offerings, bill was $440 not including tip. When comparing to the nicer, expensive places like some of the Steven starr and steakhouses in the city, its more expensive.. but again, an experience! And despite the tasting sizes, they sprinkle in lots of extras and you leave stuffed!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: The most fantastic food in Philly, but if you do the tasting menu, be prepared to consume a LOT of food! So unexpected, we are big eaters and have never been beaten by a meal! We surrendered before the last savory course, and before cheeses and dessert....these were not large portions, but there were many courses. I suggest getting up and having a brief walk outside at the 5th or 6th course! If you can afford an expensive meal, this is worth it.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: once again, this is my favorite restaurant in the world! the food is so good you can't believe it. everything about this place is top notch. of course you pay for it but why not live a little. I highly recommend this for any occation.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Food was amazing. Waiter let us try wine by the glass before selecting. Plus his service and attention were top notch. Each course both of us got a different selection chosen by the chef which let us try a majority if the dishes. Cannot wait to go back.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Superb in every way!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: How was my meal?  What more can I say then the BEST Italian restaurant in the entire Phila area. Including ACNJ.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: My friend and I enjoyed our lunch.The food was great, service attentive.- - but still rather pricey.The place could use a good cleaning.  But , overall, a lovely meal with happy (holiday) vibe.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Vetri Cucina delivers perfection in dining. Atmosphere, food and service just perfect. The decor is casual elegance. The service is highly professional never affected. The staff are attentive without being over bearing. The sense is they want you to have a wonderful dining experience. The food is inventive but never pretentious. Flavor reigns via superb ingredients in well conceived dishes. This is truly a world class restaurant.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: My wife and I dined here as part of an anniversary celebration. The restaurant is warm and quiet-a great place to have conversation and enjoy the meal. We were served a lovely cocktail-an Italian spritz-while the staff asked us about likes, dislikes, allergies, etc. We were given the option of choosing from their tasting menu or to be surprised. We opted for the surprise-but did not do the optional wine pairing (too much alcohol for a couple of light-weights!). My wife has very distinct food dislikes and I am very adventurous and chef was marvelous at meeting both our preferences! The portions were small and manageable, the food was gorgeous and delicious. The service was gracious, friendly and attentive but not cloying. Definitely worth going for a special occasion!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Great special occasion but will tip a hole in the wallet!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Amazing! I've never been so full but I just couldn't stop eating. Expensive, but well worth it.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Love Love Love! Best Birthday Dinner ever. Thank for the amazing food, wine, and above all care to everything!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Bill, our waiter, was fantastic!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: One of the best meals Ive had! If youre in Philly, definitely eat here.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Superb attention to detail by The Culinary staff and front-of-the-house staff was marvelously accommodating.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: One of the best dining experiences you'll have.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Always an outstanding culinary and service experience with a mix of old favorites, new dishes and wonderful wine pairings!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: I have eaten recently recently at L'ambroisie, Le clarence, garance, Tour d'Argent, Restaurant du Palais Royal, Le Gabriel, Gabriel Kreuther. vetri is an old favorite of mine. I have eaten here 10 times. The food was mixed. Within the tasting menu format, 3 or 4 dishes were brilliant. A few very ordinary.The service was also very mixed. Our main server was really good, but the others were poor. Compared to lunch at "Restaurant du Palais Royal", vetri was inferior, and poor value.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: An incredible meal! The food and wine pairing was SO good! The service was phenomenal as well. And it was really cool that Mark Vetri took the time to make the rounds and spend a couple minutes talking to us. Fantastic overall meal, a must if you are in the area! Cheers!!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Very good, not great.  This is due to the temperature of the pastas and the main courses.  Without exception, every dish came to the table lukewarm, like they were sitting around in the kitchen and not made to order.  For the price, I would have expected better.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: My favorite part of this whole experience was constructing the tasting menu. Our server, Tara, came to our table and announced we were to have a discussion regarding what we enjoy eating and what we do not. Was there anything we felt we absolutely needed to try? Any ingredients of which we are particularly fond? I wish every restaurant with an unset tasting menu did this, it's brilliant. Ultimately, we did not choose any particular courses, so it was a surprise, but a surprise built around our tastes. There were six main courses, 3 bread courses, an amuse-bouche, and a couple mignardises. Every other main course had an additional entree we shared. Our tasting menus were completely different from one another, so we were able to try each other's entrees as well. Overall, we tried a little over 20 dishes. All of them were exquisite and definitely on the richer side. I was pretty full about two-thirds of the way through.What made the experience amazing, food aside, was our brilliant server. Tara is an absolute food genius, emotionally intelligent, and easy to understand. Her knowledge is vast and gave an immediate answers to every question without missing a single beat. Playful and understanding, she intuitively knew when to give us space as well as when to swoop in with another brilliant display. Truly a magical night and reunion with my father, made special by Tara. P.S. I'm sorry for tripping you, I still feel guilty!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Excellent culinary experience. Superb staff and support.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: My favorite boston restaurant.  Great atmosphere, food, service, and value.  Highly recommend.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Yvonnes is my new favorite Boston restaurant. The space is unique and comfortable but with a wow factor. The small plates menu is very well balanced with meat, cheese, vegan options. Our party of four ordered 10 plates and each was uniquely seasoned, spectacular in taste and presentation. Holly our waitress was a fount of knowledge about the menu but also Locke Ober, the mens club previously in the space for a very long time. We all enjoyed learning about the interiors and renovations. Dont change a thing!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Jessica needs to time down her attitude. Awful customer service.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: We have been wanting to go to Yvonnes for a while and it just never seems to happen.   I have to say it was worth the wait. The menu has lots of short plates and we had many.  Every single item we had was delicious.  Dont miss the fritters!   Just an incredible experience.  Our server wasnt the best but she has lots of other staff helping and they were all great.  For the feast we had the brisket which was totally worth the wait.   Cant wait to go back and try the few dishes we didnt eat.  Cant say enough great things about this place

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Special place, amazing ambience, incredible bar, delicious food

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: There is no better place to have a special holiday dinner.... this has become a tradition for four of us ... the food is spectacular  in taste and presentation and everyone from entering the restaurant to wait staff is super nice.... unpretentious and great people... thank you !

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: One bartender let my wife sit there for 7-8 mins without asking her if she wanted anything... Paige the other bartender was good and were glad she was there. Our service at the table was very good, would just avoid that one bartender (sorry, didnt get a name)

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: We're big fans of Yvonne's, and while we don't go as often as we'd like, when we go our experience is excellent.We went because it was our anniversary, and our server helped make it even more special.  He recommended drinks and other menu items, took pictures for us, let my wife try a drink to be sure it was what she expected.  Great service!Our reservation was early, so it wasn't super busy, and relatively quiet.  Seemed like a good time to go if you wanted a reasonable noice level.  Dinner on a Thursday - Saturday can be quite noisy.For new visitors, think of it as mostly small plates for sharing.  Well seasoned, good quality.  We loved the lamb, the beef tartar, and potato snacks (the menu name escapes me).  The desserts didn't measure up to the rest of the menu, and were just ok.We spent about $100pp and felt like it was good value for a special occasion.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: I came here with my boyfriend for our anniversary dinner. Yvonnes really went above and beyond! I had indicated that it was our anniversary on opentable and take gave us some complimentary champagne to start off the night. The food and drinks were amazing and the service was great as well!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Very romantic. The food was superb and the service was excellent. Prices were good as well.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: I have only been to Yvonne's once and I tried to return just a week later but they were already booked! The food has a lot of flavors and came out as it was ready -- I highly recommend the hummus and shrimp!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Really cool vibe and great food.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Definitely recommended for cocktails, but could get better food for the same price elsewhere.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: We were really enjoying our evening at the bar, the drinks were great and the ambiance was perfect. But once we were brought to our dinner table the night changed. Our host escorted us past several open tables in the main dining area through a clandestine passageway into a completely different part of the Yvonne's that I was not expecting. Although intrigued at first by the completely different decor, the dark space and thumping techno music just wasn't for me. It was too loud and too club-like for what we had in mind. Given how different the two sections are, I wish the host, the website or someone gave us a choice of seating space in advance. The food was great. Not rushing to go back.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: We have been making Yvonne's a tradition to begin our evening's prior to the opening night at the Boston Ballet and have to say that the menu changes are wonderful - always great to change things up! The food is, as always, creative and delicious! The cocktails are fabulous and the wine list is excellent! We love Yvonne's and look forward to our next evening there!!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Such a great place, dishes were delicious and well thought out. Hit all the right taste buds and drinks were top notch!Recommend the steak tartare toast, lamb ribs, tater tot squares.Josephine baker was a delicious drink to end the meal!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Awesome spot for a Friday night! Our server was the best, had great recommendations for both food and drinks. Will definitely be going back soon!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: The food was way over priced and very over spiced.  Too hot and too salty!!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Very accommodating of our vegan diner; great food, service. Will definitely return

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: The food and atmosphere was great.  The service was just ok, not slow, just felt like we were putting them out with our order....

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Food and Ambiance good.  Service amongst the worst I have ever experienced

Name: Yvonne's
